<|asst|>
Today, Tom and Lily went to the park with their mom. They saw a big slide, a swing, and a sandbox. They wanted to play with everything.

"Can I go on the slide first?" Tom asked.

"No, I want to go first!" Lily said.

They both ran to the slide, but Lily got there before Tom. She climbed up the ladder and slid down. Tom was angry. He waited for Lily to come up again, and then he pinched her arm.

"Ow! That hurts!" Lily cried. "Mom, Tom pinched me!"

Mom heard Lily and came to see what was wrong. She saw the red mark on Lily's arm and the angry look on Tom's face.

"Tom, why did you pinch your sister?" Mom asked.

"Because she went on the slide first and I wanted to go first!" Tom said.

Mom shook her head. "That's not a good reason to pinch someone, Tom. Pinching is not nice. It makes people sad and hurt. You have to share and take turns with your sister. Do you understand?"

Tom nodded. He felt sorry for pinching Lily. He said sorry to her and gave her a hug.

Lily hugged him back. She said sorry for going on the slide first and not letting him go. She said they could take turns and play together.

Mom smiled. She was happy that Tom and Lily made up. She said they could play for a little while longer, and then they would go home and have a snack.

Tom and Lily were happy too. They played on the slide, the swing, and the sandbox. They had fun and did not pinch each other again. They did not care that they were not wealthy and did not have many toys. They had each other and their mom, and that was enough.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
