<|asst|>
Anna loved to play with her surf. It was a big board that she could ride on the water. She liked to feel the wind and the waves. She always wore a hat and a coat to keep warm and safe.

One day, Anna went to the beach with her mom and dad. They helped her carry her surf to the water. Anna was very happy. She wanted to show them how fast and brave she was. She put her surf on the water and climbed on it.

But the water was not calm that day. It was rough and loud. Big waves came and pushed Anna's surf. Anna was scared. She tried to hold on, but the surf was fragile. It broke in two pieces. Anna fell into the water.

Mom and dad saw what happened. They ran to help Anna. They pulled her out of the water and hugged her. They told her it was okay. They were proud of her for trying. They said they would get her a new surf.

Anna was sad. She liked her surf. She did not want a new one. She wanted her old one. She cried and hugged the pieces of her surf. She wished they would grow back together.
<|end|>


