<|asst|>
Anna liked to play dress-up with her big sister's clothes. She would sneak into her sister's room and open the wardrobe. There were so many pretty dresses and shoes and hats. Anna wanted to try them all.

One day, Anna found a long, shiny dress that looked like a princess dress. She took it out of the wardrobe and put it on. But the dress was too big for her. It dragged on the floor and got tangled around her legs. Anna tried to walk, but she tripped and fell. She felt a bump on her head and started to cry.

"Anna, what are you doing?" Her sister came into the room and saw Anna on the floor. She was angry and confused. "That's my dress! You can't wear it! It doesn't fit you!"

Anna looked up at her sister with tears in her eyes. She wanted to say sorry, but she couldn't find the words. She felt bad for taking the dress and making her sister mad.

Her sister sighed and helped Anna get up. She took off the dress and hung it back in the wardrobe. Then she gave Anna a hug and said, "It's okay, Anna. I know you like to play dress-up. But you have to ask me first, okay? And you have to wear clothes that fit you. Otherwise, you might get hurt."

Anna nodded and hugged her sister back. She said, "Okay, sister. I'm sorry. I love you."

Her sister smiled and said, "I love you too, Anna. Come on, let's go find something that fits you. Maybe we can play dress-up together."
<|end|>


