<|asst|>
Lily liked to count. She counted her fingers, her toes, her dolls, and her books. She counted everything she saw. One day, she went to the park with her mom. She saw a man playing music on a big guitar. He had a hat on the ground with some coins in it.

"Mom, can I count the coins?" Lily asked.

"Sure, honey, but be careful and polite. The man is working hard to make music for us," her mom said.

Lily walked over to the hat and knelt down. She picked up a coin and said, "One." She picked up another coin and said, "Two." She kept counting until she reached ten. She was very proud of herself.

The man noticed her and smiled. He stopped playing and said, "Hello, little girl. You are very good at counting. Do you like my music?"

Lily nodded. She liked the music. It made her happy.

"Thank you. I'm glad you like it. You know, you are very generous to count my coins. You can keep one if you want. It's a gift from me to you," the man said.

Lily was surprised. She looked at the coin in her hand. It was shiny and round. She liked it.

"Thank you, sir. You are very generous too. You make beautiful music for everyone," she said.

She gave the man a hug and ran back to her mom. She showed her the coin and told her what happened. Her mom hugged her and said, "You are very lucky, Lily. You met a kind and talented man. And you learned a new word today. Generous. Do you know what it means?"

Lily thought for a moment. She remembered how the man shared his music and his coin with her. She remembered how happy she felt.

"It means to give and make others happy," she said.

Her mom smiled and said, "That's right, Lily. You are very smart and sweet. I love you."

Lily smiled and said, "I love you too, mom. And I love counting and music."
<|end|>


