Sam and Tom were brothers. They liked to play in the park. One day, they saw a big dog. The dog had a cane in his mouth. He was chewing the cane.

"Look, Sam, a dog!" Tom said. "Can we pet him?"

"I don't know, Tom. He looks big and strong. Maybe he is not nice," Sam said.

But Tom did not listen. He ran to the dog. He wanted to touch the cane. He thought it was a toy.

"Hey, dog, can I have your cane?" Tom asked.

The dog did not like that. He growled at Tom. He showed his teeth. He was not calm. He was angry.

"Tom, come back! He is mad!" Sam shouted.

But it was too late. The dog bit Tom's hand. Tom screamed. He dropped the cane. He was hurt. He was scared.

Sam ran to Tom. He hugged him. He cried. He called for help.

The dog ran away. He took the cane with him. He did not care.

Sam and Tom were sad. They had a bad day. They learned a hard lesson. They should not bother dogs they do not know. They should be careful. They should listen to Sam.
<|end|>


