Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play with toys and books. One day, Lily has a new idea. She wants to write a letter to her grandma. She asks Tom to help her.

"Tom, can you help me write a letter?" Lily says.

"Sure, Lily. What do you want to say?" Tom says.

"I want to say I love her and I miss her. And I want to draw a picture of us," Lily says.

"Okay, Lily. Let's find some paper and crayons," Tom says.

They go to Lily's room and find some paper and crayons. They sit on the floor and start to write and draw. Lily writes her name and Tom writes his name. Then they draw a big heart and two smiling faces.

"Look, Tom. We made a letter for grandma," Lily says.

"It looks very nice, Lily. But it is not done yet. We need to fill the letter with kisses and hugs," Tom says.

"How do we do that?" Lily asks.

"Like this," Tom says. He makes a kiss sound and puts his lips on the paper. Then he makes a hug sound and wraps his arms around the paper.

"Wow, Tom. That is fun. Let me try," Lily says. She does the same as Tom. She makes a kiss sound and puts her lips on the paper. Then she makes a hug sound and wraps her arms around the paper.

They do this many times until the paper is full of kisses and hugs.

"Wow, Lily. We filled the letter with kisses and hugs. Grandma will be very happy," Tom says.

"Yes, Tom. She will be very happy. But it is hard to send the letter. How do we send the letter?" Lily says.

"I have an idea, Lily. Let's give the letter to mom. She can send the letter for us," Tom says.

"Good idea, Tom. Let's go find mom," Lily says.

They get up and run to find mom. They show her the letter and ask her to send it to grandma. Mom smiles and hugs them.

"What a lovely letter, Lily and Tom. I'm sure grandma will love it. I will send it for you today," mom says.

"Thank you, mom. We love you," Lily and Tom say.

They give mom a kiss and a hug. Then they go back to play with their toys and books. They are happy. They made a letter for grandma.
<|end|>


