Lily and Ben were playing with their toys in the living room. Lily had a furry teddy bear that she loved very much. Ben had a toy truck that he liked to zoom around. They were having fun, but they also wanted to try something new.

"Let's weigh and measure our toys!" Lily said. "We can use the scale and the ruler in the kitchen."

"OK!" Ben agreed. "That sounds like fun."

They ran to the kitchen and put their toys on the scale. Lily's teddy bear was lighter than Ben's toy truck. They used the ruler to measure their toys. Lily's teddy bear was shorter than Ben's toy truck.

"Look, my toy truck is bigger and heavier than your teddy bear!" Ben said. "That means it's better!"

"No, it's not!" Lily said. "My teddy bear is softer and cuter than your toy truck!"

They started to argue and fight over their toys. They pulled and tugged and shouted. They did not notice that the scale and the ruler were on the edge of the table. They knocked them over and they fell on the floor. The scale broke and the ruler snapped.

"Oh no!" Lily and Ben said. "We broke the scale and the ruler!"

They heard their mom coming. They knew they were in trouble. They tried to hide their toys and the broken things, but it was too late. Their mom saw the mess and was very angry.

"What have you done?" their mom said. "You were not supposed to play with the scale and the ruler. They are not toys. They are for cooking and measuring. You could have hurt yourselves or the toys. You are very naughty!"

She took away their toys and sent them to their rooms. Lily and Ben were very sad. They wished they had not fought over their toys. They wished they had not broken the scale and the ruler. They wished they had played nicely. They learned their lesson.
<|end|>


