Ben and Mia were playing in the park. They saw a big tree with many apples. They wanted to taste the apples. They ran to the tree and picked some apples.

"Look, this apple is red and shiny!" Ben said. He bit the apple. He made a face. "Yuck! This apple is sour and hard!"

Mia laughed. She looked at her apple. It was green and smooth. She bit the apple. She smiled. "Mmm! This apple is sweet and juicy!"

Ben was confused. He looked at Mia's apple. He wanted to taste it. He asked Mia, "Can I have some of your apple?"

Mia nodded. She gave Ben some of her apple. Ben tasted it. He liked it. He said, "You are right! This apple is good!"

They heard a voice. It was their mom. She called them, "Ben! Mia! It's time to go home!"

They ran to their mom. They showed her their apples. They told her about the tree.

Mom smiled. She said, "You found a knot tree! A knot tree has two kinds of apples. Some are red and sour, some are green and sweet. You can tell by the color."

Ben and Mia were surprised. They did not know that. They said, "Wow! A knot tree is cool!"

Mom said, "Yes, it is. But remember, always wash your apples before you eat them. They might have dirt or bugs on them."

Ben and Mia nodded. They washed their apples. They ate them on the way home. They were happy. They liked the knot tree. They wanted to come back to the park and taste more apples.
<|end|>


