Ben liked to play the drum. He had a big drum and two sticks. He made loud noises with the drum. He liked to make different noises. He liked to make fast noises and slow noises. He liked to make high noises and low noises. He liked to make happy noises and sad noises. He was a musician.

One day, Ben went to the park with his mom. He saw some kids playing with a ball. He wanted to play with them. He took his drum and his sticks. He walked to the kids. He said, "Hi, I am Ben. Can I play with you?"

The kids looked at Ben. They saw his drum and his sticks. They laughed. They said, "No, you can't play with us. You are different. You have a drum. We have a ball. You make noises. We play games. You are not fun. You are weird. Go away."

Ben felt sad. He did not understand. He liked his drum. He liked to make noises. He liked to be a musician. He said, "But I can play with you. I can make noises with my drum. I can make noises that match your game. I can make noises that make you happy. I can make noises that make you laugh. I can be fun. I can be your friend."

The kids looked at Ben. They saw his sad face. They saw his big drum. They saw his two sticks. They felt curious. They said, "Really? You can make noises that match our game? You can make noises that make us happy? You can make noises that make us laugh? How can you do that?"

Ben smiled. He said, "I can show you. I can make a noise for each of you. I can make a noise that tells something about you. I can make a noise that you like. Do you dare me to do that?"

The kids nodded. They said, "Yes, we dare you to do that. Show us what you can do with your drum."

Ben was happy. He said, "OK, watch me. I will make a noise for each of you." He looked at the first kid. He saw that he had a red shirt. He said, "You have a red shirt. Red is a bright color. Red is a loud color. Red is a fun color. I will make a noise that is bright, loud, and fun." He hit his drum with his sticks. He made a noise that was bright, loud, and fun. The kid smiled. He said, "Wow, that is a good noise. That is a noise that I like. That is a noise that matches my shirt."

Ben looked at the second kid. He saw that she had a blue hat. He said, "You have a blue hat. Blue is a cool color. Blue is a calm color. Blue is a nice color. I will make a noise that is cool, calm, and nice." He tapped his drum with his sticks. He made a noise that was cool, calm, and nice. The kid smiled. She said, "Wow, that is a good noise. That is a noise that I like. That is a noise that matches my hat."

