Ben looked at the fourth kid. He saw that she had a yellow dress. He said, "You have a yellow dress. Yellow is a bright color. Yellow is a happy color. Yellow is a nice color. I will make a noise that is bright, happy, and nice." He shook his drum with his sticks. He made a noise that was bright, happy, and nice. The kid smiled. She said, "Wow, that is a good noise. That is a noise that I like. That is a noise that matches my dress."

Ben looked at the fifth kid. He saw that he had a purple backpack. He said, "You have a purple backpack. Purple is a different color. Purple is a special color. Purple is a fun color. I will make a noise that is different, special, and fun." He flipped his drum with his sticks. He made a noise that was different, special, and fun. The kid smiled. He said, "Wow, that is a good noise. That is a noise that I like. That is a noise that matches
<|end|>


