Ben and Lily were playing in the garden. They saw a big jar on the table. It was full of honey. Ben liked honey very much. He wanted to eat some.

"Let's open the jar and have some honey," he said to Lily.

Lily was not sure. She saw a sign on the jar. It said: "Do not touch. This is for the hairy bear."

"What is a hairy bear?" she asked Ben.

Ben shrugged. He did not know. He did not care. He wanted honey.

He climbed on the table and reached for the jar. He tried to twist the lid. It was very tight. He pulled harder and harder. The jar slipped from his hands. It fell on the ground. It broke into pieces. The honey spilled everywhere.

"Oh no!" Lily cried. "You destroyed the jar! Now the hairy bear will be angry!"

Ben looked at the mess. He felt scared. He heard a loud roar. He turned around. He saw a big, brown, hairy bear coming out of the woods. It smelled the honey. It saw the broken jar. It saw Ben and Lily.

"Who did this?" the bear growled. "Who took my honey?"

Ben and Lily ran away as fast as they could. They did not stop until they reached their house. They learned a lesson. They never touched the hairy bear's jar again.
