Sara and Ben were playing in the kitchen. They liked to pretend they were chefs and make yummy food. They used pots and pans and spoons and bowls. They also used things from the cabinet, like flour and sugar and salt.

"Look, I made a cake!" Sara said, showing Ben a bowl of flour and water. "It has sugar and salt and eggs and milk. Do you want some?"

Ben looked at the bowl and made a face. "That does not look like a cake. That looks like mud. I do not want some. I want a real cake. A cake with frosting and sprinkles and candles."

Sara felt sad. She wanted to make Ben happy. She said, "Maybe we can have a real cake later. Maybe Mom will make one for us. Or maybe we can dream of one. Do you know how to dream?"

Ben nodded. He knew how to dream. He said, "Yes, I know how to dream. You close your eyes and think of something you like. Then you see it in your head. Like this." He closed his eyes and thought of a big, yummy cake.

Sara closed her eyes too. She thought of a cake as well. She thought of a pink cake with white frosting and red sprinkles and candles. She saw it in her head. She smiled.

They opened their eyes and looked at each other. They said, "Wow, we had the same dream! We dreamed of a cake!"

They hugged and laughed. They felt happy. They did not need a real cake. They had a dream cake. And a dream cake was yummy too.
