One day, a woman went to the shop. She wanted to buy a cake for her son. He had a birthday today. She saw many cakes in the shop. They looked yummy and pretty. She did not know which cake to choose.

She asked the shop man for help. "Which cake is good for my son?" she said. The shop man smiled. He showed her a cake with chocolate and cherries. "This cake is good for your son," he said. "It is sweet and soft. It has his name on it. See? Tom."

The woman liked the cake. She thanked the shop man. She paid for the cake. She took the cake and went home. She was happy. She wanted to make her son happy too.

She got home and saw her son. He was playing with his toys. He saw the cake and his eyes lit up. He ran to the woman and hugged her. "Thank you, mom!" he said. "This cake is good. I love you."

The woman hugged him back. She was happy. She loved him too. She said, "Happy birthday, Tom. You are a good son. I am proud of you." They cut the cake and ate it. They had a good time. They were a happy family.
