Tom and Sam are brothers. They like to play with their toys. They have a big ship with a flag and a wheel. They pretend to be pirates and sail on the sea.

One day, they find a sharp knife in the kitchen. They think it is a sword. They want to use it for their game. They take it to their room and hide it under the bed.

"Look, Sam, I have a sword for our ship!" Tom says. He shows the knife to Sam.

"Wow, that is a cool sword, Tom!" Sam says. He wants to touch it.

"Be careful, Sam, it is very sharp. It can cut you!" Tom says. He holds the knife in his hand.

Sam does not listen. He reaches for the knife. He wants to hold it too. He grabs the blade. He feels a pain in his finger. He drops the knife. He sees blood on his finger. He starts to cry.

"Ow, ow, ow! It hurts, Tom, it hurts!" Sam says. He runs to their mom.

Mom hears Sam crying. She sees the blood on his finger. She sees the knife on the floor. She is angry and scared. She picks up the knife and puts it away. She takes Sam to the bathroom. She washes his finger and puts a band-aid on it. She hugs him and kisses him.

"Sam, you are very silly. You should never touch a sharp knife. It is not a toy. It is dangerous. It can hurt you very badly. Do you understand?" Mom says.

"Yes, Mom, I understand. I am sorry. I will not touch a sharp knife again. I love you, Mom." Sam says.

Mom smiles and says, "I love you too, Sam. Now, go and play with your ship. But be nice to Tom. He is your brother. And no more swords, OK?"

"OK, Mom. Thank you, Mom." Sam says. He goes back to his room. He sees Tom waiting for him. He says sorry to Tom. Tom says sorry to Sam. They hug and make up. They play with their ship. They have fun. They are happy.
<|end|>


