<|asst|>
Lily liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna. Anna had long hair and a beautiful dress. Lily liked to brush Anna's hair and make her look pretty.

One day, Lily wanted to have a tea party with Anna and her other dolls. She put a tablecloth on the floor and set out some cups and plates. She filled a teapot with water and pretended it was tea. She poured some tea for Anna and said, "Here you go, Anna. You are my best friend."

But Lily poured too much tea. The tea spilled over the cup and onto Anna's dress. Lily gasped and said, "Oh no, Anna! I'm sorry! Your dress is wet!" She tried to wipe the tea off with a napkin, but it only made it worse. The tea stained Anna's dress and made it look dirty.

Lily felt sad and guilty. She hugged Anna and said, "I'm sorry, Anna. I ruined your beautiful dress. You must be mad at me." She looked at Anna's face and hoped she would smile.

But Anna did not smile. She did not say anything. She was just a doll. Lily knew that, but she wished Anna could talk to her and forgive her.

Then Lily heard a voice. It was her mom. She came into the room and saw Lily and Anna on the floor. She said, "What are you doing, Lily? Are you having a tea party?"

Lily nodded and said, "Yes, mom. But I spilled some tea on Anna's dress. I'm sorry, mom. I didn't mean to."

Mom smiled and said, "It's okay, Lily. It was an accident. You don't have to be sorry. Anna is not mad at you. She still loves you. And so do I."

Mom picked up Anna and said, "Look, Lily. Anna's dress is not ruined. It's just wet. We can wash it and dry it and it will be good as new. And you know what? Even if Anna's dress was ruined, she would still be beautiful. Because beauty is not about what you wear. It's about who you are. And you, Lily, are a beautiful girl. You are kind, caring, and creative. You have a beautiful heart. And that's what makes you and Anna best friends."

Lily smiled and said, "Thank you, mom. You are beautiful too. You are smart, funny, and loving. You have a beautiful heart too. And that's what makes you and me best friends."

Mom hugged Lily and Anna and said, "I love you, Lily. And I love you, Anna. You are both my beautiful girls. Now, let's go and wash Anna's dress. And then we can have some real tea and cookies. How does that sound?"

Lily nodded and said, "That sounds great, mom. Let's go." She held Anna by the waist and followed mom to the kitchen. She was happy and grateful. She had a beautiful mom, a beautiful doll, and a beautiful day.
<|end|>


