Lily and Max were best friends. They liked to play in the park and share their toys. One day, they saw a shiny thing on the ground. It was a diamond. Lily and Max both wanted it.

"I saw it first!" Lily said.

"No, I saw it first!" Max said.

They started to pull the diamond and shout at each other. They were not nice to each other. They forgot to be friends.

A lady saw them and came over. She asked them what was wrong. Lily and Max told her about the diamond. The lady smiled and said, "Do you know what this is? It is not a diamond. It is a glass bead. It is not worth anything. But your friendship is worth a lot. You should not fight over a glass bead. You should be kind and share."

Lily and Max felt embarrassed. They realized they were silly. They said sorry to each other and hugged. They gave the glass bead to the lady and thanked her. They decided to be good friends again. They learned that friendship is more important than things.
<|end|>


