Lisa and Ben are friends. They like to play together. One day, they decide to have a tea party with their toys. They put a blanket on the floor and set up some cups and plates. They pretend to pour tea and eat cookies.

"Would you like some more tea, Mr. Bear?" Lisa asks, holding a cup.

"Yes, please, Lisa. You are a very good host," Mr. Bear says, in Lisa's voice.

"Thank you, Mr. Bear. You are a very nice guest," Lisa says, smiling.

Ben watches Lisa and Mr. Bear. He wants to join the tea party, too. He picks up his toy dinosaur and makes it walk towards the blanket.

"Hello, Lisa. Hello, Mr. Bear. Can I have some tea, too?" Ben says, in his dinosaur's voice.

"Of course, Ben. You are welcome to join us," Lisa says, moving over to make some space.

"Thank you, Lisa. You are very kind," Ben says, sitting down.

Lisa pours some tea for Ben and his dinosaur. They all sip and chat and laugh. They have a lot of fun. They feel comfortable and happy.

Lisa and Ben succeed in having a good tea party. They are good friends. They love to play together.
