Tom was sad and scared. He wanted his blue car to be big again. He tried to push the button again, but he could not reach it. He cried and called for his mom.

Mom heard Tom and came to see what was wrong. She saw the small blue car and the big button. She understood what had happened. She lifted Tom and helped him push the button again. She heard another zap. She looked at the blue car. It was big again.

Tom was happy and relieved. He hugged his mom and thanked her. He played with his blue car again, but he did not touch the button anymore. He learned to be careful with things he did not know. He had fun with his blue car.
