Once upon a time, there was a tall giraffe named Jerry. Jerry loved to wear his sunglasses when it was sunny outside. One day, Jerry was walking through the jungle when he heard a loud noise. "What was that?" he asked his friend, the monkey. "I don't know," replied the monkey. "Let's go check it out!"

As they walked, they saw a big rock in the middle of the path. Suddenly, a snake struck out from behind the rock! Jerry jumped back and the monkey grabbed his sunglasses. "Thanks," said Jerry. "That was close!" The snake slithered away and Jerry and the monkey continued on their walk.

After a while, they came to a river. "How are we going to get across?" asked Jerry. "I can swing on the vines," said the monkey. "But you'll have to be careful not to get your sunglasses wet!" Jerry smiled and they crossed the river safely. "Thanks for helping me," said Jerry. "I couldn't have done it without you!"
