Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside in the forest near her house. One day, she saw a pine tree and decided to give it a big hug. But when she did, she accidentally got sap all over her hands! 

Lily went home and showed her mom her dirty hands. "Oh no, Lily! You need to wash your hands before dinner," her mom said. 

Lily went to the sink to wash her hands, but the sap wouldn't come off. "This pine tree is so mean! It made my hands dirty!" she exclaimed. 

Her mom laughed and said, "Don't worry, sweetie. The pine tree didn't mean to do that. It just wants to stay strong and healthy. You can't blame it for being a pine tree." 

Lily understood and went back outside to play. She saw the pine tree again and instead of hugging it, she gently touched its needles. "I'm sorry I got mad at you, pine tree. You're still my friend," she said. 

Just then, a gust of wind blew a pine cone and it hit Lily's cheek. "Ow! That hurt!" she yelled. 

Her mom came outside and asked what happened. "The pine cone slapped me!" Lily said. 

Her mom smiled and said, "Well, sometimes even friends can accidentally hurt each other. But it's important to forgive and move on. Just like you did with the pine tree." 

Lily nodded and went back to playing, happy to have learned a valuable lesson about forgiveness and friendship.
<|end|>


