Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. Lily loved to eat dinner with her family every night. One day, her mom made her favorite food, spaghetti with meatballs. It smelled so delicious that Lily's tummy started to growl. 

As they were eating, Lily accidentally dropped her fork on the floor. She tried to pick it up, but it was too slippery. Suddenly, her brother came over and tried to grab it, but he accidentally stepped on it and it snapped in half. 

Lily was sad because she loved that fork, but her mom told her not to worry. She gave her a new fork and said that dinner was still delicious, even without the old fork. From that day on, Lily learned that accidents happen, but it's important to enjoy the good things in life, like a yummy dinner with her family.
<|end|>


