Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She wanted to go for a walk in the park, but she needed a cane to help her walk. Her mommy had a cane, but it was broken. So, Lily's mommy went to prepare a new cane for her.

After a little while, Lily's mommy came back with a new cane. It was shiny and strong. Lily was so happy! She took the cane and said, "Thank you, mommy!" Then, they went to the park together.

When they got to the park, they saw that there were many ducks swimming in the pond. Lily wanted to feed them, but she didn't have any bread. Luckily, there was a man selling bread by the pond. He had many different kinds of bread available for people to buy. Lily's mommy bought some bread and they fed the ducks together. It was a wonderful day!
