Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She felt very lonely because she had no one to play with. But one day, she met a puppy who was also feeling lonely. Lily decided to help the puppy by giving him some food and water. The puppy was happy and started following Lily everywhere she went. 

One day, Lily and the puppy went to the park. They saw a man who was looking for his lost dog. The man asked Lily if she had seen his dog. Lily remembered that she had seen a dog that looked like the one the man was looking for. She told the man where she had seen the dog. The man was very happy and grateful to Lily for helping him find his dog. 

After helping the man, Lily and the puppy went back home. Lily felt happy that she had made a new friend and had helped someone find their lost pet. She knew that being kind and helpful was the true way to make friends and not feel lonely.
