Mom said, "That's a great idea, Timmy. Why don't you build a tower with your soft blocks?"

Timmy smiled and started to build his tower with his soft blocks. He worked quietly, trying not to disturb his baby sister. When he finished, he was proud of his tower and showed it to his mom.

Mom said, "Wow, Timmy! You built a great tower and you were so quiet. You're a good big brother."

Timmy smiled and felt happy that he could build a tower and be quiet for his baby sister.
