Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy who was very hungry. He asked his mom for some food, but she said they didn't have any. Timmy's tummy was rumbling and he felt very sad. 

Suddenly, he saw a big, yummy cake on the table. Timmy's mom had made it for a party later that day. Timmy was tempted to take a bite, but he knew he shouldn't. "I must resist the cake," he said to himself. 

Just then, his sister came into the room. She had a whip in her hand and was pretending to be a princess. "I'm going to whip you!" she said, laughing. Timmy didn't like the sound of that. "No, don't whip me!" he cried. 

His sister saw that Timmy was hungry and sad, so she decided to share the cake with him. They sat down together and ate the cake, feeling happy and full. Timmy was glad he resisted the temptation to take the cake earlier and grateful to his sister for being kind.
<|end|>


