Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a shy cat named Mittens. One day, Lily wanted to call her grandma on the telephone. She picked up the phone and dialed the number, but Mittens was scared of the loud ringing sound. 

"Meow, meow," said Mittens. 

"It's okay, Mittens," said Lily. "The phone won't hurt you." 

Suddenly, the phone rang loudly and Lily answered it. "Hello?" she said. 

"Hi, Lily! It's Grandma!" said a voice on the other end. 

"Zoom, zoom!" said Lily, excitedly. "Grandma is coming to visit us!" 

Mittens looked up at Lily and meowed happily. They both couldn't wait for Grandma to arrive.
