Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved playing outside and watching the clouds go by. One day, Timmy's mom asked him to help her supply some food to the animals in the forest. Timmy was enthusiastic to help his mom and quickly gathered some carrots and apples.

As they walked through the forest, they noticed a storm was coming. Timmy's mom told him they needed to hurry and finish supplying the food before the storm arrived. Timmy agreed and they continued on their mission.

Suddenly, the storm hit and it was very loud and scary. Timmy and his mom tried to run back home, but they got lost in the forest. They were very scared and didn't know what to do. Timmy's mom tried to call for help, but there was no one around to hear them.

Eventually, they had to spend the night in the forest. They were cold, wet, and hungry. Timmy was very sad that they couldn't make it back home. The next morning, they were finally found by a search party. Timmy and his mom were safe, but they learned to always be careful when going out in the storm.
<|end|>


