Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily who loved to cook. She had a big pot that she used to make soup and stew. One day, her mom said, "Lily, we are having a party tonight and we need to make a special dish. Can you help me?"

Lily was excited to help her mom and asked, "What should we make?"

Her mom replied, "We need to make a cake, but we don't have any eggs. Can you go to the store and get some?"

Lily went to the store, but she couldn't find any eggs. She asked the store clerk if they were available, but they were all sold out. She was sad and thought she wouldn't succeed in making the cake.

But then, she remembered that her neighbor had chickens and maybe they had some eggs. She went to her neighbor's house and asked if they had any eggs. They did! Lily was so happy and thanked her neighbor. She went back home and helped her mom make the cake. It was delicious and everyone loved it!
<|end|>


