Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside in the misty morning. One day, she saw a stubborn bird sitting on a tree branch. She wanted to make the bird fly away, so she started to clap her hands. But the bird didn't move. 

Lily clapped louder and louder, but the bird still didn't move. She wondered why the bird was so stubborn. Then, she realized that the bird was just resting and needed some peace and quiet. So, she stopped clapping and watched the bird for a while. 

After a few minutes, the bird flew away. Lily was happy that the bird was able to rest and she learned that sometimes it's important to be quiet and patient. From that day on, Lily enjoyed watching the birds and animals without disturbing them with her clapping.
<|end|>


