<|asst|>
Lila and Ben are playing in the park. They see a big cage with a lion inside. The lion looks sad and hungry.

"Hello, lion," Lila says. "Why are you in the cage?"

The lion roars softly. "I was taken from my home by bad people. They want to show me to other people for money. They lock me here and do not give me enough food or water."

"That is not fair," Ben says. "We want to help you, lion. How can we open the cage?"

The lion points with his paw. "There is a key under that rock. But be careful, the bad people might come back soon."

Lila and Ben look around. They do not see anyone. They run to the rock and lift it. They find the key and run back to the cage. They put the key in the lock and turn it. The cage door opens.

"Thank you, Lila and Ben," the lion says. "You are very helpful and brave. Now I can go back to my home and family."

The lion hugs Lila and Ben with his big paws. Then he runs away, fast and free.

Lila and Ben wave goodbye to the lion. They are happy that they helped him. They hope he will be safe and happy in his home.
<|end|>


