Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big dog. The dog is angry. It barks and runs at them.

"Help!" Tom and Mia shout. They run away from the dog. They see a small house. They go inside. The house is dark and dirty. There are many things that they do not know.

"What is this?" Mia asks. She points to a metal box. It has bars and a lock. It is a cell.

"I do not know," Tom says. He is fearful. He hears the dog outside. It scratches the door. It wants to get in.

"Go away, dog!" Tom yells. He throws a rock at the door. The dog growls and bites the rock. It does not go away.

Mia starts to cry. She is scared. She hugs Tom. Tom hugs her back. He tries to be brave.

"Maybe someone will come and help us," he says. He hopes that it is true. He does not like the cell. He does not like the dog. He wants to go home.
