Tom and Lily felt nervous. They did not know the stranger. They did not want his candy. They remembered what their mom and dad told them. Never talk to strangers. Never take anything from strangers.

They ran away from the stranger. They climbed the fence and went to the other side of the park. They found their mom and dad and told them what happened.

Their mom and dad hugged them and said, "You did the right thing. We are proud of you. You are brave and smart. The stranger was bad. He wanted to hurt you. But you are safe now. We love you."
