Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim liked to play with his friends in the park. One day, Tim found a small pebble. It was very pretty. He wanted to show it to his friends.

Tim went to his friends and said, "Look at my pebble!" His friends liked it too. But one friend, named Sam, was angry. Sam wanted the pebble for himself. He said, "Give me the pebble or I will not play with you!"

Tim did not want to make Sam more angry, so he said, "Okay, I surrender. You can have the pebble." Sam took the pebble and said, "Thank you." Then, they all played together happily in the park.
