One day, a little girl named Amy went to her friend's house. Her friend, Tim, had a big piano in his room. Amy wanted to play the piano, but Tim said, "No, it is fragile. You might break it."

Amy was sad and went to sit in a corner. She looked at the piano and thought, "I can play it just a little, and it won't break." So, she got up and played a small song on the piano. But, oh no! One of the piano keys broke!

Tim was very upset and told Amy, "I told you not to play the piano." Amy felt sorry and said, "I'm sorry, Tim. I didn't mean to break it." Tim and Amy went to Tim's mom and told her about the broken piano key. Tim's mom was not angry. She said, "It's okay. We can fix it."

Tim and Amy helped Tim's mom fix the piano key. They were very careful because the piano was fragile. After they fixed it, they played a song together on the piano. Tim and Amy were happy, and they learned to listen and be careful with fragile things.
