Once upon a time, there was a pretty little girl named Lily. She loved winter because she could play in the snow. One day, Lily went outside to build a snowman.

She started to roll a big snowball for the snowman's body. Then, she rolled a smaller one for the head. Lily put the smaller snowball on top of the big one. "Now I need to add a face," Lily said. She found two small rocks for the eyes and a carrot for the nose. She used a long stick for the mouth.

Lily's friend, Tim, came over to see her snowman. "Wow, that's a big snowman!" Tim said. "Can I add something too?" Lily smiled and said, "Yes, let's add a hat and a scarf to keep him warm!" So they found a hat and a scarf and put them on the snowman. They laughed and played in the snow all day. The pretty winter day was perfect for making new friends and having fun.
