One day, a little girl named Lucy found a big, shiny rock. She wanted to keep it, but she knew the old man's law said that all big, shiny rocks must be given to him. Lucy was sad, but she went to the old man's house to give him the rock. The old man saw how much Lucy loved the rock and said, "I will change the law. From now on, you can keep the big, shiny rocks you find."

Lucy was so happy that she told all her friends about the new law. They all went to look for big, shiny rocks to keep. As they played, they found many rocks and became very happy. The old man saw how happy the children were and knew that changing the law was a good idea. And from that day on, the town was a happier place for everyone.
