One day, Tom found a piece of paper. He wanted to make an ordinary aeroplane. He asked his mom, "Can you help me fold this paper?" Mom said, "Yes, I can help you."

They started to fold the paper. But Tom's little sister, Jane, wanted to play with the aeroplane too. Tom said, "No, it's mine!" Jane started to cry. Mom said, "Tom, you should share with your sister."

Tom thought for a moment. He said, "Okay, I will share." Jane stopped crying. They played with the aeroplane together. They had a lot of fun. The moral of the story is to share with others.
