Once upon a time, there was a charming little dog named Spot. Spot loved to play at the park with his best friend, a little girl named Jane. They would run, jump, and play all day long.

One day, Jane and Spot found a big wrap on the ground. "What is this?" Jane asked. "Let's open it," said Spot. They opened the wrap and found a beautiful toy inside. They knew someone must have lost it and felt sad.

Jane and Spot decided to find the toy's owner. They asked all their friends at the park, but no one knew who it belonged to. Finally, they found a little boy crying under a tree. "Why are you sad?" asked Jane. "I lost my toy," the boy said. Jane and Spot gave the toy back to the little boy, and he was so happy. The boy thanked Jane and Spot, and they all became good friends.

The moral of the story is to always help others and do the right thing.
