One day, a little boy named Tim went to play outside. He saw a cool tree with many leaves. Tim wanted to bring some leaves to his mom. He picked up a leaf and saw some ash under the tree. 

"Who made this ash?" Tim asked. A small bird on the tree branch said, "I made the ash. I was playing with a stick and it got hot. Then the stick turned into ash."

Tim said, "Oh, be careful next time. Ash can be dirty." The bird said, "Thank you, I will be more careful." Tim and the bird became friends. They played under the cool tree all day. Tim's mom was happy with the leaves he brought her.
