Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lucy. She had a big toy box with a lock. Every day, she would play with her toys. But there was one toy she never played with. It was a magnet. Lucy's mom told her not to play with it because it could unlock the toy box all by itself.

One day, Lucy's friend, Tom, came over to play. They played with all the toys, but they did not play with the magnet. Tom saw the magnet and asked Lucy about it. Lucy told Tom what her mom said about the magnet. Tom wanted to see if it was true. So, they put the magnet near the lock on the toy box.

The magnet unlocked the toy box! Lucy and Tom were so happy. They played with all the toys in the toy box. But they did not clean up after they were done playing. When Lucy's mom came home, she saw the mess. She was not happy. She said that Lucy and Tom had spoiled the nice clean room.

Lucy and Tom felt bad. They knew they should have cleaned up. They promised to always clean up after playing from now on. And they put the magnet back in the toy box, so it could not unlock the toy box again.
