Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a small red ball that she loved to play with. One day, she set her ball on a high shelf before she went to play outside. When Lily came back, she saw her ball was not on the shelf. She was sad and asked her mom, "Mom, have you seen my ball?"

Her mom said, "Not yet, dear. Maybe your brother took it. Let's ask him." So, they went to find Lily's brother, Tim. When they found him, Lily asked, "Tim, did you take my ball from the shelf?" Tim looked at her and said, "No, I did not. But I saw a rude cat playing with a red ball. Maybe it was your ball."

Lily and her mom went outside to look for the rude cat. They saw the cat playing with the red ball. Lily said, "Hey, cat! That is my ball! Please give it back!" The cat looked at Lily and gave the ball back. Lily was happy to have her ball again. She thanked the cat and played with her ball all day.
