Tom was a young boy who liked to help his dad with the wood. His dad had a big axe that he used to chop the wood. Tom wanted to use the axe too, but his dad said it was too sharp and heavy for him.

One day, Tom saw the axe lying on the ground near the woodpile. He thought his dad was not looking, so he ran to the axe and tried to lift it. But the axe was too heavy for him, and he dropped it on a rock. The axe made a loud clang and the blade broke.

Tom was scared and sad. He broke his dad's axe. He did not know what to do. He hid the axe behind some bushes and ran to his room.

His dad heard the clang and went to see what happened. He saw the broken axe and the rock. He knew Tom had tried to use the axe. He was angry and worried. He went to Tom's room and knocked on the door.

"Tom, come out. I need to talk to you," his dad said.

Tom opened the door and looked at his dad. He saw his dad's angry face and felt sorry.

"Dad, I'm sorry. I broke your axe. I wanted to help you with the wood. I did not mean to break it," Tom said.

His dad sighed and hugged him.

"Tom, I'm glad you are sorry. But you should not touch my axe. It is dangerous and not for you. You could have hurt yourself or someone else. You need to be careful and listen to me," his dad said.

"I know, dad. I'm sorry. I won't touch your axe again. Can you fix it?" Tom asked.

His dad smiled and nodded.

"Yes, I can fix it. I can repair it with some glue and a new handle. But you have to help me. You have to find the broken piece and bring it to me. And you have to promise me you will never touch my axe again," his dad said.

"I promise, dad. I will help you. I will find the broken piece and bring it to you. And I will never touch your axe again," Tom said.

Tom and his dad went to the woodpile and found the broken piece. They took it to the shed and repaired the axe. They worked together and had fun. Tom learned how to repair things and his dad forgave him. They hugged and said they loved each other. They were happy.
<|end|>


