Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play with pens and paper. They draw many things. They draw suns, stars, flowers and cats. They have fun.

One day, Lily has a new pen. It is big and red. It has thick ink. Lily says, "Look, Tom, I have a new pen. It is very good. It makes thick lines. Do you want to try?"

Tom says, "Yes, please. I want to try your new pen. It looks nice." He takes the pen from Lily. He draws a big circle on the paper. He likes the pen.

But then, something bad happens. The pen breaks. The ink spills out. It makes a big mess. The ink is on the paper, on the table, on the floor and on Tom's hands. Tom is scared. He says, "Oh no! The pen is broken. The ink is everywhere. What do we do?"

Lily is scared too. She says, "We have to run. We have to hide. Mom will be angry. She will see the ink. She will not like it." She grabs Tom's hand. They run to the closet. They hide inside. They hope Mom will not find them. They are sorry for the mess. They are sorry for the pen. They are not happy.
<|end|>


