Sam and Lily were playing with their toys in the living room. They liked to make loud noises and pretend they were animals or cars or superheroes. They did not hear their mom calling them from the kitchen.

"Sam! Lily! Dinner is ready!" Mom said. She sounded serious. She did not like it when they ignored her. She put the plates on the table and went to find them.

She saw them on the floor, surrounded by toys. They were still making noises and having fun. She frowned and said, "Sam, Lily, I told you dinner is ready. You need to stop playing and come eat. Now."

Sam and Lily looked at each other. They knew Mom was serious. They did not want to make her angry. They also liked dinner. It smelled good. They decided to obey Mom and put away their toys.

They ran to the kitchen and sat on their chairs. They said, "Sorry, Mom. We did not hear you. We were playing."

Mom smiled and said, "It's okay. I know you were playing. But you need to listen when I call you. Dinner is important. It is good for you. And we can talk and share our day."

Sam and Lily nodded and said, "Okay, Mom. We will listen next time. We love you. And we love dinner."

Mom hugged them and said, "I love you too. And I love dinner. Now, let's eat."
<|end|>


