Tom and Mia are playing with their toy cars in the living room. They have a big box of cars of different colors and sizes. They like to make roads and bridges with their blocks and pretend to drive around.

"Look, I have a green car!" Mia says, holding up a shiny toy. "It is very fast and pretty."

"I have a green car too!" Tom says, showing his own toy. "But mine is bigger and louder. It can go over anything!"

They start to race their cars on the floor, making vroom and beep sounds. They have fun, but they also want to win. They try to push each other's cars out of the way.

"Hey, stop that!" Mia says, as Tom bumps her car with his. "You are cheating!"

"No, I'm not!" Tom says, as Mia nudges his car with hers. "You are cheating!"

They get angry and start to fight. They grab each other's cars and throw them across the room. The cars scatter everywhere, hitting the walls and the furniture. Some of them break and lose their wheels.

"Stop, stop, stop!" Mom says, coming into the living room. She sees the mess and the broken toys. She is not happy. "What are you doing? Why are you throwing your cars?"

Tom and Mia look at Mom. They feel sorry and ashamed. They don't know what to say.

Mom sighs and picks up the cars. She puts them back in the box. She finds a switch on the wall and turns it on. The lights go off.

"Time for bed," Mom says. "You have played enough. You need to rest and say sorry to each other."

Tom and Mia nod and hug each other. They say sorry and give each other their cars. They follow Mom to their bedroom. They brush their teeth and put on their pajamas. They get into their beds and snuggle with their cars.

"Good night, Tom," Mia says.

"Good night, Mia," Tom says.

They close their eyes and fall asleep. They dream of green cars and happy races.
<|end|>


