Tom likes to play with his toy cars. He has many cars of different colors and sizes. He likes to make them zoom and crash on the floor. His favorite car is a big red truck with a loud motor. He calls it Big Red.

One day, Tom's mom tells him to bring Big Red to the park. She says they will meet his friend Sam there. Tom is happy. He likes to play with Sam. He puts Big Red in his backpack and goes with his mom to the park.

At the park, Tom sees Sam waiting for him. Sam has a blue car with a shiny hood. He calls it Bluey. Tom and Sam say hello and take out their cars. They start to race them on the grass. Big Red is faster than Bluey. Tom is proud of his car.

But then, something bad happens. Big Red starts to slow down. Its motor makes a funny noise. It stops moving. Tom is sad. He tries to make it go again, but it does not work. He thinks his car is broken.

Sam sees Tom's sad face. He feels sorry for him. He says, "Don't worry, Tom. Maybe your car is just weak. Maybe it needs new batteries. I have some in my backpack. Let me bring them to you. Maybe we can fix your car together."

Tom smiles. He says, "Thank you, Sam. You are a good friend. Maybe you are right. Maybe new batteries will make Big Red strong again. Let's try it."

Sam and Tom work together to open Big Red's motor and put in new batteries. They close it and turn it on. Big Red makes a loud noise and starts to move again. Tom is happy. He says, "Yay! Big Red is fixed! Thank you, Sam!"

Sam is happy too. He says, "You're welcome, Tom. I'm glad your car is working again. Now let's race again. Maybe this time Bluey will win."

Tom and Sam laugh and race their cars again. They have fun at the park. They are good friends.
<|end|>


