Anna likes to write in her diary every day. She has a pink diary with a lock and a key. She writes about her friends, her toys, her dreams and her feelings. She thinks her diary is her best friend.

One day, Anna hears a knock on her door. She hides her diary under her pillow and says, "Who is it?"

"It's me, your brother Tom," says a voice. "Can I come in?"

Anna does not like Tom. He is mean and noisy. He always breaks her toys and teases her. She says, "No, go away!"

But Tom does not listen. He opens the door and walks in. He sees Anna's diary on her bed. He grabs it and says, "What is this? Is this your diary? Let me see what you write!"

Anna is scared and angry. She jumps off her bed and tries to get her diary back. She says, "No, give it back! It's mine! It's private!"

Tom laughs and runs away with the diary. He says, "Too bad, I'm going to read it and tell everyone your secrets!"

Anna cries and follows him. She hopes he does not open the lock. She thinks Tom is a poor brother. She wishes he would leave her alone. She wants her diary back. She wonders what she can do.
<|end|>


