Lily and Max were cheerful. They wanted to celebrate. It was their birthday. They had a big cake with candles. They had balloons and hats. They had many friends to play with.

"Happy birthday, Lily and Max!" their friends said. They sang a song for them. Lily and Max blew out the candles. They made a wish. They wished for more fun and more friends.

"Thank you, thank you!" Lily and Max said. They cut the cake and shared it with their friends. They ate the cake and licked their fingers. It was yummy. They drank juice and giggled.

"Let's play outside!" Lily said. She put on her sunglasses. They were pink and sparkly. She liked them very much. She got them as a present from her grandma.

"OK, let's go!" Max said. He put on his sunglasses too. They were blue and cool. He liked them very much. He got them as a present from his grandpa.

They ran outside with their friends. They played tag and hide and seek. They chased and found each other. They laughed and shouted. They had a lot of fun.

Lily and Max were cheerful. They celebrated their birthday. They had a great day. They hugged their friends and their parents. They said, "We love you!" They were happy.
