Bunny was a little rabbit who loved to hop around the meadow. He liked to explore new places and meet new friends. One day, he saw a big pond with shiny water and green plants. He wanted to hop closer and see what was inside.

But Frog, who lived in the pond, did not like strangers. He saw Bunny hopping near his home and croaked loudly. "Who are you and what do you want?" he asked in a grumpy voice.

Bunny was scared and anxious. He did not know how to answer Frog's question. He thought Frog might be angry or mean. He wanted to hop away, but he also wanted to be polite. He said in a small voice, "I am Bunny and I just want to look at the pond. It is very pretty."

Frog was surprised by Bunny's answer. He realized that Bunny was not a threat, but a curious and friendly visitor. He felt sorry for being rude and decided to be nice. He said in a softer voice, "I am Frog and this is my home. You can look at the pond, but be careful not to fall in. The water is deep and cold."

Bunny was relieved and happy. He thanked Frog and hopped closer to the pond. He saw fish and ducks and water lilies. He asked Frog many questions and learned a lot. Frog answered patiently and shared his knowledge. They became friends and had fun.

The moral of the story is: Don't judge someone by their appearance or voice. Be kind and respectful to others and you might make a new friend.
<|end|>


