<|asst|>
Lily and Tom were twins who liked to play together. One day, they found a candle in a drawer and decided to light it. They thought it was fun to watch the flame flicker and make shadows on the wall.

"Look, Lily, the candle is so pretty!" Tom said.

"Yes, Tom, it is. But we have to be careful. Mommy said candles can be hot and dangerous," Lily said.

They played with the candle for a while, but then they heard Mommy calling them for dinner. They ran to the kitchen, forgetting to blow out the candle.

The candle burned slowly on the table, until it reached a paper napkin. The napkin caught fire and soon the whole table was on fire. Smoke filled the room and the fire alarm went off.

Mommy smelled the smoke and ran to the living room. She saw the fire and grabbed a blanket to put it out. She was very scared and angry.

"Lily! Tom! What have you done? You could have burned the house down! How could you play with a candle?" Mommy shouted.

Lily and Tom came back to the living room and saw the mess. They felt very sorry and ashamed. They hugged Mommy and cried.

"We're sorry, Mommy. We didn't mean to. We just wanted to see the candle. We forgot to blow it out. We love you, Mommy. Please don't be mad at us," they said.

Mommy hugged them back and calmed down. She was glad they were not hurt, but she was still upset.

"I love you too, Lily and Tom. But you have to listen to me. Candles are not toys. They are for grown-ups only. They can cause fire and hurt people. You have to be more careful and responsible. Do you understand?" Mommy said.

"Yes, Mommy. We understand. We're sorry. We won't play with candles again. We learned our lesson. We don't want to miss you or our home," they said.

Mommy kissed them and took them to dinner. She hoped they would remember their mistake and never do it again. She also hoped they would always appreciate what they have and not take it for granted. She knew they were good kids who made a bad choice. She loved them very much.
<|end|>


