Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play in Tom's house. Tom's house is warm and big. It has many toys and books. Tom and Mia have fun with the toys and books.

One day, Tom and Mia hear a loud noise. It comes from the kitchen. They are curious. They go to the kitchen. They see a big mess. There are pots and pans on the floor. There are eggs and flour on the table. There is a cat on the counter. The cat is licking a bowl of milk.

Tom and Mia are surprised. They wonder who made the mess. They see a note on the fridge. It says: "Sorry, I had to go to work. Please do not disturb the cat. He is hungry. Love, Mom."

Tom and Mia look at the cat. The cat looks at them. He meows. He jumps off the counter. He runs to the living room. He knocks over a lamp. He scratches a sofa. He chases a ball.

Tom and Mia follow the cat. They try to stop him. They say: "No, cat! Stop! You are disturbing the house! You are making more mess!"

But the cat does not listen. He is too playful. He does not care. He thinks it is fun. He disturbs the house more and more.

Tom and Mia are worried. They do not know what to do. They hope Mom will come back soon. They hope she will not be angry. They hope the cat will calm down. They hope the house will be warm and big and nice again.
<|end|>


