<|asst|>
Sara and Max are playing in the park with their dog, Spot. They like to run and chase and throw the ball for Spot. Spot is a good dog and a healthy dog. He has soft fur and four paws.

One day, they discover something new in the park. It is a big hole in the ground, near a tree. Sara and Max are curious. They want to see what is in the hole. They go closer and look inside.

"Wow, look at that!" Sara says. "It is a baby fox!"

The baby fox is small and cute. It has orange fur and a white tail. It also has four paws, like Spot. But it looks scared and lonely. It makes a soft noise.

"Hello, baby fox," Max says. "Don't be afraid. We are your friends."

He reaches out his hand to touch the baby fox. But Spot barks and jumps in front of him. He does not like the baby fox. He thinks it is a bad animal. He wants to protect Sara and Max.

"Spot, no!" Sara says. "The baby fox is not bad. He is just lost. He needs our help."

She tries to calm Spot down. She pets his fur and tells him to be nice. She also tells Max to be careful. She says they should not touch the baby fox. They should find his mom.

They look around the park. They see a big fox near the fence. She has orange fur and a white tail, like the baby fox. She is looking for her baby. She hears his noise. She runs to the hole.

The baby fox sees his mom. He is happy. He runs to her. She licks his fur and nuzzles his nose. She thanks Sara and Max for finding her baby. She says they are good kids and a good dog.

Sara and Max are happy too. They wave goodbye to the foxes. They go back to playing with Spot. They have a fun day in the park. They learn something new. They discover that foxes have paws, like dogs. But they are different animals. And they need different homes.
<|end|>


