<|asst|>
Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play with dolls and cars. One day, they find a big box in the garage. They have an idea.

"Let's make a house for our dolls and cars!" Anna says.

"Yes, let's do that!" Ben agrees.

They take the box to the backyard. They cut a door and windows with scissors. They draw flowers and stars with crayons. They put a blanket on the top. They are very happy with their house.

"Look, our house is so pretty!" Anna says.

"It is! What is its name?" Ben asks.

Anna thinks for a moment. She likes the sound of the wind and the birds. She says, "Let's name it Windy Birdy House!"

Ben likes the name. He says, "Windy Birdy House is a good name. It fits our house!"

They put their dolls and cars inside the house. They pretend to cook and eat and sleep. They have a lot of fun in their Windy Birdy House. They are very proud of their idea.
<|end|>


