<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were twins who liked to play in the woods. They had a cabin that their dad made for them. It was small and cozy, with a door and a window and a rug. They had toys and books and blankets inside.

One day, they decided to play a game of dare. They took turns daring each other to do things that were scary or hard. Lily dared Ben to touch a spider. Ben dared Lily to climb a tall tree. They laughed and screamed and had fun.

Then, Ben had an idea. He saw a big hole in the ground, near the cabin. He wondered what was inside. He dared Lily to go into the hole and see. Lily was scared, but she did not want to lose the game. She said, "OK, I will go, but you have to come with me."

They held hands and walked to the hole. It was dark and deep and smelled bad. They heard noises that sounded like growls and hisses. They felt something move under their feet. They were very afraid. They wanted to go back to the cabin, but they did not know how to get out.

Suddenly, they saw a light. It was their dad, who had followed them. He had a flashlight and a rope. He saw them in the hole and said, "What are you doing here? This is a dangerous place. There are snakes and rats and other things that can hurt you. Come on, I will help you out."

He threw the rope down and told them to grab it. He was strong and flexible, and he pulled them up. They hugged him and said, "Thank you, dad. We are sorry. We were playing a game of dare and we went too far. We will never do that again."

He smiled and said, "I'm glad you are safe. I know you like to have fun, but you have to be careful. There are some things that you should not dare to do. Come on, let's go back to the cabin. I have some cookies and milk for you."
<|end|>


