<|asst|>
Anna and Ben were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had many toys, but their favorite was a big screen that showed pictures and sounds. They could touch the screen and make things happen, like animals and colors and games.

One day, their mom said, "Anna and Ben, I have to go to the store. You can play with the screen, but be careful. It is delicate and can break. Do not hit it or throw things at it. I will be back soon."

Anna and Ben said, "Okay, mom. We will be good." They hugged their mom and watched her leave. Then they turned on the screen and started to play.

Anna liked to play with the animals. She touched the screen and made a cat meow, a dog bark, and a bird sing. She smiled and said, "Look, Ben, the animals are so cute and funny."

Ben liked to play with the colors. He touched the screen and made it change from red to blue to green to yellow. He laughed and said, "Look, Anna, the colors are so bright and pretty."

They played for a while, but then they got bored. They wanted to try something new. They looked around and saw a ball, a pillow, and a book. They had an idea.

Anna said, "Ben, let's play catch with the ball. Maybe the screen will catch it too."

Ben said, "Okay, Anna, that sounds fun. But we have to be gentle. We don't want to spoil the screen."

They threw the ball to each other, and sometimes to the screen. The screen bounced the ball back, and made funny noises. Anna and Ben giggled and clapped.

But then, Anna threw the ball too hard. It hit the screen with a loud bang. The screen cracked and went black. The pictures and sounds were gone.

Anna and Ben gasped and dropped the ball. They ran to the screen and touched it. It was cold and silent. They felt scared and sad.

They said, "Oh no, oh no, we spoiled the screen. Mom will be mad. What will we do?"

They heard the door open. It was their mom. She saw the broken screen and the ball. She frowned and said, "Anna and Ben, what did you do? You spoiled the screen. It was delicate and expensive. You were not careful. You were naughty."

Anna and Ben cried and said, "We're sorry, mom. We wanted to play catch with the screen. We didn't mean to spoil it. Please don't be mad."

Their mom sighed and said, "I'm not mad, but I'm disappointed. You should have listened to me. You should have respected the screen. Now it's ruined. You can't play with it anymore. You have to learn from your mistake."

She hugged them and said, "I love you, Anna and Ben. But you have to be more responsible. Next time, play with your toys that are not delicate. And don't throw things at the screen. It's not a toy. It's a tool."

Anna and Ben nodded and said, "We love you, mom. We're sorry. We will be more responsible. We will play with our toys that are not delicate. And we won't throw things at the screen. We promise."

Their mom smiled and said, "That's good. Now, let's go and have some cookies. And maybe we can read a book together. Books are not delicate. They are durable. And they have pictures and words that can teach you many things."

Anna and Ben smiled and said, "Okay, mom. We like cookies. And we like books. Books are fun. And they don't spoil."
<|end|>


