Lia and Ben are friends. They like to play in the forest. They find a brown hut near a stream. The hut is old and has holes in the roof.

"Let's go inside and see what is there," Lia says.

"OK, but be careful. It might be wet and dirty," Ben says.

They open the door and go in. The hut is dark and cold. There are some old pots and pans on the floor. There is also a bed with a blanket.

"Look, there is a bed. Maybe someone lives here," Lia says.

"Or maybe someone used to live here, but not anymore," Ben says.

They hear a loud noise outside. It is raining hard. The water falls on the hut and makes it leak.

"Oh no, it is raining. We have to go back home," Lia says.

"But how? We will get wet and cold," Ben says.

They look for an umbrella or a coat, but they find nothing. The water drips from the roof and soaks the blanket and the pots and pans.

"We have to run. Come on, Lia," Ben says.

They grab each other's hand and run out of the hut. The rain splashes on their faces and clothes. They run as fast as they can to their homes.

They are wet and muddy, but they are happy. They had a fun adventure in the forest. They laugh and hug each other.

"Bye, Ben. See you tomorrow," Lia says.

"Bye, Lia. That was a cool hut," Ben says.
<|end|>


