<|asst|>
Sara was a new girl in the class. She did not know anyone. She felt sad and lonely. She wanted to play with the other kids, but they did not let her.

"Go away, Sara. You are not our friend. You do not belong here," they said.

Sara ran away and hid behind a tree. She cried and wished she had a friend.

Tommy saw Sara crying. He felt sorry for her. He liked to play with everyone. He did not like to see anyone sad.

"Hi, Sara. I am Tommy. Do you want to play with me?" he asked.

Sara looked up and saw Tommy. He had a big smile and a clean shirt. He looked nice and friendly.

"Really? You want to play with me?" she asked.

"Sure. You are welcome to play with me. I have a ball and a truck. We can share them," he said.

Sara smiled and wiped her tears. She felt happy and hopeful. She followed Tommy to the playground. They played with the ball and the truck. They had fun and laughed.

The other kids saw Sara and Tommy playing. They felt curious and jealous. They wanted to join them.

"Hey, Sara. Hey, Tommy. Can we play with you?" they asked.

Sara and Tommy looked at each other. They remembered how the other kids were mean to Sara.

"What do you think, Sara? Should we let them play with us?" Tommy asked.

Sara thought for a moment. She remembered how Tommy was nice to her. She wanted to be nice too.

"Okay. They can play with us. But they have to be nice and share. They have to say sorry for being mean," she said.

The other kids nodded and said sorry. They joined Sara and Tommy. They played with the ball and the truck. They had fun and laughed.

Sara was not sad and lonely anymore. She had a friend and a group. She felt like she belonged. She felt welcome.
<|end|>


