<|asst|>
Lily was an adventurous girl who loved to play outside. She had a kite that was red and yellow and had a long tail. She liked to fly her kite in the park when the wind was strong.

One day, she saw a big hill near the park. She thought it would be fun to fly her kite from the top of the hill. She asked her mom if she could go there. Her mom said no, because the hill was too far and too steep. She said it was not safe for Lily to go there alone.

But Lily did not listen to her mom. She waited until her mom was busy and then she took her kite and ran to the hill. She climbed up the hill and felt very proud. She thought she was very brave and smart.

She took out her kite and tried to fly it. But the wind was too strong and the kite was too big. The kite pulled Lily and made her lose her balance. She fell down the hill and hurt her knee and her elbow. She cried and cried. She wished she had listened to her mom.

Her mom heard her cry and ran to the hill. She saw Lily and her kite on the ground. She was very worried and angry. She hugged Lily and said, "I told you not to go to the hill. Why did you not listen to me? You could have been hurt very badly. You were not adventurous, you were foolish."

Lily felt sorry and ashamed. She said, "I'm sorry, mom. I wanted to fly my kite from the hill. I thought it would be fun. I did not mean to disobey you. Please forgive me."

Her mom said, "I forgive you, Lily. But you have to learn to listen to me and to request permission before you do something dangerous. I love you and I want you to be safe and happy. Next time, let's fly your kite together in the park, okay?"

Lily nodded and said, "Okay, mom. I love you too. Thank you for being my mom."

The moral of the story is: Listen to your parents and request permission before you do something adventurous. They know what is best for you and they want you to be safe and happy.
<|end|>


