Sara and Tom were twins who liked to play outside. They loved to run, jump, and dig in the dirt. But they did not like to bathe. They thought it was boring and cold.

One day, their mom said, "Sara and Tom, it is time to bathe. You are very dirty and smelly. Come inside now."

Sara and Tom did not want to go. They said, "No, mom, we are not dirty. We are having fun. We want to stay outside."

Their mom said, "If you do not bathe, you will not get any food. You will be hungry and sad. And you will miss the surprise I have for you."

Sara and Tom were curious. They liked surprises. They asked, "What surprise, mom? What is it?"

Their mom said, "You will see. But you have to bathe first. Hurry up, or the surprise will be gone."

Sara and Tom decided to go inside. They did not want to miss the surprise. They hoped it was something good. Maybe a toy, or a cake, or a book.

They took off their clothes and got into the tub. Their mom poured water and soap on them. They rubbed their skin and hair. They made bubbles and splashed. They started to have fun. They forgot they did not like to bathe.

When they were clean and dry, their mom gave them towels and clothes. She said, "Now you are ready for the surprise. Follow me."

She led them to the living room. There, on the couch, was a big, furry, brown dog. He had a collar and a tag that said, "Rex". He wagged his tail and licked their faces.

Sara and Tom were amazed. They loved dogs. They hugged and petted Rex. They said, "Wow, mom, this is the best surprise ever. Thank you. Can we keep him?"

Their mom said, "Yes, you can. He is your new friend. He was in the shelter for a long time. He is very old and wise. He needs a good home and a lot of love."

Sara and Tom said, "We will love him and take care of him. We will play with him and feed him and bathe him. He is our ancient dog."

Their mom smiled and said, "I am proud of you, Sara and Tom. You are very kind and brave. Now, let's go to the kitchen and have some food. Rex is hungry too."

They all went to the kitchen and ate together. They were happy and full. They had a new family member. They learned that bathing was not so bad after all. And they looked forward to more surprises.
<|end|>


