Lily and Tom were twins. They liked to play with their toy cars. They had many cars of different colors and sizes. They pretended to drive them on the floor, on the sofa, and on the table.

Yesterday, they went to the park with their mom. They saw a big truck drive by. It was loud and fast. It made a lot of smoke. Lily and Tom were scared. They hid behind their mom and held her hand.

"Mom, what is that?" Lily asked.

"That is a truck, sweetie. It is a big car that carries things," mom said.

"Why is it so loud and fast?" Tom asked.

"Because it has a big engine and it has to go to a far place," mom said.

"Can we drive a truck when we grow up?" Lily asked.

"Maybe, if you want to. But you have to learn a lot and be careful," mom said.

Lily and Tom nodded. They were still scared, but also curious. They watched the truck drive away. Then they went to play on the swings. They forgot about the truck and had fun. They liked the park.
<|end|>


