Timmy liked to number his toys. He had a journal where he wrote the names and numbers of his toys. He was very proud of his journal. He showed it to his mom and dad every day.

One day, Timmy went to play with his friend Lily. Lily had many toys too, but she did not number them. She just played with them however she liked. Timmy wanted to number Lily's toys and write them in his journal. He asked Lily if he could do that.

"No, you can't!" Lily said. "These are my toys, not yours. You can't write on them or in your journal. That's not fun. That's boring."

Timmy felt very sad and angry. He liked to number his toys. He thought it was fun. He did not like Lily's answer. He said, "But I want to number your toys. It's my journal. I can write what I want. You are not nice. You are grumpy."

Lily felt very sad and angry too. She liked to play with her toys. She thought it was fun. She did not like Timmy's answer. She said, "But I want to play with my toys. They are my toys. I can do what I want. You are not nice. You are grumpy."

Timmy and Lily started to cry. They did not want to play with each other anymore. They wanted to go home. They did not know how to solve their problem. They needed some help.
<|end|>


