Anna and Ben are twins. They like to play with their toys, but they do not like to sort them. They leave their toys all over the floor, and their mom is not happy.

One day, mom says, "Anna and Ben, you need to sort your toys and put them in the boxes. If you do not sort your toys, you will not get any sweet treats after dinner."

Anna and Ben do not listen to mom. They keep playing with their toys and make a big mess. They think mom will forget about the sweet treats.

But mom does not forget. When dinner is over, she says, "Anna and Ben, did you sort your toys and put them in the boxes?"

Anna and Ben say, "No, mom, we did not sort our toys. We were too busy playing."

Mom says, "Then you will not get any sweet treats. You can only have water and go to bed. Maybe tomorrow you will sort your toys and be good."

Anna and Ben are sad. They do not like water and they do not want to go to bed. They wish they had sorted their toys and listened to mom.

The next day, Anna and Ben wake up early. They say, "Mom, we are sorry we did not sort our toys. We will sort them now and be good."

Mom says, "That is very nice of you, Anna and Ben. I am glad you learned your lesson. If you sort your toys and put them in the boxes, you can have some sweet treats after breakfast."

Anna and Ben are happy. They sort their toys and put them in the boxes. They say, "Sorting is fun. We like to sort our toys and make mom happy."

Mom says, "I am proud of you, Anna and Ben. You are good twins. Here are some sweet treats for you. Enjoy!"

Anna and Ben say, "Thank you, mom. We love you. We love our sweet treats. And we love our toys. But we will always sort them and put them in the boxes."

The end.
<|end|>


