Anna and Ben are twins. They like to play in the house. One day, they see a mop in the kitchen. The mop is big and wet.

"Look, a mop!" Anna says. "Let's touch it!"

"No, Anna, don't touch it!" Ben says. "Mama says the mop is dirty. It can make us sick."

But Anna does not listen. She runs to the mop and touches it with her hand. She feels the water and the dirt. She thinks it is fun.

"Anna, stop it!" Ben says. "You are not intelligent. You are silly. Come here, I will show you something better."

Ben takes Anna to the living room. He shows her a book. The book has pictures and words. Ben can read some of the words. He is intelligent.

"Look, a book!" Ben says. "Let's read it!"

"OK, Ben, let's read it!" Anna says. She forgets the mop. She likes the book. She thinks it is interesting.

They sit on the sofa and read the book. They learn new things. They are happy. Mama sees them and smiles. She is proud of them. She thinks they are intelligent.
<|end|>


