Tom and Sue are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big tree with many nuts on it. They want to get some nuts to eat.

"Look, Sue, nuts!" Tom says. "Let's climb the tree and get some."

"OK, Tom, but be careful. The tree is very old and tall," Sue says.

They climb the tree and find some nuts. They are peanuts. They are happy. They start to eat the peanuts.

But then, they hear a loud noise. It is a big bird. It is a hawk. The hawk is hungry. It sees Tom and Sue in the tree. It wants to eat them.

"Help, Sue, a hawk!" Tom says. He is scared. He drops his peanuts.

"Help, Tom, a hawk!" Sue says. She is scared too. She hangs on to a branch.

The hawk flies to the tree. It tries to catch Tom and Sue. But they are too fast. They jump from branch to branch. They dodge the hawk.

The hawk is angry. It screeches. It flaps its wings. It shakes the tree.

The tree is old. It cannot hold the hawk. It cracks. It falls. Tom and Sue fall too.

But they are lucky. They land on a soft pile of leaves. They are not hurt. They run away from the hawk.

They are safe. They hug each other. They are glad.

"Wow, Sue, that was scary," Tom says.

"Yes, Tom, that was scary. But we are OK," Sue says.

They look at the tree. It is broken. The peanuts are gone.

They are sad. They like peanuts.

"Maybe we can find some more nuts somewhere else," Tom says.

"Maybe, Tom, but not in an old tree," Sue says.

They smile. They hold hands. They walk away. They are still friends.
<|end|>


