<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They liked to dig in the sand and look for treasures. Sometimes they found shells, rocks, or coins. They put them in a bucket and pretended they were pirates.

One day, they saw something shiny in the sand. Lily reached for it, but Ben was faster. He grabbed it and held it up. It was a small, clear stone that sparkled in the sun.

"Wow, look at this!" Ben said. "It's a diamond! I'm rich!"

Lily felt angry. She wanted to see the stone too. She tried to take it from Ben, but he pulled it away.

"Hey, stop it!" Ben said. "It's mine! I found it first!"

"That's not fair!" Lily said. "You're being rude! We're supposed to share!"

Ben stuck out his tongue and ran away. He wanted to keep the diamond for himself. He thought it was very special and valuable.

Lily ran after him. She wanted to tell him that he was wrong. She had learned about diamonds in a book. They were not real stones. They were made by people. They were not worth anything in the park. They were only for grown-ups who liked to wear them on their fingers or necks.

She caught up with Ben and shouted at him.

"Ben, wait! Listen to me! That's not a diamond! It's fake! It's just glass!"

Ben stopped and looked at her. He did not believe her. He thought she was lying. He wanted to make him give her the stone.

"No, it's not! It's a diamond! It's real! You're just jealous!" Ben said.

He held the stone up to his eye and looked at it. He saw the colors of the rainbow. He smiled. He thought it was beautiful.

Lily shook her head. She felt sad. She realized that Ben was not a good friend. He did not care about her. He only cared about the stone. She decided to leave him alone. She turned around and walked back to the sand. She hoped to find a real treasure. A treasure that was not rude. A treasure that she could share.
<|end|>


