Anna and Ben are twins. They like to watch television after lunch. They sit on the sofa and hold the remote. They press the buttons to change the channels.

One day, they see a show about animals. They see a big cat with stripes. It is a tiger. The tiger is in a cage. It looks sad. Anna and Ben feel sorry for the tiger.

"Can we help the tiger?" Anna asks Ben.

"I don't know," Ben says. "Maybe we can rub its fur. It might feel better."

They get up from the sofa and walk to the television. They reach out their hands and try to rub the tiger's fur. But they are clumsy. They bump into the television and make it fall. It makes a loud noise and breaks.

"Oh no!" Anna and Ben say. They are scared. They run back to the sofa and hide under a blanket.

Mom hears the noise and comes to the living room. She sees the broken television and the twins under the blanket. She is angry.

"What did you do?" Mom asks.

"We wanted to help the tiger," Anna says.

"We tried to rub its fur," Ben says.

Mom sighs. She is not happy. She tells the twins that they cannot touch the television. It is not a real tiger. It is a picture. They can only watch it, not rub it.

She picks up the television and takes it to the garage. She says she will try to fix it later. She tells the twins to play with their toys instead. She gives them a hug and a kiss. She says she loves them, but they have to be careful.

Anna and Ben say they are sorry. They promise to be careful. They play with their toys and forget about the tiger. They hope Mom can fix the television soon. They want to watch more shows about animals. But they will not try to rub them anymore.
<|end|>


