<|asst|>
Lily is a giraffe. She has a very long neck. She can eat leaves from the tall trees. She likes to be with her friends in the savanna. They are all giraffes too.

One day, Lily sees a new animal. It is small and brown. It has a short neck and a long nose. It is an elephant. Lily is curious. She wants to say hello. She walks to the elephant.

The elephant is friendly. He says hello to Lily. He tells her his name is Sam. He says he is looking for water. He is thirsty. He asks Lily if she knows where to find water.

Lily nods. She knows where to find water. There is a big lake near the trees. She tells Sam to follow her. She leads him to the lake. Sam is happy. He thanks Lily. He drinks some water. He splashes some water on his nose.

Lily and Sam become friends. They talk and play. They learn about each other. They find out they have some things in common. They both like to eat plants. They both like to be kind. They both think their necks are important. Lily's neck helps her reach the leaves. Sam's neck helps him drink the water. They are proud of their necks. They are proud of their friendship. They are happy.
<|end|>


