<|asst|>
Lila and Ben are twins. They like to play with their toys in their room. But sometimes they fight over the toys. One day, Lila wants to play with the train, but Ben has it. Lila tries to take it from him, but Ben holds it tight.

"Give me the train!" Lila says.

"No, it is mine!" Ben says.

They pull and tug at the train. The train is heavy and hard. It hurts their hands. They yell and cry. Mom hears them and comes to their room.

"What is going on here?" Mom asks.

"They are fighting over the train!" Lila and Ben say at the same time.

Mom looks at the train. It is broken. The wheels are off and the smokestack is bent. Mom is sad and angry.

"You broke the train!" Mom says. "That was a gift from Grandma. She loves you and wanted you to share it. How could you do this?"

Lila and Ben feel bad. They know they did something wrong. They look at the floor and say nothing.

Mom shakes her head. "You need to learn to play nicely and use your words. Fighting is not a good language. It only makes things worse. Now you have no train and no fun. Go to your beds and think about what you did. And shut the door behind you."

Lila and Ben nod. They pick up their toys and go to their beds. They shut the door. They are quiet. They wish they had not fought over the train. They wish they had said sorry and shared it. They miss their mom and their grandma. They hope they can fix the train and make them happy again.
<|end|>


