<|asst|>
Lily liked to go to the library with her mom. She loved to look at the books with many pictures and colors. She also liked to listen to the stories that the nice lady read to the children. Sometimes, she would whistle along with the songs that the lady sang.

One day, when Lily and her mom were at the library, they saw a boy sitting in a corner. He had no books, no toys, and no mom. He looked sad and lonely. Lily wanted to make him happy, so she walked over to him and said, "Hi, I'm Lily. What's your name?"

The boy looked up and said, "I'm Sam. I have no books, no toys, and no mom. I'm poor."

Lily felt sorry for Sam. She said, "That's not good. Do you want to be my friend? I can share my books and toys with you. And my mom can be your mom too."

Sam smiled and said, "Really? You're very kind. I would like to be your friend. Thank you, Lily."

Lily and Sam became friends. They looked at the books together, played with the toys, and listened to the stories and songs. They also whistled along with the lady. Lily's mom was happy to see them having fun. She said, "You're both very sweet. I'm proud of you, Lily. And you're welcome, Sam."

Lily and Sam hugged her and said, "We love you, mom."
<|end|>


