<|asst|>
Lily and Ben are best friends. They like to play with their toys and make up stories. One day, they find a big box in the garage. They decide to turn it into a rocket.

"Let's go to the moon!" Ben says. He draws some windows and buttons on the box with a crayon. Lily helps him cut out a door and a cone.

They put on their helmets and get inside the rocket. They count down from ten to zero and pretend to blast off. They make loud noises and shake the box.

"We are in space!" Lily says. She looks out of the window and sees stars and planets. "Wow, it's so pretty!"

Ben nods. He sees a big round ball that looks like cheese. "That's the moon!" he says. "Let's land there and have a picnic!"

They steer the rocket towards the moon and land softly. They open the door and step out. They see a flag and a footprint. "Someone was here before us!" Ben says.

They look around and see a bunny. The bunny is white and fluffy. It hops towards them and sniffs them. Lily and Ben smile. They think the bunny is cute and friendly.

"Hello, bunny!" Lily says. She gives the bunny a carrot from her backpack. The bunny nibbles it and wags its tail.

"Can we be your friends?" Ben asks. He pets the bunny gently. The bunny nods and licks his hand.

Lily and Ben are happy. They hug the bunny and kiss it on the nose. They have a cheerful picnic on the moon with their new friend. They share their sandwiches and cookies and juice. They laugh and talk and play.

They have so much fun that they forget the time. They look at the sky and see the sun setting. They remember that they have to go home soon.

"Bye, bunny!" Lily says. She gives the bunny another carrot and a kiss.

"Bye, bunny!" Ben says. He gives the bunny a hug and a kiss.

The bunny waves and smiles. It watches them get back into their rocket and take off. It hopes to see them again.

Lily and Ben wave back and smile. They have had the best adventure ever. They fly back to Earth and land in the garage. They run inside and tell their parents all about their trip to the moon. Their parents listen and hug them and kiss them. They are proud of their brave and creative children. They tuck them into bed and wish them sweet dreams. Lily and Ben fall asleep with smiles on their faces. They dream of the moon and the bunny and their friendship.
<|end|>


