<|asst|>
Tim and Sam are best friends. They like to play outside in the park. Today, they wear their new vests. The vests are blue and have zips.

"Look at my vest!" Tim says. "I can zip it up and down. Zip, zip, zip!"

"That is fun!" Sam says. "Can I try?"

"Sure!" Tim says. He gives his vest to Sam. Sam puts it on and zips it up and down. Zip, zip, zip!

But then, something silly happens. The zip gets stuck. Sam cannot zip it up or down. He cannot take off the vest.

"Oh no!" Sam says. "Help me, Tim!"

Tim tries to help. He pulls the zip. But it does not move. It is too tight.

"Uh oh!" Tim says. "What can we do?"

They look around. They see a lady. She has a big bag. Maybe she can help.

"Excuse me, lady!" Tim says. "Can you help us? The zip is stuck!"

The lady smiles. She comes over. She looks at the zip. She takes out a pair of scissors from her bag.

"Don't worry, boys!" she says. "I can fix it. Hold still!"

She cuts the zip with the scissors. The vest opens. Sam takes it off. He is free!

"Thank you, lady!" Sam says. "You are very nice!"

"You're welcome, boys!" she says. "But be careful with zips. They can be tricky!"

Tim and Sam nod. They hug each other. They are happy. They put on their vests again. But this time, they do not zip them. They just button them. Button, button, button!
<|end|>


