<|asst|>
Lila was a very independent girl. She liked to do things by herself, like dressing up, making her bed, and reading books. She did not like to share her toys or listen to her parents. She wanted to be a guard when she grew up, because guards were strong and brave and could protect people.

One day, Lila decided to play guard in her backyard. She put on her helmet, her shield, and her sword, and pretended to guard the gate. She did not let anyone in, not even her dog, Max. She said, "Go away, Max! This is my gate. You are not welcome here!"

Max was sad. He wanted to play with Lila, but she was too busy being a guard. He barked and wagged his tail, but Lila ignored him. He tried to sneak past her, but she blocked him with her shield. He whimpered and lay down on the grass, feeling lonely.

Lila's mom saw what was happening. She came out of the house and said, "Lila, what are you doing? Why are you being so mean to Max? He is your friend. He loves you. You should be nice to him and welcome him to your game."

Lila looked at her mom and said, "But mom, I'm a guard. Guards don't let anyone in. They have to be independent and strong."

Lila's mom smiled and said, "Lila, being a guard is not only about being independent and strong. It is also about being kind and fair. You can be a guard and still share your gate with Max. He can be your helper or your partner. He can help you guard the gate or play with you when you are bored. He can be your friend and your family. Don't you think that would be more fun?"

Lila thought about it. She realized that her mom was right. She felt sorry for Max. She put down her sword and shield and ran to him. She hugged him and said, "I'm sorry, Max. You are welcome to my gate. You are my friend and my family. Do you want to play guard with me?"

Max wagged his tail and licked her face. He was happy. He barked and said, "Yes, Lila. I want to play guard with you. Thank you for being nice to me. I love you."

Lila and Max played guard together. They had fun. They were independent and strong, but also kind and fair. They were the best guards in the world.
<|end|>


