<|asst|>
Lily liked to help her mom cook in the kitchen. She had a small spoon and a small bowl. She could stir things in her bowl and pretend to make yummy food. Mom gave her some cheese and some broccoli to stir in her bowl. Lily liked cheese, but she did not like broccoli. She made a face and pushed the broccoli away.

"Broccoli is good for you, Lily," Mom said. "It makes you strong and healthy. You can eat it with cheese and it will taste better."

Lily shook her head. She did not want to eat broccoli. She looked at her big brother, Ben, who was sitting at the table. He had a big plate of pizza and a big glass of juice. He was eating and drinking and smiling. Lily felt envious. She wanted pizza and juice, too. She thought they looked much better than broccoli and cheese.

"Can I have some pizza, Mom?" Lily asked. "Please?"

Mom smiled and shook her head. "No, Lily. You have to eat your broccoli and cheese first. Then you can have a small slice of pizza and some juice. That's the deal."

Lily pouted. She did not like the deal. She looked at her bowl and saw the broccoli staring at her. She did not want to stir it anymore. She wanted to throw it away. But she knew Mom would be mad if she did that. She sighed and picked up her spoon. She stirred the broccoli and cheese slowly. She hoped they would go away. But they did not. They stayed in her bowl, waiting for her to eat them. Lily felt sad. She wished she could have pizza and juice like Ben. She wished she did not have to eat broccoli and cheese. She wished she could cook something else in her bowl. Something yummy and fun. Something like... cupcakes!
<|end|>


