Lily and Max were going to a fancy party with their mom and dad. They wore nice clothes and shiny shoes. They got in the car and drove to the big house where the party was.

"Are we there yet?" Lily asked.

"Soon, sweetie," mom said. "We have to wait for the green light."

Max looked out the window and saw many cars and people. He saw a man with a file in his hand. He wondered what was in the file.

"Look, Lily, that man has a file. Maybe he is a spy," Max said.

Lily giggled. "No, silly, he is not a spy. He is a lawyer. He has papers in his file. Mom told me."

The car stopped and they arrived at the big house. They got out and walked to the door. A lady with a smile greeted them.

"Welcome to the party. Please give me your names and I will check the list," she said.

Mom gave their names and the lady looked at her file. She nodded and let them in.

"Have fun, kids. There are games and snacks in the garden," she said.

Lily and Max ran to the garden. They saw balloons and toys and cake. They were happy. They had arrived at the fancy party.
<|end|>


