Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play with blocks and dolls. One day, Lily makes a big tower with blocks. She is very happy. She wants to show Tom her work.

She calls Tom and says, "Look, Tom, look at my work. I made a big tower with blocks. Do you like it?"

Tom comes and sees Lily's work. He does not like it. He is angry. He says, "No, I don't like it. It is ugly and boring. I can make a better work than you."

He pushes Lily's tower with his hand. The blocks fall down and make a loud noise. Lily's work is gone. Lily is very sad. She cries and says, "Tom, why did you do that? You are a bad friend. You broke my work. I don't want to play with you anymore."

Tom does not care. He laughs and says, "I don't care. I don't want to play with you either. You are a crybaby. Go away."

He takes some blocks and makes his own work. He thinks his work is better than Lily's. He is proud.

But then, a big dog comes and sees Tom's work. The dog likes to play with blocks too. The dog runs and jumps on Tom's work. The blocks fly everywhere and hit Tom. Tom's work is gone. Tom is hurt and scared. He cries and says, "Help, help, the dog broke my work. It hurts. Go away, dog, go away."

But the dog does not go away. The dog barks and chases Tom. Tom runs and hides. He is alone and sad.

Lily sees what happens. She does not help Tom. She is still angry. She says, "That is what you get for being mean to me. You deserve it. I don't care about you."

She takes her blocks and goes to play with another friend. She is happy.

The end.
<|end|>


