Lily and Ben are twins. They like to play in the big building where their mom works. One day, they sneak into the elevator when mom is busy. They push all the buttons and laugh.

The elevator starts to move up and down very fast. It makes loud noises and shakes a lot. Lily and Ben are scared. They hold each other and cry.

"Help! Help!" they shout. "We want mom!"

A man hears them from outside. He is a worker. He tries to open the door, but it is stuck. He talks to them through a small hole.

"Don't worry, kids. I'm here to help. The elevator is crazy. It needs to be fixed. Stay calm and wait for me."

He calls for more workers. They bring tools and a ladder. They work hard to open the door and stop the elevator.

After a long time, they succeed. The door opens and the elevator stops. Lily and Ben see the man and the other workers. They are happy and relieved.

"Thank you, thank you!" they say. "You saved us!"

They hug the man and the workers. Then they see mom. She is angry and worried. She runs to them and hugs them too.

"What were you thinking, kids? You could have been hurt! You should never play with the elevator. It's dangerous!"

Lily and Ben are sorry. They say sorry to mom and to the workers. They promise to never do it again.

Mom forgives them. She takes them to her office and gives them cookies and juice. She tells them to be good and stay with her.

Lily and Ben nod. They eat their cookies and drink their juice. They are glad to be safe and with mom. They don't want to play with the elevator anymore. It's too crazy.
<|end|>


