Tim and Kim were twins who liked to play with bricks. They had many bricks of different colors and shapes. They could build houses, towers, cars and animals with their bricks. They had fun with their bricks every day.

One day, they saw a big pile of bricks near their house. They wanted to play with those bricks too. They thought they could make bigger and better things with more bricks. They did not ask their mom or dad if they could go to the pile of bricks. They just ran to the pile of bricks and started to take some.

But the pile of bricks was not for playing. It was for building a new house. A big truck was coming to bring more bricks to the pile. The truck driver did not see Tim and Kim. He drove very fast and dumped the bricks on the pile. Tim and Kim were scared. They tried to run away, but it was too late. The bricks fell on them and hurt them very badly.

Their mom and dad heard the noise and ran to the pile of bricks. They saw Tim and Kim under the bricks. They were very sad and angry. They called for help, but it was too late. Tim and Kim did not wake up. They died because of the bricks. The end.
