<|asst|>
Lila and Sam were hungry. They wanted to eat rice for dinner. But Mom said they had to wait. She was cooking the rice in a big pot on the stove.

Lila and Sam did not like to wait. They ran around the house and made a lot of noise. They played with their toys and threw them on the floor. They jumped on the couch and knocked over the lamp.

Mom was not happy. She said, "Lila and Sam, stop! You are making a mess. You need to settle down and be quiet. The rice will be ready soon."

Lila and Sam did not listen. They kept running and playing and making noise. They did not see the cat sleeping on the table. They bumped into the table and the cat woke up. The cat was scared and angry. It hissed and scratched Lila and Sam.

Lila and Sam cried. They ran to Mom and showed her their scratches. Mom said, "Oh, no! You hurt the cat and yourselves. You should have listened to me. Now you need to say sorry to the cat and clean up your mess."

Lila and Sam said sorry to the cat and gave it a hug. They picked up their toys and put them away. They fixed the lamp and the couch. They settled down and waited for the rice.

Mom smiled and said, "Good job, Lila and Sam. You learned your lesson. Now you can have some rice for dinner. But be careful, it is hot and hard. You need to blow on it and chew it well."

Lila and Sam nodded and said, "Thank you, Mom. We love rice. And we love you. And we love the cat." They ate their rice and enjoyed it. They were happy and full. They said good night to Mom and the cat and went to bed. They slept well and dreamed of rice.
<|end|>


