<|asst|>
On Wednesday, Lily and Ben went to the park with Mom. They liked to play on the slide and the swings. Lily was very fast and brave. She went down the slide first and then ran to the swings. Ben was slower and careful. He waited for his turn and then slid down slowly.

"Come on, Ben, swing with me!" Lily shouted. She pushed her swing very high and felt the wind in her hair.

"I'm coming, Lily!" Ben said. He got off the slide and ran to the swings. But he did not see the puddle on the ground. He stepped on it and slipped. He fell down and hurt his knee. He cried out loud.

Mom heard Ben and ran to him. She picked him up and hugged him. She looked at his knee and saw a small cut. She took out a band-aid from her bag and put it on his knee.

"There, there, Ben, it's okay. You are very brave. The band-aid will make it better," Mom said.

"Thank you, Mom," Ben said. He sniffed and wiped his tears.

Lily stopped swinging and ran to Ben. She felt sorry for him. She gave him a hug and said, "I'm sorry, Ben. I didn't mean to make you slip. Do you want to swing with me now?"

Ben smiled and nodded. He got on the swing next to Lily. Mom pushed them gently. They swung together and felt happy. They forgot about the puddle and the hurt. They enjoyed the rest of the Wednesday at the park.
<|end|>


