<|asst|>
Ben and Lily liked to play in the park. They liked to run on the grass, swing on the swings, and slide on the slide. They liked to see the birds, the flowers, and the trees. They liked the green nature.

One day, they saw a big fence around the park. There was a sign that said, "No more park. We are building here." Ben and Lily were sad. They wanted to play in the park. They wanted to see the green nature.

They tried to find another park, but they could not. All the parks were gone. They only saw houses, shops, and cars. They only saw gray and brown. They missed the green nature.

They asked their mom and dad, "Why are they building so much? Where is the green nature?" Their mom and dad said, "They need more space for people. They don't care about the green nature. They only care about money."

Ben and Lily were angry. They did not like the people who built so much. They did not like the people who did not care about the green nature. They wanted to stop them. They wanted to save the green nature.

They made a plan. They took some seeds, some water, and some dirt. They waited until night. They sneaked out of their house. They went to the fence around the park. They dug some holes under the fence. They planted the seeds. They watered them. They hoped they would grow.

But they did not grow. The next day, the people who built came. They saw the holes under the fence. They saw the seeds. They were angry. They threw away the seeds. They filled the holes. They put more fence. They said, "No more kids. We are building here."

Ben and Lily were sad. They cried. They could not save the green nature. They could not play in the park. They could only remain in their house. They could only see gray and brown. They hated the people who built so much. They hated the people who did not care about the green nature. They hated the bad ending.
<|end|>


