<|asst|>
Lily liked to read novels. Novels were books with many words and pictures. They told stories about different people and places. Lily had many novels in her room. She liked to read them before bed.

One day, Lily found a novel she had never seen before. It was big and heavy. It had a red cover with a picture of a dragon. Lily liked dragons. She wanted to read the novel. She opened it and saw many words. Some words were unusual. She did not know what they meant.

She asked her mom, "Mom, what is this word?" She pointed to a word on the page. It was "sharp".

Mom looked at the word and said, "Sharp means something that can cut or hurt. Like a knife or a needle. Or a dragon's teeth."

Lily nodded. She understood. She said, "Thank you, mom. Can I read this novel?"

Mom smiled and said, "Yes, you can. But be careful. It might be scary. It is not for little kids."

Lily said, "I am not a little kid. I am brave. I can read this novel."

Mom said, "Okay. But if you get scared, you can always close the novel and read something else. Or you can come to me and I will hug you."

Lily said, "Okay, mom. I love you."

Mom said, "I love you too. Have fun reading."

Lily hugged her mom and went back to her room. She opened the novel and started to read. She wanted to know more about the dragon and the people who lived with it. She hoped the novel would not be too scary. She hoped the dragon would not be too sharp.
<|end|>


