<|asst|>
Tim and Mia like to play in the woods. They find a big pine tree with many cones. They want to take some cones home. But the pine tree is too tall. They cannot reach the cones.

"Look, there is a big rock!" Tim says. "We can climb on it and spring to the tree."

Mia nods. She follows Tim to the rock. They climb on it. They are very careful. They do not want to fall.

"Ready?" Tim asks. "One, two, three, spring!"

They spring to the tree. They grab some cones. They are happy. They have many cones.

But then they hear a loud roar. They turn around. They see a big gray bear. The bear is angry. The bear wants the cones. The bear runs to the rock.

"Help!" Tim and Mia scream. They drop the cones. They try to spring back to the rock. But they are too slow. The bear is too fast.

The bear catches them. The bear bites them. The bear eats them. The bear is full. The bear takes the cones. The bear leaves.

The pine tree is quiet. The rock is empty. The woods are dark. Tim and Mia are gone. The end.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
You are telling a short children's story.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Sara and Tom like to play soccer in the park. They have a ball and two cones for the goal. Sara is good at kicking the ball. Tom is good at catching the ball.

One day, they meet a new friend, Lily. Lily has long hair and a pretty dress. She wants to play with them. Sara and Tom say yes.

"Can I be the goalie?" Lily asks.

"Sure," Tom says. "But you have to kneel on the ground and use your hands."

Lily nods and kneels behind the cones. Sara and Tom take turns to kick the ball. Lily tries to catch it, but it is hard. The ball is fast and bouncy. Sometimes it goes over her head. Sometimes it goes under her arms. Sometimes it goes past her side.

"Good try, Lily!" Sara and Tom say. They are nice and do not laugh.

Lily feels sad. She wants to be good at soccer too. She does not like to kneel and miss the ball.

"Can I kick the ball too?" Lily asks.

"Sure," Sara says. "But you have to run and use your feet."

Lily nods and stands up. She runs to the ball and kicks it. But it is hard too. The ball is heavy and round. Sometimes it goes too far. Sometimes it goes too near. Sometimes it goes the wrong way.

"Good try, Lily!" Sara and Tom say. They are nice and do not laugh.

Lily feels happy. She likes to run and kick the ball. She does not mind if she misses the goal. She has fun with her new friends. They play soccer until it is time to go home. They say bye and hug.

"See you tomorrow, Lily!" Sara and Tom say.

"See you tomorrow, Sara and Tom!" Lily says.

She smiles and waves. She likes soccer and her pretty dress. She likes Sara and Tom. They are her friends.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
