<|end|>
<|asst|>
Tom loved to soar in the sky. He had a red uniform with a big star on it. He was a superhero. He could fly very fast and very high. He liked to help people and animals.

One day, he saw a big cake on a table. It looked delicious. He wanted to taste it. He flew down and landed on the table. He took a big bite of the cake. It was sweet and soft. He smiled.

But he did not see the sign on the table. It said: "Do not eat. This cake is for the birthday of Bob the dog." Bob the dog was very angry. He saw Tom eating his cake. He barked and ran to the table. He jumped and bit Tom's leg. Tom screamed and dropped the cake. He tried to fly away, but he was hurt. He fell to the ground.

Bob the dog chased him and bit him again. Tom cried and said he was sorry. But Bob the dog did not listen. He wanted his cake back. He tore Tom's uniform and made it dirty. He ate the rest of the cake. He was happy.

Tom was sad and scared. He had no cake, no uniform, and no friends. He was not a superhero anymore. He was just a boy. He wished he had not eaten the cake. He learned a hard lesson. He should not take things that are not his. He should be kind and respectful. He should soar in the sky, not on the table.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
