<|asst|>
Tom and Sam were best friends. They liked to play with their toys in the park. One day, they saw a new boy with a big red top. The top could spin very fast and make a loud noise.

"Wow, look at that top!" Tom said. "It is so cool!"

"I want to play with it too!" Sam said. "Let's go and ask the boy."

They ran to the boy and said hello. The boy looked at them and frowned.

"Who are you?" he asked. "This is my top. You can't touch it."

"Please, can we try it?" Tom said. "We will be careful."

"No, you can't!" the boy said. "You have ugly toys. Go away!"

Tom and Sam felt sad. They did not like the boy. He was mean and rude. They went back to their toys and tried to have fun.

But then, they heard a loud crash. They turned around and saw that the boy's top had hit a rock and broken into pieces. The boy started to cry.

"Help me! My top is gone!" he said.

Tom and Sam looked at each other. They felt sorry for the boy. He had lost his favorite toy. They decided to be kind and offer him their toys.

"Here, you can play with our toys," Tom said. "We have a ball, a car, and a doll. They are not ugly. They are fun."

"Really?" the boy said. "You would do that for me?"

"Yes, we would," Sam said. "We are friends. Friends share and help each other."

The boy smiled and wiped his tears. He took the toys and thanked Tom and Sam. They played together and had a good time. They learned that it is better to be nice and generous than to be mean and selfish. They also learned that tops are not the only cool toys in the park.
<|end|>


