<|asst|>
Lily and Max were playing with their blocks in the living room. They liked to build towers and bridges and castles. But they also made a lot of noise and a big mess.

"Shh, be quiet!" their mom said from the kitchen. "Your baby brother is sleeping. And clean up your blocks when you are done."

Lily and Max nodded, but they did not listen. They kept on playing and talking and laughing. They did not see their baby brother wake up and crawl out of his crib. He was curious about the blocks and wanted to play too.

He reached for a red block that was part of Max's tower. He pulled it out and the tower fell down with a loud crash. Max was angry. He shouted at his baby brother.

"Hey, stop that! You ruined my tower! Go away!"

The baby brother started to cry. He did not understand why Max was mad at him. He just wanted to have fun. He crawled away from the blocks and saw Lily's bridge. He liked the blue blocks that were part of the bridge. He grabbed one and the bridge collapsed.

Lily was upset. She yelled at her baby brother.

"Hey, stop that! You ruined my bridge! Go away!"

The baby brother cried louder. He did not understand why Lily was mad at him. He just wanted to have fun. He crawled away from the bridge and saw a green block that was on the floor. He picked it up and put it in his mouth.

Mom heard the noise and the crying. She came out of the kitchen and saw the messy living room and the unhappy children. She was not happy either.

"What is going on here?" she asked. "Why are you making so much noise and mess? And why are you being mean to your baby brother?"

Lily and Max tried to explain. They said their baby brother ruined their blocks and they wanted him to go away. They said they were just playing and having fun.

Mom shook her head. She said they were not playing nicely. She said they should share their blocks and be kind to their baby brother. She said they should prevent him from putting blocks in his mouth. She said they should help him learn and play.

Lily and Max felt sorry. They said they were sorry to their mom and their baby brother. They gave him a hug and a kiss. They gave him some soft toys to play with. They helped him build a small tower with the blocks. They cleaned up their mess.

Mom smiled. She said they were good children. She said she was proud of them. She said they could have a snack and read a story. They all went to the kitchen and had some cookies and milk. They all felt happy.
<|end|>


