<|asst|>
Lily liked to write in her diary every day. She wrote about her toys, her friends, her dreams and her secrets. She kept her diary under her pillow, where no one could find it.

One day, her brother Tom was looking for his ball in her room. He saw a lump under her pillow and pulled it out. It was Lily's diary. He opened it and started to read.

"Hey, this is Lily's diary!" he said. "She wrote that she hates me and thinks I'm filthy. That's not nice!"

He was angry and hurt. He decided to split her diary in half and throw it away. He ripped the pages and tossed them in the trash.

Lily came back from playing outside and saw her diary in the trash. She was shocked and sad. She ran to Tom and shouted.

"Tom, what did you do to my diary? You split it and threw it away! That was mine and you had no right to read it!"

Tom felt sorry and ashamed. He realized he had made a big mistake. He hugged Lily and said.

"I'm sorry, Lily. I was mad and I did a bad thing. I shouldn't have read your diary or split it. Can you forgive me?"

Lily was still upset, but she loved her brother. She hugged him back and said.

"I forgive you, Tom. But don't ever do that again. And please help me fix my diary."

They went to the trash and picked up the pages. They taped them together and put them back in the cover. Lily's diary was not the same as before, but it was still hers. She wrote a new page and said.

"Today, Tom split my diary and threw it away. But he said sorry and we fixed it. He is my brother and I love him. Even if he is sometimes filthy."
<|end|>


