<|end|>
<|asst|>
Tom and Anna were twins who liked to play all day. They had many toys and games, but they did not like to share. They always fought over who got the best toy or the most time. Their mom and dad were busy and told them to be nice, but they did not listen.

One night, Tom and Anna went to bed after a big fight. They both wanted the same book, but they ripped it in half. They shut their eyes and tried to sleep, but they had bad dreams. Tom dreamed that a big monster took all his toys and broke them. Anna dreamed that a scary witch locked her in a dark room and laughed at her. They both woke up and cried.

Mom and dad heard them and came to their room. They hugged them and asked what was wrong. Tom and Anna told them about their nightmares. Mom and dad said that nightmares can happen when you are angry or sad. They said that sharing and being kind is better than fighting and being mean. They said that they love them both and want them to be happy.

Tom and Anna felt sorry for their fight. They said sorry to each other and hugged. They gave each other half of the book and said they would share it. They smiled and said they love each other and mom and dad. They shut their eyes and fell asleep. They had good dreams of playing and having fun. They learned that sharing is caring and kindness is happiness.
<|end|>


