Ben and Lily were playing in the kitchen. They saw a big blue jug on the table. It was full of water.

"Let's pour some water in the cups," Ben said. He grabbed the jug and lifted it up.

"No, Ben, don't do that!" Lily shouted. "You will make a mess!"

But Ben did not listen. He tilted the jug and water spilled out. It splashed on the table, on the floor, and on Lily.

"Stop, stop, stop!" Lily cried. She tried to prevent Ben from pouring more water. She reached for the jug and pulled it down.

But Ben did not let go. He pulled the jug up again. They both tugged on the jug and it slipped from their hands. It fell on the floor and broke. Water and pieces of blue jug went everywhere.

"Oh no!" Ben and Lily said. They looked at the mess they made. They heard their mom coming.

"What happened here?" their mom asked. She saw the water and the broken jug. She was not happy.

"Ben and Lily, you are in trouble!" she said. "You should not play with the jug. It was not a toy. It was for drinking. Now you have wasted the water and broken the jug. And you have made a big mess. You need to clean it up and say sorry."

Ben and Lily felt bad. They knew they did something wrong. They said sorry to their mom. They helped her clean up the water and the pieces of blue jug. They learned their lesson. They decided not to play with the jug again.
<|end|>


