<|asst|>
Ben and Mia are twins. They like to play outside in the sun. One day, they see a big billboard on the road. It has a picture of a bath and some soap. The billboard says: "Bathe every day. It is good for you."

Ben and Mia are curious. They ask their mom: "What is bathe? Why is it good for us?"

Mom smiles and says: "Bathe means to wash your body with water and soap. It is good for you because it makes you clean and healthy. Do you want to try it?"

Ben and Mia nod. They follow mom to the bathroom. Mom fills the tub with warm water and bubbles. She gives them some toys and a sponge. Ben and Mia splash and giggle. They rub the soap on their skin and hair. They feel fresh and soft.

Mom says: "Good job, Ben and Mia. You are bathing very well. How do you like it?"

Ben and Mia say: "We like it, mom. It is fun and nice. But we don't like the soap in our mouth. It is bitter. Yuck!"

Mom laughs and says: "I know, soap is bitter. That is why you should not eat it. You should spit it out and rinse your mouth with water. Then you will feel better."

Ben and Mia do as mom says. They spit out the soap and rinse their mouth. They feel better. They finish bathing and dry themselves with a towel. Mom hugs them and says: "You are very good twins. You bathed very well. Now you are clean and healthy. I am proud of you."

Ben and Mia smile and say: "Thank you, mom. We love you. Can we bathe again tomorrow?"

Mom says: "Of course, you can. Bathe every day. It is good for you."
<|end|>


