Lily and Sam were very happy. They were going on a tour with Mom and Dad. They wanted to see the big zoo with many animals. They got in the car and put on their seat belts.

"Are we there yet?" Lily asked.

"Soon, honey. We have to drive for a little while," Mom said.

Sam looked out the window. He saw trees and houses and cars. He wondered what animals he would see at the zoo. He hoped to see a lion and a monkey and a giraffe.

They arrived at the zoo. Dad parked the car and turned off the engine. He got out and went to the trunk. He tried to open it, but it was locked.

"Oh no, I forgot the keys in the car!" Dad said.

Mom looked at the car. The doors were locked too. She saw the keys on the seat.

"Oh no, how will we get them?" Mom said.

Lily and Sam felt sad. They wanted to go to the zoo, but they could not. They saw other kids walking to the zoo with their parents. They wished they could join them.

Then, they saw a man in a blue shirt. He had a badge and a walkie-talkie. He was a zoo worker. He saw Mom and Dad and came to them.

"Hello, do you need help?" he asked.

"Yes, please. We locked our keys in the car. Can you help us?" Dad asked.

"Sure, I can help. I have a tool that can unlock the car. Let me try," he said.

He took out a tool from his pocket. He put it in the car door and moved it. He made a click sound. The door opened. He gave the keys to Dad.

"Thank you so much. You are very helpful," Dad said.

"You're welcome. I'm glad I could help. Have a nice day and enjoy the zoo," he said.

Lily and Sam smiled. They thanked the man too. They got their backpacks from the trunk. They followed Mom and Dad to the zoo entrance. They were ready to see the animals. They were very happy.
<|end|>


