<|asst|>
Sam and Mia were twins who liked to go to the mall with their mom. They liked to see the toys, the books, and the clothes. But they also liked to help their mom find good things to buy. They knew that some things were cheap and some things were expensive. They also knew that some things were good and some things were bad. They learned to value the things that were good and cheap.

One day, they went to the mall and saw a big sale. There were many things that were very cheap. Sam and Mia wanted to buy some things for themselves and for their mom. They ran to the toy section and saw a big teddy bear. Sam liked the teddy bear and wanted to buy it. He said, "Look, Mia, this teddy bear is only five dollars. It is so soft and cute. I want to buy it for me."

Mia looked at the teddy bear and shook her head. She said, "No, Sam, this teddy bear is not good. It has a hole in its ear and a stain on its belly. It is not worth five dollars. It is worth zero dollars. You should not buy it. You should value your money and buy something else."

Sam was sad. He liked the teddy bear and did not care about the hole and the stain. He said, "But I like it, Mia. It is my favorite color and it has a nice smile. It is not bad. It is good. You should not be so mean."

Mia was not mean. She was smart. She said, "Sam, I am not mean. I am trying to help you. You can find a better teddy bear for five dollars. Or you can buy something else that is good and cheap. Like this book. It has many pictures and stories. It is only three dollars. It is good and cheap. You should buy it instead."

Sam looked at the book and thought for a moment. He liked books too. He liked pictures and stories. He said, "Okay, Mia, you are right. This book is good and cheap. I will buy it instead. Thank you for helping me. You are a good sister."

Mia smiled and hugged Sam. She said, "You are welcome, Sam. You are a good brother. Let's go and find something for mom. She will be happy to see what we bought. She will value our gifts."

They held hands and walked to the clothes section. They were calm and happy. They liked to go to the mall with their mom. They liked to value the things that were good and cheap.
<|end|>


