<|end|>
<|asst|>
Anna and Ben like to play with their toy animals. They have a big box with many animals, like lions, elephants, monkeys and giraffes. They pretend that the box is a jungle and the animals live there.

One day, they find a new toy in the box. It is a small, shiny ball with a picture of a temple inside. Anna picks it up and says, "Look, Ben, what is this?"

Ben looks at the ball and says, "I don't know, Anna. Maybe it is a magic ball. Let me see."

He takes the ball from Anna and shakes it. The picture of the temple changes and becomes snowy and sparkly. Ben says, "Wow, this is cool. The temple is in the snow now. Maybe it is a snow globe."

Anna says, "Can I try, Ben? Please?"

Ben gives the ball back to Anna and she shakes it too. The picture of the temple changes again and becomes sunny and colorful. Anna says, "Look, Ben, the temple is in the sun now. Maybe it is a rainbow globe."

They take turns shaking the ball and watching the temple change. They are very happy and amazed by the magic ball.

But they don't know that the ball is very delicate and can break easily. They shake it too hard and too fast. The ball slips from their hands and falls on the floor. It cracks and the water and the picture spill out.

Anna and Ben are very sad and sorry. They say, "Oh no, we broke the magic ball. It was so pretty and fun. What can we do?"

They pick up the pieces and try to fix the ball. But they can't. The ball is too delicate and too broken. They hug each other and say, "We are sorry, magic ball. We didn't mean to break you. We hope you can forgive us."
<|end|>


