<|asst|>
Tom and Sam are brothers. They like to play in the park. But the park has a big road next to it. The road is dangerous. There are many cars and trucks that go fast and make noise.

One day, Tom and Sam are playing with a ball. The ball is red and shiny. They throw the ball to each other and catch it. They have fun. But then, the ball goes too far. It goes over the fence and onto the road.

Tom runs after the ball. He does not look at the road. He does not see the cars and trucks. He only sees the ball. Sam sees Tom run. He is scared. He shouts to Tom.

"Tom, stop! Come back! The road is dangerous!"

But Tom does not hear Sam. He hears the ball. He reaches the ball. He picks it up. He smiles. He turns around. He sees a big truck. The truck is coming fast. The truck is loud. The truck does not see Tom.

Sam sees the truck. He shouts louder.

"Tom, watch out! The truck is coming!"

But it is too late. The truck hits Tom. Tom falls down. The ball flies away. Sam runs to Tom. He cries. He calls for help.

"Help! Help! Someone help Tom!"

But no one comes. The park is empty. The road is quiet. Tom does not move. Tom does not breathe. Tom is gone. Sam is alone. He is sad. He is sorry. He wishes he had listened to his mom. His mom had given him an order.

"Boys, do not play near the road. The road is dangerous. Stay in the park. Be careful."

But they did not listen. They did not obey. They did not follow the order. They played near the road. They were not careful. They were in danger. And now, Tom is dead. And Sam is alive. But he wishes he was not.
<|end|>


