<|asst|>
Lily did not like the pill that Mom gave her. It was big and white and tasted weird. Mom said it would make her feel better, but Lily did not believe her.

"Please, Lily, swallow the pill. It will help you with your cough and your fever," Mom urged.

Lily shook her head and hid under the blanket. She did not want the pill. She wanted juice and a hug.

Mom sighed and sat on the bed. She lifted the blanket and smiled at Lily.

"I know you don't like the pill, but it is good for you. How about this? If you take the pill, I will give you some juice and a hug. And we can read your favorite book together. How does that sound?"

Lily thought for a moment. She liked juice and hugs and books. Maybe the pill was not so bad after all.

"Okay, Mom. I will try the pill. But you have to stay with me," she said.

Mom nodded and hugged Lily. She gave her the pill and a glass of juice. Lily made a face and swallowed the pill. It was still weird, but not as bad as she thought.

"Good girl, Lily. I'm proud of you. Now, let's cuddle and read your book. Which one do you want?"

Lily smiled and pointed to the book with the bunny on the cover. She snuggled with Mom and listened to the story. She felt a little warmer and happier. Maybe the pill did help her after all.
<|end|>


