<|asst|>
Lily was a little girl who liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Silver, a shiny doll with long hair and a dress. Lily loved to brush Silver's hair and make her talk.

One day, Lily was playing with Silver in her room, when she heard a loud noise. She ran to the window and saw a big truck outside. The truck was taking away some old things from her neighbor's house. Lily saw a big box on the truck. She gasped. It was her box of old toys that she did not want anymore.

"Mommy, mommy!" Lily cried. "They are taking my toys!"

Lily's mommy came to the room and hugged her. "Don't worry, sweetie. Those toys are going to other children who need them. You have so many new toys to play with. Remember, you said you did not like those toys anymore."

"But, mommy, Silver is in that box!" Lily sobbed. "She is my best doll. I forgot to take her out. Please, mommy, stop the truck!"

Lily's mommy looked at the truck. It was already driving away. She felt sorry for Lily, but she did not know what to do. She tried to comfort her. "I'm sorry, honey. I didn't know Silver was in that box. Maybe we can find another doll like her. Or maybe you can make a new friend with one of your other dolls."

Lily shook her head. She did not want another doll. She wanted Silver. She imagined Silver lying in the box, helpless and scared. She wished she could save her. She cried and cried. She did not want to play anymore.
<|end|>


