Tom and Jen are friends. They like to play soccer together. They are very good at soccer. They want to win a trophy.

One day, they have a big game. They play hard and score many goals. They are happy. They win the game and get a trophy. They hug and cheer.

They want to show their trophy to their moms and dads. They walk home with the trophy. They are proud.

On the way home, they see a big dog. The dog is playful. He likes to chase things. He sees the trophy. He thinks it is a toy.

The dog runs after Tom and Jen. He barks and jumps. He wants the trophy. Tom and Jen are scared. They run faster.

The dog is faster. He catches up with them. He bites the trophy. He pulls it away from them. He runs away with the trophy.

Tom and Jen are sad. They cry. They lost their trophy. They go home without it. They have no trophy to show their moms and dads. They have a bad day.
<|end|>


