Mia and Ben were playing with their toy cars in the garden. They liked to pretend they were driving to different places. Mia had a pink car and Ben had a blue car.

"Where are you going, Mia?" Ben asked.

"I'm going to the park. It's lovely there. I can see the flowers and the swings and the slide," Mia said.

"Can I come with you?" Ben said.

"Sure, but you need a license to drive," Mia said.

"A license? What's that?" Ben said.

"It's a card that says you can drive. Like this one," Mia said, showing him a card with her name and picture on it. She had made it with crayons and stickers.

"Wow, that's cool. Can I have one too?" Ben said.

"OK, I'll make one for you. But you have to be careful and follow the rules," Mia said.

"What rules?" Ben said.

"You have to stop at the red light, go at the green light, and say beep beep when you pass someone," Mia said.

"OK, I can do that," Ben said.

Mia and Ben made a license for Ben with crayons and stickers. Then they got in their cars and drove to the park. They seemed very happy and had a lot of fun.
<|end|>


