Lila and Tom were at the beach with their mom and dad. They liked to play in the sand and splash in the water. They saw many fish and shells and crabs. They were happy.

"Look, mom, look!" Lila shouted. She pointed to a big rock in the water. "There is an octopus on the rock! It has many arms and spots!"

Mom came closer and saw the octopus too. She smiled and said, "Yes, that is an octopus. It is a very smart animal. It can twist and squeeze and hide in small places. It can also change its color to match its surroundings."

"Wow, that is cool!" Tom said. He wanted to see the octopus better. He ran to the water and got closer to the rock. He did not listen to mom, who told him to be careful and stay away.

The octopus saw Tom and did not like him. It felt scared and angry. It twisted its arms and grabbed Tom's leg. It pulled him into the water. Tom screamed and tried to get free, but the octopus was too strong.

Mom and dad heard Tom and ran to help him. They saw the octopus and Tom in the water. They were scared and sad. They tried to get the octopus off Tom, but it was too late. The octopus had bitten Tom and made him bleed. Tom was hurt and sick. He did not wake up.

The octopus let go of Tom and swam away. It was not hungry anymore. It had eaten a yummy snack. It did not care about Tom or his family. It only cared about itself. It was a bad octopus.
<|end|>


