<|asst|>
Lily and Ben are friends. They like to draw with pencils and paper. Lily has a big eraser. She can make her mistakes go away. Ben has a small eraser. He can only make some mistakes go away.

One day, Lily and Ben are drawing animals. Lily draws a cat. Ben draws a dog. But Ben makes a mistake. He draws the dog's tail too long. He tries to erase it, but his eraser is too small. He asks Lily to share her eraser.

"Can I use your eraser, Lily? My eraser is too small."

"No, Ben. This is my eraser. It is expensive. My mom gave it to me. You can't use it."

"But I need to fix my dog. It looks funny. Please, Lily. Just for a little bit."

"No, Ben. Go away. Find your own eraser."

Lily and Ben start to fight. They pull and tug on the eraser. The eraser breaks in half. Lily and Ben are sad. They both cry.

"Look what you did, Ben. You broke my eraser. It was expensive. Now I can't make my mistakes go away."

"I'm sorry, Lily. I didn't mean to break your eraser. I just wanted to fix my dog. Now I can't make my mistakes go away either."

Lily and Ben look at each other. They feel sorry. They hug and say sorry.

"I'm sorry, Lily. You can have the bigger half of the eraser. I don't need it."

"I'm sorry, Ben. You can have the smaller half of the eraser. I can share it."

Lily and Ben smile. They are friends again. They finish their drawings. They show them to each other. They like them.

"Your cat is nice, Lily. I like the whiskers."

"Your dog is nice, Ben. I like the tail."

Lily and Ben are happy. They learned to share. They learned to make up. They learned to draw.
<|end|>


