Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play with toys and books. One day, they find a big box in the yard. They open the box and see many things inside. They see paper, pens, glue, scissors, and stickers.

"Look, Mia! We can make signs with these things!" Tom says.

"Yes, Tom! Let's make signs for our club. We can cut the paper into strips and write our names on them. Then we can glue the stickers on them. They will be pretty and fun!" Mia says.

They take the things out of the box and start to make signs. They cut the paper into long and short strips. They write their names on the strips with the pens. They glue the stickers on the strips. They make stars, hearts, flowers, and animals. They are happy and proud of their signs.

"Wow, Mia! Your sign is very pretty! I like the pink heart and the yellow flower!" Tom says.

"Thank you, Tom! Your sign is very cool! I like the blue star and the green frog!" Mia says.

They finish their signs and show them to each other. They smile and hug. They decide to hang their signs on the wall of their club. Their club is a big tent made of blankets and pillows. They go inside the tent and hang their signs on the wall. They feel cozy and happy.

"Tom, Mia, it's time for lunch!" Mom calls from the house.

"Okay, Mom! We are coming!" Tom and Mia say.

They leave the tent and run to the house. They wash their hands and sit at the table. Mom gives them sandwiches and juice. They eat and drink. The sandwiches and juice are delicious. They thank Mom and tell her about their signs.

"That's wonderful, Tom and Mia! I'm glad you had fun making signs. Can I see them later?" Mom says.

"Sure, Mom! You can see them after lunch. They are in our club. We will show you!" Tom and Mia say.

They finish their lunch and go back to their club. They show Mom their signs and tell her what they mean. Mom says they are very creative and clever. She hugs them and kisses them. They hug and kiss her back. They are happy and love each other.
<|end|>


