Lily and Ben were playing in the park with their ball. They liked to throw the ball to each other and catch it. Sometimes they missed and the ball rolled away. Then they ran after it and laughed.

One time, the ball went too far and landed near a big tree. Lily and Ben ran to get it, but they saw a shadow behind the tree. It was a big dog. The dog barked and ran to the ball. It picked up the ball in its mouth and ran away.

"Hey, that's our ball!" Lily shouted. "Give it back!"

But the dog did not listen. It ran to the other side of the park, where its owner was sitting on a bench. The owner saw the dog with the ball and looked surprised.

"Bad dog!" the owner said. "Where did you get that ball? Did you steal it from someone?"

The dog looked guilty. It dropped the ball and wagged its tail. The owner picked up the ball and saw Lily and Ben running towards them.

"I'm sorry, kids," the owner said. "My dog likes to play with balls, but he shouldn't take yours. Here, you can have it back."

Lily and Ben took the ball and thanked the owner. They were happy to have their ball back, but they were also a little scared of the dog.

"Let's play somewhere else," Ben said.

"OK," Lily said. "But next time, let's throw the ball closer to us."
<|end|>


