Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play football in the park. They have a big red football. They kick it and run and laugh.

One day, they play football until it is dark. They are very tired and hungry. They want to go home. But they forget something. They forget the football. They leave it in the park.

The next day, they go to the park again. They want to play football. But they cannot find the football. They look everywhere. They ask other kids. They ask the dog. They ask the tree. No one knows where the football is.

They are very sad and angry. They think someone took their football. They think someone is very mean. They want their football back.

But then they see something. They see a big red football. It is on the roof of a house. They wonder how it got there. They remember. They remember they kicked the football very hard. They kicked it over the fence. They kicked it on the roof. They were very foolish. They forgot the football.

They try to get the football. They throw sticks and stones. They climb the fence. They shout and cry. But they cannot get the football. The football is too high. They need help.

They see a man. He lives in the house. He has a ladder. He sees the football. He sees the kids. He smiles. He helps them. He gets the ladder. He climbs the roof. He gets the football. He gives it to the kids.

The kids are very happy and grateful. They thank the man. They hug the football. They promise to be careful. They do not want to forget the football again. They go to the park. They play football. They have fun.
<|end|>


