Ben and Lily went to the pond to play. They saw many frogs jumping in the water. Ben wanted to catch a frog and show it to Lily. He ran after a big green frog and grabbed it with his hand. The frog was scared and angry. It opened its mouth and bit Ben's finger. "Ow!" Ben cried. He let go of the frog and it hopped away.

Lily heard Ben's cry and ran to him. She saw his finger was red and sore. She felt sorry for him. "Are you okay, Ben?" she asked. "That frog was mean. It bit you hard."

Ben nodded. He was okay, but he was also ashamed. He knew he should not have chased the frog. He did not ask the frog if it wanted to play. He was rude to the frog. He said to Lily, "I'm sorry, Lily. I was bad. I made the frog bite me. I won't do it again."

Lily smiled. She hugged Ben and said, "It's okay, Ben. You made a mistake. You learned your lesson. Next time, we can watch the frogs from far away. They are happy in the pond. They don't like to be caught."

Ben smiled back. He hugged Lily and said, "Thank you, Lily. You are a good friend. You helped me feel better. Next time, we can watch the frogs and listen to their songs. They are funny and cute."

They walked back to their mom, who was waiting for them with a picnic basket. They told her what happened and she gave Ben a band-aid and a kiss. They ate their sandwiches and cookies and drank their juice. They enjoyed the sunny day and the pond. They did not bother the frogs anymore. They were happy and kind.
<|end|>


