Lila and Tom are twins. They like to play in the mud. They make mud pies and mud castles. They get very dirty.

"Time to bathe, Lila and Tom!" Mom calls. "You are too dirty to eat dinner!"

Lila and Tom do not want to bathe. They want to play more. They run away from Mom. They hide behind a big tree.

Mom looks for them. She sees their footprints in the mud. She follows them to the tree. She finds them.

"Got you!" Mom says. "You cannot hide from me. Come on, let's go to the bath."

Lila and Tom pout. They do not like the bath. They think it is boring.

Mom takes them to the bath. She fills it with warm water and bubbles. She gives them a wide tub to sit in. She gives them some toys to play with. She gives them a useful sponge to wash with.

"See, the bath is not so bad," Mom says. "It is fun and cozy. And it makes you clean and fresh. You can play with the bubbles and the toys. And you can use the sponge to scrub your face and hair."

Lila and Tom try the bath. They splash the water and blow the bubbles. They play with the toys and use the sponge. They laugh and giggle.

"Okay, Mom, you are right," Lila says. "The bath is not boring. It is fun and cozy. And it makes us clean and fresh. Thank you for the wide tub and the useful sponge."

"You are welcome, Lila and Tom," Mom says. "I am glad you like the bath. Now you are ready to eat dinner. And then you can go to bed and have sweet dreams."

Lila and Tom get out of the bath. They dry themselves with a soft towel. They put on their pajamas. They hug Mom and say, "We love you, Mom."

"I love you too, Lila and Tom," Mom says. "You are my sweet and clean twins."
<|end|>


