Anna was curious about the dishwasher. She liked to watch the water and soap clean the dirty dishes. Sometimes she helped her mom put the dishes in and out of the dishwasher. But one day, the dishwasher stopped working. It made a loud noise and then no water came out.

"Oh no, the dishwasher is broken!" Mom said. "We have to call someone to fix it."

Anna was sad. She wanted to see the dishwasher work again. She wondered who would come to fix it and how they would do it.

The next day, a man came to their house. He had a big toolbox and a friendly smile. He said hello to Anna and Mom and went to the kitchen.

"Hello, I'm here to restore your dishwasher," he said. "It looks like there's a problem with the pump. I need to open it and replace some parts."

Anna watched him carefully. She saw him use a screwdriver, a wrench, and a flashlight. He took out some old parts and put in some new ones. He closed the dishwasher and turned it on.

"Look, it's working again!" he said. "The water is flowing and the dishes are getting clean."

Anna clapped her hands. She was happy. She thanked the man for restoring the dishwasher. He smiled and said goodbye.

Anna and Mom put the dishes in the dishwasher and turned it on. Anna liked to watch the water and soap clean the dirty dishes. She was curious about how the dishwasher worked, but she was also glad that it was fixed.
<|end|>


