<|asst|>
Lily and Tom like to play with cards. They have a game with many cards that have pictures on them. They put the cards face down and take turns to flip two cards. If the cards have the same picture, they are a match and they keep them. If the cards have different pictures, they put them back face down and try again.

One day, they find a new card in the game. It has a picture of a big, ugly monster with green skin, sharp teeth and horns. Lily and Tom do not like the monster card. They think it is scary and mean. They do not want to find the match for the monster card.

They start to play the game and flip the cards. Lily flips a card with a flower and Tom flips a card with a star. They are not a match. They put them back and try again. Lily flips a card with a cat and Tom flips a card with a dog. They are not a match either. They put them back and try again.

Lily flips a card with a cake and Tom flips the card with the monster. They are not a match, but Tom is scared. He does not want to see the monster again. He says, "Lily, you guess where the other monster card is. I do not want to flip it."

Lily looks at the cards and tries to guess where the other monster card is. She does not want to flip it either, but she wants to finish the game. She points to a card and says, "Maybe it is this one." She flips it and sees a picture of a rainbow. She is happy. It is not the monster card.

They keep playing until they find all the matches, except for the monster card. They leave the monster card face down and do not touch it. They say, "We do not like the monster card. It is ugly and scary. We like the other cards. They are pretty and nice." They put the cards away and play with something else.
<|end|>


