Tom and Sue like to play with trains. They have a big box of trains and a long track. They make the track go around the room and under the table. They take turns to push the trains and make noises.

One day, Tom has a bad idea. He sees a big train outside the window. It is on a real track. It is very fast and loud. Tom wants to see it up close. He urges Sue to go with him.

"Come on, Sue, let's go to the big train. It will be fun. We can touch it and ride it."

Sue is scared. She knows they are not allowed to go outside alone. She knows the big train is dangerous. She shakes her head.

"No, Tom, we can't go. Mommy said to stay inside. The big train can hurt us. It is too big and too fast."

Tom does not listen. He grabs Sue's hand and pulls her. He runs to the door and opens it. He drags Sue to the street. He sees the big train coming. He runs to the track.

Sue tries to stop him. She cries and screams. She pulls his hand. She sees the big train getting closer. She sees the thick smoke and the bright light. She hears the horn and the brakes.

"Tom, stop, stop, stop! The big train will hit us! We have to go back!"

But it is too late. Tom and Sue are on the track. The big train cannot stop. It hits them with a loud crash. They fly in the air and fall on the ground. They do not move. They do not make noises. They are gone.

The end.
<|end|>


