<|asst|>
Lily was a little girl who liked to play with her toys. She had a big clock that made a loud sound every hour. She thought the clock was very wise, because it knew the time and told her when to eat and sleep.

One day, Lily had a new friend come to her house. His name was Ben. He brought his own toys, and they played together in Lily's room. Ben saw the clock and wanted to touch it. He said, "What is this? Can I play with it?"

Lily said, "No, this is my clock. It is very wise and important. You can't play with it. You can play with my other toys."

Ben was sad and angry. He said, "That's not fair. You have so many toys, and you don't share. I don't like you. I want to go home."

Lily felt bad. She didn't want to lose her friend. She said, "I'm sorry, Ben. I didn't mean to be mean. You can play with my clock, but you have to be careful. It is very old and fragile. Please don't break it."

Ben smiled and said, "Thank you, Lily. You are very kind. I will be gentle with your clock. Can we still be friends?"

Lily said, "Yes, of course. You are welcome to play with me anytime. We can have fun together."

They hugged and played with the clock and the other toys. They learned to share and respect each other's things. The clock was happy to see them get along. It made a loud sound and said, "It is time for a snack. Come and eat, my little friends. You are very wise and good."
<|end|>


