<|asst|>
Sara and Tom were very cold. They lived in a small house with no fire. Their father worked hard to find coal, but he could not find much. He brought home a little coal every day, but it was not enough to make a warm fire.

One night, Sara and Tom were shivering in their bed. They heard their father come home. He sounded sad. He said to their mother, "I'm sorry, I could not find any more coal today. We have to pray for a miracle."

Sara and Tom did not know what a miracle was, but they wanted to help their father. They got out of their bed and went to their father. They hugged him and said, "We love you, father. We will pray with you."

They all knelt down and closed their eyes. They prayed to God to help them. They prayed for coal, for fire, for warmth, for happiness.

The next morning, they heard a knock on the door. They opened it and saw a big truck. The truck was full of coal. The driver smiled and said, "Hello, I'm from the church. We heard that you need some coal. We have plenty to share. God bless you."

Sara and Tom could not believe their eyes. They jumped and clapped and cheered. They thanked the driver and helped their father unload the coal. They made a big fire in the fireplace. They felt warm and cozy. They thanked God for the miracle. They hugged each other and smiled.
<|end|>


