Sara and Ben love to go to the beach with Mom and Dad. They like to play in the sand, make castles and dig holes. They also like to watch the big waves and the surfers who ride on them.

One day, Sara and Ben see a surf shop near the beach. They see many colorful boards and suits. They want to try surfing too. They ask Mom and Dad if they can.

"Surfing is fun, but it is also hard," Mom says. "You need to learn how to balance and steer. And you need to be careful of the water and the rocks."

"Can we take a lesson?" Ben asks.

"Maybe when you are older," Dad says. "But we can rent a board and play in the shallow water. Do you want to do that?"

Sara and Ben nod and smile. They follow Mom and Dad to the surf shop. They pick a board that is big and blue. They carry it to the water.

Mom and Dad help Sara and Ben to put the board in the water. They tell them to lie on the board and paddle with their hands. They show them how to watch the waves and avoid the rocks.

Sara and Ben have fun on the board. They feel the water splash on their faces. They see the fish and the shells. They hear the seagulls and the wind.

Sometimes, a small wave comes and lifts the board. Sara and Ben laugh and scream. They try to stand up on the board. They fall into the water. They get back on the board and try again.

"Look, Mom, look, Dad!" Sara shouts. "I can step on the board!"

"Wow, Sara, you are amazing!" Mom says.

"Me too, me too!" Ben says. "I can step on the board too!"

"Good job, Ben, you are amazing too!" Dad says.

Sara and Ben are very happy. They hug each other on the board. They love surfing. They want to do it again.
<|end|>


