Jill and Ben were playing in the garden. They saw a big bunch of grapes on the vine. They liked grapes. They wanted to eat some.

"Let's pick some grapes," Jill said.

"OK," Ben said. They ran to the vine and reached for the grapes.

But the grapes were not ripe. They were green and hard. They did not taste good.

"Yuck!" Jill said. "These grapes are sour!"

"Maybe we can make them sweet," Ben said. He had an idea. He took a grape and squeezed it hard in his hand. He hoped it would turn into juice.

But the grape did not turn into juice. It burst and squirted in his face. He felt a sting in his eye. He dropped the grape and cried.

"Ow! Ow! Ow!" Ben said. "It hurts!"

Jill saw Ben crying. She felt sorry for him. She wanted to help him. She took a grape and squeezed it too. She thought she could wash his eye with the juice.

But the grape did not wash his eye. It squirted in his other eye. He felt another sting. He cried louder.

"Ow! Ow! Ow!" Ben said. "Stop it!"

Jill was scared. She did not mean to hurt Ben. She dropped the grape and ran away.

Ben was alone. He had two sore eyes. He could not see. He was angry and sad. He did not like grapes. He did not like Jill. He wished he had never played in the garden.
<|end|>


