<|asst|>
One day, a little boy named Ben saw a big dragon in the sky. He was not afraid, he was curious. He wanted to talk to the dragon and make friends.

"Hello, dragon!" he shouted. "Can you come down and play with me?"

The dragon heard the boy and flew down to the ground. He was a friendly dragon, but he was also ignorant. He did not know much about people and their things.

"Hello, little one," he said. "What do you want to play?"

Ben smiled and pointed to his toy car. "This is my car. It can go fast and make noises. Do you want to try?"

The dragon nodded and picked up the car with his claws. He tried to make it go, but he did not know how. He pushed it, he pulled it, he shook it, but nothing happened. He got frustrated and angry.

"This car is broken!" he roared. "It does not work!"

He threw the car away and it landed on a rock. It broke into pieces. Ben was sad and angry too.

"No, dragon, no!" he cried. "You broke my car! You are ignorant! You do not know how to play!"

The dragon felt sorry and ashamed. He did not mean to break the car. He did not know it was important to the boy.

"I am sorry, little one," he said. "I did not know. I am ignorant. I do not know much about your things. But I can provide something else for you. I can provide fire."

He opened his mouth and breathed out a stream of fire. He made shapes and patterns with the fire in the air. He made a circle, a star, a heart, and a smiley face. He hoped the boy would like it.

Ben watched the fire and forgot about his car. He was amazed and happy. He liked the fire. He liked the dragon.

"Wow, dragon, wow!" he exclaimed. "You can provide fire! That is amazing! You are not ignorant, you are smart! You know how to make fire!"

He clapped his hands and laughed. He ran to the dragon and hugged his neck. The dragon hugged him back with his wings. They became friends. They played with fire and had fun.
<|end|>


