Sara and Ben were twins. They liked to play with their toys. But Sara had more toys than Ben. Ben was envious of Sara. He wanted to have her toys too.

One day, Sara and Ben went to the store with their mom. Mom said they could each choose one toy. Sara saw a big doll with a pink dress. She wanted it very much. She ran to the doll and picked it up. She said, "This is my toy. I like it. It is pretty."

Ben saw a small car with blue wheels. He wanted it too. But he also wanted Sara's doll. He ran to Sara and tried to take the doll from her. He said, "Give me the doll. I want it. It is nice."

Sara and Ben started to fight. They pulled and pushed each other. They shouted and cried. Mom heard them and came to them. She was angry. She said, "Stop fighting. You are being naughty. You cannot have both toys. You have to share. You have to be kind."

Sara and Ben felt sorry. They said, "We are sorry, Mom. We will not fight. We will share. We will be kind." Mom smiled and hugged them. She said, "That is good. I am proud of you. You can each have one toy. But you have to open them at home. Not in the store."

Sara and Ben nodded. They chose their toys. Sara had the doll and Ben had the car. They thanked Mom and went to the cashier. They paid for their toys and left the store. They were happy. They were not envious anymore. They were excited to open their toys at home. They said, "We love our toys. And we love each other."
<|end|>


