Anna and Ben are playing hide and seek in the park. Anna is the seeker and Ben is the hider. Anna counts to ten and then looks for Ben.

She sees a big tree with many leaves. She thinks Ben might be hiding behind it. She runs to the tree and says, "I found you, Ben!"

But there is no Ben. There is only a squirrel that runs away. Anna is confused. She looks around and sees a slide, a swing, and a sandbox. Where is Ben?

She hears a giggle from above. She looks up and sees Ben on top of the slide. He is holding a big circle made of paper. He says, "Surprise, Anna! I made this circle for you. It is your favorite color, pink!"

Anna smiles and says, "Wow, Ben! That is a very nice circle. How did you get so high?"

Ben says, "I climbed the ladder and then I slid down. But I stopped in the middle and I hid under the circle. I wanted to reveal it to you when you came close. Do you like it?"

Anna says, "I love it, Ben! Thank you for making it for me. You are very clever and kind. Can I slide down with you?"

Ben says, "Of course, Anna! Come on, let's slide together. Hold the circle and we can pretend we are flying!"

Anna and Ben slide down the slide, holding the circle. They laugh and have fun. They are very happy. They are the best friends.
