Lily and Max are twins. They like to sing songs together. They sing in the morning, in the car, and at night. They have a lot of fun.

One day, Mom makes cocoa for them. She puts it in two mugs. One mug is red and one mug is blue. She tells them to share and be nice.

Lily and Max run to the table. They both want the red mug. They both grab it and pull. The cocoa spills on the floor. The mug is empty. Mom is mad.

Lily and Max are sad. They say sorry to Mom. They say sorry to each other. They hug and make up.

Mom gets a towel and cleans the floor. She makes more cocoa. She puts it in two new mugs. One mug is green and one mug is yellow. She gives them to Lily and Max.

Lily and Max smile. They thank Mom. They sip their cocoa. They sing a song. They are happy.
