Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play at the park. They see a big swing. They want to swing on it.

"Can I swing first?" Anna asks.

"OK, but not too long," Ben says.

Anna runs to the swing. She sits on it. She holds the ropes. She pushes with her feet. She swings high and low. She feels happy.

"Wow, you swing so fast!" Ben says.

"I like to swing fast. It is fun," Anna says.

"Can I swing now?" Ben asks.

"OK, it is your turn," Anna says.

She jumps off the swing. She gives it to Ben. Ben sits on it. He holds the ropes. He pushes with his feet. He swings high and low. He feels happy.

"Wow, you swing so high!" Anna says.

"I like to swing high. It is fun," Ben says.

They swing for a long time. They laugh and smile. They get thirsty.

"Let's have some juice," Anna says.

"OK, let's go to the bench," Ben says.

They leave the swing. They walk to the bench. They see a bottle of juice. They share it. They drink it. It is sweet and cold. They feel good.

"Juice is yummy," Anna says.

"Juice is yummy," Ben says.

They finish the juice. They hug each other. They are friends. They like to play at the park. They like to swing.
