Lila and Ben like to play in the garden. They have a well with a bucket and a rope. They like to pull up the bucket and see the water. Sometimes they find frogs or stones in the bucket.

One day, Lila and Ben find a shiny thing in the bucket. It is round and hard and has a picture on it. Lila says, "It is a coin. It is very old and dirty. We can polish it and make it new."

They take the coin to the house and ask Mom for a cloth. Mom gives them a cloth and some soap. They rub the coin with the cloth and the soap. They see more of the picture. It is a man with a crown and a beard.

They rinse the coin with water and dry it with another cloth. They show Mom the coin. Mom says, "Wow, you found a very special coin. It is from a long time ago, when a king lived here. He threw coins in the well for good luck. You can keep it as a treasure."

Lila and Ben are very happy. They put the coin in a box and hide it under the bed. They say, "We will polish it again tomorrow. Maybe we will find more coins in the well." They hug Mom and go to sleep.
