Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play with toys. One day, Tom finds a laser in his dad's room. He thinks it is a fun toy. He takes it to Mia's house.

Tom and Mia play with the laser. They point it at things and make bright lights. They think it is funny. They laugh and have fun. They do not know that the laser is not a toy. It is a tool for dad's work.

The laser is very strong. It can make holes in things. It can hurt eyes. Tom and Mia do not see the danger. They point the laser at the wall, the floor, the sofa, the books, and the cat. They make a big mess. They scare the cat.

Mia's mom hears the noise. She comes to see what is going on. She sees the laser and the mess. She is very angry. She takes the laser from Tom and Mia. She tells them that the laser is not a toy. It is a dangerous thing. She tells them that they could have hurt themselves or the cat. She tells them that they have to say sorry and help clean up.

Tom and Mia feel bad. They say sorry to Mia's mom and the cat. They help clean up the mess. They learn a lesson. They learn that they have to be careful with things they do not know. They learn that they have to ask before they take things. They learn that some things are not toys. They learn that playing with lasers is not funny. It is silly and risky.
<|end|>


