Tom and Lily liked to play with their toy boats in the pond. They had many boats of different colors and sizes. Tom had a big navy boat that he was very proud of. Lily had a small pink boat that she loved.

One day, Tom saw Lily's boat and wanted to tease her. He said, "Your boat is so silly and small. My boat is much better and stronger. Your boat cannot go fast or far. My boat can do anything." Lily felt sad and angry. She said, "No, your boat is not better. Your boat is mean and rude. My boat is pretty and nice. My boat can go fast and far too."

Tom did not listen to Lily. He took his navy boat and chased Lily's boat in the pond. He bumped into Lily's boat and made it spin and splash. He laughed and said, "Ha ha, look at your boat. It is so weak and scared. My boat is so brave and smart. It can catch your boat easily."

Lily cried and said, "Stop it, stop it. You are hurting my boat. You are not nice. You are not my friend." She tried to get her boat back, but Tom was too fast and strong. He kept bumping into Lily's boat and laughing.

Then, something bad happened. Tom's navy boat hit a rock in the pond and broke. The rock made a hole in the boat and water came in. The boat sank and disappeared. Tom was shocked and sad. He said, "Oh no, oh no. My boat, my boat. It is gone, it is gone." He looked for his boat, but he could not find it.

Lily saw Tom's boat sink and felt sorry for him. She said, "I am sorry, Tom. I know you liked your boat. I did not want your boat to break. I wanted to play with you and your boat." She offered him her boat and said, "Here, you can have my boat. It is still good and whole. It can go fast and far too. We can share and be friends."

But Tom did not want Lily's boat. He said, "No, no. I do not want your boat. Your boat is silly and small. I do not like your boat. I do not like you. You are not my friend." He ran away from Lily and the pond. He left Lily alone with her boat.

Lily felt sad and lonely. She said, "Why is Tom so mean and rude? Why does he not want to be my friend? Why does he not like my boat? My boat is pretty and nice. My boat is my friend." She hugged her boat and cried.

The pond was peaceful and quiet. But Tom and Lily were not happy. They lost their boats and their friendship. They learned a hard lesson. Teasing is not fun. Teasing can hurt. Teasing can break things. Teasing can make you lose things. Teasing is not good.
<|end|>


