Anna likes to visit her grandma every week. Grandma lives in a big house with a garden and a cat. Anna loves to play with the cat and help grandma with the flowers.

One day, Anna wants to bring a gift for grandma. She thinks hard about what grandma likes. She remembers that grandma likes books and tea. She asks her mom to help her find a book and a tea bag.

Mom helps Anna wrap the book and the tea bag in a nice paper. She tells Anna to be honest and say thank you to grandma. Anna nods and puts the gift in her backpack.

They take the bus to grandma's house. Anna is excited to see grandma and the cat. She runs to the door and knocks. Grandma opens the door and smiles. She hugs Anna and mom.

Anna gives grandma the gift and says, "This is for you, grandma. I hope you like it. It is a book and a tea bag. Mom helped me find them. Thank you for letting me visit you. You are the best grandma ever."

Grandma is very happy and proud of Anna. She says, "Thank you, Anna. You are very sweet and honest. I love the book and the tea bag. They are perfect for me. I love to read and drink tea. You are the best granddaughter ever."

They go inside and have a nice time. They read the book together and drink tea. They play with the cat and the flowers. Anna is glad that she brought a gift for grandma. She thinks that grandma is glad too. She loves to visit her grandma.
