Lily and Tom were playing in the kitchen. They liked to pretend they were chefs and make food with pots and pans. Lily found a big spoon and said, "Look, Tom, I can stir the soup with this spoon." She put the spoon in a pot and moved it around.

Tom saw a shiny tap on the sink. He wanted to see what it did. He climbed on a chair and reached for the tap. He turned it and water came out. He said, "Wow, Lily, look, I can make water with this tap." He turned it more and more and water splashed everywhere.

Lily heard the water and looked at Tom. She saw the water on the floor and on the walls. She said, "Tom, stop, stop, you are making a mess. Turn off the tap, turn off the tap." She ran to the sink and tried to turn the tap. But the tap was too tight and she could not move it.

Tom got nervous. He said, "Lily, I can't turn it off, I can't turn it off. What do we do?" He jumped off the chair and ran to the door. He said, "Let's go and get mom, let's go and get mom."

Lily was scared. She said, "No, Tom, we can't go. Mom will be angry. We have to fix the tap, we have to fix the tap." She grabbed the spoon and hit the tap with it. She hoped the tap would stop. But the tap did not stop. The tap broke. Water sprayed out of the tap like a fountain. Lily and Tom screamed. They heard mom coming. They were in big trouble.
