Lily loves fashion. She likes to wear pink clothes and pink shoes. She has a pink hat, a pink dress, and a pink bag. She thinks pink is the best color.

One day, Lily goes to the park with her mom. She sees a girl with a purple coat and a purple bike. The girl looks happy and rides fast. Lily wants a purple coat and a purple bike too. She thinks purple is a cool color.

She tells her mom, "Mom, I want a purple coat and a purple bike. Can we buy them?" Her mom smiles and says, "Maybe for your birthday, Lily. But you have many pink things that you love. Why do you want purple things?"

Lily thinks for a moment. She remembers her pink hat, her pink dress, and her pink bag. She remembers how they make her feel pretty and happy. She says, "You are right, mom. I love my pink things. I don't need purple things. Pink is the best color."

She hugs her mom and they go to the swings. Lily sees the girl with the purple coat and the purple bike again. She waves and says, "Hi, I like your purple things. They are cool. But I like my pink things more. They are the best." The girl smiles and says, "Hi, I like your pink things too. They are pretty. But I like my purple things more. They are the best." They both laugh and play together. They are friends. They like fashion. They like different colors. And they are happy.
