Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play in the snow. They make a snowman with a hat and a scarf. They give him a carrot nose and two buttons for eyes. They are happy.

But then, a big dog comes. He runs to the snowman and barks. He bites the hat and the scarf. He pulls the carrot nose and the buttons. He makes the snowman fall down. Anna and Ben are sad and angry.

"Go away, dog! You are bad! You broke our snowman!" Anna shouts.

"Leave us alone, dog! You are mean! You ruined our fun!" Ben cries.

The dog does not listen. He wags his tail and jumps. He thinks it is a game. He sees Anna's glove on the ground. He picks it up with his mouth and runs away. Anna and Ben chase him.

"Give me back my glove, dog! It is mine!" Anna says.

"Stop, dog! It is not yours!" Ben says.

They run and run, but the dog is faster. He goes to a house and jumps over the fence. He goes to the door and barks. A lady opens the door. She sees the dog with the glove.

"Hello, dog! What do you have there? Is it a present for me?" she says.

She takes the glove from the dog and smiles. She sees Anna and Ben outside the fence. They look tired and sad.

"Are you the dog's friends? Do you want to come in?" she says.

She opens the gate and lets them in. She gives Anna her glove and hugs her. She gives Ben a cookie and pats his head. She welcomes them to her home.

"Thank you, lady. You are nice. You have a funny dog," Anna says.

"Thank you, lady. You are kind. You have a playful dog," Ben says.

They sit on the couch and play with the dog. They forget about the snowman. They are happy again.
