<|asst|>
One day, a little girl named Lucy went to play with her friend, Tom. They were playing with their toys in Tom's room. Lucy saw a pretty doll with a dress that had a pin on it. She wanted to play with the doll, but she was too shy to ask Tom.

Tom saw Lucy looking at the doll and said, "Do you want to play with my doll? I can lend it to you." Lucy felt happy and said, "Yes, please! Thank you, Tom!" So, Tom gave Lucy the doll to play with.

As they played, they both became impatient. They wanted to play outside in the sun. So, they put the toys away and went to the park. Lucy remembered to give the doll back to Tom. They had a fun day playing in the park, and they learned that sharing and being patient can make playtime even better.
<|end|>


