<|end|>
<|asst|>
Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little boy named Tim. Tim had a big nose. One day, he went outside to play in the park.

While playing, Tim met a new friend named Sam. They both loved to run and jump. As they played, Tim started to feel dizzy. He sat down on the grass and said, "Sam, I feel dizzy."

Sam looked at Tim's big nose and said, "Maybe you need to breathe through your nose more." Tim tried to breathe through his nose, and he started to feel better.

As they played more, they discovered a big tree. They climbed the tree and saw many birds. Tim and Sam laughed and played until the sun went down. They were very happy to have found each other and the big tree.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
You are telling a short children's story.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
One day, a little girl named Lily went to a farm with her mom. The farm was big and had many animals. Lily liked the funny ducks that went "quack, quack" and the pigs that went "oink, oink". She also liked the big red barn where the animals slept.

Lily saw a big cow and wanted to touch it. She asked her mom, "Can I touch the cow?" Her mom said, "No, Lily, the cow might be scared. We can just look." Lily felt sad because she wanted to be friends with the cow.

Lily's mom had an idea. She said, "Let's point at the animals and say their names." They pointed at the ducks and said, "Duck!" They pointed at the pigs and said, "Pig!" When they pointed at the cow and said, "Cow!" the cow looked at them and went "moo!" Lily laughed and felt happy again. The farm was a fun place to be.
<|end|>


