Once upon a time, there was a bossy cat named Tom. Tom liked to tell all the other animals what to do. One day, Tom saw a little bird named Timmy. Timmy was enjoying his day, playing in the sun. Tom wanted to make trouble for Timmy.

Tom said to Timmy, "You have to play with me now!" Timmy did not want to play with Tom, but Tom was very bossy. So, Timmy said, "Okay, I will play with you." They played a game, but Tom always wanted to win. Timmy did not enjoy playing with Tom.

As they played, Tom made more and more trouble. He made Timmy do things that were not fun. Timmy became very sad. In the end, Tom was still bossy, and Timmy did not want to play with him anymore. Tom did not have any friends because he was always making trouble and being bossy.
<|end|>


