One day, a boy named Tim went to the store with his mom. They needed to buy some sugar for a cake they were going to make. Tim thought it was very important to help his mom.

At the store, Tim saw his friend Sam. Sam said, "Hi, Tim! I have a joke for you. Why did the sugar go to school?" Tim thought about it and said, "I don't know, why?" Sam laughed and said, "Because it wanted to be a sweet student!" Tim laughed too.

Tim and his mom bought the sugar and went home. They made the cake together and shared it with Sam. They all laughed and had fun, and Tim felt happy that he could help his mom with something important.
<|end|>


