Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim was very hungry. He went to his mom and said, "Mom, I am hungry. Can I have some food?"

His mom smiled and said, "Yes, Tim. Let's go to the kitchen and find something to eat." They went to the kitchen and Tim's mom asked him to kneel down by the cupboard. Tim kneeled down and opened the cupboard.

Inside the cupboard, there were many snacks. Tim saw cookies, chips, and fruits. He looked at his mom and asked, "What is the truth, Mom? Can I eat all of these snacks?"

His mom laughed and said, "No, Tim. You can only pick one snack. Eating too many will make your tummy hurt." Tim thought for a moment and picked an apple. He was happy with his choice and ate the apple with a big smile on his face.
<|end|>


