One day, a little girl named Lucy went to play outside. She found a bottle with a wand that had a big circle on it. Lucy knew it was for making bubbles. She dipped the wand into the bottle and blew. Many harmless bubbles came out and floated in the air.

Lucy saw a big tree and thought, "Maybe the tree will yield more bubbles." She took the bottle and wand and walked to the tree. She blew more bubbles under the tree. More and more bubbles came out, and they looked so pretty.

A little boy named Tim saw the bubbles and came to play with Lucy. Tim said, "Wow, so many bubbles! Can I play with you?" Lucy said, "Yes, let's make more bubbles together!" They both played with the bubbles under the tree and had lots of fun.
<|end|>


