One day, a boy named Tom found a rag. It was not a clean rag, but Tom did not mind. He took the rag home to show his mom. "Look, Mom," said Tom, "I found a rag."

His mom looked at the rag and smiled. "That's an honest rag, Tom," she said. "But it is dirty. We should wash it." Tom agreed, and they washed the rag together.

Later, Tom found a small box. It was a box to record sounds. Tom thought it was fun to record his voice. He played with the box all day. But when it was time for bed, Tom did not want to stop playing. He hid the box under his pillow.

In the night, Tom woke up and played with the box. He recorded his voice, but he was very loud. His mom and dad woke up. They were not happy. Tom was sad because he made his mom and dad angry. The next day, Tom had to give the box back, and he did not have any more fun with the rag.
<|end|>


