<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a furry cat named Kitty. Kitty loved to play with her ball of yarn. One day, she found a big knot in her yarn. She tried to untie the knot, but it was too hard.

Kitty asked her friend, Doggy, for help. "Doggy, can you help me untie this knot?" Doggy tried to help, but the knot was still too hard for him too. They both thought hard about what to do.

Then, they had an idea. They would ask Birdy to deliver a message to Wise Owl for help. Birdy flew to Wise Owl and told him about the knot. Wise Owl knew just what to do. He told Birdy to tell Kitty and Doggy to pull the yarn gently from both sides of the knot.

Birdy delivered the message to Kitty and Doggy. They followed Wise Owl's advice and pulled the yarn gently. The knot became loose and finally untied! They were so happy and thanked Birdy for delivering the message. Kitty, Doggy, and Birdy played together with the yarn, and they all lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


