One day, a little girl named Lucy went to the beach with her mom. They saw many interesting things, like shells, fish, and oysters. Lucy loved to look at the oysters because they were shiny and pretty.

While they were walking, they met a sneaky crab. The crab said, "I like to steal shiny things, like oysters." Lucy was surprised and told the crab, "Stealing is bad! You should not take things that are not yours."

The crab thought about what Lucy said and decided to stop stealing. Instead, he helped Lucy and her mom find more oysters on the beach. They all had a fun day together, and Lucy taught the crab that sharing is better than stealing.
<|end|>


