<|asst|>
One day, a cheerful pepper went for a walk. As the pepper walked, it saw a big bird. The bird said, "Hello, little pepper! What are you doing?"

The pepper said, "I am going for a walk to see my friend, the sun. He makes me warm and happy."

As the pepper walked, it started to get cold. The pepper did not like the cold. It wanted the sun to come out and make it warm again. The pepper began to freeze.

Just then, the sun came out from behind a cloud. The sun said, "Hello, little pepper! I heard you were cold. I am here to make you warm again."

The pepper smiled and said, "Thank you, sun! You are my best friend." The sun made the pepper warm and they were both very happy.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
You are telling a short children's story.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Once upon a time, in a small house, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim had a favorite jacket with a zipper. One day, the zipper on his jacket was broken. Tim was very sad because he loved his jacket so much.

Tim asked his mom to fix the broken zipper. His mom tried her best, but she could not fix it. Tim was even more sad now. He decided to go outside and play with his friends to forget about his broken zipper.

While playing, Tim saw a big hill. He wanted to speed down the hill on his bike. He thought it would make him happy. So, Tim and his friends went to the top of the hill. Tim got on his bike and started to speed down very fast.

But, because his jacket was open with the broken zipper, it caught on a tree branch. Tim fell off his bike and hurt his knee. His friends helped him get up, but Tim was very sad and in pain.

In the end, Tim learned that speeding down the hill was not a good idea. He wished he had been more careful and listened to his mom. Now, Tim had a broken zipper and a hurt knee, and he was not happy at all.
<|end|>


