<|end|>
<|asst|>
One day, a little girl named Lucy went to the park. She saw a good spot to lay her blanket. She put her blanket down and lay on it. Lucy wanted to have a fun day at the park.

Soon, Lucy's friend Tom came to the park. He saw Lucy's blanket and said, "Lucy, I want to lay on your blanket too!" Lucy said, "Okay, Tom. But first, we have to pass a test. We have to find five rocks."

Tom and Lucy looked all around the park for rocks. They found one, two, three, four, but they could not find the fifth rock. Tom was sad. He said, "I don't think we can pass the test, Lucy."

Lucy did not want Tom to be sad. She said, "I have an idea! Let's look for the last rock together!" They looked and looked, and finally they found the fifth rock. They passed the test and were both happy. Tom and Lucy lay on the blanket together, and they had a great day at the park.
<|end|>


