<|asst|>
One day, a little girl named Lucy found a colorful birdcage in her room. She looked at it and said, "Wow! This is pretty!" She put the birdcage on her table and went to play outside.

While Lucy was playing, she saw a small bird with many colors. The bird looked sad and lost. Lucy said, "Hello, bird! Why do you frown?" The bird replied, "I can't find my home." Lucy smiled and said, "I have a colorful birdcage! Maybe it's your home!"

Lucy took the bird to her room and showed it the birdcage. The bird's eyes lit up, and it said, "Yes! That's my home!" Lucy opened the birdcage, and the bird went inside. The bird was happy to be home, and Lucy was happy to help her new friend. From that day on, Lucy and the bird played together every day, and they both smiled all the time.
<|end|>


