<|asst|>
Once upon a time, in a big forest, there lived an honest leopard. The leopard had many friends because he was always nice and played fair. One day, the leopard met a small bird who was lost.

"Hello, little bird. Why are you sad?" asked the leopard. The bird said, "I am lost. I can't find my family." The honest leopard wanted to help the bird, so they went on a journey to find the bird's family.

They walked and walked until they found a big tree. The tree had many nests with birds. The little bird saw his family and was very happy. The leopard and the bird settled under the tree to rest.

"Thank you for helping me find my family," said the little bird. The honest leopard smiled and said, "You're welcome, my friend. I'm glad we found them."

From that day on, the leopard and the little bird were the best of friends. They played together and shared many happy moments in the big forest.
<|end|>


