Once upon a time, there was a wild cat. The wild cat had a friend, a little girl named Sue. Sue and the wild cat liked to play together. They played in the sun and had lots of fun.

One day, Sue found a bottle of ink. She wanted to use the ink to draw a picture. But the wild cat did not care about the ink. The wild cat just wanted to play with Sue. So, they played and played.

Sue was happy to play with the wild cat, but she still wanted to draw with the ink. She asked the wild cat to help her draw. The wild cat did not know how to draw, but it tried to help Sue. They made a big mess with the ink, but they had fun. Sue and the wild cat cared for each other and had a great day.
<|end|>


