Once upon a time, there was a clever cat named Kitty. Kitty loved to write. She would write all day long. She wrote stories, songs, and even a list of her favorite toys.

One day, Kitty decided she wanted to write a license. She thought it would be fun to have a license to do special things. So, she got a big piece of paper and her favorite pen. She wrote her name, "Kitty the Clever Cat," on the paper. Then, she drew a picture of herself and wrote, "This is my special license."

Kitty showed her license to her best friend, a dog named Buddy. Buddy looked at the license and said, "Wow, Kitty! You are so clever! I want a license too!" So, Kitty helped Buddy write his own license. They both felt very special with their new licenses. From that day on, Kitty and Buddy used their licenses to do many fun and special things together. They were very happy and proud of their clever work.
<|end|>


