One day, a little boy named Tim found a filthy vase in the park. The vase was covered in dirt and had leaves stuck to it. Tim wanted to clean it, so he took it home.

At home, Tim showed the vase to his mom. She said, "Tim, that vase is very dirty. Let's clean it together." They used soap and water, and soon the vase was shiny and clean. But as they cleaned, Tim's hands started to tremble. He was scared he might break the vase.

Tim's mom saw him tremble and said, "Don't worry, Tim. I will help you hold the vase." They carefully put the vase on the table, and Tim felt better. Later, they put pretty flowers in the vase and placed it on the window sill.

The vase made their home look lovely, and Tim was happy he found it. The moral of the story is that when we work together and help each other, we can make something dirty and old into something beautiful and new.
<|end|>


