One day, a little boy named Tim went to the park. He wanted to play with his big, round basketball. Tim was very excited to play with his friends. The sun was shining and the sky was blue. It was a perfect day to play outside.

As Tim started to play, he saw a small, helpless bird on the ground. The bird looked sad and could not fly. Tim wanted to help the bird, so he called his friends over. They all tried to think of a way to help the bird feel better.

Tim and his friends decided to make a soft bed for the bird using leaves and grass. They gently picked up the bird and placed it on the bed. The bird started to feel better and soon, it could fly again. The bird was so happy that it decided to stay and watch Tim and his friends play basketball. They all had a great day at the park and Tim was glad he could help the bird.
<|end|>


