Once upon a time, there was a red couch in a small house. The couch was very happy because it was always being used by a nice family. They would sit on the couch to watch TV, read books, and talk to each other.

One day, a green chair came to live in the house. The chair looked at the couch and felt envious. It wanted to be used like the couch, but the family did not sit on the chair as much. The chair felt sad and lonely.

The chair said to the couch, "I wish I was like you. The family uses you all the time, but they don't use me." The couch replied, "Don't be sad. You are new here. Soon, they will use you too." The chair smiled and waited. After some days, the family started to use the chair more, and the chair was happy. The couch and the chair became good friends, and they enjoyed being used by the family together.
