Once upon a time, there was a clumsy girl named Lily. She always dropped things and tripped over her feet. One day, Lily found a pretty veil in her mom's room. The veil was soft and shiny.

Lily wanted to show her friend, Tim. She ran to Tim's house, but she tripped and fell. The veil got dirty. "Oh no!" said Lily. "I spoil the veil. What do I do?"

Tim looked at the veil and said, "Don't worry, Lily. We can clean it." They washed the veil together and it became clean again. Lily was happy and thanked Tim.

Lily learned that being clumsy can make a mess, but friends can help fix it. The moral of the story is: if you make a mistake, it's okay to ask for help.
