Once upon a time, there was a little bird named Timmy. Timmy loved to whistle all day long. He would whistle when he was happy, and he would whistle when he was sad. Timmy's whistling made the other birds in the forest happy too.

One day, Timmy saw a big door with the word "exit" on it. He was very curious and impatient to see what was on the other side. So, Timmy whistled a happy tune and went through the exit door.

Behind the exit door, Timmy found a beautiful garden with lots of yummy food. He whistled a happy song and ate his fill. After that, Timmy went back through the exit door and told all his friends about the wonderful place he had found. They all whistled happy songs and went to the garden together. And they all lived happily ever after.
