One day, a little girl named Mia went to the grocery store with her mom. They needed to buy food for their home. Mia was excited to help her mom. She wanted to be a good helper.

In the grocery store, Mia saw a filthy cart. "Mom, look at this dirty cart," she said. Her mom replied, "Let's clean it up, Mia." So, they cleaned the cart together, and it looked much better. Mia was happy to make the cart clean.

Next, they went to the fruit area. Mia's mom asked her to help sort the fruits. Mia put apples with apples, and oranges with oranges. She liked to sort things. When they were done, Mia's mom said, "Thank you, Mia. You are a great helper!" Mia smiled and felt proud of herself. They went home with their groceries, and Mia couldn't wait to help her mom again.
