One day, a little bird named Tim was flying in the sky. He was fearful because he saw a big, mean cat. The cat was hiding behind a tree, watching Tim. Tim knew he needed to protect himself and his friends from the cat.

Tim flew to his friend, the wise old owl. "Help me, please!" said Tim. "I saw a big, mean cat, and I am fearful. How can we protect ourselves and our friends?" The wise old owl thought for a moment and said, "I have an idea. Let's make a plan to scare the cat away."

The wise old owl and Tim gathered all their friends in the forest. They made a plan to protect everyone from the big, mean cat. The plan was to make a lot of noise and scare the cat away.

The next day, when the big, mean cat came back, Tim and his friends were ready. They all made loud noises and scared the cat away. The cat ran away, never to be seen again.

From that day on, Tim and his friends were no longer fearful. They knew that by working together, they could protect themselves from anything. And they all lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


