Tom and Lily were playful twins who liked to run and hide. One day, they saw a big maze in the park. They wanted to go inside and explore. But their mom said no. She said the maze was not for children. It was for grown-ups who paid money.

Tom and Lily did not listen. They waited until their mom was busy. Then they ran to the maze and sneaked in. They thought it was fun to find their way through the paths and walls. They laughed and shouted.

But soon they got lost. They could not see the exit. They could not see their mom. They could not see each other. They were scared and alone. They cried and called for help.

A man heard them. He came to the maze. He saw Tom and Lily. He did not look nice. He looked mean. He had a big bag. He said he would help them. But he lied. He grabbed Tom and Lily and put them in his bag. He wanted to steal them. He ran away with them.

Their mom heard them scream. She looked for them. She saw the man with the bag. She ran after him. She shouted for help. But it was too late. The man was faster. He got in a car and drove away. He took Tom and Lily with him. Their mom could not catch him. She could not save them. She was very sad. She wished they had listened to her.
<|end|>


