Lily was a shy girl who liked to play with her dolls. She did not talk much to the other kids at school. She was afraid they would laugh at her or be mean to her.

One day, a new boy came to her class. His name was Max. He had curly hair and a big smile. He sat next to Lily and said hello. Lily did not say anything. She looked down at her desk and hoped he would go away.

Max did not go away. He wanted to be friends with Lily. He saw her dolls and asked if he could play with them. Lily shook her head and hugged her dolls tighter. Max did not give up. He poked Lily gently on the arm and said, "Please, can I play with you? I like dolls too. They are fun and pretty."

Lily felt the poke and looked up at Max. She saw his smile and his kind eyes. She felt a warm feeling in her chest. She wondered if he was really nice and not mean. She decided to give him a chance. She nodded and said, "Okay, you can play with me. But be careful with my dolls. They are my friends."

Max was happy. He thanked Lily and picked up a doll. He said, "This one is my favorite. She has a pink dress and a bow. What is her name?" Lily smiled and said, "Her name is Rose. She is my favorite too. She likes hugs and stories." Max said, "Me too. Can I hug her?" Lily said, "Yes, you can. But only if I can hug this one." She pointed to a doll with a blue shirt and a hat. Max said, "Sure, you can. His name is Jack. He likes jokes and games." Lily said, "I like jokes and games too. Do you know any jokes?" Max said, "Yes, I do. Do you want to hear one?" Lily said, "Yes, please."

They laughed and played with the dolls. They told jokes and stories. They hugged the dolls and each other. They became friends. Lily was not shy anymore. She was happy.
<|end|>


