Sam and Tom are brothers. They like to play outside in the mud. They make mud pies and mud castles. They have fun, but they get very filthy.

"Boys, time for your meal!" Mom calls from the kitchen. "Come inside and bathe first!"

Sam and Tom run to the bathroom. They take off their clothes and jump in the tub. They splash water and soap on each other. They wash their hair and their faces. They rinse off the mud and the dirt.

"Look, we are clean now!" Sam says to Tom.

"Yes, we are!" Tom says to Sam.

They dry themselves with towels and put on fresh clothes. They go to the kitchen and sit at the table. Mom serves them soup and bread. They eat their meal and say thank you to Mom.

"Did you have fun playing outside?" Mom asks them.

"Yes, we did!" Sam and Tom say together.

"But we also like to bathe and eat!" Sam adds.

Mom smiles and hugs them. She is happy that they are clean and full. She loves her boys.
<|end|>


