Tom and Lily were playing in the sand. They liked to make castles and dig holes. They had a bucket and a shovel each. They were having fun.

But then Tom saw something shiny in the sand. He dug it out with his shovel. It was a necklace with a blue stone. Tom liked it. He put it around his neck.

Lily saw the necklace and wanted it. She said, "Give me the necklace, Tom. It is mine." Tom said, "No, it is mine. I found it." They started to fight.

A man was walking by. He saw them fighting. He said, "Stop fighting, children. Why don't you share the necklace? Or you can replace it with something else. Look, there is an oasis over there. Maybe you can find something nice there."

Tom and Lily looked at the oasis. It was a place with water and trees and flowers in the sand. It looked pretty. They decided to go there. They took their bucket and shovel.

They found many things in the oasis. They found shells and rocks and feathers and fruits. They were flexible. They traded some things with each other. They both got something they liked. They forgot about the necklace.

They thanked the man and went back to their sand. They played with their new things. They were happy. They did not fight anymore.
<|end|>


