Sara and Ben like to play in the sand near the sea. They make castles and dig holes and look for shells. One day, they find a big shell that is shiny and pretty. Sara wants to keep it, but Ben wants it too.

"Give me the shell, Sara!" Ben says. "It is mine!"

"No, it is mine!" Sara says. "I saw it first!"

They pull and tug at the shell, but it does not break. They get angry and yell at each other. They do not see the octopus that is hiding under the water.

The octopus is hungry and curious. It sees the shiny shell and wants to touch it. It reaches out with one of its arms and grabs the shell from Sara and Ben. They are surprised and scared. They let go of the shell and run away.

The octopus is happy. It has a new toy to play with. It opens the shell and finds a pearl inside. The pearl is round and white and smooth. The octopus thinks it is beautiful. It puts the pearl in its mouth and feels how hard it is. It bites the pearl and hears a crunch.

"Ow!" the octopus says. "This pearl is sharp! It hurts my teeth!"

The octopus spits out the pearl and the shell. It does not want them anymore. It swims away to look for something else to eat.

Sara and Ben come back to the sand. They see the shell and the pearl on the ground. They are happy and amazed. They pick them up and look at them.

"Wow!" Sara says. "This is a pearl! It is so rich and rare!"

"Wow!" Ben says. "This is a sharp pearl! It can cut things!"

They decide to share the shell and the pearl. They make a necklace with them and put it around Sara's neck. They hug and say sorry to each other. They are friends again. They play in the sand and have fun. They do not see the octopus that is watching them from the water. The octopus is not hungry and curious anymore. It is sad and lonely. It wishes it had a friend to play with.
<|end|>


