<|asst|>
Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a man with a stick in his mouth. The stick makes smoke. Tom and Sam are curious.

"Hello, man. What is that?" Tom asks.

"This is a cigarette. It helps me relax. Do you want to try?" the man says.

Tom and Sam shake their heads. They know cigarettes are bad. They make people sick and smell bad.

"No, thank you. Cigarettes are stupid. They hurt your lungs and teeth. We don't want to smoke," Sam says.

The man laughs. He thinks Tom and Sam are silly. He blows smoke in their faces. Tom and Sam cough and run away.

"Hey, come back. Don't be afraid. Smoking is cool. You are missing out," the man says.

Tom and Sam ignore him. They find a bench and sit down. They see a dog. The dog is friendly. He wags his tail and licks their hands. Tom and Sam pet the dog. They like the dog.

"Hello, dog. What is your name?" Tom asks.

The dog barks. He does not have a name. He is a stray. He is hungry and lonely.

"Can we be your friends?" Sam asks.

The dog nods. He is happy. He likes Tom and Sam. They share their snacks with him. They play fetch with him. They hug him.

"You are a good dog. We love you," Tom and Sam say.

The dog loves them too. He bites the man's cigarette and spits it out. The man is angry. He yells at the dog. He tries to kick the dog. Tom and Sam protect the dog. They bite the man's leg. The man screams and runs away.

"Good job, dog. You are brave. You saved us from the smoke," Tom and Sam say.

The dog barks. He is proud. He thanks Tom and Sam. They thank him too. They decide to adopt him. They name him Spot. They take him home. They give him a bath, a bed, and a collar. They are a family.

The moral of the story is: Smoking is bad for you and others. It is not cool or relaxing. It is stupid and harmful. Friends are good for you and others. They are not silly or afraid. They are kind and helpful. Friends are the best.
<|end|>


