<|asst|>
Ben and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to swing on the ropes and slide on the slides. They saw a big rope hanging from a tree. It looked like fun.

"Let's swing on the rope!" Ben said.

"OK!" Lily said.

They ran to the rope and took turns to swing. Ben swung high and low. Lily swung fast and slow. They laughed and shouted.

But then a boy came. He was bigger than Ben and Lily. He had a mean face and a loud voice. He wanted the rope.

"Get off the rope! It's mine!" he said.

"No, it's not! We were here first!" Ben said.

The boy got angry. He grabbed the rope and pulled it hard. Ben and Lily fell to the ground. They hurt their knees and elbows. They cried.

The boy laughed. He swung on the rope. He thought he was smart.

But he was not smart. He was crazy. He swung too high and too fast. He lost his grip and flew off the rope. He landed on a bush. The bush had thorns. The thorns pinched his skin. He screamed.

Ben and Lily stopped crying. They saw the boy in the bush. They felt sorry for him. They went to help him.

"Are you OK?" Lily asked.

"No, I'm not! The bush pinched me! It hurts!" the boy said.

"Maybe you should not be mean to other kids. Maybe you should share the rope." Ben said.

The boy nodded. He was sorry. He said sorry to Ben and Lily. They said it was OK. They helped him out of the bush. They gave him a band-aid.

They became friends. They swung on the rope together. They had fun. They learned to be nice. The end.
<|end|>


