Tom and Jen are twins. They like to play in the snow. They wear warm coats, hats, gloves and boots. They make a snowman and a snow fort. They have fun.

But then they hear a loud noise. It is a big dog. The dog is crazy. It runs and barks and jumps. It knocks down the snowman and the snow fort. It makes a mess.

Tom and Jen are scared. They run to their house. They call their mom.

"Mom, mom, there is a crazy dog outside. It ruined our snowman and our snow fort. It is scary."

Mom comes to the door. She sees the dog. She is not scared. She knows the dog. It is Rex, the neighbor's dog. He is not crazy. He is playful. He likes the snow.

Mom says, "Don't worry, Tom and Jen. That is Rex. He is a friendly dog. He just wants to play with you. He likes your snowman and your snow fort. He thinks they are toys."

Tom and Jen look at Rex. He wags his tail. He licks his nose. He looks happy.

Tom and Jen are not scared anymore. They are curious. They go outside. They pet Rex. They play with him. They make a new snowman and a new snow fort. They share their gloves and hats and boots with Rex. They have more fun.
