<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were twins who loved to sing. They sang all the time, at home, at school, and in the park. They wanted to be opera singers when they grew up, because they heard that opera was brilliant and beautiful.

One day, their mom took them to see a real opera at a big theater. They were very excited and curious. They wore their best clothes and sat in their seats. The lights went down and the music started.

But when the opera singers came on stage, Tom and Lily were scared. They sang very loud and high, and made funny faces and gestures. They sounded like angry animals or ghosts. Tom and Lily did not like it at all. They wanted to go home.

"Mom, can we leave?" Tom whispered. "This opera is scary and ugly."

"Shh, be quiet," mom said. "This opera is brilliant and wonderful. You have to listen and learn. Maybe you will like it later."

But Tom and Lily did not like it later. They felt bored and frightened. They wished they could sing their own songs, or listen to something else.

At the end of the opera, the singers bowed and the audience clapped. Mom was happy and proud. She said to Tom and Lily, "Did you enjoy the opera? Wasn't it amazing?"

Tom and Lily shook their heads. They said, "No, mom, we did not enjoy the opera. It was not amazing. It was scary and ugly. We like our songs better. Can we go home now?"

Mom was surprised and sad. She said, "But Tom and Lily, you love to sing. You want to be opera singers. How can you not like opera?"

Tom and Lily said, "We love to sing, but we do not love opera. Opera is not for us. We want to sing our own way, and listen to different music. Can we try something else?"

Mom thought for a moment. She said, "Well, I guess you have your own tastes and preferences. I'm sorry you did not like the opera, but I'm glad you tried something new. Maybe you will find another kind of music that you love. There are many kinds of music in the world, and you can sing them all. But you have to be respectful and open-minded. You never know what you might learn or enjoy."

Tom and Lily nodded. They said, "We're sorry, mom. We did not mean to be rude or close-minded. We will try to be respectful and open-minded. But can we go home now?"

Mom smiled. She said, "Yes, we can go home now. But maybe next time, we can try something else. How about jazz, or rock, or folk? There are many kinds of music in the world, and you can sing them all."

Tom and Lily smiled. They said, "OK, mom. We will try something else. Maybe we will like it. But we will always love our songs, too. Can we sing them on the way home?"

Mom said, "Of course, you can. Let's sing together. There are many kinds of music in the world, and you can sing them all."

And they did.
<|end|>


