<|asst|>
Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play with cars and trucks. They have many cars and trucks, but they have one big truck that they both love. It is red and shiny and makes loud noises.

One day, they want to play with the big truck on the road. The road is not busy, but they have to be careful. They take turns to drive the big truck and make it go fast and slow and beep the horn. They have fun and laugh.

But then, a big dog comes to the road. It is black and furry and has sharp teeth. It sees the big truck and wants to play with it too. It runs to the truck and barks and tries to bite it. Lily and Ben are scared. They do not want the dog to hurt their big truck or them.

They run to their house and call for help. Their mom and dad come out and see the dog. They are not happy. They tell the dog to go away and leave the big truck alone. The dog is not loyal. It does not listen. It keeps barking and biting.

Lily and Ben are sad. They think they have lost their big truck. But then, they see something. Their cat, Max, is on the road. He is small and orange and has soft fur. He is loyal. He likes Lily and Ben and their big truck. He sees the dog and does not like it. He hisses and scratches and chases the dog away. The dog is scared. It runs away and does not come back.

Lily and Ben are happy. They hug Max and thank him. They get their big truck and bring it to their house. They share it with Max and let him sit on it. They play with their cars and trucks and their cat. They are loyal friends. They have fun and laugh.
<|end|>


