Sara and Ben went to see a show with their mom and dad. They saw many people on the stage. Some people sang songs, some people danced, and some people told jokes. Sara and Ben liked the show very much. They clapped their hands when the people did something good. That is called applaud.

One lady on the stage had a big hat with flowers on it. She sang a song about a rainbow. Sara and Ben liked her song. They wanted to tell her. After the show, they saw the lady outside. She was talking to some other people.

Sara and Ben ran to the lady. They said, "Hello, lady. We liked your song. You have a nice hat." The lady smiled. She said, "Thank you, Sara and Ben. You are very polite. I'm glad you enjoyed the show." She gave them each a flower from her hat.

Sara and Ben were happy. They thanked the lady and gave her a hug. Then they went back to their mom and dad. They told them about the lady and the flowers. Mom and dad said, "You are very lucky. The lady is very kind. You should always be polite to people who make you happy." Sara and Ben nodded. They agreed. They liked being polite.
<|end|>


