<|asst|>
Lily loved cookies. She wanted to eat them all the time. But Mom said no. She said cookies were for after dinner. Lily was sad. She wished she could fly and get the cookies from the jar on the high shelf.

One day, Lily saw a big balloon in the park. It was red and shiny. She wanted to play with it. She asked Mom if she could have it. Mom said yes, but she had to hold it tight. Lily was happy. She took the balloon and ran to the swings.

She saw Ben, her friend, on the slide. He waved at her. She waved back. She wanted to show him her balloon. She let go of the swing and ran to him. But she forgot to hold the balloon. It flew away, up in the sky. Lily was sad. She cried.

"Look, Lily, look!" Ben said. He pointed at the balloon. It was flying towards the cookie jar on the high shelf. Lily looked. She saw the balloon touch the jar. The jar tipped over and fell. Cookies spilled out on the floor. Lily was happy. She smiled.

"Wow, Lily, your balloon can fly and get cookies!" Ben said. "That's great!"

Lily nodded. She agreed. She ran to the cookies and picked one up. She gave one to Ben. They ate the cookies and laughed. They thanked the balloon for the great surprise. They were happy. The end.
<|end|>


