<|asst|>
Lila was a playful girl who liked to run and jump and sing. She had a fairy friend who lived in the garden. Her name was Zee and she had wings and a wand. Zee liked to play with Lila and make magic.

One day, Lila and Zee were playing hide and seek in the garden. Lila counted to ten and then looked for Zee. She checked behind the flowers, under the leaves, and in the birdhouse. But she could not find Zee. She called out, "Zee, where are you? I give up!"

Zee giggled and flew out of a rose. She landed on Lila's shoulder and said, "Here I am! You could not find me because I used my wand to make myself very small. Do you want to see?"

Lila nodded and Zee waved her wand. Lila felt a tickle and then she saw everything change. The grass became like a forest, the ants became like elephants, and the rose became like a castle. Lila gasped and said, "Wow, this is amazing! Can we explore?"

Zee smiled and said, "Of course! Come on, let's go!" She took Lila's hand and flew with her to the rose castle. They saw many wonders and had many adventures. They met a ladybug who was a queen, a spider who was a knight, and a worm who was a dragon. They had fun and laughed a lot.

After a while, Lila said, "Zee, this is very nice, but I miss my mom and dad. Can we go back to normal?"

Zee nodded and said, "Sure, we can. But first, let me show you one more thing." She flew with Lila to the top of the rose and pointed to the sky. Lila saw a rainbow and said, "Oh, how pretty!"

Zee said, "Yes, it is. And do you know what? There is a pot of gold at the end of the rainbow. And it belongs to the fairies. Do you want to see it?"

Lila looked at Zee and said, "Really? Is that true?"

Zee winked and said, "Maybe. Maybe not. What do you think?"

Lila thought for a moment and then she shrugged. She said, "I don't know. But I know I love you and I love playing with you. You are my best fairy friend."

Zee hugged Lila and said, "I love you too and I love playing with you. You are my best human friend."

Then they flew back to the ground and Zee waved her wand. Lila felt a tickle and then she saw everything change back to normal. She ran to her mom and dad and told them about her fairy friend and their magic game. They smiled and hugged her and said, "We are happy you have such a playful imagination. And we are happy you have such a good friend."
<|end|>


