Ben and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to run and jump and slide. They saw a fat man sitting on a bench. He was wearing a big hat and funny clothes. He had a big bag next to him.

"Look at that man!" Ben said to Lily. "He looks like a clown!"

Lily giggled. She wanted to see the man's face. She ran to the bench and pulled his hat off. The man was angry. He had a red nose and a big mouth. He looked like a clown, but he was not happy.

"Hey, give me back my hat!" the man shouted. He grabbed his hat from Lily and slapped her hand. Lily cried. She ran back to Ben.

"That man is mean!" Lily said. "He slapped me!"

Ben was mad. He wanted to help Lily. He picked up a stick and ran to the man. He hit the man's bag with the stick. The bag opened and lots of things fell out. There were balls and balloons and flowers and toys. The man was a clown, but he was not funny.

"Stop that!" the man yelled. He tried to catch his things, but they flew everywhere. The other children in the park saw the mess and laughed. They ran to the man and took his things. They played with the balls and balloons and flowers and toys. The man was sad. He had no hat and no things.

Ben and Lily felt sorry for the man. They gave him back his things and said sorry. The man smiled. He was not mean. He was just tired. He gave Ben and Lily a balloon each and said thank you. He put on his hat and left the park. Ben and Lily waved goodbye. They learned not to judge people by their clothes. They went back to playing. They had fun.
<|end|>


