<|asst|>
Ben and Mia liked to swim in the sea. They had masks and fins to see the fish and the reef. The reef was like a big garden under the water, with many colors and shapes. Ben and Mia liked to play with the fish and look for shells and starfish.

One day, they saw a big boat near the reef. The boat had a big net that it threw into the water. Ben and Mia were curious and swam closer to see what the boat was doing. They saw that the net was catching many fish and some of the reef. They felt sad and angry. They wanted to help the fish and the reef.

They saw a man on the boat who was speaking to another man. They could not hear what he was saying, but they saw that he was pointing at the net and smiling. He looked happy and greedy. Ben and Mia did not like him. They wanted to make him stop.

They had an idea. They swam to the net and started to pull and bite it. They made holes in the net and let some of the fish and the reef out. They hoped that the man would see and get scared. They hoped that he would leave the reef alone.

But the man did not see. He was too busy speaking and laughing. He did not care about the fish and the reef. He only cared about the money he would get. He did not know that there was something else in the water. Something big and fierce. Something that did not like boats and nets. Something that liked to eat fish and men.

It was a shark. A big, fierce shark. It smelled the fish and the blood in the water. It saw the boat and the net. It saw the man who was speaking and laughing. It felt hungry and angry. It wanted to make him stop.

It swam fast and hard. It jumped out of the water and bit the net. It tore the net and let all the fish and the reef out. It saw the man who was speaking and laughing. It bit him too. It made him stop.

Ben and Mia saw the shark. They were scared and amazed. They swam away from the boat and the net. They swam back to the shore. They were safe and happy. They thanked the shark for saving the fish and the reef. They hoped that the man would learn his lesson. They hoped that he would never come back.
<|end|>


