Lila and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they find a big stick on the ground. Lila says, "Look, Tom, a stick! We can use it for many things. We can pretend it is a sword, or a wand, or a fishing rod. We are lucky to find this stick!"

Tom agrees. He says, "Yes, Lila, this is a good stick. Let us play with it. I want to be a knight and you can be a princess. I will protect you from the dragon with my stick-sword." He swings the stick in the air and makes a whoosh sound.

Lila laughs. She says, "OK, Tom, I will be a princess. But I also have a stick-wand. I can do magic with it. I can make the dragon friendly and give him a hug. Watch this!" She waves the stick and makes a ding sound.

Tom and Lila play with the stick for a long time. They have fun and use their imagination. They are happy and lucky to have each other and the stick. The stick is their favorite toy. They do not need anything else.
<|end|>


