Tom and Lily were twins who loved to play in the water. One day, their dad took them to the lake and gave them a big surprise. He had a kayak for them to ride in. A kayak is a long boat that you sit inside and move with a stick that has a paddle on each end.

"Wow, a kayak!" Tom and Lily shouted. They put on their life jackets and helmets and climbed into the kayak with their dad. He showed them how to hold the stick and paddle together. "Are you ready for some fun?" he asked.

"Yes, dad!" they said. They were very jolly and excited. They paddled around the lake, looking at the fish, the ducks, and the trees. They sang songs and made funny noises. They felt the sun on their faces and the breeze in their hair.

Suddenly, they saw a big splash in the water. It was a frog that had jumped out of a lily pad. Tom and Lily laughed and tried to catch the frog. But the frog was too fast and slippery. It jumped back into the water and swam away.

"Bye, frog!" Tom and Lily shouted. They waved their sticks and smiled. They had so much fun in the kayak. They thanked their dad for the surprise and hugged him. They were very happy and tired. They went back to the shore and had a picnic. They ate sandwiches, cookies, and juice. They told their mom about their adventure in the kayak. They said it was the best day ever.
<|end|>


