<|asst|>
Lily loved to bake with her mom. They would mix flour, sugar, eggs and butter in a big bowl. Then they would roll out the dough and cut out shapes with cookie cutters. Lily liked to make stars, hearts and flowers.

"Can I put the sprinkles on?" Lily asked her mom.

"Sure, honey. But not too many, or they will be too sweet," her mom said. She gave Lily a small bowl of colorful sprinkles and a spoon. Lily sprinkled some on each cookie, trying to make them look pretty.

Mom put the cookies on a tray and slid them into the oven. She set the timer and said, "Now we have to wait for them to bake. Do you want to read a book while we wait?"

Lily nodded and picked up her favorite book. It was about a princess who lived in a castle. Mom read the book to Lily and they looked at the pictures. Lily imagined she was the princess and wore a beautiful dress.

Ding! The timer went off and mom said, "The cookies are ready! Let's take them out and let them cool." She put on oven mitts and took out the tray. The cookies smelled yummy and looked golden. Lily clapped her hands and said, "They are so impressive, mom!"

Mom smiled and said, "Thank you, sweetie. You did a great job. Let's put them on the shelf to cool down. Then we can have some with milk."

Lily helped mom put the cookies on the shelf. She counted them and said, "We have twelve cookies. Can we share them with dad and grandma?"

"Of course, we can. They will love them too. You are such a kind and generous girl, Lily," mom said. She hugged Lily and said, "I love you, my little baker."

"I love you too, mom," Lily said. She felt happy and proud. She couldn't wait to taste the cookies and share them with her family.
<|end|>


