Tom and Lily went to the park with Mom. They saw a big swing and ran to it. Tom got on the swing first and Lily pushed him. Tom liked to go high and feel the wind on his face.

"Look, Lily, I can touch the sky!" Tom said.

Lily wanted to swing too, so she asked Tom to share. Tom said yes and got off the swing. Lily got on the swing and Tom pushed her. Lily liked to go fast and feel the breeze on her hair.

"Look, Tom, I can fly!" Lily said.

Then they saw a yellow bug on the grass. It had wings and spots and a long nose. They got off the swing and went to see the bug. The bug was busy sucking nectar from a flower. It did not see Tom and Lily.

"Wow, what is that?" Tom asked.

"I think it is a bee," Lily said.

They wanted to touch the bee, but Mom stopped them. She said the bee could sting them and hurt them. She said the bee was nice and helped the flowers grow. She said they should watch the bee from a distance and not bother it.

"Okay, Mom," Tom and Lily said.

They watched the bee for a while and then went back to the swing. They took turns swinging and laughing. They had fun at the park with Mom and the yellow bug.
<|end|>


