Lily liked to stare at the big tree in her yard. It had many green leaves and brown branches. Sometimes she saw birds and squirrels on the tree. She wanted to climb the tree and touch the sky.

One day, Lily asked her mom if she could climb the tree. Her mom said no, it was too high and dangerous. Lily was sad, but she obeyed her mom. She went to play with her ball instead.

But the next day, when her mom was busy in the kitchen, Lily saw the tree again. It looked so fun and pretty. She forgot what her mom said. She ran to the tree and tried to grab a branch. She was not strong enough. She fell down and hurt her knee. She cried very loud.

Her mom heard her cry and came outside. She saw Lily on the ground and the tree above her. She was scared and angry. She hugged Lily and checked her knee. It was bleeding a little, but not too bad. She put a band-aid on it and took Lily inside.

She told Lily that she was very naughty and that she should never climb the tree again. She said that the tree was not a toy and that she could have been hurt more. Lily felt sorry and said she was sorry. She learned her lesson. She did not stare at the tree anymore. She played with her ball and her mom. She was happy and safe.
<|end|>


