Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big bin. The bin is full of things. They want to look inside.

"Can we see what is in the bin?" Tom asks Mia.

"OK, but we have to be careful. Maybe there are bad things in the bin," Mia says.

They go to the bin and lift the lid. They see many things. They see cans, bottles, papers, and boxes. They also see something shiny. It is a necklace. The necklace has many colors. It is amazing.

"Wow, look at this!" Tom says. He takes the necklace out of the bin. He puts it around his neck. He feels happy.

"That is so pretty! Where did it come from?" Mia says. She wants to touch the necklace too.

"I don't know. Maybe someone threw it away. Maybe it is magic," Tom says.

They hear a loud noise. It is a truck. The truck is coming to the bin. It is going to take the things away.

"Oh no, we have to go!" Mia says. She is scared.

"Wait, I want to keep the necklace!" Tom says. He likes the necklace.

"No, you can't! It is not yours! It is from the bin!" Mia says. She pulls Tom away from the bin.

They run to the slide. They hide behind the slide. They watch the truck. The truck lifts the bin. The bin is empty. The necklace is gone.

Tom feels sad. He liked the necklace. He wanted to keep it.

Mia feels sorry. She hugs Tom. She says, "Don't be sad, Tom. Maybe the necklace will come back. Maybe it will find another bin. Maybe it will find another kid. Maybe it will make them happy too."

Tom smiles. He says, "Maybe you are right, Mia. Maybe the necklace is magic. Maybe it will happen again."

They hold hands. They go to the swings. They have fun. They are friends.
<|end|>


