<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing with blocks. They wanted to build a big tower. They had many blocks of different colors and shapes. They took turns to put one block on top of another.

"Look, Lily, I have a red block. It is a square. Where should I put it?" Ben asked.

"Put it here, Ben. It will make the tower stronger. I have a blue block. It is a circle. I will put it on top of your red block." Lily said.

They kept building the tower higher and higher. They were happy and proud of their work. They counted the blocks they used. They knew some numbers, like one, two, three, four, and five.

"Ben, how many blocks do we have?" Lily asked.

"I don't know, Lily. I can't count more than five. Let's ask Mom. She knows all the numbers." Ben said.

They ran to the kitchen, where Mom was making cookies. They asked her to come and see their tower. They wanted her to tell them how many blocks they used.

"Wow, Lily and Ben, you made a very big tower. It is very nice. You used a lot of blocks. Let me see. You used one, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten, eleven, twelve, thirteen, fourteen, fifteen, sixteen, seventeen, eighteen, nineteen, twenty blocks. That is a big number." Mom said.

Lily and Ben were confused. They did not understand what Mom said. They did not know what twenty meant. They thought it was a funny word. They laughed and repeated it.

"Twenty, twenty, twenty. Ha ha ha." They said.

They ran back to their tower. They wanted to play some more. They wanted to make the tower even bigger. They looked for more blocks. They saw a box in the corner. It had a label that said "Supply". They did not know what that meant. They thought it was another funny word. They opened the box. It had more blocks inside. They were happy. They took some blocks and added them to their tower.

But the box did not have blocks for playing. It had blocks for building. They were heavy and hard. They were not meant for children. They were meant for Dad. He was a builder. He used them to make houses and walls. He left them in the corner by mistake. He forgot to put them away.

When Lily and Ben put the heavy blocks on their tower, the tower became unstable. It could not hold the weight. It started to wobble and shake. It fell down with a loud crash. It broke into pieces. It hurt Lily and Ben. They cried and screamed. They had cuts and bruises. They were scared and sad.

Mom heard the noise. She ran to the living room. She saw the mess and the children. She was shocked and angry. She called Dad. He came home quickly. He saw what happened. He was sorry and worried. He took Lily and Ben to the hospital. They had to get stitches and bandages. They had to stay in bed for a long time. They could not play with blocks anymore.

The moral of the story is: Do not play with things you do not know. They can be dangerous and hurt you. Always ask your parents before you use something new. They can tell you what it is and how to use it safely. They can supply you with the right toys and the right numbers. They can help you have fun and learn. They love you and want you to be happy and healthy.
<|end|>


