<|asst|>
Lily was a little girl who loved to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna, who had long hair and a pink dress. Lily liked to pretend that Anna was her sister and they had many adventures together.

One night, Lily had a bad dream. She dreamed that a big monster came and took Anna away from her. Lily was very scared and sad. She wanted to wake up, but she could not. She tried to call for her mom and dad, but they did not hear her.

Then, Lily heard a voice. It was Anna! Anna said, "Don't be afraid, Lily. I am here with you. The monster can't hurt us. We are brave and strong. We can manage to escape." Lily felt a little better. She asked, "How can we escape, Anna?"

Anna said, "We have to use our imagination. Imagine that we have wings and we can fly. Imagine that the monster is a silly clown and we can laugh at him. Imagine that we are in a beautiful garden and we can smell the flowers. Imagine that we are happy and safe."

Lily did what Anna said. She imagined that they had wings and they flew away from the monster. She imagined that the monster was a silly clown and she laughed at him. She imagined that they were in a beautiful garden and she smelled the flowers. She imagined that they were happy and safe.

Soon, Lily felt a warm hand on her shoulder. It was her mom. She said, "Lily, wake up. It's morning. You had a bad dream, but it's over now. I'm here with you." Lily opened her eyes and saw her mom smiling at her. She also saw Anna on her pillow. She hugged Anna and said, "Thank you, Anna. You are incredible. You helped me escape from the bad dream."

Her mom said, "You are incredible, too, Lily. You managed to use your imagination and overcome your fear. I'm proud of you. Now, let's go and have some breakfast. How about some pancakes and strawberries?" Lily nodded and smiled. She was happy. She had her mom and her doll. She had no more bad dreams. She had a good day.
<|end|>


