Tom and Lily love to play games. They have many games in their room. Some games are easy, some games are hard. They like to try different games and see who can win.

One day, they find a new game in their closet. It is a puzzle game. It has many pieces that make a picture. The picture is of a farm with animals and plants. Tom and Lily want to play the puzzle game.

They open the box and spread the pieces on the floor. They look at the picture on the box and try to find the pieces that match. They work together and help each other. They have fun and talk and laugh.

Soon, they finish the puzzle. They see the whole picture on the floor. It is very pretty and colorful. They are happy and proud. They hug and say, "We did it! We win!"

They show their mom and dad the puzzle. Mom and dad are also happy and proud. They say, "You did a great job! You are very smart and creative!" They take a picture of Tom and Lily and the puzzle.

Tom and Lily love their new game. They say, "This is our favorite game! Can we play it again?" Mom and dad say, "Yes, you can. The game is available anytime you want. But first, let's have some snacks. You must be hungry after working so hard." Tom and Lily nod and smile. They follow mom and dad to the kitchen. They are hungry and thirsty. They love snacks. They love their family. They love their game. They are very happy.
