Tom and Mia were happy to move to a new house. They had many boxes with their toys and books. They wanted to unpack them and play in their new room.

Tom found a big magnet in one of the boxes. He liked to make it stick to things. He saw a shiny thing on the wall. It was a picture of their family. Tom thought it was metal. He tried to stick the magnet to it.

But the picture was not metal. It was glass. The magnet did not stick. It made the picture fall and break. Tom heard a loud noise. He saw many pieces of glass on the floor. He was scared and sad.

Mia heard the noise too. She came to see what happened. She saw the broken picture and the magnet. She was angry and sad. She said to Tom, "You are bad! You broke our picture! Mom and Dad will be mad!"

Tom felt ashamed. He did not mean to break the picture. He said to Mia, "I am sorry. I did not know it was glass. I wanted to play with the magnet. Please don't be mad at me."

Mia saw that Tom was sorry. She felt sorry too. She said to Tom, "It's okay. I know you did not mean it. But we have to tell Mom and Dad. Maybe they can fix it. And we have to be careful with the magnet. It can be dangerous."

Tom and Mia hugged each other. They picked up the pieces of glass and the magnet. They went to find Mom and Dad. They told them what happened. Mom and Dad were not mad. They were glad that Tom and Mia were not hurt. They said they would try to fix the picture. They said they loved them. They said they could unpack their boxes and play in their new room. But they had to be careful with the magnet and other things. Tom and Mia said they would. They were happy to have a new house and a new room. And they were happy to have each other.
<|end|>


