Tom and Lily are friends. They like to play music together. Tom has a drum and Lily has a trumpet. They make loud sounds with their instruments.

One day, they go to the park with their moms. They see a big band playing music on a stage. The band has many trumpets, drums, guitars, and other instruments. Tom and Lily are excited. They want to watch and listen.

They sit on the grass with their moms and clap their hands. The band plays happy songs. Tom and Lily try to copy the sounds with their drum and trumpet. They have fun.

"Look, Lily, they have a trumpet like yours!" Tom says.

"Yes, Tom, and they have a drum like yours!" Lily says.

"Do you think we can play with them?" Tom asks.

"Maybe, if we ask nicely," Lily says.

They go to the band leader and say hello. They show him their drum and trumpet. They ask if they can play with the band.

The band leader smiles. He says they are very brave and healthy. He says they can play with the band for one song. He gives them a signal when to start and stop.

Tom and Lily are happy. They play their drum and trumpet with the band. They make loud and happy sounds. The people in the park clap and cheer. Tom and Lily feel proud. They thank the band leader and go back to their moms.

Their moms hug them and say they did a great job. They say they are proud of them. They say they are very talented and healthy. They give them a snack and a drink. Tom and Lily share their snack and drink. They are happy. They are friends. They like to play music together.
<|end|>


