Ben and Lily went to camp with Mom and Dad. They slept in a big tent and ate hot dogs and marshmallows. They liked to play with the other kids and sing songs by the fire.

One night, Ben saw something in the sky. It was bright and shiny and moved very fast. He pointed at it and said, "Look, Lily, a star!"

Lily looked up and saw it too. She said, "Wow, Ben, it's so pretty! What is it?"

Ben said, "I don't know, Lily. Maybe it's a plane or a rocket or a fairy."

Lily said, "Maybe it's a wish star. Do you have a wish, Ben?"

Ben thought for a moment and said, "Yes, Lily, I do. I wish we could stay at camp forever. It's so much fun!"

Lily smiled and said, "Me too, Ben, me too. Let's make a wish together."

They closed their eyes and wished hard. Then they opened them and saw the star was gone. They hugged each other and said, "Maybe our wish will come true."

They went back to the tent and snuggled with Mom and Dad. They dreamed of camp and stars and wishes. They were very happy.
<|end|>


