<|asst|>
Tom and Sue were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had many toys, but their favorite was a big bear that they called Ted. Ted was soft and cuddly, and he had a red bow on his neck. Tom and Sue loved Ted very much, and they always shared him.

One day, their mom gave them a treat. She baked some cookies and put them on a plate. She said, "You can have one cookie each, but only after you finish your lunch. And be nice to each other and to Ted." Then she went to do some work.

Tom and Sue ate their lunch quickly, and then they ran to the plate of cookies. They both wanted the biggest cookie, and they started to fight. They pulled and pushed and shouted, and they did not listen to their mom. They also did not see that Ted was on the floor, near the plate.

As they fought, they stepped on Ted and tore his ear. Ted's stuffing came out, and he looked very sad. Tom and Sue did not notice, and they kept fighting. They tore the biggest cookie in half, and they each grabbed a piece. But as they did, they knocked over the plate, and the rest of the cookies fell on the floor.

Their mom heard the noise and came to see what happened. She saw the mess, and she saw Ted. She was very angry and sad. She said, "Look what you did! You were greedy and mean, and you hurt Ted. He was your best friend, and you did not care. Now you have no cookies and no Ted. You should be sorry and learn to share."

Tom and Sue felt very bad. They looked at Ted, and they cried. They wished they had been nice to each other and to Ted. They learned that being greedy and mean is not a good way to get a treat. They learned that sharing and caring is much better. But it was too late. They had a bad ending.
<|end|>


