Tom was a restless boy. He did not like to sit still or be quiet. He liked to run and jump and shout and play. He hated when his mom said it was time for a nap. He hated naps more than anything.

One day, Tom's mom had to go to the store. She asked Tom's old grandma to watch him. Tom did not like his old grandma. She was slow and boring and always told him to be good. She said he had to take a nap with her on the couch. Tom hated that idea.

He tried to sneak away, but his old grandma saw him. She grabbed his hand and pulled him to the couch. She said naps were good for him and her. She said they would feel better after a nap. Tom hated that lie.

He lay down on the couch, but he did not close his eyes. He waited for his old grandma to fall asleep. Then he got up and ran to his room. He found his toys and started to play. He made a lot of noise. He was happy.

But his old grandma heard him. She woke up and walked to his room. She was angry. She said he was a bad boy. She said he had to go back to the couch. She said he had to stay there until his mom came back. Tom hated that punishment.

He cried and kicked and screamed. He did not want to nap. He did not want to be with his old grandma. He wanted to play. He wanted his mom. He hated this day.
<|end|>


