Tom and Anna were friends who liked to play outside. One day, they went to the park with their moms. They saw a big pond with ducks and geese. The water was icy and shiny.

"Look, Anna, the ducks are swimming in the icy water. They are brave and strong," Tom said.

"I like the geese better. They have long necks and make funny noises. They are smart and funny," Anna said.

They admired the ducks and geese for a while. Then they heard their moms calling them.

"Tom, Anna, it's time for lunch. Come here, we have sandwiches and juice for you," their moms said.

Tom and Anna ran to their moms. They were hungry and happy. They ate their lunch on a bench near the pond. They shared their sandwiches and juice. They thanked their moms for the yummy lunch.

"Can we play some more after lunch, mom?" Tom asked.

"Sure, honey, but you have to wear your hats and gloves. It's very cold today," his mom said.

"OK, mom. We will be careful and warm," Anna said.

They finished their lunch and put their hats and gloves on. Then they went back to the pond. They played with the ducks and geese. They threw some bread crumbs for them. They had a lot of fun. They liked the icy pond and the animals. They were good friends.
<|end|>


