Lily and Max were twins who liked to play outside. They had a big yard with a swing, a slide and a sandbox. One day, they saw a new truck in front of their house. It was a dessert truck, with a picture of a big ice cream cone on the side.

"Look, Max, ice cream!" Lily said, pointing to the truck.

"Yum, yum, let's go get some!" Max said, grabbing Lily's hand.

They ran to the truck, but they forgot to ask their mom first. They waited in line with other kids, and when it was their turn, they saw a nice lady with a big smile.

"Hello, what can I get you?" the lady asked.

"I want chocolate ice cream, please," Lily said.

"I want vanilla ice cream, please," Max said.

The lady nodded and scooped some ice cream into two cones. She handed them to Lily and Max, who thanked her politely.

"Enjoy your dessert, and have a nice day," the lady said.

Lily and Max licked their ice cream happily, but then they heard their mom calling them.

"Lily, Max, where are you?" their mom said, looking worried.

They turned around and saw their mom walking towards them. They realized they had been naughty and ran away without telling her.

"Mom, we're sorry, we saw the dessert truck and we wanted ice cream," Lily said.

"We didn't mean to make you worry, we were polite to the lady," Max said.

Their mom hugged them and said, "I'm glad you're safe, and I'm proud of you for being polite, but you have to ask me before you run off. That's the rule, okay?"

Lily and Max nodded and said, "Okay, mom, we're sorry."

Their mom smiled and said, "It's okay, I forgive you. But next time, please listen to me. Now, let's go home and wash your faces. You have ice cream all over them."

Lily and Max giggled and followed their mom home. They learned their lesson and never ran away again. They still liked dessert, but they always asked their mom first.
<|end|>


