Sam and Jen were twins who liked to play in the yard. They had a big box of junk that they used to make things. They made cars, robots, houses, and more. They had fun with their junk.

One day, a big storm came and blew away their junk. The wind was very strong and loud. Sam and Jen were scared and ran inside. They looked out the window and saw their junk flying in the air. They cried and cried.

They asked their mom if they could get their junk back. Their mom said no, the storm was too dangerous. She said they had to stay inside and be safe. She said they could pray for the storm to stop and for their junk to land somewhere nice.

Sam and Jen did not like that. They wanted their junk now. They did not want to pray. They thought praying was boring and silly. They were angry and bitter. They said mean things to their mom and to each other.

The storm did not stop for a long time. Sam and Jen did not stop fighting for a long time. Their mom was sad and tired. She wished they would be nice and pray. But they did not. They lost their junk and their joy. The end.
<|end|>


