Bunny and Dog were friends. They liked to play in the park. One day, they saw a big pond with ducks and fish. Bunny wanted to hop on the water and see the fish. Dog wanted to chase the ducks and bark.

"Come on, Dog, let's hop on the water!" said Bunny.

"No, Bunny, that is not a good idea. The water is deep and wet. You will sink and get cold. You have to be careful," said Dog.

But Bunny did not listen. He hopped on the water and splashed. He felt the water go into his nose and mouth. He was scared and cold. He cried for help.

Dog heard Bunny cry. He ran to the pond and saw Bunny sinking. He was worried and brave. He used his heel to push the water and swim. He reached Bunny and grabbed his ear. He pulled him to the shore and licked his face.

"Bunny, are you okay?" asked Dog.

"Yes, Dog, I am okay. Thank you for saving me. You are a good friend. I am sorry I did not listen to you. I was silly and not careful. I will not hop on the water again," said Bunny.

Dog and Bunny hugged. They learned a lesson. They went home and dried off. They were happy and safe.
<|end|>


