Lily and Sam were friends. They liked to play with toys. One day, Lily saw a new toy car in Sam's room. She wanted to play with it.

"Can I borrow your car?" Lily asked Sam.

"OK, but only for a little while. It is my favorite car. My mom gave it to me for my birthday." Sam said.

Lily took the car and ran to the living room. She made the car zoom and beep on the floor. She had fun with the car.

Sam waited for Lily to bring back his car. He waited and waited. He felt upset. He wanted his car back.

He went to the living room and saw Lily still playing with his car. He was angry.

"Lily, give me back my car! You borrowed it for too long!" Sam shouted.

"No, I like it. It is my car now. Go away!" Lily shouted back.

They started to fight over the car. They pulled and pushed. They yelled and cried.

Their moms heard the noise and came to see what was wrong. They saw Lily and Sam fighting over the car.

"What is going on here?" Lily's mom asked.

"Lily borrowed my car and won't give it back. It is my car!" Sam said.

"Lily, is that true? Did you borrow Sam's car?" Lily's mom asked.

"Yes, but I want to keep it. It is a nice car." Lily said.

"Lily, that is not nice. You can't keep something that is not yours. You have to give it back to Sam. He let you borrow it, but you have to respect his name and his things." Lily's mom said.

Lily felt sorry. She realized she was wrong. She gave the car back to Sam.

"I'm sorry, Sam. I was selfish. Can we still be friends?" Lily said.

Sam felt happy. He got his car back. He forgave Lily.

"It's OK, Lily. I'm sorry I yelled at you. We can still be friends. Do you want to play with my car together?" Sam said.

Lily nodded. She smiled. They played with the car together. They shared and took turns. They had fun.

Their moms were proud. They hugged their kids.

"Good job, Lily and Sam. You learned how to borrow and return things. You also learned how to say sorry and forgive. You are good friends." Their moms said.
<|end|>


