Anna and Ben were playing in the yard. They liked to pretend they were pirates and sail on a big ship. They used a barrel as their ship and a stick as their flag.

"Ahoy, matey!" Ben said. "We are the best pirates in the world!"

"Yes, we are!" Anna said. "We can find treasure and have fun!"

They sailed around the yard, looking for adventure. But then they saw Tom, the mean boy from next door. He was holding a water gun and a bucket.

"Hey, you two!" Tom shouted. "This is my yard, not yours! Get off my barrel!"

He ran towards them, spraying water everywhere. Anna and Ben were scared. They did not like Tom. He was always rude and nasty.

"Go away, Tom!" Anna said. "This is our ship, not your barrel!"

"No, it's not!" Tom said. "It's mine, and I'll take it!"

He grabbed the barrel and tried to pull it away. Anna and Ben held on tight. They did not want to lose their ship.

"Stop it, Tom!" Ben said. "You're being mean!"

"I don't care!" Tom said. "I'm bigger and stronger than you!"

They tugged and pulled, but no one could win. The barrel rolled and bounced, making a loud noise. They were making a mess of the yard.

"Hey, what's going on here?" a voice said.

They looked up and saw Mom. She was holding a basket of laundry. She looked angry.

"Mom!" Anna and Ben cried. "Tom is trying to take our ship!"

"Tom!" Mom said. "Is that true?"

Tom dropped the barrel and the water gun. He looked guilty.

"Um, yes, Mom," he said. "But they started it!"

Mom shook her head. She was not happy.

"Tom, you know better than that," she said. "You can't just take things that don't belong to you. And you can't be mean to other kids. That's not nice."

She turned to Anna and Ben.

"And you two, you can't play in the yard without asking me first," she said. "And you can't make so much noise. You're disturbing the neighbors."

She sighed.

"Come on, all of you," she said. "Let's go inside and have a snack. Maybe you can play nicely together after that."

She took them by the hand and led them to the house. The barrel and the stick stayed in the yard.

Anna and Ben were sad. They liked their ship. They liked to dream of being pirates. They wished Tom was kind and friendly.

Maybe one day, they thought, he would be.
<|end|>


