<|asst|>
Tom and Lily were twins who liked to play with water. They had a big spray bottle that they filled with water and took outside. They sprayed water on the flowers, the grass, the bugs and each other. They laughed and had fun.

One day, they saw a big truck parked outside their house. It had a sign that said "Pest Control". They did not know what that meant, but they saw a man wearing a mask and a suit. He had a big hose that he used to spray something on the house. They thought he was playing with water too.

They ran to the truck and grabbed the hose. They turned it on and sprayed the man, the truck, the house and themselves. They thought it was funny, but the man did not. He shouted and tried to stop them, but it was too late.

The spray was not water. It was poison. It was for killing bugs, not for playing. It made the man, the truck, the house and the twins very sick. They started to cough and itch and burn. They felt bad and scared.

Their family came outside and saw what happened. They were angry and sad. They called for help, but it was too late. The poison was too strong. The twins and the man died. The house and the truck were ruined. The family lost everything.

The spray was not a toy. It was dangerous. Playing with it was a big mistake. It was not fun. It was bad. The twins did not know, but they should have asked. They should have listened. They should have been careful. They learned too late that some things are not for playing. Some things are important.
<|end|>


