<|asst|>
Ben likes to write. He has a big book and a red pen. He writes many things in his book. He writes his name, his age, his friends, his toys, his dreams. He writes every day.

One day, Ben's mom says, "Ben, it is time to go to bed. You have to sleep. You have a big day tomorrow."

Ben says, "But mom, I want to write more. I have many things to write. Please, let me write a little more."

Mom says, "No, Ben, you have to sleep. You are very tired. You have been writing all day. Writing is good, but sleeping is good too. You need to rest your eyes and your brain. If you don't sleep, you will be grumpy and sick tomorrow."

Ben says, "But mom, writing is fun. Writing is serious. I want to be a writer when I grow up. I want to write stories and books and letters. I want to write for you and dad and everyone."

Mom says, "I know, Ben, and I am proud of you. You are a good writer. But you can write more tomorrow. You can write after breakfast, after school, after dinner. You can write anytime you want. But now, you have to sleep. Come on, let me tuck you in."

Mom takes Ben's book and pen and puts them on his desk. She carries Ben to his bed and kisses him good night. She turns off the light and says, "Sleep well, Ben. I love you."

Ben says, "I love you too, mom. Good night."

Ben closes his eyes and falls asleep. He dreams of writing.
<|end|>


