Tom and Lily were twins who liked to play with their toys. One day, they found a big box of old clothes and buttons and ribbons in the attic. They decided to make some dolls and animals with them.

They took some cloth and stuffing and scissors and glue and started to work. Tom made a bear and Lily made a cat. They were very happy with their creations. But they needed something to make the eyes and noses.

Tom saw a shiny jar of needles on a shelf. He thought they would be perfect for the eyes and noses. He reached for the jar and opened it.

"Tom, don't touch those!" Lily said. "They are sharp and can hurt you. Mama said we should never play with needles. They are not for children."

Tom did not listen to Lily. He thought he knew better. He said, "Don't be fearful, Lily. I can choose the right needles and be careful. Look, these ones are small and round and pretty. They will make our dolls and animals look real."

He took some needles and stuck them into his bear's face. He smiled and showed it to Lily.

Lily did not like Tom's bear. She thought it looked scary and mean. She said, "Tom, your bear is not nice. It has needles for eyes and nose. They can poke you and make you bleed. You should take them out and use something else."

Tom did not listen to Lily. He thought his bear was the best. He said, "Don't be silly, Lily. My bear is fine. It has needles for eyes and nose. They make it look strong and brave. You should do the same for your cat."

He took some more needles and tried to put them into Lily's cat's face. Lily did not want Tom to touch her cat. She said, "No, Tom, stop! You are ruining my cat. I don't want needles for eyes and nose. I want buttons and ribbons. They are soft and cute. They are for children."

She pulled her cat away from Tom and ran to the other side of the room. Tom was angry and followed her. He said, "Give me your cat, Lily. I will make it better. You are wrong and I am right. You should do what I say."

He grabbed her cat and tried to take it from her. Lily held on tight and screamed. They fought and tugged and pulled. The needles fell out of Tom's bear and scattered on the floor. They did not see them. They stepped on them and felt a sharp pain. They cried and dropped their dolls and animals. They looked at their feet and saw blood. They were hurt and scared.

Mama heard their cries and came to the attic. She saw what happened and was shocked and angry. She said, "What have you done, Tom and Lily? You played with needles and hurt yourselves and your dolls and animals. You did not listen to me or to each other. You were foolish and stubborn and rude. You should be sorry and ashamed."

She took them to the bathroom and cleaned their wounds and put bandages on them. She took their dolls and animals and threw them in the trash. She said, "You can't play with these anymore. They are dangerous and ugly. You need to learn your lesson and be more careful and kind. You need to choose wisely and respect each other. You need to say sorry and hug each other."

Tom and Lily felt bad and sorry. They realized they made a big mistake. They said sorry to Mama and to each other. They hugged each other and promised to be more careful and kind. They learned their lesson and never played with needles again.
<|end|>


