Lily and Ben were waiting for their dad to come home. They were hungry and wanted to eat dinner. Mom had cooked some pasta and cheese, their favorite food.

"Where is dad?" Lily asked. She looked out the window and saw the sun going down.

"He will be here soon," Mom said. "He had to work late today. But he called me and said he was on his way."

Lily and Ben nodded. They hoped dad would arrive before it was dark. They liked to hug him and tell him about their day.

They heard a car stop outside. They ran to the door and opened it. It was dad!

"Dad, dad, you're here!" they shouted. They hugged him and kissed him.

"Hello, my loves," dad said. He smiled and carried them inside. "I'm sorry I'm late. I had a lot of work to do. But I brought you something."

He reached into his pocket and pulled out two shiny forks. They had funny shapes on the handles. One had a star and the other had a heart.

"These are for you," dad said. He gave Lily the star fork and Ben the heart fork. "They are special forks. They make your food taste better."

Lily and Ben looked at their forks. They were not ordinary forks. They were magic forks!

"Wow, thank you, dad!" they said. They ran to the table and sat down. They used their forks to eat their pasta and cheese. It was delicious!

Mom and dad joined them and they all ate together. They talked and laughed and had a good time. Lily and Ben were happy. They loved their dad and their forks. They were a happy family.
<|end|>


