Tom and Lily liked to play pirates in the garden. They had a big cardboard box that they pretended was a ship. They wore hats and eye patches and said "Arrr!" a lot.

One day, they saw an elderly man walking by the fence. He had a long beard and a wooden leg. He looked like a real pirate! Tom and Lily waved to him and said "Hello, pirate!"

The man smiled and came closer. He said "Hello, little pirates. I'm Captain Jim. I used to sail the seas and look for treasure. Do you want to hear some of my stories?"

Tom and Lily nodded eagerly. They loved stories. They invited Captain Jim to join them in their ship. They made room for him and gave him a hat and an eye patch.

Captain Jim thanked them and offered them some candy from his pocket. He said "This is pirate candy. It's very sweet and chewy. I got it from a faraway island. Do you want some?"

Tom and Lily said "Yes, please!" They took the candy and tasted it. It was delicious. They said "Thank you, pirate!"

Captain Jim smiled and said "You're welcome, little pirates. Now, let me tell you about the time I met a giant squid..."
