Tom and Mia like to play with water in the garden. They have a hose that makes water come out. They can spray the water on the plants, on the grass, and on each other. They laugh and have fun.

One day, the hose breaks. It has a big hole and the water goes everywhere. Tom and Mia are sad. They cannot play with the hose anymore.

"Can we get a new hose, Mom?" Tom asks.

"Maybe, but not today. We have to go to the store and find one. Why don't you play with something else?" Mom says.

Tom and Mia look around the garden. They see a bucket, a ball, and a shovel. They try to play with them, but they are not as fun as the hose.

Then, Mia has an idea. She runs to the kitchen and comes back with a plastic bottle. She fills it with water from the tap. She makes a small hole in the cap with the shovel.

"Look, Tom! I made a new hose!" Mia says. She squeezes the bottle and water comes out of the hole.

"Wow, that's amazing!" Tom says. He takes another bottle and does the same thing. They have two new hoses.

They run to the garden and spray the water on the plants, on the grass, and on each other. They laugh and have fun.

They replace the old hose with the new hoses. They are happy. Mom smiles and watches them. She thinks they are very clever.
<|end|>


