Ben and Lily were playing in the park. They liked to run, jump and slide. They saw a big hill with many trees. They wanted to see what was on the other side.

"Let's go find out!" said Ben.

"OK, but be careful!" said Lily.

They climbed the hill and ran through the trees. They saw many birds, flowers and bugs. They also saw a small house. It was old and dirty. It had a broken door and a hole in the roof.

"Who lives here?" asked Lily.

"I don't know. Maybe no one," said Ben.

They went closer to the house. They heard a noise. It was a soft and sad noise. They looked inside the house. They saw a dog. It was thin and dirty. It had no collar and no food. It looked at them with big and sad eyes.

"Hello, dog," said Ben.

"Are you OK?" asked Lily.

The dog wagged its tail a little. It was happy to see them. But it was also hungry and cold. It needed help.

"Ben, this dog is poor. It has no home and no family. It needs us," said Lily.

"You're right, Lily. We should help it. Maybe we can take it to our home. Maybe mom and dad will let us keep it," said Ben.

They went inside the house. They petted the dog and gave it some water. They found a blanket and wrapped it around the dog. They lifted the dog and carried it out of the house.

"Come on, dog. We will find you a new home. We will be your new family," said Ben.

The dog licked their faces. It was grateful and happy. It had found new friends. Ben and Lily smiled. They had found a new friend too. They walked down the hill with the dog. They hoped mom and dad would say yes. They wanted to give the dog a new turn in life.
<|end|>


