Tim and Sue were twins. They liked to play with their toys. They had a big yellow taxi that they could drive around the house. They pretended to be taxi drivers and pick up people.

One day, they saw their mom and dad getting ready to go out. They had a big bag and nice clothes. They said they were going to a party. Tim and Sue wanted to go too, but mom and dad said no. They said they were too little and they had to stay with grandma.

Tim and Sue were sad. They did not like grandma. She was old and boring. She always told them to eat healthy food and go to bed early. They wanted to have fun and eat candy and stay up late.

They had an idea. They decided to sneak out of the house and drive the taxi to the party. They put on their hats and coats and grabbed the keys. They opened the door and ran to the garage. They got in the taxi and started the engine. They were very happy.

They drove out of the garage and onto the street. They did not know how to drive well. They did not look at the lights or the signs or the other cars. They just drove fast and loud. They did not see the big truck coming from the other side. The truck was very big and very fast. It hit the taxi and made a loud noise. The taxi was broken and Tim and Sue were hurt. They cried and cried.

The truck driver got out and called for help. He saw Tim and Sue and felt sorry for them. He tried to help them, but they were too hurt. The ambulance came and took them to the hospital. Mom and dad came too. They were very sad and very angry. They hugged Tim and Sue and said they loved them, but they also said they were very naughty and very stupid. They said they could have died. They said they would never let them play with the taxi again. Tim and Sue were sorry, but it was too late. They had to stay in the hospital for a long time and they missed the party. They learned a hard lesson. They wished they had listened to mom and dad and stayed with grandma.
<|end|>


