"Go away, dog!" Ben says. He tries to scare the dog. But the dog does not listen. It jumps on Sara. It bites her dress. It tears her dress. It makes a hole.

Sara screams. She is sad. She cries. Her dress is ruined. She does not like the dog.

"Help, help!" Sara and Ben shout. They want someone to help them. But no one comes. The dog runs away. It is happy. It has a piece of dress in its mouth.

Sara and Ben are alone. They are sad. They do not play anymore. They go home. Sara's mom is angry. She sees Sara's dress. She is not happy.

"Why did you do this, Sara?" Sara's mom says. "Your dress was new. It was expensive. You are naughty."

Sara does not know what to say. She is sorry. She is sad. She hugs Ben. Ben hugs her back. They are friends. But they are not happy. The end.
