Anna and Ben were playing in the park with their mom. They saw a big truck with a sign that said "Fancy Toilets". They were curious and wanted to see what was inside.

"Mom, can we go and look at the fancy toilets?" Anna asked.

"Sure, but be careful and don't touch anything," mom said.

Anna and Ben ran to the truck and opened the door. They saw many toilets that looked different from the ones at home. Some were pink, some were blue, some had flowers, some had stars. They also saw a big mirror, a sink, and a soap dispenser.

"Wow, these are fancy toilets!" Ben said.

"Look, this one has a button!" Anna said, pointing to a toilet with a small panel next to it.

She pressed the button and suddenly, a jet of water sprayed out of the toilet and hit her in the face.

"Ahh! It's wet! It's wet!" Anna screamed.

Ben laughed and said, "That's not a button, that's a bidet! It's for washing your bottom!"

Anna was not happy. She ran to the sink and tried to dry her face with a paper towel. But the paper towel was stuck in the dispenser.

"Help! I can't get the paper towel out!" Anna cried.

Mom heard the noise and came to the truck. She saw Anna and Ben in a mess.

"What happened here?" mom asked.

"We were examining the fancy toilets, but they are too fancy for us!" Anna said.

Mom smiled and said, "I see. Well, let's go and find a normal toilet for you to use. And next time, don't press any buttons you don't know!"

Anna and Ben nodded and followed mom out of the truck. They decided that fancy toilets were not for them. They liked their simple toilets at home better.
