Lily and Max were playing in the park with their toy soldiers. They liked to pretend they were in a big army and march around the grass. They made loud noises with their mouths and waved their arms.

"Look, Max, a yacht!" Lily said, pointing to the pond. She saw a big white boat with a sail and a flag. It looked very pretty and shiny.

"Wow, can we go see it?" Max asked, dropping his toy soldier. He loved boats and wanted to touch the yacht.

They ran to the pond and saw a man sitting on the yacht. He had a hat and a beard and a big smile. He waved at them and said, "Hello, little ones. Do you like my yacht?"

"Yes, sir, it's very nice. Can we come on board?" Lily asked politely. She was curious about the yacht and wanted to see inside.

"Sure, why not? I'm feeling compassionate today. Come on, I'll show you around." The man said, lowering a ladder for them. He helped them climb up and gave them each a life jacket.

Lily and Max were very happy and excited. They saw the sail, the flag, the steering wheel, and the compass. The man told them stories about his travels and adventures. He even let them steer the yacht for a little while.

They had so much fun on the yacht that they forgot about their toy soldiers. They thanked the man for his kindness and said goodbye. They ran back to their parents, who were waiting for them on the bench.

"Mom, Dad, we went on a yacht!" Lily and Max said, bursting with joy. They told them everything they saw and did on the boat.

"That sounds wonderful, kids. You're very lucky to meet such a compassionate man." Their parents said, hugging them. They were glad their children had a good time and learned something new.

They all went home, happy and tired. Lily and Max dreamed of sailing on a yacht again.
