Sam and Mia are going to the station with Mom. They want to see the big trains that go fast and make noise. Mom says they have to wear masks because of the germs. Sam and Mia do not like masks. They are hot and itchy and make them feel funny.

On the way to the station, Sam sees a man selling balloons. He wants a red one. He asks Mom if he can have one. Mom says no, they are too expensive and they might pop. Sam is sad. He sees a blue balloon that looks like a dog. He thinks it is cute. He wants to touch it.

He runs to the balloon man and grabs the blue balloon. But the balloon is not real. It is fake. It is made of paper and has a string inside. When Sam pulls the string, the balloon makes a loud sound. It sounds like a sneeze. Sam is scared. He drops the balloon and runs back to Mom.

The balloon man is angry. He yells at Sam. He says Sam broke his balloon and he has to pay. Mom is sorry. She gives the balloon man some money and takes Sam and Mia away. She says Sam was naughty and he has to say sorry. Sam says sorry. He feels bad.

They get to the station and see the big trains. Sam and Mia forget about the balloon. They are happy. They watch the trains go by and wave to the people. They do not sneeze. They do not need masks. They have fun.
