Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play outside. But today it is winter. It is very cold and white. Lily and Tom see snow on the ground and in the air.

"Let's make a snowman!" Lily says. She picks up some snow and rolls it into a ball.

"Good idea!" Tom says. He helps Lily make a bigger ball. Then they make another ball and put it on top. They find a stick, a carrot and some stones. They make a face and arms for the snowman.

"Look, our snowman is high!" Tom says. He is happy.

"Yes, he is high and nice!" Lily says. She is happy too.

But then they hear a loud noise. It is a big truck. It is coming to their street. It has a shovel in front. It pushes the snow away.

"Oh no, the truck will break our snowman!" Lily says. She is scared.

"Quick, let's move him!" Tom says. He is scared too.

They try to move the snowman, but he is too heavy. They cannot lift him.

"What can we do?" Lily asks. She is sad.

Tom thinks hard. He has an idea.

"I know! Let's suggest to the truck driver to go around our snowman!" Tom says. He is brave.

"OK, let's try!" Lily says. She is brave too.

They run to the truck driver. They wave their hands. They shout.

"Please, please, don't break our snowman!" Tom says.

"He is our friend! We made him with love!" Lily says.

The truck driver sees them. He stops the truck. He smiles.

"Hello, kids. What a nice snowman you have!" he says.

"Thank you, sir. Can you please go around him? We don't want him to be gone!" Tom says.

"Sure, I can do that. I don't want to ruin your fun!" the truck driver says.

He drives the truck around the snowman. He honks his horn. He waves to them.

"Bye, kids. Have a good winter!" he says.

"Bye, sir. Thank you very much!" Lily and Tom say.

They hug each other. They hug their snowman. They are happy. They have a good winter.
<|end|>


