Ben and Lily like to play chess. Chess is a game with black and white pieces. They have a big board with squares. They put the pieces on the board and move them. They try to catch the other's king.

One day, Ben and Lily play chess in the park. They sit on a bench under a tree. They are very jolly. They laugh and talk. They say things like, "Your turn!" and "Good move!" and "Oh no!"

A dog comes to the park. The dog is brown and fluffy. He likes to run and jump. He sees Ben and Lily playing chess. He thinks they are playing with him. He runs to the bench and barks. He wags his tail.

"Hello, dog!" Ben says. "Do you want to play chess?"

The dog does not understand chess. He thinks the pieces are toys. He jumps on the board and grabs a piece. He runs away with it.

"Hey, come back!" Lily says. "That's my queen!"

Ben and Lily chase the dog. They want their piece back. The dog thinks they are playing with him. He runs faster and faster. He drops the piece and picks another one.

"Oh no, not my knight!" Ben says.

Ben and Lily keep chasing the dog. They run around the park. They are not jolly anymore. They are tired and sad. They want their chess game back.

The dog sees a pond. He likes water. He runs to the pond and jumps in. He splashes and swims. He drops the pieces in the water.

"Stop, dog, stop!" Ben and Lily shout. "You are ruining our chess game!"

The dog does not listen. He is having fun. He does not know he is making Ben and Lily unhappy. He thinks they are his friends. He barks and wags his tail. He wants them to join him in the pond.
<|end|>


