<|asst|>
Sara liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Lily. Lily had long hair, a pink dress, and shiny shoes. Sara loved to brush Lily's hair and make her look pretty.

One day, Sara saw a new doll in the store. The doll had pale skin, big eyes, and a red dress. Sara wanted the doll very much. She asked her mom to buy the doll for her. Her mom said no. She said Sara had enough dolls and she should be happy with what she had. Sara was angry. She cried and stomped her feet.

Sara decided to take the doll anyway. She waited until her mom was not looking and put the doll in her bag. She ran out of the store with the doll. She did not see the sign that said "Do not touch. This doll is made of powder and will break easily."

Sara got home and took the doll out of her bag. She wanted to play with the doll and make her look pretty. She tried to brush the doll's hair, but the hair fell off. She tried to put a ribbon on the doll, but the ribbon ripped the doll's dress. She tried to hug the doll, but the doll crumbled in her arms. Sara was shocked. She looked at the doll and saw that it was not a real doll. It was a doll made of powder. Sara had stolen a powder doll.

Sara felt very bad. She had done a wrong thing. She had taken something that was not hers. She had lied to her mom. She had broken the doll. She had wasted her money. She had lost her favorite doll. She wished she had listened to her mom and been happy with Lily. She learned a hard lesson. She learned that stealing is wrong and that powder dolls are not fun.
<|end|>


