Sara and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. They see many colorful things in the park. They see red flowers, blue sky, green grass and yellow sun.

One day, they find a big rainbow in the sky. They are very happy. They run to the rainbow. They want to touch it.

"Look, Sara, the rainbow is so pretty!" Tom says.

"Yes, Tom, it is. Can we catch it?" Sara asks.

They try to catch the rainbow, but it is too high. They jump and stretch, but they cannot reach it.

They are sad. They sit on the grass.

"Maybe we can kiss the rainbow," Tom says.

"Kiss the rainbow? How?" Sara asks.

"Like this," Tom says. He leans over and kisses Sara on the cheek.

Sara is surprised. She feels warm and shy. She smiles.

"Did you catch the rainbow?" Tom asks.

"I think so," Sara says. She kisses Tom back on the cheek.

They hug and giggle. They see the rainbow shine brighter.

They are happy. They kiss the rainbow. They are quick. They do not want the rainbow to go away.
