Tom and Mia went to the beach with Mom and Dad. They liked to play in the sand and make castles and holes. They also liked to splash in the water and look for shells and crabs.

One day, they saw a big empty bottle in the sand. Tom picked it up and shook it. He heard something inside. He said, "Look, Mia, there is a secret in the bottle!"

Mia was curious. She said, "What is it, Tom? Can we open it?" Tom nodded and twisted the cap. He pulled out a piece of paper. It had some words on it.

Tom and Mia could not read the words. They showed the paper to Mom and Dad. Mom and Dad looked at the paper and smiled. They said, "This is a joke, Tom and Mia. Someone wrote a funny thing on the paper and put it in the bottle. Do you want to hear it?"

Tom and Mia said, "Yes, please!" Mom and Dad read the paper. It said, "Why did the crab cross the road? To get to the other tide!" Tom and Mia did not understand the joke. They said, "What does that mean?" Mom and Dad explained that the crab wanted to go to the water when it was high and low. Tom and Mia still did not get it. They said, "But why is that funny?"

Mom and Dad laughed. They said, "It is funny because it sounds like another joke that people say. Why did the chicken cross the road? To get to the other side!" Tom and Mia thought about it. They said, "Oh, we get it now!" Then they laughed too. They thought the joke was silly and fun. They put the paper back in the bottle and buried it in the sand. They hoped someone else would find it and laugh too.
<|end|>


