Tom and Lily were playing in the garden. They liked to dig in the dirt and find bugs and worms. They also liked to plant seeds and watch them grow. One day, they found a big bean in a pod. They wanted to see what was inside.

They took the bean to their playhouse and put it on a table. They tried to open the pod, but it was too hard. They used a spoon, a fork, and a knife, but nothing worked. They were about to give up, when they heard a loud bark.

It was Rex, their dog. He had smelled the bean and wanted to eat it. He ran to the playhouse and jumped on the table. He knocked over the spoon, the fork, and the knife. He grabbed the pod in his mouth and started to chew.

Tom and Lily were scared. They loved Rex, but they did not want him to eat their bean. They wanted to protect it. They shouted, "No, Rex, no! Drop it, drop it!" They pulled on his ears and his tail, but he did not listen. He growled and shook his head.

Then, something amazing happened. The pod cracked open in Rex's mouth. He spat out the pieces and the bean. He did not like the taste. He ran away, looking for something else to eat.

Tom and Lily were happy. They picked up the bean and looked at it. It was shiny and smooth. It had a little hole in the middle. They wondered what it was for. They decided to keep it as a treasure. They put it in a box and hid it under their bed. They hugged each other and smiled. They had found a magic bean.
<|end|>


