Tom and Sue were friends who liked to play with blocks. They liked to build towers and houses and cars with the blocks. One day, they found a big box of new blocks in the playroom. They were very happy and wanted to use them all.

"Let's have a contest," Tom said. "Who can build the highest tower with the new blocks?"

"OK," Sue said. "But we have to share the blocks and be fair."

They started to build their towers, using different colors and shapes of blocks. Tom was very fast and used a lot of blocks. He wanted to win the contest and have the highest tower. Sue was slower and used fewer blocks. She wanted to make a nice and strong tower.

Soon, Tom's tower was very high, but it was also very wobbly. He had to be careful not to knock it down. Sue's tower was lower, but it was also very sturdy. She had to use some smart tricks to make it stand.

"Look at my tower!" Tom said. "It is higher than yours! I am going to win!"

"Look at my tower!" Sue said. "It is nicer than yours! I am going to win!"

They kept building and arguing, until they ran out of blocks. Tom put the last block on top of his tower, and it was very, very high. He raised his arms and cheered.

"I did it! I did it! I have the highest tower! I win!"

But then, something bad happened. Tom's tower was too high and too wobbly, and it fell down with a loud crash. All the blocks scattered on the floor. Tom was sad and angry. He had lost his tower and his contest.

Sue saw what happened and felt sorry for Tom. She had the lowest tower, but it was still standing. She had won the contest, but she did not want to make Tom feel worse. She had a big heart and a good idea.

"Tom, don't be sad," Sue said. "We can use your blocks and my blocks and build a new tower together. It will be higher and nicer than our towers. We can both win!"

Tom looked at Sue and smiled. He liked her idea and her kindness. He had a big heart too.

"OK, Sue, let's do that," Tom said. "You are a good friend and a smart builder. We can both win!"

They hugged and started to build a new tower together. They used all the blocks and shared them and were fair. They had fun and learned a lesson. The new tower was the highest and the nicest tower they ever built. They both raised their arms and cheered.

"We did it! We did it! We have the best tower! We win!"

The end.
<|end|>


