Lila was a little girl who liked to play in the park. She had a toy lion that she took with her everywhere. She loved her lion very much and pretended it was her friend.

One day, she saw a big sign in the park that said "Rare Animals Show". She was curious and wanted to see the rare animals. She asked her mom if they could go, and her mom said yes. They walked to the show and saw many different animals. Lila saw a snake, a monkey, a parrot, and a zebra. She was amazed and happy.

Then she saw a real lion in a cage. It was big and yellow and had a long mane. It looked like her toy lion, but much bigger and scarier. Lila wanted to see it closer, so she ran to the cage. Her mom shouted "Lila, wait! Don't go near the lion!" But Lila did not listen. She thought the lion was friendly and wanted to play with her.

She reached the cage and said "Hello, lion. Do you want to be my friend? I have a toy lion like you. See?" She held up her toy lion and showed it to the real lion. The real lion saw the toy lion and growled. It did not like the toy lion. It thought it was a rival and wanted to attack it. It jumped at the cage and tried to grab the toy lion.

Lila was scared and dropped her toy lion. The real lion caught the toy lion in its mouth and tore it apart. Lila cried and screamed. Her mom ran to her and hugged her. She said "Lila, I'm sorry. You should have listened to me. The lion is not a friend. It is a wild animal. It can hurt you and your toy. You should never go near a wild animal. You should relax and stay safe."

Lila learned a hard lesson that day. She lost her toy lion and her trust in the real lion. She realized that not all animals are friendly and that she should obey her mom. She wished she had relaxed and played with her toy lion in the park instead of going to the show. She was sad and sorry. The end.
<|end|>


