Anna and Ben are twins. They like to play with their toys and their dog, Spot. Spot is a cute dog. He has brown fur and a black nose. He likes to run and jump and lick Anna and Ben.

One day, Anna and Ben are playing in the living room. They hear Spot barking in the kitchen. They run to see what is wrong. They see Spot standing on his hind legs, trying to reach the cupboard. The cupboard has the dog food inside.

"Spot, what are you doing?" Anna asks. "You are not supposed to open the cupboard. That is naughty."

"Maybe he is hungry," Ben says. "Let's feed him some dog food."

Anna and Ben get a bowl and a scoop. They open the cupboard and take out some dog food. They pour some dog food into the bowl and put it on the floor. Spot wags his tail and runs to the bowl. He starts to eat the dog food.

"Good boy, Spot," Anna says. "You are a good dog. We love you."

"Yes, we love you, Spot," Ben says. "But next time, wait for us to feed you. Don't try to open the cupboard by yourself. You could hurt yourself or make a mess."

Spot looks up at Anna and Ben. He licks his lips and barks. He is happy and full. He thanks Anna and Ben for feeding him. He cuddles with them on the couch. They play and laugh together. They are a happy family.
