Lisa and Ben are friends. They like to play together in the park. One day, they see a big sign. The sign says: "Circus is here! Come and see the clowns, the animals and the tricks!"

Lisa and Ben want to go to the circus. They run to their moms and ask for tickets. Their moms say yes, but they have to be careful and stay together.

Lisa and Ben are very happy. They get their tickets and go to the circus. They see many things. They see a clown who makes funny jokes. They see a lion who roars and jumps through a hoop. They see a girl who walks on a rope high in the air.

But then, something bad happens. Ben trips and falls. He hurts his knee. He cries and says: "Ow, ow, ow! It hurts!"

Lisa sees Ben and runs to him. She says: "Don't cry, Ben. I will help you. I have a band-aid in my pocket. I will put it on your knee. It will make you feel better. It will heal your boo-boo."

Lisa takes out her band-aid and puts it on Ben's knee. She gives him a hug and says: "There, there. You are brave, Ben. You are my friend. Do you want to see more of the circus?"

Ben smiles and says: "Yes, Lisa. Thank you. You are my friend too. You are very kind and independent. You can do many things. Let's go and see more of the circus."

Lisa and Ben hold hands and go to see more of the circus. They have a lot of fun. They are happy. They are friends.
