Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play with trucks in the park. They have big trucks and small trucks. They make noises like vroom and beep.

One day, Tom has a new truck. It is red and shiny. It can carry many things. Tom is happy. He wants to show Sam his new truck.

"Look, Sam, look!" Tom says. "I have a new truck. It is red and shiny. It can carry many things. Do you want to play with it?"

Sam looks at Tom's new truck. He likes it. He wants to play with it. But he also has his own truck. It is blue and old. It can carry some things. Sam is sad. He thinks Tom will not like his truck.

"Your truck is nice, Tom," Sam says. "But I have my own truck. It is blue and old. It can carry some things. Do you want to play with it?"

Tom looks at Sam's truck. He does not care if it is blue and old. He cares if it is fun. He sees that Sam's truck can carry some things. He has an idea.

"Let's play together, Sam," Tom says. "We can bring our trucks to the sandbox. We can fill them with sand and dump them. We can make a castle or a hill. We can have fun with our trucks."

Sam smiles. He likes Tom's idea. He thinks Tom is a good friend. He agrees to play with Tom.

"OK, Tom, let's play together," Sam says. "We can bring our trucks to the sandbox. We can fill them with sand and dump them. We can make a castle or a hill. We can have fun with our trucks."

Tom and Sam run to the sandbox. They bring their trucks. They fill them with sand and dump them. They make a castle and a hill. They have fun with their trucks. They are happy.

