<|asst|>
Tom and Sam were brothers who liked to play with their toy trucks. They had a big pile of sand in the backyard, and they pretended to be builders. They used their trucks to load and unload the sand, and made roads and hills and castles.

One day, it was very hot and sunny, and they got sweaty and dirty from playing. Their mom called them inside and said, "It's time for a shower, boys. You need to wash off the sand and cool down." But Tom and Sam did not want to stop playing. They said, "No, mom, we want to play more. We are not dirty, we are builders."

Their mom was not happy. She said, "You are not builders, you are boys. And boys need to listen to their mom and take a shower. If you don't, you will get itchy and smelly and have bad dreams. Now come on, or I will take away your trucks."

Tom and Sam did not like that. They did not want to lose their trucks. But they were also restless and wanted to play more. They thought of a plan. They said, "OK, mom, we will take a shower. But can we take our trucks with us? They are dirty too, and they need a shower."

Their mom thought for a moment. She said, "Well, I guess you can, but only if you promise to wash them well and not make a mess in the bathroom. And you have to be quick, because it's almost time for dinner."

Tom and Sam agreed. They ran to the bathroom with their trucks, and turned on the shower. They put their trucks under the water, and pretended to wash them. But they also splashed and sprayed and made a lot of noise. They had fun, but they also made the bathroom wet and sandy.

Their mom heard the noise and came to check on them. She was not happy. She said, "Boys, what are you doing? You are not taking a shower, you are making a mess. Look at the floor, and the walls, and the towels. They are all wet and sandy. And you are still dirty. You did not wash yourselves, you only played with your trucks."

Tom and Sam felt ashamed. They knew they did not listen to their mom, and they did not do what they said. They said, "Sorry, mom, we were having fun. We did not mean to make a mess. We will clean it up, and we will take a real shower."

Their mom said, "You better do that, boys. And next time, when I tell you to do something, you do it. Playing is good, but you also need to take care of yourself and your things. And you need to respect your mom and your home. Do you understand?"

Tom and Sam nodded. They said, "Yes, mom, we understand. We will do better next time. We love you, mom."

Their mom smiled. She said, "I love you too, boys. Now go and take a shower, and then come for dinner. And don't forget to dry your trucks."

The moral of the story is: Listen to your mom and do what she says. Playing is good, but you also need to take care of yourself and your things. And you need to respect your mom and your home.
<|end|>


