Lily and Ben were at the beach with their mom and dad. They saw a big boat on the water. It was white and shiny. It had a flag and a sail. Lily said, "Look, Ben, a yacht! It is so pretty!"

Ben nodded. He liked the boat too. He wanted to go on it and play. He asked his mom, "Can we go on the yacht, mom? Please?"

Mom shook her head. She said, "No, Ben, we can't. The yacht belongs to someone else. We have to stay on the sand and play with our toys."

Ben was sad. He pouted. He said, "But I want to go on the yacht. It is not fair."

Lily saw that Ben was sad. She wanted to cheer him up. She said, "Don't be sad, Ben. We can have fun on the sand too. Look, I made a castle with a moat. Do you want to help me?"

Ben looked at Lily's castle. It was nice. He smiled. He said, "Okay, Lily. I will help you. Thank you."

Lily and Ben hugged. They played with the castle and the moat. They filled the moat with water and put shells and stones on the castle. They had fun. They forgot about the yacht. They were happy.
