<|asst|>
Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play with toys. They have a big box of toys. They have cars, trains, dolls, balls and a plane. The plane is red and blue. It has wings and wheels. It can fly in the air.

One day, Tom and Sam decide to play with the plane. They want to make it fly. They take the plane out of the box. They put some toys inside the plane. They load the plane with cars, trains, dolls and balls. They say, "The plane is full. It is ready to fly."

They look for a place to fly the plane. They see a tall tree in the yard. They think, "The tree is tall. It is good for flying." They run to the tree. They hold the plane in their hands. They count, "One, two, three, go!" They throw the plane in the air.

But the plane is too heavy. It has too many toys inside. It does not fly. It falls down. It hits the tree. It breaks into pieces. The toys fall out of the plane. They scatter on the ground. The plane is ruined. The toys are dirty.

Tom and Sam are sad. They cry. They say, "Our plane is broken. Our toys are dirty. We are sorry. We are bad." They pick up the pieces of the plane and the toys. They put them back in the box. They go inside the house. They do not play with the plane anymore. They have no fun. They have a bad day.
<|end|>


