<|asst|>
Lily and Anna were best friends. They liked to play with dolls and dress up. Lily had long, brown hair. Anna had short, blond hair. Lily always wanted to have blond hair like Anna. She thought it was adorable.

One day, Lily found a pair of scissors in her mom's drawer. She had an idea. She took the scissors and went to Anna's house. She knocked on the door and Anna opened it.

"Hi, Lily! Do you want to play?" Anna asked.

"Yes, I do. But first, can I see your hair?" Lily said.

"Sure, come in." Anna said. She led Lily to her room.

Lily followed Anna and pretended to admire her hair. She waited until Anna turned her back. Then, she grabbed the scissors and cut off a big chunk of Anna's hair.

"Hey! What are you doing?" Anna screamed. She touched her head and saw her hair falling to the floor.

"I'm sorry, Anna. I just wanted to have your hair. It's so adorable. Now I can own it." Lily said. She held the hair in her hand and smiled.

Anna started to cry. She ran to her mom and told her what Lily did. Her mom was very angry. She called Lily's mom and told her to come and get her.

Lily's mom came and saw what Lily did. She was very disappointed. She scolded Lily and took her home. She threw away the hair and made Lily apologize to Anna.

But Anna did not want to be friends with Lily anymore. She was very sad and hurt. She did not like her hair anymore. She did not trust Lily anymore.

Lily lost her best friend. She was very sorry. She realized that she made a big mistake. She wished she could take it back. But it was too late.
<|end|>


