<|asst|>
Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play outside. One day, the sky is dark and windy. Tom and Mia hear a loud noise.

"What is that?" Mia asks.

"It is a hurricane," Tom says. "It is a big storm that can break things and hurt people."

"Where is your mom?" Mia asks.

"She is at work. She will come soon," Tom says.

They run to Tom's house. They lock the door and hide under the bed. They are scared.

Tom has a toy car. He likes to play with it. He forgets to bring it inside. The hurricane blows it away.

Tom is sad. He cries.

"I am sorry, Tom," Mia says. "I know you love your car."

"Thank you, Mia," Tom says. "You are a good friend."

They hug. They wait for the hurricane to stop.

After a long time, the hurricane is gone. The sky is blue and sunny. Tom and Mia go outside. They see many things are broken. Trees, houses, cars.

They look for Tom's car. They cannot find it.

Tom's mom comes. She is happy to see Tom and Mia. She hugs them.

"Are you okay?" she asks.

"Yes, mom," Tom says. "But I lost my car."

"I am sorry, Tom," she says. "But I am glad you are safe. We can get you a new car."

Tom smiles. He is still sad, but he feels better.

He looks at Mia. She smiles too.

They are normal kids. They like to play outside. They have each other. They are happy.
<|end|>


