<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were bored. They wanted to play, but they had no toys. All their toys were old and broken. They were cheap toys that their mom got from the store.

"Let's make our own toys!" Lily said. She had an idea. She ran to the kitchen and got some paper cups and a spoon. Ben followed her.

"What are you doing?" Ben asked.

"Watch!" Lily said. She filled the cups with water from the tap. Then she banged the spoon on the cups. They made different sounds. "See? We have drums!"

Ben smiled. He liked the sounds. He got another spoon and joined Lily. They banged the cups and made music.

"Let's march!" Lily said. She picked up two cups and held them like a drum. Ben did the same. They marched around the house, banging their cups and singing. They felt happy.

Their mom heard the noise and came to see. She saw Lily and Ben marching with their cups. She smiled. She was proud of them. They were creative and fun.

"That's a nice march!" she said. "Can I join you?"

"Yes, mom!" Lily and Ben said. They gave her a cup and a spoon. They marched together, making music and laughing. They had a lot of fun. They did not need cheap toys. They had each other.
<|end|>


