Lily and her mom went to the market. The market was big and noisy. There were many people and things to see. Lily liked the market. She wanted to see everything.

"Mom, can I step on the scales?" Lily asked. She saw a big machine that told how heavy people were.

"Sure, honey. But be careful. Don't step too hard," Mom said. She lifted Lily and put her on the scales. The machine made a beep and showed a number.

"Wow, you are very light, Lily. Only twenty pounds," Mom said.

Lily smiled. She felt proud. She stepped off the scales and looked around. She saw a man with a funny hat and a big guitar. He was singing a song. People were clapping and giving him money.

"Mom, who is he?" Lily asked.

"He is a famous singer, Lily. He sings very well. Do you want to listen to him?" Mom asked.

"Yes, please. I like his song," Lily said.

They walked closer to the singer. Lily and Mom listened to his song. Lily liked his voice and his guitar. She clapped her hands and danced. The singer saw Lily and smiled. He sang a special song for her.

"Hello, little girl. You are so cute and bright. You make me happy with your smile and light. You are a star, you are a wonder. You are the best thing in the market," he sang.

Lily was very happy. She felt special. She thanked the singer and gave him a hug. Mom also thanked him and gave him some money.

They left the market. Lily and Mom had a great day. They went home and told Dad about their adventure. Lily said she wanted to go to the market again. Mom said they would. Lily was excited. She dreamed of the market and the famous singer. She dreamed of stepping on the scales and dancing to the song. She was a star. She was a wonder. She was the best thing in the market.
<|end|>


