Sara and Ben were twins who liked to share everything. They shared their toys, their clothes, and their snacks. But one day, they had a problem. They only had one peanut left, and they both wanted it.

"Give me the peanut!" Sara said.

"No, it's mine!" Ben said.

They pulled and tugged on the peanut, but it did not break. They started to cry and yell.

Mom heard the noise and came to see what was wrong. She saw the twins fighting over the peanut. She felt sad and angry.

"Stop it, Sara and Ben!" Mom said. "You are being very naughty. You need to learn how to separate and share. If you can't do that, you will have no peanut at all."

She took the peanut from their hands and put it on the table. She told them to go to their rooms and think about what they did. She said they could not come out until they said sorry to each other.

Sara and Ben felt very gloomy. They did not like to be apart from each other. They did not like to make Mom unhappy. They did not like to lose the peanut. They wished they had been nicer to each other.

They sat on their beds and thought about how to fix their mistake. They decided to say sorry to each other and to Mom. They decided to split the peanut in half and share it. They decided to hug and smile.

They ran out of their rooms and found Mom in the kitchen. They said sorry to her and to each other. They asked for the peanut and broke it in half. They gave each other a piece and ate it happily.

Mom was very proud of them. She hugged them and kissed them. She said they were very good twins. She said they had learned how to separate and share. She said she loved them very much.

The end.
<|end|>


