Lily loved her bunny, Fluffy. Fluffy was white and soft and had long ears. Fluffy liked to bounce around the garden and eat carrots. Lily liked to hug Fluffy and play with him.

One day, Fluffy got sick. He did not bounce or eat. He lay in his cage and made sad noises. Lily was very worried. She told her mom, "Mom, Fluffy is sick. He needs help."

Mom said, "Don't worry, Lily. We will take Fluffy to the veterinarian. The veterinarian is a doctor for animals. He will make Fluffy better."

Lily and Mom put Fluffy in a basket and drove to the veterinarian. The veterinarian was a nice man with a white coat and a stethoscope. He looked at Fluffy and said, "Hello, Fluffy. You are an adorable bunny. What is wrong with you?"

He checked Fluffy's ears, eyes, nose, and teeth. He gave Fluffy some medicine and a bandage. He said, "Fluffy has a cold and a sore paw. He will be fine in a few days. Just keep him warm and give him lots of water and carrots."

Lily was very happy. She thanked the veterinarian and hugged Fluffy. She said, "Fluffy, I love you. You are my best friend. I'm glad you are better."

Fluffy snuggled with Lily and made happy noises. He felt better already. He was ready to bounce again.
<|end|>


