Tom and Anna are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big tent. It is for a fair. They want to go inside.

"Can we go, please?" Tom asks his mom.

"Sure, but stay close to me," his mom says.

They go inside the tent. There are many things to see and do. There are games, toys, books, and food. Tom and Anna are happy.

They see a man who can cook. He has a big pot. He puts things in the pot. He stirs and stirs. He makes soup. It smells good.

"Can we have some soup?" Anna asks her mom.

"OK, but first you have to untie this knot," her mom says. She gives Anna a rope with a knot. "If you can untie it, you can have some soup."

Anna tries to untie the knot. She pulls and twists. But the knot is too hard. She cannot untie it.

Tom sees Anna. He wants to help her. He knows how to untie knots. He learned from his dad. He goes to Anna.

"Can I help you?" he asks.

"No, I can do it myself," Anna says. She is jealous. She does not want Tom to untie the knot. She wants to do it herself.

But Tom does not listen. He takes the rope from Anna. He unties the knot. He gives it back to Anna.

"Here you go," he says. "Now you can have some soup."

Anna is angry. She does not say thank you. She does not want the soup. She wants the knot. She snatches the rope from Tom. She ties the knot again. She runs away.

Tom is sad. He does not understand. He only wanted to help. He goes to his mom.

"Why is Anna mad at me?" he asks.

"Sometimes people get jealous when they think someone else is better than them," his mom says. "But you did nothing wrong. You were kind and generous. Maybe Anna will say sorry later."

Tom nods. He hopes Anna will be his friend again. He goes to the man who can cook. He asks for some soup. He shares it with his mom. It is warm and tasty. He smiles.
<|end|>


