Lily and Tom were friends. They liked to play in the park. One day, they saw a big dog. The dog was brown and had a long tail. The dog looked mild and friendly.

"Can we pet the dog?" Lily asked Tom.

"I don't know," Tom said. "Maybe we should ask the owner first."

But the owner was not in the park. The dog was alone. Lily and Tom walked closer to the dog. The dog wagged its tail and licked its nose.

"Hello, dog," Lily said. "You are so cute. Can we help you? Are you lost?"

The dog barked and jumped on Lily. It bit her arm and made her cry. Tom was scared and ran away. He did not help Lily. He did not call for help. He left Lily alone with the dog.

Lily was hurt and sad. She wished Tom was still her friend. She wished the dog was not mild. She wished someone would help her. But no one came. No one heard her cry. No one helped her yet.
