Tom likes to drive his toy car. He makes it go fast and slow, and he makes it turn and stop. He likes to drive it on the floor, on the table, and on the sofa. He likes to drive it everywhere.

One day, Tom sees a big car in the street. It is red and shiny, and it has four doors and four wheels. Tom thinks it is a nice car. He wants to drive it too. He runs to the car and opens the door. He climbs inside and sits on the seat. He puts his hands on the wheel and his feet on the pedals.

Tom does not know how to drive a big car. He pushes the pedals and turns the wheel. The car makes a loud noise and moves. Tom is scared. He does not know how to stop the car. He sees a tree in front of him. He screams.

Mom hears Tom scream. She runs to the street and sees the car. She is very angry and very worried. She runs to the car and opens the door. She pulls Tom out of the car and hugs him. She checks his finger and his head. He is not hurt, but he is very sorry.

Mom tells Tom that he should never drive a big car. He should only drive his toy car. He should always ask before he touches something that is not his. He should always be careful and listen to Mom. Tom nods and says he is sorry. He says he loves Mom and he loves his toy car. Mom says she loves Tom and she is glad he is okay. She gives him a kiss and takes him home. She gives him his toy car and tells him to drive it nicely. Tom smiles and says he will. He drives his toy car nicely on the floor. He is happy.
