Lily likes to eat. She eats a lot of food every day. She eats bread and jam for breakfast. She eats soup and cheese for lunch. She eats pasta and meat for dinner. She also eats fruits and cookies for snacks.

Lily's mom has a job. She works at a big store. She sells clothes and shoes to people. She likes her job, but sometimes it is hard. She has to talk to many people and help them find what they want. She has to work for many hours and carry heavy boxes.

One day, Lily goes to the store with her mom. She wants to see what her mom does. She follows her mom around the store and watches her work. She sees her mom smile and say hello to the people. She sees her mom measure and fold the clothes. She sees her mom scan and bag the shoes.

Lily thinks her mom's job is easy. She thinks she can do it too. She picks up a shirt and tries to put it on a hanger. But the shirt is too big and the hanger is too small. The shirt falls on the floor. Lily picks up a shoe and tries to scan it. But the shoe is too heavy and the scanner is too high. The shoe drops on the counter. Lily makes a loud noise and everyone looks at her.

Lily's mom hears the noise and comes to see what happened. She sees Lily with the shirt and the shoe. She sees the mess on the floor and the counter. She is not happy. She says to Lily, "Lily, what are you doing? You can't do my job. My job is not easy. My job is hard. You are too little to work here. You have to stay with me and be quiet."

Lily feels sad. She says to her mom, "I'm sorry, mom. I just wanted to help you. I wanted to do your job. I thought your job was easy. I thought your job was fun."

Lily's mom hugs her and says, "I know, Lily. I know you wanted to help me. But you don't have to do my job. You have your own job. Your job is to eat and grow and learn and play. Your job is easy and fun. Your job is to be my sweet girl."

Lily smiles and says, "I love you, mom. I love your job. I love my job too."
<|end|>


