Sam and Mia were playing in the park. They saw a big slide that looked like a tube. Sam wanted to go on the slide, but Mia was scared.

"Come on, Mia, it will be fun!" Sam urged. "You can go first, and I will follow you."

Mia shook her head. "No, Sam, it is too high and too fast. I don't like it."

Sam tried to make Mia feel better. "Don't be afraid, Mia. I will be right behind you. You can hold my hand if you want. It is not scary, it is impressive. You will feel like a rocket!"

Mia looked at the slide again. She saw other kids laughing and sliding down. She wondered if it was really fun. She decided to be brave and try it.

"Okay, Sam, I will go with you. But you have to hold my hand, okay?"

"Okay, Mia, I will hold your hand. You are very brave. Let's go!"

Sam and Mia climbed up the stairs and sat on the slide. They held hands and smiled at each other. Then they pushed off and slid down the tube. They felt the wind in their hair and the sun on their faces. They screamed and giggled as they went faster and faster. They reached the bottom and jumped off the slide. They were happy and proud.

"That was awesome, Mia!" Sam said. "You did it! You are impressive!"

"That was fun, Sam!" Mia said. "You were right! It was not scary, it was impressive! Can we do it again?"

Sam and Mia hugged and ran back to the slide. They had a great time playing in the park.
<|end|>


