Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to eat with her fork, especially when she had spaghetti for dinner. One day, Lily was playing outside when she saw a shiny penny on the ground. She picked it up and showed it to her mommy. "Look, mommy! It shines!" she said. 

Later that day, Lily went to the park with her mommy. While she was playing on the slide, she saw a charming puppy running towards her. "Hi there, little puppy!" she said. The puppy licked her face and ran away. Lily loved the puppy and wanted to take him home. 

The next day, Lily and her mommy went back to the park. They saw the same puppy running around. "Let's take him home, mommy!" Lily said. But her mommy said they needed to find the puppy's owner first. They searched and searched until they found a man who was looking for his lost puppy. "Thank you for finding my puppy," the man said. "You are very kind and charming." Lily felt happy that she helped the man find his puppy. She knew that good things happen when you do good things.
