Once upon a time, there was a big farm with lots of animals. One day, a little piggy named Benny got sick. His friend, the cow, asked him what was wrong. Benny said he didn't feel good and his tummy hurt. The cow knew just what to do. She told Benny to eat some healthy food and rest.

But Benny didn't want to eat. He wanted to play with his friends. So, he went outside and started to run around. But soon, he felt worse. He started to yell for help. The cow heard him and came over. She told Benny that he needed to listen to his body and take care of himself. Benny realized that the cow was right. He ate some healthy food and took a nap.

The next day, Benny felt much better. He thanked the cow for her help and promised to listen to his body from now on. The moral of the story is that it's important to take care of ourselves and listen to our bodies when we don't feel good.
