Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to bake cakes with her mom. One day, Lily's mom gave her a big bowl of flour and asked her to measure it. Lily didn't know how to measure, so her mom taught her how to use a measuring cup.

After they finished baking the cake, Lily's mom asked her to help with the laundry. She showed Lily how to use the iron to make the clothes smooth. Lily was excited to help and she did a great job.

Later that day, Lily's mom gave her a piece of candy. It was so sweet and delicious! Lily loved it so much that she asked for another one. Her mom said no and told her that too much sweet is not good for her body. Lily learned that it's important to measure how much sweet she eats.

The moral of the story is that measuring things can be helpful, whether it's measuring ingredients for baking or measuring how much sweet we eat. It's important to learn how to measure so we can make things just right!
<|end|>


