Once upon a time, there was a big, hairy bear named Benny. Benny lived in a forest with his friends, the birds and the squirrels. One day, Benny wanted to climb a tall tree, but he couldn't reach the top.

"I can't do it," Benny said to his friends. "I'm not strong enough."

"You can do it, Benny!" the birds and squirrels cheered. "Just try!"

Benny took a deep breath and tried again. He climbed higher and higher until he reached the top. When he got there, he felt so happy and proud. He released a big roar of success that echoed through the forest.

"I did it!" Benny exclaimed. "I climbed the tree all by myself!"

His friends cheered and congratulated him. From that day on, Benny knew that he could do anything he set his mind to.
<|end|>


