Once upon a time, there was a little bear named Benny. Benny loved to play with his friends in the forest, but today he was feeling very tired. He walked slowly and yawned a lot.

Benny's friend, a wise owl, noticed that Benny was struggling to keep up with the others. "What's wrong, Benny?" asked the owl.

"I'm just so tired," replied Benny. "I didn't sleep well last night."

The owl looked up at the moon in the sky and said, "Maybe you should take a nap under the moon. It always helps me feel better when I'm tired."

Benny thought that was a great idea. He found a cozy spot under a tree and fell asleep under the moon's gentle glow. When he woke up, he felt much better and was ready to play with his friends again.
<|end|>


