Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved playing outside in her backyard. One day, she saw a big gate. It was shiny and new, and it looked like it could keep anything out.

Lily wanted to open the gate and see what was on the other side. But her mom warned her that it was hot outside and she should wait until it was cooler. Lily didn't want to wait, so she went outside anyway.

She tried to open the gate, but it was stuck. She pulled and pulled until finally, she heard a loud tear. The gate had ripped right off its hinges! Lily felt bad for breaking it, but she also felt brave for trying to open it. From then on, she always listened to her mom's advice and waited until it was cooler outside before playing.
