Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside and run around in the grass. One day, her mommy gave her some orange powder to play with. Lily thought it was so pretty and started to sprinkle it all over herself.

Her mommy said, "Lily, don't make a mess with the powder. It's not for playing."

Lily didn't listen and kept playing with the powder. Suddenly, she started to cough and couldn't breathe. Her mommy called for help, but it was too late. Lily had quit breathing and passed away.

Her mommy was very sad and wished she had taken the powder away from Lily. She learned a hard lesson that day and never gave Lily anything that wasn't safe to play with again.
