Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a small house with her mommy and daddy. One day, Lily saw a chubby chicken walking in her yard. 

"Mommy, look at the chubby chicken!" Lily said.

"I believe that chicken belongs to our neighbor," Mommy said. "Let's go ask if it's lost."

So, Lily and Mommy walked to their neighbor's house and knocked on the door. The neighbor answered and Lily said, "Excuse me, did you lose your chubby chicken?"

The neighbor smiled and said, "Yes, I did! Thank you so much for finding her."

Lily felt happy that she helped the neighbor find their chicken. From that day on, Lily always looked for chubby chickens in her yard to make sure they weren't lost.
