Once upon a time, there was a little train who liked to do things by himself. He would chug-chug around the tracks and stop at every station. One day, the little train got confused and didn't know which way to go. He saw a station in the distance and decided to stop there. 

At the station, the little train met a kind conductor who asked him what was wrong. The little train explained that he was confused and didn't know which way to go. The conductor listened carefully and then showed the little train the right way to go. 

Feeling much better, the little train said goodbye to the conductor and continued on his journey. He knew that if he ever got confused again, he could always stop at a station and ask for help. From that day on, the little train never felt lost or confused again.
