Once upon a time there was a little girl named Sara. She was only three, but she loved to travel. Whenever there was an exciting place to go, Sara would set her luggage by the door so she could be ready to go.

One day, Sara and her family were going on a road trip. They carefully packed their suitcases and set them in the car. Sara was excited for her adventure. 

But when they got to the next city, it started to rain. It rained and rained, and Sara and her family were stuck indoors all day. Sara felt miserable.

The next day, the sun came out and Sara's family decided to go explore the city. They filled their luggage with snacks and set it on the back seat of the car. Sara smiled, forgetting about how miserable she had been the day before.

Sara and her family drove around the city, taking in all of the new sights and sounds. When they finally got home, exhausted but happy, Sara couldn't wait to set her luggage in the corner to remind her of her exciting adventure.
