Once there was a little girl named Ella. She was three years old. One day she wanted to go outside and play. But her mom said, "We have to stay inside today."

Ella started to complain. She did not like to stay inside. She said, "No, I want to go out and play with my friends!"

Her mom said, "I'm sorry, but we have to stay inside today. We have to stay home and take a rest."

Ella sighed and said, "I'm so uncomfortable. It's boring inside. I don't want to stay here and do nothing all day."

Her mom said, "We can play some other games. We'll get a pass to go to the park tomorrow. That way, we won't have to stay inside today."

Ella was happy. She stopped complaining. "Yes, I want to go to the park tomorrow!" she said.

And so, Ella looked forward to going to the park the next day and not having to stay inside and be uncomfortable.
<|end|>


