Once upon a time, there was a fox. The fox was gray. He wanted to take a journey and explore the world. So, he decided to sail away. He sailed high above the clouds. He looked down and he saw a beautiful, big lake. He saw a big fish in the lake. So, the fox jumped off his boat and he swam in the lake to catch the big fish. But before he could, the fish swam away. The fox was so sad, so he climbed back into his boat and sailed away. He sailed and sailed until he saw a beautiful green forest. He stopped and stepped off his boat and explored the forest. The fox had a lot of fun and made many new friends. Finally, when the sun had set, the gray fox hopped back on his boat and sailed home.
