Once upon a time, there was a little girl who wanted to see the world. Each day, she would stand at her window and order the same view of the city. She saw happy people, high buildings, and cars going by. 

One day, the little girl saw something different â€“ a broken window. She wondered why it was broken. She asked her mom why it was broken, but her mom didn't know. 

The next day, the little girl still wanted to see the same view. So, she went to the broken window and tried to order the same view. But the window wouldn't open. It was broken. 

The little girl was sad, so she went outside and looked around her neighborhood. She found a new and exciting view from a tree. She looked up and smiled, happy that she discovered something new. 

The End.
<|end|>


