John was eager to go play in the snow. He put on his coat, boots, and hat and ran outside. His eyes widened when he saw the snow everywhere.

John shouted in delight and began to run around in circles. He laughed as the snow crunched beneath his feet. He made a snowball and threw it at his mom.

Then, John saw a great big snowman. He was so excited that he shouted for his mom and dad. His mom and dad came running over with sticks and rocks.

They built the snowman together and made it even bigger. John shouted in joy when the snowman was finished. He hugged his mom and dad, delighted to see something so wonderful.
<|end|>


