Once upon a time, there lived a beautiful and graceful little girl. Her name was Jasmine and she was 3 years old.

Jasmine loved to study in the mornings and often did her homework with her teacher. She liked to learn new things and found it all very exciting.

One day, she decided to make something special for her teacher. She knew that her teacher liked butter, so Jasmine went to the store to buy some. She chose the prettiest butter she could find. Then she went home to carefully wrap the butter in some special paper and ribbon.

Jasmine was very proud of her present and decided to give it to her teacher the next day. When the teacher opened the present, she was so delighted by Jasmine's thoughtful gift.

Jasmine was so happy. She was so proud of the graceful gift she had made for her teacher. From that day on, she kept studying so that she could learn lots more new things.
<|end|>


