Once upon a time, there were two friends, Jane and Andy. Jane and Andy used to play together every day. They had so much fun!

One day, Jane wanted to make something special for Andy. She mixed some rice and water together in a bowl. She stirred it until it was just right.

Then she separated the rice into two parts. She took one part for Andy and one part for herself. Jane and Andy ate the rice together and it tasted very yummy.

After a while, Jane and Andy noticed that the pieces of rice fit perfectly together. They were so excited! They put the rice back together and enjoyed it.

Jane and Andy had a great time eating the rice together. They were so happy to share it. They laughed and smiled, and knew that they would always be special friends.
