Jim was a happy little boy. He had a pet dog called Spot. Every day Jim and Spot went for a walk down the street. One day, on their walk, they saw a big chimney. The chimney was tall and crooked. Spot got a bit too close to the chimney and his tail brushed against it. Suddenly, something flew out of the chimney! It was a big poor bird. It hit Spot on the head. Spot was very scared! He ran away and Jim ran after him. Jim was very worried about Spot. 

When Jim got back to his house, he saw Spot lying by the door. Spot was very happy to see Jim. He was so grateful. Jim hugged his pet dog and scratched his ears. Then Jim laughed. He saw that Spot had a big red mark on his forehead. It looked like a slap from the poor bird! Jim was so grateful that Spot was okay. From then on, Jim was very careful when walking near chimneys!
<|end|>


