Once upon a time there was a little girl named Anna. Anna wanted to go outside and play but her mom wouldn't allow it. Anna was sad and asked, "Why can't I play?" 

"Because it's too dangerous," said Mom. "There's a big hole in the ground that's not safe."

Anna was feeling very impatient. She wanted to go out and swing on the swing. She asked her mom again, "Can I please go outside and play?"

Mom smiled and said, "Yes, you may. But first you need to promise to stay away from the big hole in the ground. Can you do that?"

Anna smiled and said, "Yes, I promise!" 

So Mom allowed Anna to go play outside. Anna was so happy that she ran to the swing and started swinging higher and higher!
<|end|>


