Once upon a time, there was a chicken. It was a big, friendly chicken that everyone liked. One day, the chicken went out for a walk and it felt something on its back. It was soft and it felt nice. The chicken turned around to see what was there. It was a little girl! She was smiling and she reached out her hand to touch the chicken. The chicken was happy! It clucked softly, and the little girl laughed.

The next day, the chicken and the girl went for a walk together in the park. They had a lot of fun running and playing together. The chicken followed the little girl wherever she went. Then the girl had an idea. She took a stick and made a maze in the dirt. She said the chicken could try to find its way out. It was easy, and the chicken found its way out in no time! The girl laughed and clapped her hands.

The girl and the chicken were best friends. She loved to touch the soft feathers of the chicken, and it loved being tickled. They played together all day, every day. It was easy and it felt nice.
