Once upon a time, there was a truck. It was a cheap truck. Every night it would rise. Up, up, up it went. It didn't drive, it flew! The truck flew over the hills, rivers, and trees. It was so high, it looked like a star in the sky.

The truck kept rising until it was so far away. Up in the sky there were so many beautiful stars. The truck was so happy and so free!

But as the night went on, the truck had to come down and it started to gently lower. Down, down, down it went. Eventually, it reached the ground again and it was time to rest. 

The truck was so happy and so proud. It had risen so high, it felt like a fighter jet in the sky! Now it was time to take a little rest, until the next night when it would rise again!
