Once upon a time there was a girl called Liz. She was very young, only three years old. One day Liz was in the hall with her mum and she wanted to know something. She asked her mum "what is easy?". 

Her mum smiled and said "sometimes things are easy and sometimes they are not. But don't worry, you will know what's easy when you are older". Liz was sad because she wanted to know the answer now. 

Suddenly, Liz saw a fly in the hall. She chased it and tried to catch it. She ran around for a while and then finally she caught the fly. Liz was so happy and she said to her mum "see, it was very easy". 

Her mum smiled, Liz had finally learnt that sometimes things are easy!
