Once there was a little girl named Lucy. She was full of energy and always on the go. One day she wanted to go for a walk with her mom. So Lucy excitedly gathered her leash and shouted, "Let's go!"

Mom was still getting dressed, so Lucy waited and waited. She grew more and more impatient, so she started shouting again, "Let's go!" Mom still wasn't ready and Lucy started to stomp her foot. Then mom finally grabbed her shoes and said, "Come on! Let's go for a walk!"

Lucy and mom put on the leash and went outside. Lucy shouted with happiness, "Yay! Walk time!" Mom laughed and said, "Let's go explore the park." 

So they walked through the park, exploring the trees and flowers. Lucy shouted with joy, "Let's go this way!" Mom laughed and said, "Yes, let's go!"

And so they continued walking, exploring the park and having fun.
