Once there was a fierce dog called Smokey. Smokey was always very grumpy and he hated taking his daily walk. One morning, Smokey's owner decided to try something new. She put a battery in Smokey's collar and told him it was time for their walk. Smokey barked and growled in protest but the battery released a noise that scared him. So, Smokey reluctantly followed his owner outside. 

On the walk, Smokey didn't bark as much and he even seemed a little happier! He sniffed around and even wagged his tail at some of the other dogs. When it was finally time to go home, Smokey was surprisingly content. The battery made a great difference in Smokey's behavior and his owner smiled with satisfaction. 

From then on, Smokey looked forward to his daily walk and the battery helped him to behave. Smokey no longer hated his walks and was much friendlier to others. The battery allowed Smokey to enjoy his daily walks with his owner and that made them both very happy.
