Once upon a time there were two bears. One was named Peter and the other was named Lime. Peter was a big, strong bear with lots of nice fur. Lime was a little, ugly bear and had only a few patches of fur. 

One day, Peter and Lime decided to number. Together they counted to ten, but then Lime got confused. He couldn't remember the numbers, so he started to cry. 

Peter saw that Lime was feeling sad, so he gave him a big hug. "Don't worry," he said. "I will help you learn the numbers." Peter slowly counted the numbers again, starting with one. He helped Lime count up to ten. 

Once Lime had learned all the numbers, he was so happy. He thanked Peter and gave him a big hug. "You are the best, Peter," he said. 

With a smile, Peter replied: "It was my pleasure, Lime. Let's count together again soon!"
<|end|>


