Once upon a time there were two friends called Jack and Joe. Every day they would play together and have lots of fun. 

One day Jack had an idea. He said: "Let's play dress up!" So they got out all their clothes and got changed. Joe put on his red pants and Jack put on his blue ones.

Once they were dressed up, they decided to play hide and seek. Joe ran away and looked for a good hiding place. He found a spot behind the sofa and waited for Jack to try and find him. 

Jack counted to ten as loudly as he could. Then he started looking for Joe. He looked everywhere - under the bed, inside the wardrobe and behind the curtains. But he couldn't find Joe.

Suddenly, Joe jumped out from behind the sofa and shouted "Boo!" He had been hiding there the whole time! Jack was so surprised he laughed out loud. The two of them hugged each other and it was the best game of hide and seek they had ever played!
