Once upon a time, there was a very small and scared bunny. He was all alone in the forest, with no one to help him. He wanted to run away, but he was too scared. All around him were tall trees and long twigs. 

Suddenly, he heard a loud noise and he jumped up in surprise. He started to run away, as fast as his little legs could go. He was scared and didn't know where to go!

He ran towards a big bush and hid between the leaves. He was safe there, but he was still very scared. 

He stayed there for a while, until he saw a long twig sticking out of the bush. He grabbed it and used it to push away the leaves. As he looked out, he saw a big meadow with lots of green grass. He smiled, he wasn't scared anymore! 

He stepped out of the bush and ran towards the meadow. The grass felt so soft underneath his tiny feet. He had found a safe place to stay!
