Once upon a time there lived a dove. The dove was very sad and every night it would weep. It wept and wept until one day, something special happened.

One warm summer evening, the dove was sitting alone in the trees, looking out across the meadows. All of a sudden, up in the clouds appeared something different. It was beautiful and shines with a golden light. 

The dove was speechless, unsure of what to do. Then all of a sudden the dove stopped weeping and its eyes started to sparkle. The dove had found its new home, in the clouds.

The dove now had a place to be happy and safe. It no longer had to worry about sadness or loneliness, for it now had a place it could call home. 

The dove and the clouds became friends, and as the sun sets over the meadows, the dove and its new friends laughed, sang and soared in the sky. 

The dove no longer wept, because it had found a special friend, different from all the others.
