Once upon a time there was a flea that lived in a sunny spot. She liked the bright light. Every day, the flea would move around the warm spot. She jumped and hopped and played. 

The flea heard some loud noises coming from the other side of town. Curious, she decided to move in that direction. As she moved closer, the loud noises got louder and louder. What was making so much noise? 

When the flea arrived at the source of the noise, she saw lots of people playing music and singing. There were also lots of people dancing. Everyone was having fun and being very loud! 

The flea enjoyed watching and listening to the music. She even joined in with her tiny little jumps. Sooner or later, it was time to leave and the flea said goodbye to all the people. 

As the flea moved away, she heard the loud music and the happy sounds of laughter. She was glad that she had decided to move in that direction and find out what was making all the noise.
<|end|>


