George was so excited. He and his mother were going to go on a ride. His mother was holding his hand as they walked to the hidden place. George had never been to this place before. 

When they arrived, there was a tall horse with a saddle. His mother helped him climb onto the horse and she grabbed the reins. Then, she hopped on and George had his arms around his mother. He felt so secure and happy. 

The horse started to move and it felt so exciting for George. His mother trotted the horse around the field, which was full of tall grasses. There were birds singing and George could smell the sweet, fresh air. 

After a while, the horse slowed and the two of them were back where they started. George was so sad to leave the hidden place. But his mother promised they would come back again. He smiled, knowing he would get to ride with his mother again soon.
<|end|>


