When Jane arrived at the park, she saw a big, long bench. She ran to it and said "I want to load the bench!" She hopped on the bench and sat down.

Then, a smart, little bird flew down and sat on the bench too. Jane was very surprised and started giggling. She and the bird talked and laughed until the sun set.

Jane had so much fun that day. She loaded the bench with wonderful memories of her adventure at the park. She was so excited to have made a new feathered friend!
