Once upon a time, there was a small sausage. The sausage wanted to hide, so it tried to find a safe place. It looked in the kitchen, but it was too noisy. It looked under the bed, but it was too dusty. Finally, it found a perfect place. It hopped into a little crack in the wall and hid.

The sausage stayed inside the wall for a long time. It was so quiet there and felt completely safe. Suddenly, it heard a noise. It was a small mouse! The mouse had seen the sausage hiding in the wall. The mouse asked, "Can I play with you?"

The sausage was so happy! It was no longer alone. The sausage and the mouse played together for a long time. They laughed and jumped and danced around. Finally, it was time to go home. The mouse scurried away and the sausage hopped back into the wall to hide again. 

The small sausage was happy that it had a new friend. It was also glad that it had such a great place to hide.
