Old Albert was very dizzy. He was so dizzy that he couldn't do anything without getting confused. One day, his daughter Sarah asked if she could have permission to go on an adventure. Old Albert wasn't sure if he should permit her to go. He didn't want her to get lost. 

Sarah kept asking permission to go, but Albert still felt uneasy. Then, one day Albert had a new idea. He said he would permit Sarah to go if she promised to be careful and never go too far away.

Sarah was so excited and thanked her father for permitting her to go. She grabbed her coat and ran out the door. She ran this way and that way and hopped over stones and around trees. Albert watched from his porch and smiled, knowing that Sarah was having a wonderful adventure and that he had permitted it.
