His mom was in the kitchen. He was still scared but his mom hugged him and made him feel safe. He felt better and went back outside but this time he didn't venture so far. 

He sat down in the grass and stuck his thumb in his mouth. He looked about and suddenly realized his thumb was very important. He enjoyed tasting his thumb so he decided to keep it there. 

He looked around and spotted some birds and butterflies. He was very happy to see them again and he stayed in the garden all afternoon, enjoying the afternoon sun and his important thumb.
