Once upon a time there was a kind, compassionate cheese named Cheese. Cheese was very warm and friendly, but he didn't know many people.

One day, Cheese went for a walk in the park and he saw a little girl. He waved hello and the girl smiled back. Cheese felt so happy! Cheese and the girl became fast friends.

That evening Cheese asked the girl, "What do you know?" The girl thought for a moment and then said, "I know how to be kind to others and I know how to show compassion." Cheese was so happy that he jumped up and down.

The girl and Cheese spent many days together, learning new things and having fun. Cheese taught her how to make cheese sandwiches and the girl showed Cheese how to play tag. They both laughed and enjoyed their time together.

Cheese and the girl became very close and together they shared their knowledge and love of cheese. They both learned a lot from each other and they both grew to be much more compassionate and kind. The girl was very glad she met Cheese and Cheese was so grateful that he had a friend.
