One morning, Joe was in a hurry. He grabbed his hat and ran outside. He saw his mom and dad in the garden. They were picking big, juicy tomatoes.

"Mom! Dad!" yelled Joe.

His mom smiled and said, "Good morning, Joe! What do you need?"

Joe said, "I need some milk. Can I get some, please?"

His dad laughed and said, "Of course! We have plenty of milk. Come and I'll get it for you."

Joe's dad carried him to the kitchen. He filled a cup full of cold, white milk. Joe grabbed the cup and gulped it down. He was so glad he had milk.

Joe thanked his dad and ran back outside. The tomatoes were ready, so they all picked them together. Joe was glad they were done in time to go to the park. They all hurried to the park, and had a wonderful day.
