Then, the friends saw something crawling in the water. It was a little frog! The frog asked the friends to help him find his family. So, the friends said yes and they all went searching together.

They searched and searched, but they couldn't find the frog's family. So, the rabbit and mouse said goodbye to the frog and left. They promised the frog that they'd come back and look for his family the next day.

The rabbit and mouse waved goodbye to the frog, and hopped back home. Even though they didn't find the frog's family, they had a wonderful day together.
