Once upon a time there was a little boy called Joe. Joe was a very happy little boy who loved to play. One day Joe was playing with a pen and some ink. All of a sudden, some of the ink flew up and tickled Joe's nose. So he started to sneeze.

Joe's sneeze was so powerful it sent the ink flying up into the air. The ink spread out everywhere and the room suddenly turned into a bright, light blue! Joe was so amazed. He had never seen anything like it before.

Joe decided to use his ink to create pictures. He spread out the ink on the walls, the floor and even on the ceiling. It was so much fun! He created all kinds of beautiful light blue pictures. Joe was so proud of his creations.

The next day, Joe liked to show off his artwork to his friends. He told them about the sneeze and the wonderful light blue pictures he had created. Everyone was amazed and impressed! Soon, other people in the neighborhood heard about Joe's story, and so the story of the Ink sneeze was spread far and wide.
