When Amy got there, she couldn't find any candy that she liked. Every kind of candy looked the same.

Then, Amy spotted something in the back of the store. It was a clear jar full of small, colorful pieces of candy. Amy was very excited and asked the shopkeeper if she could have some candy. The shopkeeper smiled and gave her the clear jar of candy. 

Amy was so happy! She thanked the shopkeeper and ran back home. When she got there, her mom was impressed with Amy's amazing find. She said to Amy, "Well done! I can't believe you found such amazing candy. You should go back to the store and get some more". So Amy put on her shoes and happily returned to the store.
