Once upon a time, there was a nurse. She was very kind and always helping people. She worked at the hospital, taking care of all the sick children. 

One day she noticed one of the rooms was empty. She wondered why nobody was inside it. Then she noticed a little boy. He was standing by the window and looking up at the sky. 

The nurse smiled and asked him what he was doing. The boy said he was looking for rainbows. So the nurse told him they weren't in the sky, they were in his heart. 

The boy smiled and the nurse asked him if he would like to play a game. The little boy said yes, so the nurse said they had to find claps in the room. The boy was very excited and started to look around. 

Suddenly the little boy shouted out "I found them!" 
He had found all the claps in the room and he was so proud of himself that he started to applaud. 

The nurse applauded too, and then she gave him a big hug. It was such a lovely moment and everyone in the room was so filled with joy that they all applauded together. 

The end.
