So she grabbed the branch and took it down to the river. Then she washed it with her hands. The water made the branch look sparkly and clean!

When Gracie was finished washing the branch, she put it back in its original spot. Everyone was so happy because the branch finally looked nice and tidy.

Gracie felt very proud of herself for making the branch clean. From that day on, she made sure to keep it neat and tidy.
