Once there was a little soldier. He was brave and strong. One cold and icy day, he ventured out into the woods. He saw a small log, and decided to take a rest. He sat down, and started to rub his hands together to keep warm. As he rubbed and rubbed, he noticed a bright light in the distance.

He hopped up and started to walk towards the light. As he got closer, he heard the sound of voices getting louder and louder. Finally, he made it to the clearing and saw a group of soldiers around a campfire. The little soldier waved, but no one noticed him.

So he started to quietly rub his hands together again. Suddenly, a soldier noticed him and jumped up. With a big smile, the soldier welcomed him to the campfire. The little soldier was so happy and he sat down with all the other soldiers.

They put a big blanket around him and he sat there, rubbing his hands and feeling the warmth from the fire. He was so happy and thankful for the kind soldier. He had found a new home.
<|end|>


