The other baby was confused and scared. He wanted to help, but he didn't know what to do. He looked around and saw the crib. He remembered that when he was feeling scared, his mom would put him back in his crib. 

He grabbed the screaming baby and gently laid her in the crib. Sure enough, the baby stopped screaming and soon fell fast asleep. 

The other baby was amazed. He was proud of himself for being so independent and helping his friend. He realized that he was very capable of solving problems by himself.
