Once upon a time there was a tiny bird in a backyard. The bird's feathers were yellow and green, and it could sing the prettiest songs. One day, the bird's wings started to feel heavy so it decided to take a rest. Suddenly, the bird felt a cold breeze and the backyard got dark. When the bird opened its eyes, it saw that the sky was filled with black clouds.

The bird knew that it was in danger. It flapped its wings and flew into the sky. But the sky kept getting darker. Then the wind started to blow harder and the bird grew tired. The bird knew it could no longer fly, so it decided to find a safe place to rest.

Suddenly, the bird saw a dead tree in the backyard. It flew to the tree and perched on the branch. The bird listened to the wind and watched the darkness rise. Then it felt the rain.

The bird stayed on the dead tree for a long time, until the storm was over. Finally, when the sun came out, the bird opened its wings and flew away back to safety in the backyard.
<|end|>


