Once upon a time, there was a big, smelly skeleton. It lived in a dark, dank cave that nobody ever visited. The skeleton was sad, so it decided to stretch its arms and legs. It reached up as high as it could, and then down as low as it could.

As it stretched, the smelly skeleton heard a sound. It heard somebody else in the cave! It was scared, so it stopped stretching. But then it heard a kind voice that said, "It's ok! I won't hurt you. I just wanted to play with you."

The skeleton was so happy to have a friend. They stretched their arms and legs together and laughed. When they were done stretching, the skeleton smiled, and thanked his new friend for being so nice.

From that day on, the skeleton wasn't alone anymore. It had a friend who would come and visit it in the dark, smelly cave. They would always stretch together and have fun.
<|end|>


