Once upon a time there was an old mattress. The mattress was quite clever. It had been in the same bedroom since the day it was born. But now it was starting to rot.

The mattress was sad and embarrassed. It knew its days were numbered, and it didn't want anyone to see it in its sorry state.

One day, a little toddler came into the bedroom. He had never seen a mattress before, and he was very curious. He walked up to it and said, "What's that?"

The mattress was scared, but it found its courage. It explained to the child why it was starting to rot. The little toddler was so impressed. He said, "I'm going to help you!"

He grabbed some cleaning supplies and began to scrub the mattress. After a few minutes of hard work, the mattress began to look better. The toddler had worked so hard, and the mattress was so grateful!

The toddler had been so clever, and the mattress was thankful. It wouldn't have to worry about its rotting anymore. They both smiled and the bedroom was filled with happiness. The end.
<|end|>


