Once upon a time there was a little girl called Lucy. She loved playing outdoors in her garden. One day, when she was playing, she discovered a small onion. It was so little that it was almost hidden in the grass.

Lucy was so excited to find the onion and she shouted 'Onion!' as loud as she could. All the animals in the garden heard her and ran away. She laughed and laughed, enjoying her discovery.

But then a big surprise happened. After Lucy shouted, an onion monster appeared! It was very big and had lots of onions around it.

Lucy was very scared, so she waved her hands and shouted 'Go away!' The onion monster was so surprised that it ran away and disappeared!

Lucy was so proud of herself for getting rid of the onion monster. From that day on, she always kept an eye out for little onions in the garden.
