Once upon a time, there was a beautiful princess. She lived in the castle with her family. One day, the princess decided to go for a walk in the misty forest. As she walked, the princess saw something very impressive. 

She did not recognize it, so she cautiously walked closer. As she got closer, she saw that it was a dragon. The dragon had scales of all different shades of green and a long, spiralling tail. The princess was amazed! She thought it was the most impressive thing she had ever seen.

The princess and the dragon looked at each other. After a few moments, the dragon bent down and put its head close to the princess. The princess realized the dragon was not dangerous at all. She reached out and the dragon let her pet it.

The dragon liked the princess and from then on, they were friends! The princess started visiting the forest every day to see her dragon friend. Every time, the mist enclosed them as the princess interacted with her new friend. It was an impressive sight to behold.
