Once, there was a little girl called Lucy. She loved to explore the garden, and she always wore a fur coat that Daddy had made for her. 

One day when she was out playing, she saw a big, colourful butterfly. She wondered what it was doing. She watched carefully, and the butterfly fluttered around the garden.

After a minute it flew away, and Lucy went looking for the butterfly. She searched among the flowers and trees, under the bushes and over the fences. Finally she spotted the butterfly, and it landed on her fur coat. She wondered why the butterfly had chosen her coat to land on. 

Lucy held out her finger, and the butterfly landed on it. It felt so nice and soft. She looked at the butterfly and saw it's beautiful, colourful wings. She smiled, and walked on.

Lucy was happy, and she felt so nice in her fur coat. She enjoyed the rest of her day wandering in the garden, wondering what else she might find.
