Once upon a time, there was a thin man. He wanted something that wasn't his. So, he decided to steal it. He crept to the picture, lifted it up very softly and ran away.

The picture was very special - it was an image of a beautiful princess. He wanted it very much. He took it back to his house, and put it on his wall.

But then the princess saw him. She was very, very angry. She came to his house and shouted, "that is my picture! You stole it!"

The man was very sad. He apologised to the princess and offered to give her back her picture. The princess smiled and accepted the picture. She said that it was his now - but, he had to promise to be more careful with what he took.

The man was very happy, and he thanked the princess. From that day on, he was more careful with what he took, and he never tried to steal something that didn't belong to him again.
