Once upon a time there was a potato. It was a big and round potato. Every day it would stretch and grow a bit bigger. This interested the little girl who lived nearby. She loved to watch the potato stretch and she visited it everyday. Every time she saw it, it had grown bigger. She soon started to give it a special name; Mr. Stretchy Potato. 

One day, Mr Stretchy Potato was so big that it popped. This made the little girl so happy that she danced around and clapped her hands. When she opened the potato, she was even more excited! Inside was a surprise; a little toy rabbit! The rabbit was very cute and she named him Floppy Ear. 

The little girl and Floppy Ear were best friends. Together they would go on adventures, play in the garden and help around the house. And best of all, they would go and visit Mr Stretchy Potato every day and see how much he had grown. 


The end.
