Once upon a time, there was a little boy. His name was Jack, and he was three years old. He had a dependable friend, her name was Jill.

One day, Jack wanted to grow bigger. He wanted to be like the big boys. Jill had an idea. She told Jack that if he put on a special vest, he would grow bigger.

Jack was excited. He raced to the closet and grabbed the vest. He put it on as fast as he could.

Jack waited and waited, but he didn't grow bigger. He was sad. But then Jill said something. She reminded Jack that being dependable was bigger than any vest. Jack smiled. He finally understood. He could be big just by being dependable.
