Once, there was a yummy bookshelf in a room. The bookshelf was filled with books, and a little mouse and a big bear both wanted the bookshelf. The bear said, "I should have the bookshelf, because it is so big and I'm so strong, I can take it away." The mouse disagreed. She said, "I should have it, because I'm smaller and I can fit more books in it." The bear and the mouse had a big disagreement. Then, they decided to ask the wise owl. The wise owl said, "You can both have the bookshelf. You can share it." The bear and the mouse were very happy. They both had a yummy bookshelf and they agreed to share it together.
