Once upon a time, there was a gray flower in a meadow. One day the flower said that the meadow was very wonderful. But the cloud in the sky disagreed. The cloud said the meadow was too green and not enough blue. The flower and the cloud did not agree.

The wind came and said to the flower and the cloud, "Let's try something else." The wind blew high and strong, and made the cloud turn into lots of raindrops. The raindrops made the meadow turn from green to blue.

The flower and the cloud looked around and smiled. They both agreed that the meadow was now very wonderful. The flower smiled and said, "I'm so happy we could disagree."
