Once upon a time, there was a dark parrot who lived in a tree. He loved to look down on all of the animals in the forest who ran around playing.

One day, a tiger came stomping out of the trees. He was scary and he wanted to hurt the animals. The parrot flew down and hovered above the tiger. He shouted to the animals to get away.

The parrot flapped his wings and flew around the tiger, trying to keep him away. He flew higher and higher, until the tiger could not reach him. The other animals were safe!

The parrot protected the animals and they all sang him a thank you song. He looked back from the sky and smiled. He was happy to help and he knew he made a difference.
