Once there was a girl who had long and beautiful hair. Her hair was a gleaming, golden colour and it shone in the sun. One day, the girl asked her mum for a special request - she wanted to go to the hairdresser's to have her hair cut.

So, the girl and her mum went to the hairdresser's. The hairdresser asked the girl what style she would like, but all the girl could say was "CUT". And so the hairdresser cut her hair. When the girl looked in the mirror, she saw that her hair was bad. It was too short and it didn't look nice.

The girl was very sad and she wanted to fix her hair. So she asked her mum if they could go to the hairdresser's again. Her mum said they could, but they had to wait until her hair grew back.

The girl was very patient and she waited every day until her hair was long again. After a few months, her hair was back to how it used to be and it was beautiful.

The girl learnt her lesson - next time, she won't make the same bad request.
