Once upon a time there was a wise old man. He carried a cane and he always had a smile on his face.

One day, the man set his cane down and he started to walk. He walked a long way until he saw a lake. He settled down by the lake and looked up at the sky.

The wise old man stayed at the lake for a long time. He watched the birds flying and the fish swimming. The man settled into the calmness and enjoyed the peace of nature.

But then one day, a storm came and it knocked the man's cane into the lake. The old man tried to dive in and find it, but it was too deep. He was sad and he knew he wouldn't get home without it.

Suddenly, a fish swam up and put the man's cane in his hand. It was amazing! The wise old man was so grateful.

He thanked the fish and then settled back by the lake, this time with his cane. He rested there until the storm passed.

The wise old man was happy to have his cane and he went back home with a smile on his face.
<|end|>


