One day, a hunter was walking through a forest. Suddenly, she saw a small animal stuck in a trap! She knew she had to help it. Quickly, the hunter ran over to the animal. She carefully used her hands to help free the animal. Then, the hunter carefully carried the animal away to safety.

The animal was so impressed by the hunter's help. It was so thankful to be safe! It wanted to thank the hunter in some way. So, the animal ran off and came back with a special gift. It was a rainbow coloured feather! The hunter was so surprised. She had never seen a feather like it. She felt so happy to have saved the animal - it was so impressive!

The hunter took the feather home and kept it to remember her special day. She never forgot how brave she had been to save the animal. The hunter kept the feather safe for many years, and it always reminded her of her incredible journey.
