Mama and Papa were measuring the wall. Mama said, " We need to measure to see if our new cabinet will fit!"
Papa was careful as he measured. He made marks on the wall with a pen so he could remember where the cabinet would go.

After Papa finished measuring, he went to the store to look for a cabinet. He saw a big cabinet with lots of shelves.

When Papa brought the cabinet back, it was dirty. Mama said, "Let's clean it before we put it up!"

Papa and Mama scrubbed the cabinet with soap and water until it was shining like new.

Then Papa got his tools out and he used the marks on the wall to help him put the cabinet up. When he was finished, the cabinet was secured on the wall.

Mama said, "Now we have a place to keep our things!"
