Then she asked her mom "What can I do with this cardboard?" Her mom said, "Why don't you make a special project?". Lisa thought it was a great idea and started to build a castle.

She used the cardboard as walls and to build towers. She even used her felt tip markers to make a beautiful flag for the castle! When she finished, she was very proud of herself.

Her mom was so impressed she decided to place Lisa's castle in the front yard so everyone walking past could admire it.

From that day on, Lisa knew just how important it was to take care of the environment and reuse things like cardboard.
