Once upon a time, there was a little girl who was very stubborn. She always wanted to do what she wanted to do and nothing else.

One day, the little girl decided that she wanted to mail the sunrise. She got an envelope, put the sunrise inside, and then wrote a note on the envelope. She stuck a stamp on the envelope and gave it to the mailman.

He was very surprised, but he mailed it anyway!

The next morning, when the sun rose in the sky, it was the same sunrise that the little girl had mailed the day before! Everyone was amazed and they all cheered.

The stubborn little girl had done the impossible - she had mailed the sunrise!
<|end|>


