Once upon a time there was a girl who was very worried. She was worried about a story she had heard. When she asked her mum what the story was, her mum only smiled and said nothing.

The girl said again: "Mum, why can't you tell me the story?" 

Her mum replied: "I think it's for you to find out."

The girl was even more worried but decided to look for the story. She asked everyone she knew but nobody could tell her.

Then one day, while she was walking in the garden, she saw an old lady who was smiling. She asked the old lady her question and the old lady replied: 

"Why don't you look up at the stars and tell me a story?" 

The girl looked at the stars and thought of all the stories she knew. She closed her eyes and when she opened them, a big bright star was shining right in front of her. She felt happy knowing that she had found the story she was looking for.
