Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside and collect pretty flowers. One day, she found a shiny rock and showed it to her mommy. 

"Wow, that's beautiful!" said her mommy. "How much did it cost?"

"It didn't cost anything, mommy," replied Lily. "It was just lying on the ground."

Her mommy smiled and said, "That's wonderful, Lily. You don't always have to pay a price for something special."

Later that day, Lily's friend came over to play. They decided to make cupcakes, but it got very messy in the kitchen. When Lily's mommy saw the messy kitchen, she said, "Oh my! What a messy kitchen! You girls need to clean up this mess."

Lily's friend said, "I didn't make the mess, Lily did!"

Lily looked at her friend and said, "That's not true, you're lying! We both made the mess, so we both need to clean it up."

And so, Lily and her friend cleaned up the messy kitchen together and learned that it's always better to tell the truth.
<|end|>


