Once upon a time, there was a dog named Max. Max loved to play outside and chase squirrels. One day, Max saw a collar on the ground. It was a messy collar with dirt and leaves all over it. Max picked up the collar in his mouth and ran to his owner, Lily.

"Lily, look what I found!" Max said, dropping the collar at her feet.

"Oh, Max, that's not ours. It belongs to someone else," Lily said.

Max looked sad. "Can I keep it?" he asked.

"No, Max. That wouldn't be right. We need to find the owner," Lily explained.

Just then, a little girl came running up to them. "That's my dog's collar!" she said, taking it from Max's mouth. Max didn't mean to bite it, but he was just trying to play. The little girl thanked Max for finding it and Max wagged his tail happily.
