Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to look at the stars at night. One day, she saw a shooting star and made a wish. "I wish to be smart," she said.

The next day, Lily went to school and her friend Tommy asked her to cheat on a test. "No, Tommy. Cheating is bad. It's not smart," Lily said.

Tommy shook his head and said, "But I don't know the answers."

"That's okay. We can study together and learn," Lily replied.

In the end, Lily and Tommy studied together and both did well on the test. Lily felt happy that she did the right thing and learned that being smart isn't just about knowing the answers, it's about doing what's right.
<|end|>


