Once upon a time, there was a little dog named Spot. Spot loved to run and play outside in the grass. One day, Spot saw a tiny bug jumping around on his fur. It was a flea! Spot didn't like fleas because they made him itchy. 

Spot tried to catch the flea with his paws, but it was too fast. Spot got a crazy idea. He ran to his owner and barked until she came outside. Spot's owner saw the flea and said, "That's a tiny bug!" Spot barked again and his owner got a magnifying glass to see the flea better. 

Spot's owner said, "Wow, that's a big number of fleas on you! We need to give you a bath." Spot didn't like baths, but he was happy to get rid of the fleas. After his bath, Spot felt much better and went back to playing in the grass.
