Once upon a time, there was a kind little duck. He liked to swim in the pond and play with his friends. One day, he saw a big apple on a tree and wanted to eat it. He climbed up the tree but then he fell down and hurt his wing.

His friend, the frog, saw what happened and said, "Oh no! Are you okay, little duck?"

The duck replied, "No, I hurt my wing. I can't fly anymore."

The frog said, "Don't worry, I'll help you. I'll bring you some food and keep you company until you feel better."

The little duck was very happy to have such a kind friend. From that day on, they played together every day and the duck's wing got better. They never forgot the time when the duck fell from the tree, but they were glad it brought them closer together.
