Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play with his toys, especially his toy car. He would zoom it around the house all day long. One day, Timmy's car stopped moving. He looked at it and saw that the battery was dead. Timmy was sad because he couldn't play with his car anymore.

Timmy's mommy saw him looking sad and asked him what was wrong. Timmy told her about his car and the dead battery. His mommy said not to worry and went to get a new battery. Timmy watched as his mommy put the new battery in his car. He was so happy to see his car move again, he couldn't stop gazing at it.

But then, Timmy's little sister came and took his car away. Timmy got angry and started crying. His mommy came over and asked what happened. Timmy told her about his sister taking his car. His mommy talked to his sister and gave Timmy his car back. Timmy was happy again and continued to play with his car all day long.
