Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to chew on gum all day long. One day, she found a vine that was very thin and she decided to chew on it. 

Lily chewed and chewed on the vine, but it didn't taste very good. She thought to herself, "I shouldn't have chewed on this vine, it's not yummy like my gum." 

Later that day, Lily's mom made her a sandwich for lunch. As Lily took a bite, she noticed something hard in her mouth. She spit it out and saw that it was a small piece of the vine she had chewed on earlier. She realized that sometimes things that look fun to chew on aren't always good for you. 

From that day on, Lily only chewed on her favorite gum and never on any vines again.
