Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to eat candy and play with his toys. One day, he saw his dog chewing on his shoe. Timmy said, "Bad dog! Don't eat my shoe!" 

Later that day, Timmy's friend Billy came over to play. Billy had a lot of toys and Timmy was jealous. Timmy said, "Billy, you are so rich! I wish I had more toys like you." 

Billy replied, "Timmy, having a lot of toys doesn't make you rich. Being happy and having good friends is what makes you rich." 

Timmy thought about what Billy said and realized that he was right. From that day on, Timmy was happy with what he had and knew that having good friends was the most important thing.
