Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play in the park with her friends. One day, while playing hide-and-seek, Lily disturbed a big, wild bird. The bird flew away, but Lily felt bad for bothering it.

Later, Lily and her friends saw a pretty flower. They wanted to touch it, but it was on a high branch. "How can we get it?" asked Lily. "Maybe we can ask the bird to help us," suggested her friend. So, they called for the bird and asked it to get the flower for them. The bird was happy to help and flew up to the branch. It plucked the flower with its beak and gave it to the children.

"Thank you, bird!" said Lily. "You're welcome," replied the bird. "But please don't disturb me again, okay?" Lily promised not to disturb the bird anymore, and they all played happily in the park.
