Once upon a time, there was a monkey named Bobo. Bobo loved bananas, and he had a fancy hat that he wore all the time. One day, Bobo was eating a banana in the forest when he heard a loud noise.

"Listen, what's that sound?" Bobo said to his friend, a bird named Tweetie.

"I don't know," Tweetie said. "Let's go see what it is."

As they got closer, they saw that a tree had fallen down and was blocking the path. A group of animals were standing around, trying to figure out what to do.

Bobo had an idea. "I can use my fancy hat to help us move the tree!" he said. And with his hat, they were able to push the tree out of the way.

The animals were grateful and thanked Bobo for his help. Bobo felt happy that he could use his fancy hat to make a difference.

The moral of the story is that even small things, like a fancy hat or a banana, can be used to help others. And if we listen to the sounds around us, we might be able to find ways to help too.
