Once upon a time, there was a boy named Timmy who had a big boo-boo on his knee. He went to the doctor's office and sat in the waiting room with other sick kids. Timmy was very patient and waited for his turn to see the doctor. 

When it was finally Timmy's turn, the doctor gave him a little pill to make the boo-boo go away. Timmy took the pill and felt much better. He thanked the doctor and went home with his mom. 

Later that night, Timmy started to cry. His knee hurt again and he couldn't sleep. His mom tried to help him, but the little pill didn't work anymore. Timmy cried and cried until his mom took him back to the doctor. 

The doctor said that Timmy needed a big operation to fix his knee. Timmy was scared, but his mom told him it would be okay. The next day, Timmy went to the hospital for the operation. The doctor put him to sleep and fixed his knee. When Timmy woke up, he felt much better. But he had a big bandage on his knee and couldn't play outside for a while.
<|end|>


