Once upon a time, there was a little bird named Bob. Bob had a black feather on his shoulder that he was very proud of. One day, he saw his friends working hard to build their nests. Bob thought he didn't need to work because he had a beautiful black feather on his shoulder.

Days went by and Bob was still sitting on a tree branch, watching his friends work. But one day, a big storm came and destroyed all the nests except for Bob's friend's nest. Bob realized that he should have worked hard too, just like his friends. He learned that having a beautiful feather on his shoulder was not as important as working hard to keep himself safe.

From that day on, Bob worked hard to build his nest and never forgot the lesson he learned. He knew that having a strong home was better than having a pretty feather on his shoulder.
<|end|>


