Once upon a time, there was a little bird named Blue. Blue was very intelligent and loved to fly around the forest. Blue had many friends, but he always wanted to have more. One day, Blue saw a big bird with many feathers. Blue thought to himself, "I want to be friends with that bird."

So, Blue planned to impress the big bird with his flying skills. Blue practiced every day and became very good at flying. He finally felt ready to show off his skills to the big bird. Blue flew up high in the sky and did many tricks. The big bird was impressed and they became friends.

However, Blue's other friends were not happy that he had a new friend. They started to argue and fight with Blue. Blue tried to make peace between his friends, but it did not work. One day, Blue was flying with his new friend when a storm came. Blue's friends were stuck in the storm and Blue had to choose who to help. Blue chose to help his new friend and left his old friends behind.

In the end, Blue realized that his plan to impress the big bird was not worth losing his old friends. Blue was sad and alone without his friends. He learned that true peace and happiness come from being kind to others and not just trying to impress them.
<|end|>


