Once upon a time, there was a girl named Lily. She loved to play in the garden with her spade. One day, while she was digging, she found a big, shiny rock. She was so happy and showed it to her mom.

Mom: "Wow, Lily! That's a beautiful rock. Where did you find it?"

Lily: "I found it in the garden while digging with my spade."

Mom: "That's amazing, Lily! But remember, we should always ask before taking things that don't belong to us. Do you understand?"

Lily nodded her head, feeling guilty for taking the rock without asking. She promised to always ask before taking things from now on. From that day on, Lily learned to be a responsible and honest girl. She continued to play with her spade and found many more treasures in the garden, always asking before taking them.
<|end|>


