Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to explore and play in the woods behind his house. One day, he found a big wrecked car. The car was all smashed up and broken. Timmy wanted to examine it closer, but he didn't know how to open the door.

Just then, Timmy's friend Billy came by. "What are you doing?" asked Billy. "I found a wrecked car, but I can't open the door to examine it," said Timmy. "Let me try," said Billy. Billy knew just what to do. He pulled on the door handle and it opened right up.

But inside the car, they found a wallet. "What should we do with it?" asked Timmy. "We should give it to the police," said Billy. So they took the wallet to the police station. The police officer was very happy and thanked them for being honest. Timmy and Billy felt proud that they did the right thing.

The moral of the story is that it's important to be honest and do the right thing, even if it's hard.
<|end|>


