Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy liked to play outside with his friends. One day, Timmy and his friends were playing soccer when Timmy stumbled and fell down. His friends helped him up and asked if he was okay.

Timmy said, "I'm okay, thank you for helping me." His friends smiled and continued playing.

Later that day, Timmy's mom asked him to help her sort the recycling. Timmy saw a lot of waste that could have been recycled. He said to his mom, "Mom, we should recycle more so we don't waste so much."

His mom was proud of Timmy for being so thoughtful. She said, "You're right, Timmy. Let's recycle more."

Timmy felt happy that he helped his mom and the environment. He looked up at the sky and saw the beautiful blue color. He said, "The sky is so blue, it's my favorite color."

His mom smiled and said, "That's a great choice, Timmy. Blue is a wonderful color."

The moral of the story is that even when we stumble, we have friends to help us up. And we should always try to reduce waste and take care of our planet.
<|end|>


