Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a modest bed in her room, but she loved it very much. One day, Lily's mom came to her room and said, "Lily, we need to lock the door because we are going out." Lily asked, "Why do we need to lock the door?" Mom replied, "To keep our home safe from strangers." 

Lily didn't understand what "strangers" meant, so she asked, "What are strangers?" Mom explained, "Strangers are people we don't know. We don't want them to come inside our home when we are not here." Lily nodded her head and said, "Okay, let's lock the door." 

Mom and Lily went to the door and Mom locked it. Lily looked at her modest bed and said, "Goodbye bed, I will miss you." Mom smiled and said, "Don't worry, we will be back soon and you can play on your bed." Lily felt happy and went to play with her toys.
