Once upon a time, there was a little crab named Carl. Carl liked to play in the sand and look for shiny rocks. One day, Carl saw a shrimp that was stuck in a big shell. The shrimp was very sad and confused.

"Can you help me, please?" asked the shrimp.

Carl replied, "Yes, I can fix it!"

Carl used his strong claws to break open the shell and the shrimp was free. The shrimp was very happy and said, "Thank you so much, Carl! You're my hero!"

From that day on, Carl and the shrimp became best friends and they played in the sand together every day. Carl was happy that he could help his friend and fix the problem.
<|end|>


