Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a pet dog named Max. Max was very hairy and loved to play with Lily. One day, Lily and Max went to the park to play. They ran around and had so much fun.

Suddenly, Lily saw a sign that said "No Dogs Allowed". She was sad because she didn't want to leave Max behind. She asked Max, "What should we do? They don't want you here." Max barked and licked Lily's face. Then, Lily had an idea. She took a marker and made a mark on Max's fur to make him look like a different dog. 

They walked back to the park and the people didn't notice that Max was a dog. They thought he was a big, hairy stuffed animal! Lily and Max played all day and had a great time. When it was time to go home, Lily said to Max, "You're my best friend. I'll always love you, even if you're not allowed in the park." Max barked and wagged his tail, knowing he had the best friend in the world.
<|end|>


