Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play with his blue cube. He would stack it up high and knock it down like a tower. One day, Timmy went outside to play and saw some pretty flowers. He wanted to gather them for his mommy. 

Timmy walked through the grass and saw a big tree. He looked up and saw a squirrel gathering nuts. Timmy thought it was funny how the squirrel stored the nuts in a little hole. He wondered if he could gather things too. 

As Timmy picked the flowers, he saw a blue butterfly. It was fluttering its wings and looked so pretty. Timmy followed the butterfly and it led him to a pond. There, he saw some kids gathering rocks. Timmy joined in and they all gathered different colored rocks. 

When Timmy got home, he gave his mommy the flowers and showed her the rocks. She smiled and said, "Wow! You sure know how to gather things, Timmy!" Timmy felt proud and happy that he could gather things too, just like the squirrel and the kids at the pond.
<|end|>


