Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to read books with her mommy before bedtime. One day, they went to the store to buy candy. But Lily's mommy said they could only buy the cheap candy because they didn't have a lot of money. 

Lily was sad because she wanted the fancy candy with pretty colors. But then her mommy showed her a book about a princess who was kind and brave. Lily loved the story and forgot about the candy. She realized that reading books was even better than eating candy.

From that day on, Lily and her mommy read books every night before bed. And sometimes, they would have a little bit of cheap candy as a special treat.
