Once upon a time, there was a boy named Timmy. Timmy loved dressing up in costumes. His favorite costume was a superhero costume he got for his birthday. One day, Timmy went to the store with his mommy. He saw a costume he liked, but it was too expensive. Timmy's mommy said it was too expensive and they had to leave.

Timmy was sad, but then he saw a cheap costume on a shelf. It wasn't a superhero costume, but it was still cool. Timmy decided to take it, but he didn't pay for it. That means he stole it. When Timmy got home, he put on the costume and played with his toys. But he didn't feel good about stealing. The next day, Timmy told his mommy what he did and they went back to the store to return the stolen costume. Timmy learned that it's not okay to steal things, even if they are cheap.
