Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to jog around his backyard every day. One day, Timmy saw his neighbor, Billy, jogging too. Timmy said, "Hi Billy, do you want to jog with me?"

Billy said, "Yes, I would love to jog with you, Timmy!" So they started jogging together. After a while, Timmy's mom came outside with a jug of fuel for the lawnmower. Billy looked at the jug and said, "I'm envious of your fuel, Timmy. My dad needs to buy some for our lawnmower."

Timmy's mom overheard Billy and said, "Don't worry, Billy. We have plenty of fuel to share. Here, take some for your dad's lawnmower." Billy was so happy and thanked Timmy's mom. From that day on, Timmy and Billy jogged together every day and shared their fuel and toys with each other. The end.
