Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to listen to the birds sing outside her window every morning. One day, Lily's mommy asked her to go to bed early because she had to wake up early for school. Lily cuddled up with her favorite pillow and closed her eyes, but she couldn't sleep. 

"Mommy, I can't sleep," said Lily. 

"Close your eyes and listen to the sound of your breathing," replied her mommy. 

Lily did as her mommy said and soon fell asleep. The next morning, Lily woke up feeling refreshed and ready for school. She hugged her mommy and thanked her for the good night's sleep. From then on, Lily remembered to listen to her breathing and use her favorite pillow to help her fall asleep.
<|end|>


