Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a pretty dress with delicate flowers on it. One day, while she was playing outside, she fell down and got a big cut on her knee. Her mommy took her inside and stitched up her boo-boo. Lily was sad because she couldn't play outside anymore. But her mommy told her that her knee would grow stronger and she would be able to play again soon. And sure enough, after a few days, Lily's knee was all better and she could run and play outside again. The end.
