Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a small house with her mommy and daddy. One day, Lily went to the park to play with her friends. She saw a butterfly and tried to catch it, but it flew away.

Lily's friend, Timmy, came over and asked, "Why are you sad, Lily?"

"I wanted to catch the butterfly, but it flew away," Lily replied.

Timmy said, "Don't worry, Lily. You have the wisdom to know that the butterfly is meant to fly freely. Let's raise our hands and try to touch the sky instead."

Lily and Timmy raised their hands high and felt happy. They realized that being rich in friendship and love was more important than catching a butterfly.
