Once upon a time, there was a kind girl named Lily. She loved animals and would often play with them in the forest. One day, she found a hurt bird with a broken wing. She felt sad for the bird and wanted to help it.

Lily went to her dad, who worked as a veterinarian. She asked him to measure the bird's injury and fix its wing. Her dad was compassionate and agreed to help. He used a special tape measure to measure the bird's wing and then carefully fixed it.

The bird was now able to fly again, but there was a new problem. A big, mean cat saw the bird and wanted to eat it! Lily knew she had to protect the bird. She used a compass to draw a circle around the bird and told the cat it was her special area. The cat couldn't cross the line and the bird was safe.

From that day on, Lily made sure to always be compassionate and help animals in need.
<|end|>


