Once upon a time, there was a happy otter who lived by the river. The otter loved to play in the water and catch fish. One day, the otter met a little girl who was sad. The otter asked the girl why she was sad and the girl said that she lost her perfect toy.

The otter wanted to help the girl so he started to rub his nose against hers. Suddenly, the girl remembered where she left her toy. She thanked the otter and went to find her toy.

The otter was happy that he could help the little girl. He learned that helping others can make them happy and that made him happy too.
