Once upon a time, there was a nice boy named Tim. Tim loved to race with his friends. One day, Tim saw a big statue in the park. The statue was of a man running. Tim thought it was fun.

Tim's friend, Sue, came to the park too. She saw the statue and said, "Wow! Look at that big statue!" Tim said, "Yes, it's a man running. Let's race like him!" Sue agreed, and they both stood next to the statue, ready to race.

Tim and Sue raced from the statue to the big tree and back. They laughed and had fun. Tim won the race, but Sue didn't mind. They both had a great time racing like the statue. They went home tired, but happy.
