Once upon a time, in a small town, there was a boy named Tim. Tim was a little boy who liked to wear a uniform to school. One day, Tim saw a weird bird in his yard. The bird was very big and had many colors. Tim thought it was very cool.

The next day, Tim went to school and told his friends about the weird bird. His friends did not believe him. They said, "There is no such thing as a weird bird!" Tim was sad that his friends did not believe him. That night, Tim wished that the weird bird would come back and show his friends that it was real.

The next day, Tim and his friends were playing outside when they heard a loud noise. The weird bird was back! The bird had a big bag in its beak. It flew down and dropped the bag in front of Tim and his friends. They opened the bag and found that it was full of toys and treats! The weird bird had supplied them with lots of fun things to play with. Tim's friends were very sorry for not believing him, and they all played together with the toys and treats the weird bird had given them. From that day on, they always believed in the weird bird and the magic it brought to their lives.
