Once upon a time, there was a boy named Tim. Tim had a magic toy. The toy was very useful. It could help Tim find things he lost. One day, Tim lost his toy. He was very sad.

Tim asked his friend, Sam, "Did you see my magic toy?" Sam said, "No, but I can help you look." They looked everywhere, but they could not find the toy. Tim thought maybe someone had buried it.

Tim and Sam started to dig in the dirt. They dug and dug until they found the magic toy. Tim was so happy! He said, "Thank you, Sam, for helping me find my useful magic toy!"

From that day on, Tim and Sam always helped each other. They learned that being a good friend is the best kind of magic. And they never buried their toys again.
