Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little boy named Tim and his dog, Spot. Tim loved to play with Spot in the backyard. They would run, jump, and have so much fun together. Tim's friend, Sue, would watch them play from her window. She felt envious because she wanted to play in the backyard too.

One day, Sue went to Tim and said, "Can I play with you and Spot in the backyard?" Tim smiled and said, "Of course, Sue! We would love to have you play with us!" So, Sue, Tim, and Spot played together in the backyard. They had a great time, and Sue was very happy.

After a while, it was time for Sue to go home. She didn't want to leave, but her mom insisted. Sue said, "Thank you, Tim, for letting me play with you and Spot. I had so much fun!" Tim replied, "You're welcome, Sue! You can come and play with us anytime you want!" From that day on, Sue, Tim, and Spot played together in the backyard every day, and they all became the best of friends.
