Once upon a time, there was a little bird named Blue. Blue lived in a big tree with his family. They loved to fly high up in the sky.

One day, there were big, bad clouds in the sky. Blue's mom told him not to fly today. "Trust me," she said. But Blue wanted to fly and see his friend, Red.

Blue didn't listen to his mom. He flew into the sky with the bad clouds. It started to rain, and Blue got scared. He didn't know what to do.

Just then, Red came to help Blue. They flew back to the tree together. Blue was happy to see Red, but he knew he should have trusted his mom. From that day on, Blue always trusted his mom and stayed safe.
