Once upon a time, there was a big giant. He was very tall and strong. He could run very fast. He lived in a big house near the woods.

One day, a little girl went to the giant's house. She was very small, but she was not afraid. She had a request for the giant. She asked him to help her find her lost cat. The giant said yes and they started to look for the cat.

They looked all day and all night. The giant ran fast and the little girl ran slow. But they did not give up. At last, they found the cat. The giant and the little girl were very happy. They went back to the giant's house and had a big party.

The giant learned that it is good to help others, even if they are small. And the little girl learned that it is okay to ask for help, even from a giant. They became good friends and lived happily ever after.

The moral of the story is: always be kind and help others, no matter how big or small they are.
<|end|>


