Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. He had a toy fork that he loved very much. Tim's fork was always there for him, so he thought it was very reliable. He played with his fork every day.

One day, Tim saw his friend, Sam, playing with a shiny new toy. Tim wanted to play with the toy too, but Sam said no. Tim felt sad, but he thought about his reliable fork and decided to ask Sam if he would like to play with it. Sam said yes, and they played together with the fork.

After playing with the fork, Sam allowed Tim to play with his shiny new toy. They both had a lot of fun and became best friends. The moral of the story is to be kind and share with others, and good things will come to you.
<|end|>


