Once upon a time, there was a man and his wife. They lived in a small house. One day, the man wanted to make a spicy soup for his wife. He went to the market and bought some spicy peppers.

When the man got home, he started to cook the soup. He put the spicy peppers in the pot. The smell was strong and made his nose tickle. The wife walked into the kitchen and asked, "What are you making?"

The man smiled and said, "I am making a spicy soup for you." The wife was happy and excited to try the soup. The man finished cooking and put the soup in a bowl for his wife to taste.

The wife took a sip of the soup and her face turned red. She pointed at the spicy peppers and said, "These are very spicy!" The man laughed and said, "Yes, they are! But I hope you like it." They both smiled and enjoyed the spicy soup together.
<|end|>


