Once upon a time, there was a smart little fox. The fox lived in a big forest. One day, the fox saw a flame. The flame was near a small house.

The fox knew that the flame could burn the house. So, the fox ran to the house. He saw a little girl inside. The fox said, "Little girl, there is a flame outside. It can burn your house. We must put it out."

The little girl listened to the smart fox. They worked together to put out the flame. The house did not burn. The little girl said, "Thank you, smart fox. You saved my house."

From that day on, the smart fox and the little girl were best friends. They played and had fun in the big forest every day.
<|end|>


