Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lucy. She loved to dance. Every day, she would put on her pretty dress and dance around her room. She would jump, spin, and wiggle like a crazy dancer. Lucy always had a big smile on her face when she danced.

One sunny day, Lucy went to the park with her mom. She saw a group of kids playing and dancing to music. She wanted to join them, so she asked her mom if she could. Her mom said yes, and Lucy ran over to the kids. They were all dancing and having lots of fun.

Lucy started to dance with the kids. They played a game called "Follow the Leader." One kid would do a dance move, and the others would follow. They all took turns being the leader. Lucy did her crazy dance moves, and everyone laughed and had a great time. The day was full of fun, and Lucy was so happy to make new friends who loved to dance just like her.
