Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. He had a big, old toy called Mr. Bear. Tim loved Mr. Bear and took him everywhere he went.

One day, Tim and Mr. Bear went to the park. They played on the swings, the slide, and in the sandbox. Tim was very happy. But then, Tim did something that made Mr. Bear feel not good. He left Mr. Bear on the swing and went to play with other kids. Mr. Bear felt alone and sad.

Later, Tim saw Mr. Bear on the swing and remembered he left him there. He felt bad for making Mr. Bear feel not good. He picked up Mr. Bear and said sorry. Tim told Mr. Bear the truth - that he still loved him and would not leave him alone again. Mr. Bear felt happy and they went home together, the best of friends.
