Once upon a time, there was a purple car named Cara. Cara loved to drive fast, but she did not like to stop for gas. One sunny day, she was driving with her friend, a little boy named Tom.

"Leave the gas station, Cara," Tom said. "We want to go fast."

Cara left the gas station, even though she needed gas. They drove fast and had fun, but soon the car started to slow down. Cara was out of gas.

"Oh no, we have no gas!" said Tom. "What do we do now?"

A wise old truck named Trucky saw them and stopped to help. He gave Cara some gas and said, "Always stop for gas when you need it. It is better to be safe than sorry."

Cara and Tom learned the importance of being prepared and not ignoring their needs. They thanked Trucky and drove away, always remembering to stop for gas when they needed it.
<|end|>


