Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Tim. Tim loved to serve his toys tea. One day, Tim went to the museum with his mom. At the museum, he saw big animals that did not move. Tim was frightened.

Tim wanted to go home, but his mom said no. She wanted to see more things at the museum. Tim felt sad and scared. He held his mom's hand very tight.

Then, a big, loud noise came from the museum. Tim was very frightened. He ran away from his mom and got lost. He cried and cried, but he could not find his mom. The museum was big and dark, and Tim was all alone.
