Once upon a time, in a small house, there lived a little girl named Lucy. She had a favorite toy, a teddy bear named Teddy. Teddy had a big red button on his belly. Lucy loved to play with Teddy every day.

One day, while Lucy was playing with Teddy, her little dog, Spot, came into the room. Spot saw Teddy and thought he was a toy to play with too. Spot ran up to Teddy and bit the big red button. Lucy saw what happened and shouted, "No, Spot! Don't bite Teddy!"

Lucy felt helpless as she watched the button come off Teddy's belly. She picked up Teddy and gave him a hug. She knew she had to fix Teddy. Lucy found some thread and a needle. She carefully sewed the big red button back onto Teddy's belly.

Now, Teddy was all better. Lucy was happy that she could help her friend. She promised to keep Teddy safe from Spot. From that day on, Lucy, Teddy, and Spot played together, but Lucy always made sure to keep an eye on her little dog.
<|end|>


