Once upon a time, there was a big building. It was old and some people said it was disgusting. Tom, a little boy, wanted to see the building. He asked his mom if he could go.

Tom's mom said, "Okay, but be careful and examine everything before you touch it." Tom was happy and went to the building. He saw a big door and opened it. Inside, he found a lot of trash. He remembered what his mom said and did not touch it.

Tom saw a little cat in the corner. The cat was dirty and sad. Tom examined the cat and saw it was hurt. He went home and told his mom. They both went back to the building and helped the cat. They cleaned the cat and gave it a new home. The moral of the story is to always be careful and help those in need.
<|end|>


