Once upon a time, there was a thoughtful little girl named Lucy. She loved to play with her ball outside. One day, she saw a sad boy sitting on the grass. His name was Tom. He was holding his stomach and looked like he was in pain.

Lucy walked up to Tom and asked, "Why are you sad? Does your stomach hurt?" Tom nodded his head and said, "Yes, my stomach hurts because I am hungry." Lucy felt bad for Tom and wanted to help him.

Lucy had an idea. She went to her house and got some food. She came back and gave the food to Tom. Tom ate the food and felt much better. Then, Lucy said, "Let's play with my ball!" Tom smiled and agreed. They took turns to throw the ball to each other and had a lot of fun. From that day on, Lucy and Tom became best friends.
