Once upon a time, in a friendly forest, there lived a little bunny named Ben. Ben was a happy bunny who loved to joke and play with his friends. One day, Ben was hopping around the forest when he saw a big spear stuck in the ground.

"Wow, what is that?" Ben said to his friend, a tiny bird named Tim. Tim flew down and looked at the spear. "It's a spear," Tim said. "But we should be careful. It might be sharp."

Ben and Tim decided to play a joke on their other friend, a squirrel named Sam. They hid the spear behind a tree and called Sam over. "Sam, come see what we found!" Ben said, trying not to laugh.

Sam came running over, excited to see what his friends had found. "What is it?" he asked. Ben and Tim moved aside, showing the spear. "It's a spear!" they said together, laughing. Sam laughed too, happy to be part of the joke.

From that day on, the three friends had even more fun playing in the friendly forest. They always remembered their joke with the spear and it brought them closer together. And they all lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


