Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to dream about all sorts of things like unicorns and rainbows. One day, Lily went to school to learn new things. Her teacher, Miss Rose, was very kind and taught her about numbers and letters. Lily thought Miss Rose was very unique because she wore a colorful dress and had a big smile.

After school, Lily went to the park to play with her friends. She told them about her dream of riding a unicorn and they laughed and said it was silly. Lily felt sad and didn't understand why they didn't like her dream. She went home and told her mom about what happened. Her mom said, "Lily, everyone is different and it's okay to have unique dreams. Don't let anyone teach you otherwise."

The next day, Lily went back to school and told Miss Rose about her dream. Miss Rose smiled and said, "That's a wonderful dream, Lily. You should always follow your dreams and never let anyone tell you otherwise." Lily felt happy and knew that her dream was special. From that day on, Lily always remembered to follow her unique dreams and never let anyone teach her otherwise.
