Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily who loved to play her green flute. She would play it every day, making beautiful music that everyone loved to hear. One day, Lily went to the park to play her flute. She saw a boy who was sad and asked him why. The boy said he lost his toy car and couldn't find it. Lily wanted to help, so she played her flute and the boy found his toy car.

Suddenly, a mean dog came and tried to take the boy's toy car. Lily played her flute again, and the dog ran away. The boy was happy and thanked Lily. But then, Lily's mom came and saw that she was in the park alone. She told Lily that she couldn't be alone and that she needed to come home. Lily was sad and said, "But I was helping the boy find his toy car." Her mom said, "I know, but you still need to come home. You didn't listen to me, so I will have to punish you." Lily was sad, but she knew she had to listen to her mom.
