Once upon a time, there was a little rabbit named Benny. Benny loved to play in his burrow with his friends. One day, Benny and his friends decided to explore a tunnel they had never been in before. It was dark and scary, but Benny was brave and led the way.

As they walked through the tunnel, they saw lots of different things. Benny's friend, Sally, saw a spider and got scared, but Benny told her not to worry. They also saw some pretty rocks and counted them as they went along. 

Finally, they reached the end of the tunnel and found a big, open field. Benny and his friends were so happy to be outside again! They played tag and had a lot of fun. Benny was the most playful of them all and made everyone laugh. They stayed outside until the sun went down and then went back to their burrows for a good night's sleep.
