Once upon a time, there was a big, wild forest. In the forest, there lived many animals, like rabbits, squirrels, and birds. One day, a hunter came to the forest. The hunter had a big gun and wanted to catch some animals.

The animals were scared of the hunter. They knew he wanted to hurt them. So, they decided to ask the owl what to do. The wise owl said, "We need to be careful. I will lend my wings to the fastest animal so they can go and warn the others."

The rabbit was the fastest animal, so he borrowed the owl's wings and flew to the other side of the forest. There, he told the other animals about the hunter. They all ran away and the hunter went back home empty-handed.

From that day on, the animals in the forest were more careful. They knew that there might be hunters around. But they were also happy because they knew they could help each other when they needed to.
