Once upon a time, there was a big and strong bull. The bull was walking in a field and enjoying the green grass when he saw a little girl. The little girl was holding a red balloon and was looking at the bull. The bull thought that the balloon was interesting and he wanted to play with it. 

The bull walked towards the little girl and said, "Hello, little girl. Can I play with your balloon?" The little girl looked at the bull and said, "No, Mr. Bull. This is my balloon. I don't want to give it to you." The bull felt sad and said, "Please, little girl. I promise I will give it back to you." 

The little girl thought for a moment and said, "Okay, Mr. Bull. But you have to promise to surrender the balloon back to me when you are done playing with it." The bull nodded his head and took the balloon gently from the little girl. The bull played with the balloon for a while and had a lot of fun. When he was done, he surrendered the balloon back to the little girl, just like he promised. The little girl was happy and thanked the bull for playing with her.
