Once upon a time, there was a little bug named Billy. Billy liked to crawl around and explore the world. One day, he met a big ant named Andy.

"Hi there, little bug! What are you doing?" asked Andy.

"I'm just crawling around, looking for food," replied Billy.

Andy looked at Billy's tiny brain and felt upset. "You know, little bug, you should be careful. You have a small brain and you might get hurt."

Billy felt sad and upset. "But I want to explore and have fun," he said.

Andy thought for a moment and then said, "Well, I can help you. I have a big brain and I can show you how to crawl safely."

Billy was happy and excited. "Thank you, Andy!" he said.

And so, Andy taught Billy how to crawl safely and they became good friends. From that day on, Billy was careful and always remembered to use his brain.
