Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a big house with her mommy and daddy. One day, Lily's mommy asked her to help with the laundry. "Can you help me complete the laundry, Lily?" her mommy asked. 

Lily replied, "Yes, mommy. I can help you." She felt happy to help her mommy. Together, they washed and dried the clothes. 

When they finished, they went outside to play. Suddenly, they saw smoke coming from their neighbor's house. Lily's mommy quickly called the fire department. 

While they waited for the fire department to arrive, Lily's mommy made her comfortable by giving her a hug. "Don't worry, Lily. We are safe," she said. 

Finally, the fire department arrived and put out the fire. Lily felt relieved that everyone was okay. She knew that helping her mommy complete the laundry and being comfortable with her mommy made her feel happy.
