Once upon a time, there was a little bunny named Bun Bun. Bun Bun was always hungry and loved to eat carrots. One day, Bun Bun was hopping through the forest when a mist came. The mist was very thick and Bun Bun couldn't see where he was going. 

Bun Bun decided to stay still and wait for the mist to go away. But while he was waiting, he heard a loud growling sound. It was his tummy! He was so hungry that he couldn't wait any longer. 

Bun Bun decided to keep hopping even though he couldn't see well. But he hopped too far and got lost in the mist. He couldn't find his way back home and he was still very hungry. 

The moral of the story is that sometimes it's better to stay still and wait for things to get better instead of making hasty decisions.
<|end|>


