"The flowers! They have different colors and shapes. It's so interesting!" Lily exclaimed.
Her mom smiled and said, "Yes, those are special flowers. They include many different kinds in that patch."

Lily was happy to learn something new and continued to explore the patch of flowers. She picked one and showed it to her mom. "Look, Mommy! I found a pretty patch on this flower," she said, pointing to a small spot on the petal.
"That's called a patch too!" her mom said, impressed by her daughter's observation skills.

Lily was proud of herself for discovering the interesting patch of flowers and couldn't wait to tell her friends about it. She knew they would love it just as much as she did.
