Once upon a time, there was a boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to draw and design things. He would make pictures of cars and houses with his crayons. One day, Timmy's mom took him to the park to play. 

As they played, a mist started to form. Timmy thought it was cool how the mist made everything look blurry. "Mommy, look at the mist! It's so cool!" Timmy said. 

His mom smiled and said, "Yes, it is. You know, Timmy, you could design a picture of the mist if you wanted to." 

Timmy's eyes lit up. "That's a brilliant idea, Mommy!" he said. So, he took out his crayons and drew a picture of the mist. It was a beautiful picture and Timmy was very proud of it. 

From that day on, Timmy loved designing pictures of different things he saw in the world. And whenever there was mist, he would always remember the day his mom gave him a brilliant idea.
