Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to talk and sing in her language. Her language was special to her, but it was just an ordinary language to others.

One day, Lily's parents took her to the park to play. She met a new friend, a boy named Max. They played together and had so much fun. Max liked Lily's language and asked her to teach him.

Lily was happy to teach Max her language. They spent the whole day speaking and singing in Lily's language. But when it was time to go home, Lily's parents told her they had to finish playing and go home.

Lily said goodbye to Max and promised to teach him more of her language next time. But as they were leaving the park, Lily's parents noticed that Max had followed them. He had taken Lily's bag with all her toys and treasures.

Lily was upset and cried. Her parents called the police, but they couldn't find Max or Lily's bag. Lily never saw her bag or Max again. She learned a hard lesson that day - not everyone is kind and trustworthy.
