Once upon a time, there was a pretty little bird. She lived in a big tree with lots of leaves. One day, the bird saw a big storm coming. She knew she had to warn her friends to leave the tree and find a safe exit.

The bird flew around the tree and chirped loudly to her friends, "Storm is coming! Leave the tree and find a safe exit!" But her friends didn't listen. They thought the bird was just being silly and didn't want to leave their cozy home.

The storm came and the wind blew so hard that the tree shook. The bird's friends were scared and wished they had listened to her warning. Suddenly, the tree cracked and fell down. The bird's friends were trapped inside and couldn't find an exit. The pretty little bird tried to help them, but it was too late. The bad ending made the bird very sad. She wished her friends had listened to her warning and left the tree.
