Once upon a time, there was a sailor. He loved to sail on his big boat. One day, he met a little girl on the shore. She was lost and scared. The sailor was compassionate and took her on his boat. 

The little girl trusted the sailor and felt safe with him. They sailed together for many days, and the little girl was happy. But one day, a big storm came. The waves were high, and the wind was strong. The boat flipped over, and the sailor and the little girl fell into the water. 

The sailor tried to save the little girl, but the waves were too strong. They both drowned, and their bodies were never found. The people on the shore were sad because they knew the sailor was a good man, and the little girl was too young to die.
