Once upon a time, there was a little bird named Tweetie. Tweetie loved to fly high up in the sky and soar with the clouds. One day, Tweetie saw a mixer in the yard. The mixer was big and made lots of noise.

Tweetie flew down to the mixer and asked, "What are you doing, mixer?"

"I'm mixing some cake batter," said the mixer.

Tweetie was curious and asked, "Can I help you mix, mixer?"

"Of course, little bird," said the mixer. "You can help me mix the batter by flapping your wings."

So Tweetie flapped his wings and helped the mixer mix the batter. The cake turned out to be delicious and Tweetie was happy to have helped. From that day on, Tweetie would often fly down to the mixer to help mix things. And every time he flew back up into the sky, he would soar with joy.
