Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play outside with his friends. They would run, jump and have fun together. One day, Timmy fell and hurt his knee. He cried and cried until his mommy came to help.

Mommy said, "Let's go see the doctor. He will make your knee better." Timmy felt scared but mommy held his hand and they went to the doctor's office. The doctor was very nice and he talked to Timmy in a soft voice. He checked Timmy's knee and said, "Don't worry, Timmy. You will be okay. Just rest and be alert for any pain."

Timmy felt better and he smiled. He said, "Thank you, doctor!" and mommy gave him a big hug. They went home and Timmy rested. Soon, he was back to playing with his friends, running and jumping just like before. He knew that if he ever got hurt again, the doctor would be there to help him.
