Once upon a time, there was a little bird who loved to whistle. He would sit on a branch and whistle all day long. One day, he saw a group of birds flying by, wearing fashionable feathers. He felt sad because he didn't have any fancy feathers like them.

So, he decided to go on a journey to find fashionable feathers. He flew for a long time until he found a place where there were many different kinds of feathers. He picked out the most fashionable feathers he could find and put them on.

As he flew back to his branch, he realized that his new feathers were making too much noise and he couldn't whistle quietly anymore. He missed his old quiet whistle. So, he took off his fashionable feathers and went back to his old self, happily whistling on his branch.
