Sara and Ben are brother and sister. They like to play with their toys in the living room. Sara has a doll and Ben has a car. They are happy.

But then, a big dog comes in. The dog is unknown. He is not their dog. He is a bad dog. He runs to the toys and grabs the car with his mouth. He chews the car. Ben is angry. He shouts at the dog.

"Hey, dog! That is my car! Give it back! You are a bad dog!"

The dog does not listen. He chews the car more. He makes it broken. Ben is sad. He cries.

Sara sees Ben crying. She feels sorry for him. She wants to help him. She has an idea. She takes her doll and waves it at the dog.

"Look, dog! Here is a doll! Do you want the doll? The doll is better than the car. Come and get the doll!"

The dog sees the doll. He drops the car and runs to the doll. He grabs the doll with his mouth. He chews the doll. Sara is brave. She does not cry. She lets the dog have the doll.

Ben sees Sara giving the dog the doll. He feels happy. He hugs Sara.

"Thank you, Sara. You are a good sister. You gave the dog your doll to save my car. I love you."

Sara hugs Ben back.

"I love you too, Ben. You are a good brother. I don't need the doll. I have you."

The dog chews the doll and leaves. Sara and Ben play with the car. They are happy.
<|end|>


