Sara and Ben like to play in the kitchen. They pretend to be chefs and make yummy food. They use pots, pans, spoons and bowls. They also use things from the fridge and the cupboard.

One day, they find a teaspoon with something green and fuzzy on it. It smells bad.

"Yuck! What is this?" Sara asks.

"It is rot. It means the food is old and sick. We cannot use it," Ben says.

"Where did it come from?" Sara wonders.

"Maybe from the jam. Mama said we have to close the jar tight or the jam will rot," Ben remembers.

They look at the jar of jam. It is open and has more green and fuzzy stuff on it.

"Oh no! We have to throw it away. Mama will be mad if she sees it," Sara says.

They take the jar and the teaspoon and put them in the trash. Then they wash their hands and find something else to play with.

They decide to make a cake with flour, sugar, eggs and milk. They are very creative. They add some chocolate chips, raisins and sprinkles. They mix everything in a big bowl and pour it in a pan.

They ask Mama if they can bake it in the oven. Mama says yes, but she will help them. She is proud of their cake. She says it looks delicious.

They wait for the cake to bake. They smell the sweet and yummy smell. They are happy and hungry. They can't wait to eat their cake.
<|end|>


