Lily and Max were playing in the park. They liked to run and jump and slide. But Lily was not careful. She ran too fast and fell down. She hurt her knee and it was bleeding.

"Ow, ow, ow!" Lily cried. She felt pain and scared.

Max saw Lily and ran to her. He wanted to help her. He had a bandage in his pocket. He gave it to Lily.

"Here, use this," he said. "It will make your knee better."

Lily took the bandage and thanked Max. She wrapped it around her knee. It felt better, but it still hurt a little.

"Thank you, Max. You are a good friend," she said.

Max smiled. He was happy to help Lily. But he also felt embarrassed. He had the bandage because he had a boo-boo on his elbow. He got it when he tried to ride his bike without training wheels. He was afraid that Lily would laugh at him.

"Don't worry, Max. I won't laugh at you," Lily said. She saw his elbow and gave him a hug. "We all have boo-boos sometimes. They will go away soon."

Max felt better. He hugged Lily back. They were both brave and kind. They decided to play some more, but more carefully. They had fun in the park.
<|end|>


