Lily was a little girl who liked to play dress-up. She had many pretty clothes in her closet, but she wanted more. One day, she saw her mom's laundry basket in the hall. It had some big clothes that looked nice and soft. Lily decided to borrow some of them and try them on.

She took a pink sweater, a blue skirt, and a yellow scarf from the basket. She put them on and looked at herself in the mirror. She felt very happy and pretty. She did not think her mom would mind if she borrowed them for a little while.

She went outside to show her friends her new outfit. They were playing in the yard with a ball. Lily joined them and threw the ball around. She did not notice that the sweater was too long and the skirt was too wide. They got caught on a branch and ripped. The scarf got dirty from the grass and mud.

Lily's mom came out to see what was going on. She saw Lily wearing her clothes and how they were ruined. She was very angry and sad. She asked Lily why she took her clothes without asking. Lily said she just wanted to borrow them and play dress-up. She said she was sorry and did not mean to hurt them.

But Lily's mom did not forgive her. She said Lily was naughty and selfish. She said she had to pay for the clothes and do extra chores. She took Lily inside and made her take off the clothes. She did not let her play with her friends or watch TV. She sent her to her room and told her to think about what she did.

Lily felt very bad and lonely. She wished she had not borrowed her mom's clothes. She wished she had asked first or used her own clothes. She wished she could say sorry again and make her mom happy. She cried and cried until she fell asleep. She had a bad day.
<|end|>


