Lily and Ben were friends who liked to play with blocks. They liked to build towers and houses and bridges with their blocks. One day, they decided to make a big map of the country with their blocks. They used different colors and shapes to show the mountains, the rivers, the cities and the farms.

They worked hard and had fun, but they also had some problems. Sometimes, they ran out of blocks or they disagreed on where to put them. Sometimes, they knocked over each other's blocks by accident or on purpose. They started to argue and shout and cry.

"Stop it, Ben! You ruined my city!" Lily said.

"No, you stop it, Lily! You took my blocks!" Ben said.

They were very angry and sad. They did not want to play together anymore. They sat on opposite sides of the room and glared at each other.

Then, their teacher came in and saw their map. She smiled and clapped her hands.

"Wow, Lily and Ben, what a wonderful map of the country you made! You are very clever and creative. I am so proud of you!" she said.

Lily and Ben looked at their teacher and then at their map. They saw how big and beautiful it was. They saw how they used all their blocks and how they made different parts of the country. They remembered how they helped each other and had fun.

They felt sorry for being mean and rude to each other. They got up and walked towards each other.

"I'm sorry, Lily. I should not have ruined your city. Can we be friends again?" Ben said.

"I'm sorry, Ben. I should not have taken your blocks. Can we be friends again?" Lily said.

They hugged and smiled. They were happy again. They finished their map and showed it to their teacher and their classmates. Everyone liked their map and praised them. They learned that playing together is better than fighting and that sharing and caring make them happy.
<|end|>


