Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play with trains. They have a big track with many trains. They make the trains go fast and slow, and stop and go.

One day, a new boy comes to play. His name is Tom. He has a pretty train. It is red and shiny. Anna and Ben want to see his train. They ask him nicely.

"Can we play with your train, Tom?" they say.

But Tom is not nice. He says no. He says his train is better than their trains. He says they have old and ugly trains. He teases them.

"That is not nice, Tom," Anna says. "You should share your train. We share our trains with you."

But Tom does not listen. He keeps his train to himself. He makes it go around the track. He laughs at Anna and Ben.

Anna and Ben are sad. They do not like Tom. They do not want to play with him. They go to another corner. They play with their trains. They have fun.

Tom sees them. He wants to play with them. He feels lonely. He says sorry.

"Can I play with you, Anna and Ben?" he says. "I am sorry I teased you. Your trains are nice too. Can we share our trains?"

Anna and Ben think. They are still mad at Tom. But they are also kind. They decide to give him a chance.

"Okay, Tom," they say. "You can play with us. But you have to be nice. You have to share your train. And you have to say nice things."

Tom nods. He is happy. He gives his train to Anna. He takes a train from Ben. They play together. They make the trains go fast and slow, and stop and go. They have fun. They are friends.
