Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They have a dog named Spot. Spot is big and brown. He likes to run and bark.

One day, Lily and Ben see a pond in the park. The pond is deep and blue. They want to swim in the pond. But they do not have swimsuits. They have an idea. They take off their shoes and socks. They tie their socks together. They make a rope. They throw the rope in the pond. They want to pull the rope and splash the water.

But Spot sees the rope. He thinks it is a toy. He runs to the pond. He grabs the rope with his teeth. He pulls the rope hard. Lily and Ben fall in the pond. They get wet and cold. They cry for help.

A man hears them. He comes to the pond. He sees Lily and Ben and Spot. He helps them out of the pond. He gives them a towel. He says, "You should not play near the pond. The pond is deep and dangerous. You could drown. And you should not tie your socks together. You could lose them. And you should not leave your dog alone. He could get into trouble. You should be careful and responsible."

Lily and Ben are sorry. They say, "Thank you for helping us. We are sorry for being silly. We will not play near the pond again. We will not tie our socks together again. We will watch our dog better. We will be careful and responsible."

The man smiles. He says, "You are welcome. I am glad you are safe. You are good kids. You learned a lesson today. You should always respect the water and your things and your pet. They are important and precious."

Lily and Ben nod. They hug Spot. They put on their shoes and socks. They go home with the man. They tell their parents what happened. They say they learned a lesson. They say they will be careful and responsible. Their parents are proud of them. They hug them and kiss them. They say they love them. Lily and Ben are happy. They love their parents and their dog. They are good friends. They are good kids.
<|end|>


