Anna and Ben like to play in the garden. They have a big tent that they can hide in. They pretend that they are on an adventure in the jungle.

One day, they hear a loud noise outside the tent. They peek out and see a big dog. The dog is friendly and wags its tail. He wants to play with them.

"Hello, doggy!" Anna says. "Do you want to join our adventure?"

The dog barks and runs into the tent. He sniffs around and finds a toy ball. He picks it up and drops it at Ben's feet.

"Good doggy!" Ben says. "You can be our helper. We are looking for treasure in the jungle. Can you help us find it?"

The dog barks again and nods his head. He follows Ben and Anna as they crawl out of the tent. They look around the garden and pretend that they see lions, monkeys and snakes. They have a lot of fun.

After a while, they get tired and hungry. They go back to the tent and sit down. Anna has a basket with some sandwiches and juice. She shares them with Ben and the dog.

"Let me serve you, Ben," Anna says. "You are the leader of our adventure. You need to eat well."

"Thank you, Anna," Ben says. "You are very kind. And thank you, doggy, for being our helper. You are very brave."

The dog wags his tail and licks their faces. He is happy to have new friends. They eat and drink and then lie down in the tent. They close their eyes and dream of more adventures.
<|end|>


