Anna and Ben were playing in the park. They saw a big, fancy car with shiny windows and wheels. They ran to the car and looked inside.

"Wow, look at all the toys and books!" Anna said. She pointed to a teddy bear and a puzzle on the back seat.

"Can we take them?" Ben asked. He reached for the door handle.

"No, we can't!" Anna said. "They are not ours. They belong to someone else. Maybe they are a mystery. Maybe they are a spy or a princess or a superhero."

Ben did not listen. He opened the door and grabbed the teddy bear. He ran away with it.

"Ben, come back!" Anna shouted. "That is bad. You are stealing. You have to give it back."

But Ben did not hear her. He was too happy with his new toy.

Suddenly, they heard a loud honk. They turned around and saw a man in a suit and a hat. He was angry. He was the owner of the car.

"Hey, you little thieves!" he yelled. "Give me back my stuff. That is my teddy bear. It is very special to me. It was a gift from my grandma."

He ran after Ben and Anna. Ben was scared. He dropped the teddy bear and ran faster. Anna followed him. They ran to the swings and hid behind them.

The man picked up the teddy bear and looked at it. He sighed. He was sad. He missed his grandma. He put the teddy bear back in the car and drove away.

Anna and Ben felt sorry. They learned a lesson. They should not take things that are not theirs. They should respect other people's things. They should be nice and honest. They hugged each other and said sorry. They decided to play with their own toys and books. They had fun and forgot about the fancy car and the mystery.
<|end|>


