Tom and Sam like to play hockey. They have sticks and a ball. They play in the park with their friends. They clap when they score a goal. They have fun.

One day, it is very dark. The sky is black and there is thunder. Tom and Sam are still playing hockey. Their friends go home. They say, "It is going to rain. You should go home too." But Tom and Sam do not listen. They want to play more.

The rain comes. It is heavy and cold. Tom and Sam get wet and muddy. They cannot see the ball. They slip and fall. They hurt themselves. They cry.

They try to go home. But they are lost. They do not know where they are. They are scared. They call for help. But no one hears them. They are alone in the dark. They wish they had listened to their friends.
<|end|>


