Sam and Mia were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had many cars, trucks, trains and planes that they could zoom around the house. One day, their dad said he had a surprise for them in the garage. He took them by the hand and led them outside.

When they opened the garage door, they saw an enormous box with a big bow on it. It was bigger than their bed, bigger than their sofa, bigger than their fridge. Sam and Mia gasped and clapped their hands. "What is it, dad?" they asked.

"It's a gift for you two," dad said. "Do you want to open it and see?"

Sam and Mia nodded and ran to the box. They pulled the bow and tore the paper. Inside, they found a huge playset with roads, bridges, tunnels, buildings and signs. It was like a mini city for their toys. There were also many new cars, trucks, trains and planes that they had never seen before.

"Wow, dad, this is amazing!" Sam said. "Thank you so much!"

"This is the best gift ever!" Mia said. "Can we play with it now?"

"Of course you can," dad said. "But remember to share and be careful with your toys. And don't forget to clean up when you're done."

Sam and Mia hugged their dad and thanked him again. Then they started to fill the garage with their toys. They made vroom and beep and choo-choo noises as they drove and flew their vehicles around the playset. They had so much fun that they didn't want to stop. They played until it was dark and mom called them for dinner. They smiled and said they had the best day ever.
<|end|>


