Lily and Sam went to the zoo with Mom and Dad. They saw many animals, like lions, monkeys, and elephants. Lily liked the lions best. They were big and fierce and had loud roars. Sam liked the monkeys best. They were funny and playful and had long tails.

"Can we try to feed the monkeys?" Sam asked Mom.

"Sure, we can try," Mom said. "But we have to be careful and follow the rules."

Mom bought some nuts from a machine and gave some to Sam and Lily. They walked to the monkey cage and saw the monkeys swinging and jumping on the ropes and trees.

"Hello, monkeys!" Sam said. "Do you want some nuts?"

He threw a nut to a monkey. The monkey caught it and ate it. Then it made a happy noise and threw a nut back to Sam.

"Wow, the monkey is playing with me!" Sam said. He threw another nut and the monkey did the same.

Lily wanted to try too. She threw a nut to another monkey. But the monkey did not catch it. It bounced off the cage and hit a lion on the head.

The lion was angry. It roared very loud and showed its teeth. Lily was scared. She ran to Mom and hugged her.

"Sorry, lion!" Lily said. "I did not mean to hit you!"

The lion calmed down and licked its paw. It did not want to hurt Lily. It was just surprised.

"It's okay, Lily," Mom said. "The lion is not mad at you. But we have to be more careful when we try to feed the animals. They are not like our pets. They are wild and fierce."

Lily nodded. She learned her lesson. She still liked the lions, but she liked the monkeys more. She and Sam gave the rest of the nuts to the monkeys and thanked them for playing with them. Then they went to see the other animals in the zoo. They had a lot of fun.
<|end|>


