Tom and Lily were playing in the park. It was a sunny day and the park was peaceful. They liked to run, swing, slide and climb. They saw a big tree with a hole in it. They wanted to see what was inside.

"Let's find out what's in there!" Tom said.

"OK, but be careful!" Lily said.

They went to the tree and looked inside the hole. They saw something shiny and black. It looked like a toy.

"Wow, look at this!" Tom said. He reached inside and pulled out the shiny thing. It was a gun.

"What is that?" Lily asked.

"It's a toy gun. It makes a loud noise. Watch!" Tom said. He pointed the gun at the sky and pulled the trigger.

BANG!

The gun was not a toy. It was real. The loud noise scared Tom and Lily. They dropped the gun and ran away. But it was too late. The bullet hit a bird that was flying in the sky. The bird fell down and died.

The park was not peaceful anymore. It was sad and scary. Tom and Lily cried. They wished they never found the gun. They wished they never hurt the bird. They wished they could go back to playing. But they couldn't. They had done something very bad.
<|end|>


