Lila and Ben were playing with their blocks. They liked to make towers and bridges and houses. They also liked to draw symbols on some blocks with their crayons. Lila drew a star, Ben drew a heart, and they both drew a smiley face.

"Look, we made a happy town!" Lila said, pointing to their blocks.

"Yes, we did! It is very pretty and colorful!" Ben said, smiling.

They decided to have a snack. They went to the kitchen and asked their mom for some crackers and cheese. Their mom gave them a plate and a glass of water.

"Be careful, some of the cheese is spicy. It might make your mouth hot," their mom warned them.

Lila and Ben nodded and thanked their mom. They took their plate and water to the living room, where their blocks were. They put the plate on the coffee table and sat on the floor.

They ate some crackers and cheese. Lila liked the spicy cheese, but Ben did not. He made a funny face and drank some water.

"Spicy cheese is yucky!" Ben said.

"I like spicy cheese. It is yummy!" Lila said.

They finished their snack and looked at their blocks. They saw something strange. Some of their blocks had disappeared!

"Hey, where are our blocks?" Lila asked.

"I don't know. Maybe someone took them," Ben said.

They looked around and saw their dog, Max, hiding under the sofa. He had some blocks in his mouth. He had eaten the blocks with the symbols on them!

"Max, you bad dog! You ate our blocks!" Lila said.

"Bad, bad, bad!" Ben said.

They ran to the sofa and tried to get their blocks back. Max wagged his tail and licked their faces. He thought they were playing with him.

"Max, give us our blocks! They are not food!" Lila said.

"Please, please, please!" Ben said.

But Max did not listen. He swallowed the blocks and burped. He looked happy and sleepy.

Lila and Ben were sad and angry. They had lost their blocks and their symbols. They did not want to play with Max anymore.

They went to their mom and told her what happened. Their mom hugged them and said she was sorry.

"Don't worry, we can buy some new blocks. And you can draw some new symbols. And maybe next time, we can give Max some spicy cheese. Maybe he will not like it and leave your blocks alone," their mom said.

Lila and Ben smiled and nodded. They liked that idea. They hoped Max would learn his lesson. They went to their room and drew some new symbols. They drew a star, a heart, and a smiley face. And they also drew a dog with a big X on it.
<|end|>


