Lily and Tom were playing in the park. They saw a big bird fly in the sky. It had a long tail and bright colors.

"Wow, look at that bird!" Lily said. "It is so pretty. I wish I could fly like that."

"Me too," Tom said. "But we can't fly. We can only run and jump and swing."

They ran after the bird, trying to follow its trail. But the bird was too fast and flew away.

They came to a big tree. They saw some red berries on the branches.

"Maybe we can eat these berries," Lily said. "They look yummy."

She picked one and put it in her mouth. But it was not yummy. It was bitter. She spat it out and made a face.

"Yuck, these berries are bad!" she said. "They are not sweet. They are sour."

Tom laughed. He picked another berry and threw it at Lily. Lily dodged and threw one back at him. They started a berry fight, laughing and throwing.

They forgot about the bird and the flying. They had fun with the berries and the tree. They were happy.
