Lily and Tom were friends. They liked to play in the park. Yesterday, they saw many red and yellow leaves on the ground. They wanted to gather them and make a big pile.

"Let's gather the leaves and jump on them!" Lily said.

"OK, that sounds fun!" Tom said.

They ran around the park and gathered the leaves. They made a big pile near a bench. They were happy and excited.

"Ready, set, go!" Lily said. She jumped on the pile of leaves.

But Tom did not jump. He saw something shiny under the bench. He went to look at it. It was a coin. He picked it up and smiled.

"Wow, a coin! I can buy candy with this!" Tom said.

He forgot about Lily and the leaves. He ran to the candy store. He did not say goodbye to Lily.

Lily was sad and angry. She jumped off the pile of leaves. She looked for Tom. She did not see him. She saw the coin on the ground. She realized what Tom did.

"Tom is a bad friend!" Lily said. She cried. She threw the coin away. She went home alone.

The end.
