Ben and Lily were friends who liked to play in the farm. They liked to run in the grass, chase the chickens and watch the cows. Sometimes they helped their dads with the work, like picking corn or feeding the pigs.

One day, Ben and Lily decided to play a game. They wanted to see who could pick more corn from the field. They each took a big basket and ran to the corn plants. They started to pull the yellow ears and put them in their baskets.

"Look, Lily, I have more corn than you!" Ben said, showing his basket.

"No, you don't, Ben, I have more corn than you!" Lily said, showing her basket.

They kept picking corn and arguing, not paying attention to anything else. They did not see the sky getting dark and the wind getting strong. They did not hear the thunder and the rain. They did not notice the corn plants shaking and bending.

Suddenly, a loud noise made them stop and look up. They saw a big, black cloud spinning in the air. It was coming towards them, fast and angry. It was a tornado!

"Ben, Lily, run!" their dads shouted from the barn. "The tornado is coming! It will increase and destroy everything!"

Ben and Lily dropped their baskets and tried to run, but it was too late. The tornado was too close and too strong. It picked them up and threw them in the air, along with the corn, the baskets, the chickens and the cows. They screamed and cried, but no one could hear them or help them.

The tornado carried them far away, to a place where the sky was clear, but the land was empty and cold. There was no farm, no grass, no animals, no dads. There was only corn, scattered and broken. Ben and Lily were alone and scared. They wished they had not played that game. They wished they had listened to their dads. They wished they had been good friends. But it was too late. The end.
<|end|>


