Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. They like to slide, swing and run. But today, they have a problem. There is only one red bike in the park. Lily and Tom both want the red bike.

Lily says, "I saw the red bike first. It is mine. You can have the ugly green bike." Tom says, "No, I want the red bike. It is faster and nicer. You can have the ugly green bike." They both pull the red bike. They are angry and sad.

Then, a big boy comes. He is mean and rude. He says, "Give me the red bike. It is mine now. You can have no bike." He pushes Lily and Tom. He takes the red bike. He rides away. He laughs.

Lily and Tom are scared and hurt. They cry. They hug each other. They say, "Sorry, I was selfish. You are my friend. I don't care about the bike. I care about you." They smile.

They see the ugly green bike. It is not so ugly. It is big and strong. It has two seats. Lily and Tom say, "Let's share the green bike. We can ride together. We can have fun." They hop on the green bike. They pedal fast. They go to the slide, the swing and the run. They finish their play. They are happy.
<|end|>


