One day, Tom and Sam went to the park to play. They saw a big hill with many rocks and sticks. Tom said, "Let's go to the hill and make a mine. We can dig and find treasures." Sam said, "Yes, let's go. That sounds fun."

They ran to the hill and started to dig with their hands and sticks. They made a hole and put some rocks and leaves inside. They said, "This is our mine. We are mighty miners. No one can take our treasures." They were very happy.

But then, they heard a loud noise. They looked up and saw a group of ducks. The ducks were marching to the hill. They quacked and flapped their wings. They wanted to eat the leaves and rocks in the hole. Tom and Sam were scared. They said, "Oh no, the ducks are coming. They want our mine. What can we do?"

They thought for a moment. Then, they had an idea. They picked up some sticks and waved them in the air. They shouted, "Go away, ducks. This is our mine. You cannot have it. We are mighty miners. We will not let you in." They made a lot of noise and scared the ducks.

The ducks stopped marching. They turned around and ran away. They quacked and flapped their wings. They did not want to fight with Tom and Sam. They looked for another place to eat.

Tom and Sam cheered. They said, "We did it. We saved our mine. We are mighty miners. We are brave and strong." They hugged each other and smiled. They went back to their hole and dug some more. They had a lot of fun.
<|end|>


