Sara and Ben were twins who lived on a farm with their mom and dad. They liked to play with the animals, but they were not allowed to go near the big red barn. Mom and dad said there was something scary inside.

One day, Sara and Ben were bored and curious. They decided to sneak to the big red barn and see what was inside. They opened the door and saw a lot of hay and tools. They also heard a loud roar.

"What is that?" Sara asked, feeling worry.

"I don't know, let's go closer," Ben said, feeling brave.

They walked towards the roar and saw a big, furry, brown animal with horns and a long tail. It was a bull. The bull saw them and snorted.

"Hello, bull," Ben said, trying to be friendly. "We are Sara and Ben. We live on this farm. You are harmless, right?"

The bull did not answer. He lowered his head and charged at them. Sara and Ben screamed and ran back to the door. They slammed it shut and leaned against it.

"Mom! Dad! Help!" they shouted.

Mom and dad heard them and came running. They opened the door and saw the bull. They were angry and scared.

"What are you doing here?" mom asked. "We told you not to come near the barn. The bull is dangerous. He could have hurt you."

"We are sorry, mom," Sara said. "We were bored and curious. We thought the bull was harmless."

"You were wrong," dad said. "The bull is not a toy. He is a wild animal. He does not like strangers. You have to stay away from him."

Sara and Ben nodded. They felt sorry and scared. They hugged mom and dad and said they would never go near the barn again. Mom and dad forgave them and took them back to the house. They gave them some cookies and milk and told them a story about a friendly cow. Sara and Ben learned their lesson and never bothered the bull again.
<|end|>


