Tom and Sue are twins. They like to play with their toys, but sometimes they quarrel. One day, they both want to play with the same train. Tom says, "It is my train. I got it for my birthday." Sue says, "No, it is our train. We share everything." They pull the train from each other and shout.

Mom hears them and comes to their room. She is not happy. She says, "Stop quarreling, you two. You have to be kind and take turns. Quarreling is not nice." Tom and Sue feel sorry. They say, "We are sorry, Mom. We will not quarrel again." Mom smiles and hugs them. She says, "That is good. I love you both."

Then, the phone rings. Mom goes to answer it. She comes back with a worried face. She says, "That was Dad. He had an emergency at work. He needs me to help him. I have to go now. Grandma will come soon to watch you. Be good and listen to her." Tom and Sue are surprised. They say, "What is an emergency, Mom?" Mom says, "An emergency is something very important and urgent. It does not happen often. It is rare. Dad and I have to fix a problem. We will be back soon. Don't worry." She kisses them and leaves.

Tom and Sue are curious. They wonder what the problem is. They hope Mom and Dad are okay. They decide to play nicely with their toys until Grandma comes. They share the train and take turns. They do not quarrel anymore. They are good twins.
<|end|>


