Sam and Anna are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big slide. Sam wants to go first. He runs to the slide and climbs up the ladder. Anna follows him.

"Wait for me, Sam!" Anna says. "We can slide together!"

Sam nods. He sees a tie on the slide. It is red and shiny. He likes it. He grabs the tie and pulls it. He thinks it is a toy.

"Look, Anna, I found a tie!" Sam says. "It is pretty!"

Anna reaches the top of the slide. She sees the tie too. She knows it is not a toy. It is a man's tie. She sees a man on a bench. He is reading a book. He does not see Sam and Anna.

"Sam, that is not a toy!" Anna says. "That is a man's tie! You should not pull it!"

But Sam does not listen. He pulls the tie harder. The tie is long and strong. It is dependable. It does not break. But the man feels it. He looks up from his book. He sees Sam and Anna on the slide. He sees his tie in Sam's hand. He is angry.

"Hey, you kids, stop that!" the man shouts. "That is my tie! Give it back!"

Sam and Anna are scared. They let go of the tie. They slide down fast. They run away from the slide. They do not look back. They do not want to play with the tie anymore. They want to play with something else. Something that is a toy.
