Lily and Ben were playing in their room. They had a big mattress on the floor. They pretended it was a boat. They put pillows and blankets on it. They had some toys and books too.

"Let's go on an adventure!" Lily said. "I will be the captain and you will be the cook."

"OK!" Ben said. "What do you want to eat?"

Lily thought for a moment. "I want some cake and juice. Can you serve me some?"

Ben nodded. He went to the kitchen and got a plate and a cup. He found some cake and juice in the fridge. He carried them carefully to the room. He put them on the mattress.

"Here you go, captain!" he said. "Your cake and juice are ready!"

"Thank you, cook!" Lily said. She smiled and took a bite of the cake. It was yummy. She drank some juice. It was sweet.

Suddenly, they heard a loud noise. It was their dog, Rex. He ran into the room. He saw the mattress and the food. He jumped on the mattress. He wanted to eat the cake and drink the juice.

"Hey, Rex, no!" Lily shouted. "This is our boat and our food! Go away!"

But Rex was too strong and fast. He pushed Lily and Ben off the mattress. He ate the cake and drank the juice. He made a mess.

Lily and Ben were sad and angry. They tried to get back on the mattress. But Rex barked and growled at them. He was not nice.

"Rex, stop it!" Ben said. "You are a bad dog! You are not our friend!"

But Rex did not listen. He was happy. He had a big mattress and a full belly.

Lily and Ben felt weak and helpless. They did not know what to do. They wished their mom or dad would come and help them. They hugged each other and waited.
