One day, a big storm came to the farm where Tom and his family lived. The sky was dark and loud, and the wind was very strong. Tom was scared, and he ran to his mom and dad in the house. They hugged him and told him to be brave.

But then, they saw something scary outside. It was a big, spinning thing that looked like a snake. It was a tornado, and it was coming to the farm. The tornado was very fast and very angry. It bit the trees and the fences and the barn. It made a lot of noise and threw things in the air.

Tom and his family ran to the basement, where they had a safe place to hide. They took their dog and their cat and some food and water. They waited for the tornado to go away. They prayed and hoped that everything would be okay.

After a long time, the storm was over. Tom and his family came out of the basement. They saw that the tornado had done a lot of damage. The barn was gone, and some of the animals were hurt. The house was still standing, but it had some holes and cracks. Tom felt sad and scared.

But then, he saw something that made him smile. It was his bike, that he loved so much. The tornado had not bitten his bike. It was still there, shiny and red. Tom ran to his bike and hugged it. He was happy that his bike was safe.

His mom and dad came to him and hugged him too. They told him that they were proud of him for being so brave. They told him that they were lucky to have each other, and that they would fix the farm together. They told him that the tornado was serious, but that they would be okay. Tom felt better, and he thanked his bike for being strong. He hoped that the tornado would never come back.
<|end|>


