Lily liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna. Anna had a pink dress, blue eyes and long hair. Lily thought Anna was charming.

One day, Lily's aunt came to visit. She brought a big box for Lily. Lily was happy and curious. She opened the box and saw a new doll. The doll had a yellow dress, green eyes and curly hair. She also had a buckle on her belt. Lily's aunt said, "This is Belle. She is from France. I bought her for you when I was there. Do you like her?"

Lily looked at Belle and smiled. She liked her too. She said, "Thank you, auntie. She is very pretty. I like her buckle. It is shiny." She hugged Belle and kissed her cheek.

Lily's aunt said, "You're welcome, sweetie. I'm glad you like her. I have to go now, but I will see you soon. I love you." She hugged Lily and kissed her forehead.

Lily said, "I love you too, auntie. Bye bye." She waved at her aunt as she left.

Lily took Belle and Anna to her room. She said, "Anna, this is Belle. She is your new friend. Belle, this is Anna. She is my best friend. You can play with us." She put them on her bed and gave them each a toy. She said, "Let's pretend we are princesses. We can send letters to each other with our toys. It will be fun." She smiled and started to play.
