Lily and Tom are playing by the lake. They see many stones on the ground. Lily picks up a white stone and shows it to Tom.

"Look, Tom, a white stone!" Lily says.

"Wow, it is very pretty!" Tom says.

Lily throws the white stone into the lake. It makes a big splash. Lily and Tom laugh.

"Let me try!" Tom says. He picks up a brown stone and throws it into the lake. It makes a small splash.

"That was not a big splash!" Lily says.

Tom picks up another stone. It is black and shiny. He throws it into the lake. It makes a huge splash. Lily and Tom clap.

"That was a great splash!" Lily says.

They see a fish jump out of the water. It is silver and wet. It makes a splash too. Lily and Tom smile.

"Hello, fish!" they say.

The fish goes back into the water. Lily and Tom look for more stones. They have fun splashing them into the lake.
<|end|>


