Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big tree with red and yellow leaves. They want to make a pile of leaves and jump in it.

"Let's spread the leaves on the ground," Lily says.

"OK, I will help you," Tom says.

They work hard and make a big pile of leaves. They run and jump in it. They laugh and have fun.

The next day, they go to the park again. But the pile of leaves is gone. The wind has blown them away.

"Oh no, where are our leaves?" Lily says.

"Maybe we can make another pile," Tom says.

But they look around and see that there are not many leaves left on the tree. Most of them have fallen off.

"Maybe we can wait for next week," Lily says.

"Maybe the tree will have more leaves then," Tom says.

They hope that the tree will grow more leaves. They go to play with their toys instead. They are still friends. They still like the park. They still like the tree. They wait for next week.
<|end|>


