Lila and Ben were playing in the kitchen. They liked to pretend they were chefs and make food with pots and pans. But they also made a big mess. There was water and flour and eggs on the floor.

"Uh-oh," Lila said. "Mom will be mad. We have to clean up."

Ben nodded. He saw a mop in the corner. He grabbed it and started to wipe the floor. Lila helped him with a cloth. They worked hard and fast.

Suddenly, they heard a knock on the door. They stopped and looked at each other. Who could it be?

They ran to the door and opened it. They saw a man with a big smile and a bag. He was wearing a red suit and a hat. He looked like Santa.

"Hello, Lila and Ben," he said. "I'm here to give you a present. You have been very good and fair this year. You always share and help and say sorry. And you are cleaning up your mess. That's very nice of you."

Lila and Ben gasped. They couldn't believe it. Santa had come to their house. They felt very happy and excited.

"Wow, thank you, Santa," they said. "What did you bring us?"

Santa reached into his bag and pulled out two boxes. He gave one to Lila and one to Ben. They opened them and saw what was inside. Lila got a doll and Ben got a car. They were the toys they had wished for.

"Wow, wow, wow," they said. "We love them. Thank you, thank you, thank you."

Santa smiled and hugged them. He said, "You're very welcome. I'm glad you like them. Now, I have to go. I have more presents to deliver. But I'll see you next year. Merry Christmas, Lila and Ben."

"Merry Christmas, Santa," they said. They waved goodbye and watched him leave. Then they ran back to the kitchen and played with their new toys. They were very happy. They had the best day ever.
<|end|>


