Lily and Tom are friends. They like to play with dolls and cars. One day, they find a pin on the floor. It is shiny and sharp.

Lily says, "I want the pin. I can make a necklace for my doll."

Tom says, "No, I want the pin. I can make a wheel for my car."

They disagree. They pull the pin from each other. They are angry and sad.

Mom sees them. She is not happy. She says, "Stop! The pin is not a toy. It can hurt you. Give it to me."

Lily and Tom are scared. They let go of the pin. Mom takes it away. She says, "You need to share and be kind. Why don't you play with something else?"

Lily and Tom say sorry to each other. They hug and smile. They find a ball and a book. They play together. They are friends again.
