Sara and Ben were twins who liked to play with their toys. One day, they got a big box of new toys from their aunt in the post. They were very happy and excited, and they opened the box and took out all the toys.

But Sara and Ben did not want to share their toys with each other. They each wanted to have the best and the most toys for themselves. They started to fight and grab and pull the toys from each other. They did not say thank you or please or sorry. They did not care about their aunt or each other.

Soon, the toys started to disappear. One by one, the toys vanished from their hands and from the floor. Sara and Ben did not notice at first, because they were too busy fighting. But when they looked around, they saw that the box was empty and there were no toys left.

They were very sad and confused. They wondered where the toys went. They wished they had played nicely and shared their toys. They felt sorry for their aunt who had sent them the gift.

Then they heard a voice from the box. It was their aunt. She said, "I sent you these toys to make you happy, but you were not humble and kind. You did not appreciate what you had or each other. So I made the toys disappear with a magic spell. If you want them back, you have to learn to share and be grateful and love each other."

Sara and Ben realized their mistake. They hugged each other and said they were sorry. They promised to be humble and kind and share and be grateful and love each other. They asked their aunt to forgive them and to bring back the toys.

Their aunt smiled and said, "I'm glad you learned your lesson. I love you both very much. Here are your toys. Enjoy them, but remember to be good and happy." She waved her hand and the toys reappeared in the box. Sara and Ben thanked their aunt and played with their toys together. They never fought over them again. They were humble and kind and happy.
<|end|>


