Lily and Ben are at the park with Mom. They see a big pond with ducks and fish. Lily and Ben want to feed the ducks. Mom gives them some bread.

Lily and Ben break the bread into small pieces. They throw the pieces into the pond. The ducks swim to the bread and eat it. Lily and Ben laugh and clap.

"Look, Ben, that duck is fat!" Lily says. "He ate too much bread!"

Ben nods. He sees a fish jump out of the water. The fish makes a big splash. Ben wants to touch the fish.

"Can I touch the fish, Mom?" Ben asks.

Mom shakes her head. "No, Ben, the fish are too fast. And the water is too deep. You might fall in."

Ben pouts. He leans over the edge of the pond. He stretches his arm to reach the water. He wants to splash the fish.

But he leans too far. He loses his balance. He falls into the pond. He makes a bigger splash than the fish.

Lily screams. Mom runs to the pond. She grabs Ben's arm and pulls him out. Ben is wet and cold. He cries.

Mom hugs Ben and wraps him in a towel. She scolds him gently.

"Ben, you have to be careful. You could have hurt yourself. And you scared Lily and the ducks."

Ben sniffles. He says sorry to Mom and Lily and the ducks. He learns his lesson. He does not try to touch the fish again.
<|end|>


