<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing with their toy cars on the floor. They liked to make noises and pretend they were driving fast. Lily had a red car and Ben had a blue car. They had a long tube that they used as a tunnel for their cars.

"Look, Lily, I can make my car go through the tube and come out the other side!" Ben said, as he pushed his car into the tube.

"That's cool, Ben, but I can do something better!" Lily said, as she put her car in reverse and backed it up into the tube. "I can make my car go backwards through the tube and come out the same side!"

"Wow, Lily, you are very creative!" Ben said, as he watched her car emerge from the tube. "How did you do that?"

"I just used the reverse button on my car. It makes it go the opposite way. Do you want to try?" Lily said, as she handed her car to Ben.

"Sure, thank you, Lily!" Ben said, as he took her car and pressed the reverse button. He smiled as he made his car go backwards through the tube. "This is fun, Lily! You are a good friend for sharing your car with me!"

Lily smiled back at Ben. "You are welcome, Ben! You are a good friend for playing with me! We can both use the reverse button and the tube to make our cars do creative things!"

The moral of the story is: Sharing and being creative can make playing more fun and make friends happy.
<|end|>


