Ben and Lily were playing in the garden. They liked to dig and water the plants. They saw some red things on the vines. They were tomatoes!

"Look, Ben, tomatoes!" Lily said. "Can we pick them?"

Ben nodded. He reached for a tomato. But it was too high. He could not get it.

"Let me help you," Lily said. She stood on a rock. She grabbed a tomato. She pulled hard. The tomato came off. But Lily lost her balance. She fell off the rock. She landed on the ground. The tomato splashed on her head.

"Ouch!" Lily said. "That hurt!"

Ben ran to her. He saw the tomato on her head. He laughed. He thought it was funny.

"Lily, you have a tomato hat!" Ben said. "You look silly!"

Lily felt the tomato on her head. She was wet and sticky. She did not like it. She frowned. She did not think it was funny.

"Ben, that's not nice!" Lily said. "You should not laugh at me!"

Ben saw that Lily was sad. He felt sorry. He did not want to make her sad.

"I'm sorry, Lily," Ben said. "I did not mean to hurt your feelings. You are not silly. You are my friend."

He gave her a hug. He helped her get up. He wiped the tomato off her head.

"Thank you, Ben," Lily said. "You are my friend too."

They smiled. They hugged again. They decided to pick some more tomatoes. But this time, they were careful. They did not want to fall again. They had fun in the garden.
