Anna is a daughter. She likes to help her mom cook. Mom cooks soup and bread for lunch. Anna stirs the soup and puts cheese on the bread. She smells the yummy food and smiles.

But Anna is also sleepy. She wakes up early today and plays a lot. She yawns and rubs her eyes. Mom sees Anna is sleepy and says, "Why don't you take a nap, sweetie? You can eat later when you wake up."

Anna nods and hugs her mom. She says, "I love you, mom. And I love your soup and bread." Mom says, "I love you too, Anna. And I'm proud of you for helping me cook." She kisses Anna and takes her to her bed. She tucks her in and sings a soft song. Anna closes her eyes and falls asleep. She dreams of soup and bread and mom.
