Ben likes hockey. He has a hockey stick and a ball. He plays hockey with his dad in the park. He runs and hits the ball with his stick. He is happy and healthy.

One day, Ben sees a big boy in the park. The big boy has a hockey stick and a ball too. He plays hockey with his friends. He is fast and strong. Ben wants to play with him.

"Hi, can I play with you?" Ben asks the big boy.

The big boy looks at Ben. He sees his hockey stick and his ball. He wants them.

"No, you can't play with us. You are too small. And this is my hockey stick and my ball now." The big boy says. He takes Ben's hockey stick and ball and runs away.

Ben is sad and angry. He cries and shouts. His dad hears him and comes to him.

"What's wrong, Ben?" His dad asks.

"The big boy took my hockey stick and my ball. He is mean and bad." Ben says.

His dad hugs him and says, "Don't worry, Ben. We will get them back. The big boy is not nice. He should share and be kind."

His dad and Ben go to the big boy and his friends. His dad talks to the big boy and says, "Give back Ben's hockey stick and ball. They are his. You can't take them. You have to ask and say please."

The big boy is scared of Ben's dad. He gives back Ben's hockey stick and ball. He says sorry to Ben.

Ben is happy and says thank you. He plays hockey with his dad again. He is happy and healthy.
