Anna was a lonely girl. She had no friends to play with at school. She only had one toy, a brown bear named Ben. Ben was her best friend. She hugged him every night and told him stories.

One day, Anna saw a new girl in her class. Her name was Lily. Lily had a lot of toys in her backpack. She had dolls, cars, puzzles, and books. Anna wanted to talk to Lily, but she was shy.

At recess, Anna sat on a bench with Ben. She watched Lily play with her toys. Lily looked happy and fun. Anna wished she could join her.

"Hi, I'm Lily. What's your name?" Lily came over to Anna and smiled.

Anna was surprised. She looked at Lily and said, "I'm Anna. This is Ben. He's my bear."

Lily nodded. She looked at Ben and said, "He's cute. Can I play with him?"

Anna hesitated. She loved Ben, but she also wanted to make a friend. She decided to share. She said, "Okay, you can play with him. But be careful. He's very special to me."

Lily smiled. She took Ben and hugged him. She said, "Thank you, Anna. You're very nice. Do you want to play with my toys, too?"

Anna nodded. She felt happy. She said, "Yes, please. I like your toys. They look fun."

Lily and Anna became friends. They played with their toys and talked. They laughed and had fun. Anna was not lonely anymore. She had a new friend and a bear. She was glad she mentioned Ben to Lily.
<|end|>


