Tom and Sue are twins. They like to play in the park. But today, they are bored. They want to do something new.

"Let's go to the zoo!" Tom says.

"Yes, let's go!" Sue says.

They run to their mom. She is on the bench. She is reading a book. She is lazy.

"Mom, can we go to the zoo?" Tom asks.

"Please, mom, please!" Sue begs.

Mom looks at them. She shakes her head. She says, "No, we can't go to the zoo. It is too far. It is too expensive. It is too noisy."

Tom and Sue are sad. They are angry. They start to cry. They shout at mom.

"That's not fair! You are lazy! You never take us anywhere! We hate you!" they shout.

Mom is shocked. She is hurt. She says, "How can you say that? I love you. I work hard for you. I take you to the park every day. You are ungrateful. You are rude. You should say sorry."

Tom and Sue are quiet. They think. They feel bad. They say sorry.

"Sorry, mom. We love you. We don't hate you. We were wrong. We are sorry." they say.

Mom smiles. She hugs them. She says, "It's okay. I forgive you. I love you too. But you should not shout at me. You should be polite. You should be happy with what you have."

Tom and Sue nod. They say, "Yes, mom. You are right. We are sorry. We are happy."

They go back to the park. They play with their ball. They see a dog. They pet it. They laugh. They have fun. They forget about the zoo. They are happy.
<|end|>


