Anna and Ben are playing in the park. They see a big slide. Anna wants to go on the slide, but Ben is scared.

"Come on, Ben, it is fun!" Anna says. "Don't be silly, it is not scary."

Ben shakes his head. "No, Anna, it is too high. And it is hot. The sun makes the slide hot. It will hurt."

Anna rolls her eyes. She thinks Ben is silly. She runs to the slide and climbs up the ladder. She sits on the top and smiles.

"Look, Ben, I am on the slide. It is not hot. It is cool. And it is fun. Whee!" She slides down fast and laughs.

Ben watches Anna. He sees that she is happy. He wants to be happy too. He decides to act brave. He runs to the slide and climbs up the ladder. He sits on the top and looks down. He feels scared, but he does not want to be silly.

"Here I go, Anna. I am brave. Whee!" He slides down fast and laughs.

Anna and Ben hug each other. They are happy. They play on the slide again and again. They have fun. They are not silly. They are brave.
<|end|>


