Sara and Ben are playing with paint. They make many colors on paper. They have fun. But their fingers are dirty. They need to wash them.

"Look, Sara, my fingers are blue and green!" Ben says.

"My fingers are red and yellow!" Sara says.

They show each other their fingers. They laugh.

But then they hear Mom call.

"Kids, time for lunch! Come and wash your hands!"

Sara and Ben run to the bathroom. They turn on the faucet. They put soap on their hands. They rub their fingers. They see the paint go away.

"Wow, the water is amazing!" Ben says. "It makes our fingers clean!"

"Yes, it is amazing!" Sara says. "But we can still see our colors on the paper!"

They rinse their hands. They dry them with a towel. They go to the kitchen. They see Mom waiting for them.

"Look, Mom, we made art with paint!" Sara says.

She gives Mom her paper. Ben gives Mom his paper.

Mom smiles. She hugs them.

"That's wonderful, Sara and Ben!" Mom says. "You are very creative! And you have very clean fingers!"
