Dan and Sam are friends. They like to play baseball in the park. Dan is good at hitting the ball. Sam is good at catching the ball. They have fun together.

One day, a big boy comes to the park. He has a red hat and a loud voice. He says he wants to play baseball with Dan and Sam. He says he is tough and he can hit the ball very far. He says Dan and Sam are not tough and they can only hit the ball a little bit.

Dan and Sam do not like the big boy. He is mean and rude. They do not want to play with him. They say no, thank you. The big boy gets angry. He says he will take their ball and bat. He says they are scared of him. He says they are babies.

Dan and Sam are not scared. They are brave. They say they are not babies. They say they are friends. They say they have a secret weapon. The big boy laughs. He says what is it? A toy? A candy? A diaper?

Dan and Sam smile. They say no, it is not a toy, a candy, or a diaper. It is a song. They start to sing a song. It is a funny song. It is a silly song. It is a song about the big boy. They sing he has a red hat, but he has no hair. They sing he has a loud voice, but he has no words. They sing he is tough, but he is a bluff. They sing he is mean, but he is a bean.

The big boy does not like the song. He does not think it is funny. He does not think it is silly. He thinks it is mean. He gets very mad. He tries to grab the ball and bat, but Dan and Sam run away. They keep singing the song. They sing louder and louder. They sing all the way to the other side of the park.

The big boy cannot catch them. He cannot stop them. He cannot make them stop singing. He feels sad and alone. He wishes he had not been mean and rude. He wishes he had been nice and polite. He wishes he had friends like Dan and Sam. He wishes he could sing a song with them.
<|end|>


