Tom and Lily wanted to buy a flashlight. They liked to play with flashlights in the dark. They had some money from their piggy bank. They asked their mom if they could go to the store.

Mom said yes, but they had to be careful and come back soon. She gave them a big hug and a kiss. Tom and Lily put on their coats and shoes. They took their money and walked to the store.

At the store, they saw many flashlights. Some were big, some were small, some were red, some were blue. They looked at all of them. They liked a small yellow flashlight. It was shiny and bright. They asked the store lady how much it was.

The store lady said it was five dollars. Tom and Lily counted their money. They had four dollars and fifty cents. They were sad. They did not have enough money.

Then they saw a naughty boy. He was sneaking behind the store lady. He grabbed a big green flashlight and ran away. He did not pay for it. He was stealing.

Tom and Lily saw what he did. They were shocked. They knew stealing was very bad. They decided to tell the store lady.

They ran to the store lady and said, "Excuse us, miss. We saw a naughty boy. He took a flashlight and ran away. He did not give you any money. He was stealing."

The store lady was surprised and angry. She thanked Tom and Lily for telling her. She said they were very good and honest. She said she would call the police and find the naughty boy.

Then she said, "You know what? You can have the yellow flashlight for free. You deserve it. You are very brave and kind."

Tom and Lily were very happy. They thanked the store lady and hugged her. They took the yellow flashlight and ran back home. They showed their mom their new flashlight. They told her what happened at the store.

Mom was very proud of them. She said they did the right thing. She said they could play with the flashlight in the dark. She said she loved them very much. Tom and Lily smiled and hugged her. They said they loved her too. They turned on the flashlight and had fun.
<|end|>


