Tim and Sam were two otters who liked to play in the river. They swam and slid and splashed all day. They had a lot of fun with their friends, the fish and the frogs and the ducks.

One day, they saw a big light in the sky. It was bright and shiny and made them curious. They wanted to see what it was, so they swam closer and closer. They did not see the big bird that was flying above them. The bird had sharp claws and a hungry mouth. It saw the two otters and wanted to eat them.

"Look, Sam, the light is so pretty!" Tim said. "I wonder what it is."

"I don't know, Tim, but it makes me feel warm and happy," Sam said. "Let's go closer and touch it."

They did not hear the bird as it swooped down and grabbed them with its claws. They did not feel the light as it burned their fur and skin. They only felt pain and fear as the bird carried them away. They cried and screamed, but no one heard them. They never saw their friends or the river again. They did not grow old and happy. They only grew cold and dead. The light was not pretty. It was bad.
<|end|>


