Lila and Tom were friends who liked to play outside. They had a big zip that they could slide down from a tree. It was fun and fast. One day, they saw a new thing in the sky. It was a sail. It was white and had a long tail. It moved with the wind.

"Wow, look at that!" Tom said. "What is it?"

"It is a sail," Lila said. "My dad told me. He said people use them to fly in the air."

"Can we fly with it?" Tom asked.

"I don't know. Maybe we can try," Lila said.

They ran to the field where the sail was. They saw a man holding a string. He smiled at them.

"Hello, kids. Do you like my sail?" he asked.

"Yes, it is very pretty," Lila said.

"Can we fly with it?" Tom asked.

"Sure, you can take turns. But be careful, it is very strong," the man said.

He gave the string to Lila. She held it tight. The sail pulled her up. She felt like a bird. She laughed.

"Wow, this is fun!" she said.

Tom watched her. He wanted to fly too. He waited for his turn.

But then, the wind changed. The sail went higher and higher. Lila got scared. She tried to pull the string down. But it was too hard.

"Help! Help!" she cried.

Tom and the man heard her. They ran to help her. They grabbed the string. They pulled and pulled. But the sail was too strong. It dragged them along.

"Help! Help!" they cried.

They were lonely and afraid. They wished they had stayed on the zip.
<|end|>


