Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play with toys and books. One day, they go to the park with their moms. They see a big slide. Lily wants to go on the slide, but Ben is scared.

"Come on, Ben, it is fun!" Lily says. "I will teach you how to slide."

"No, no, no, it is too high!" Ben says. "I will fall and hurt myself."

Lily shakes her head. She thinks Ben is stupid. She runs to the slide and climbs up the ladder. She sits on the top and smiles at Ben.

"Look, Ben, it is easy!" she says. "You just zip down and land on the sand. Whee!"

She pushes herself and slides down. She laughs and feels the wind on her face. She lands on the sand and jumps up.

"See, Ben, I did it!" she says. "It was so much fun! You should try it too!"

Ben watches Lily. He sees that she is happy and not hurt. He feels a little brave. He walks to the slide and looks up. It is still high, but not as high as before. He climbs up the ladder slowly. He sits on the top and holds the sides. He looks at Lily.

"Lily, I am scared!" he says.

"Don't be scared, Ben, you can do it!" Lily says. "Just zip down like me. I will catch you!"

Ben takes a deep breath. He lets go of the sides and slides down. He feels the wind on his face too. He lands on the sand and Lily catches him.

"Ben, you did it!" Lily says. "You are not stupid, you are brave!"

Ben smiles. He feels proud and happy. He hugs Lily.

"Thank you, Lily, you are a good friend!" he says. "You are a good teach too!"

They laugh and hug. They go on the slide again and again. They have a lot of fun. Their moms watch them and smile. They are proud of their kids. They are good friends too.
<|end|>


