Tom and Lily are playing with blocks. They want to build a big tower. They put one block on top of another block. They are happy.

But then, Max comes. Max is not nice. He wants to play with the blocks too. He does not ask. He just takes some blocks from Tom and Lily. He says, "These are my blocks now. Go away!"

Tom and Lily are sad and angry. They say, "No, Max! These are our blocks. We were playing first. Give them back!"

Max does not listen. He tries to build his own tower. But he is not careful. He puts too many blocks on one side. His tower falls down. The blocks make a loud noise.

Tom and Lily see what happens. They say, "Ha ha, Max! Your tower is bad. Our tower is better. You are not successful. You are silly."

Max is ashamed and mad. He wants to make Tom and Lily's tower fall down too. He runs to their tower. He tries to push it. But Tom and Lily are smart. They see him coming. They close their stand. They hold their tower with their hands. They say, "Stop, Max! You cannot break our tower. We worked hard. We are successful. You are mean."

Max cannot reach their tower. He stops. He feels sorry. He says, "I'm sorry, Tom and Lily. You are right. I was mean. Can I play with you? Can I help you build your tower?"

Tom and Lily think for a moment. They say, "OK, Max. You can play with us. But you have to be nice. You have to share. You have to be careful."

Max nods. He says, "OK. I will be nice. I will share. I will be careful."

They smile. They give Max some blocks. They build their tower together. They are happy.
<|end|>


