Lily and Ben are twins. They like to play outside when it rains. They put on their boots and coats and hats. They go to the park with Mom.

"Look, Lily, a big puddle!" Ben says. He runs to the puddle and jumps in. Splash! Water goes everywhere. Ben laughs.

"Me too, me too!" Lily says. She follows Ben and jumps in the puddle. Splash! Water goes everywhere. Lily laughs.

Mom watches them and smiles. She likes to see them have fun.

"Let's march in the puddle!" Ben says. He starts to march like a soldier. His boots make loud noises. Lily marches with him. They march and splash and laugh.

Mom joins them. She marches with them. They march and splash and laugh together.

They are all glad. They like the rain. They like the puddle. They like to march.
