Tom and Jen are friends. They like to play in the park. One day, they see a big jar of sugar on a bench. They are hungry and want some sugar.

"Look, Jen, sugar!" Tom says. "Let's eat some. It is sweet and good."

"OK, Tom, but be careful. Maybe someone left it there for a reason." Jen says. She is a little scared.

They run to the bench and open the jar. They take big handfuls of sugar and put them in their mouths. They smile and laugh. The sugar is very sweet and good.

But then, they hear a loud roar. They turn around and see a big lion. The lion is angry and hungry. The lion was hiding behind a tree. The sugar was a trap. The lion wanted to catch some kids.

"Run, Jen, run!" Tom shouts. He drops the sugar and tries to run away.

But the lion is faster and stronger. The lion jumps on Tom and bites him. Tom screams and cries. Jen is too scared to move. She drops the sugar and falls to the ground.

The lion sees Jen and roars again. The lion is wild and hungry. The lion wants more sugar and more kids.

Jen closes her eyes and hopes for help. But no one comes. The lion eats Jen too. The lion is happy and full. The lion relaxes on the bench and licks the sugar from his paws. The end.
