Tom and Lily are brother and sister. They like to play in their room. But their room is full of junk. Toys, books, clothes, and papers are everywhere. Mom is not happy. She tells them to clean up.

"Tom, Lily, come here!" Mom says. "Look at this mess. You have to put away your junk. Or you can't go to the park."

Tom and Lily do not want to clean up. They want to go to the park. They like to swing, slide, and run. They look at each other. They have an idea.

"Mom, we can clean up fast. Watch us!" Tom says. He grabs a big blanket. He spreads it over the junk. He tucks the edges under the bed. "There, all done!"

Lily smiles. She grabs a pillow. She puts it on the blanket. "Look, Mom, we made a mountain. Can we go to the park now?"

Mom shakes her head. She is not fooled. She lifts the blanket. She sees the junk. She is not happy. She frowns.

"Tom, Lily, this is not cleaning up. This is hiding. You have to put away your junk in the right places. Or you can't go to the park."

Tom and Lily are sad. They do not like to clean up. But they want to go to the park. They sigh. They start to pick up their junk. They put the toys in the toy box, the books on the shelf, the clothes in the closet, and the papers in the trash. It takes a long time. But they finish.

"Mom, we cleaned up. Can we go to the park now?" Lily asks.

Mom looks at their room. She sees no junk. She is happy. She smiles.

"Yes, you can go to the park now. You did a good job. I'm proud of you." Mom says.

Tom and Lily are happy. They hug Mom. They grab their coats and hats. They run to the door.

"Thank you, Mom. We love you." Tom says.

"Bye, Mom. See you later." Lily says.

They go to the park. They swing, slide, and run. They have fun. They are happy.
<|end|>


