"What do I have to promise?" Lily asked.

"You have to promise to share it with me. We can take turns playing with it. And we have to be careful not to break it. It looks fragile." Tom said.

Lily nodded. She hugged the bottle and said, "I promise, Tom. I will share it with you. And we will be careful. Thank you for giving me the bottle. You are a good friend."

Tom and Lily hugged each other. They were happy. They took the bottle to the sandbox and pretended it was a rocket. They had a lot of fun with their new toy. They kept their promise and shared it. They were good friends.
