Sara and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They see many things in the park. They see birds, dogs, flowers and swings. They speak to each other about what they see.

One day, they see something rare in the park. They see a big red truck. The truck has a ladder and a hose. The truck makes a loud noise. Sara and Ben are curious. They want to see the truck closer.

They walk to the truck. They see some men in yellow suits. The men are firefighters. They are here to help. They speak to Sara and Ben. They tell them that there is a fire in a house. They are going to put out the fire. They ask Sara and Ben to stay away from the truck and the fire.

Sara and Ben are scared. They do not like fire. They do not want to see the fire. They want to go home. They look for the exit of the park. They see a gate. They run to the gate. They leave the park. They go home. They are safe. They hug their moms. They tell them what they saw. They are glad that the firefighters are brave. They hope that the fire is gone. They hope that everyone is okay. They say thank you to the firefighters in their hearts.
