Tom and Mia are friends. They like to play with tools. They have hammers, saws, nails and wood. They want to make a house for their toys.

They find a big box in the yard. They think it is perfect for their house. They use a marker to draw a door and windows on the box. They use a saw to cut the box. They use nails to fix the box.

But then, a hairy dog comes. The dog is big and loud. He sees the box and thinks it is a toy. He runs to the box and bites it. He tears the box with his teeth.

Tom and Mia are scared and angry. They shout at the dog.

"Go away, dog! This is our house, not your toy!"

The dog does not listen. He keeps biting the box. He makes a big mess.

Tom and Mia are sad. They worked hard on their house. Now it is ruined.

They run to their mom. They tell her what happened. She hugs them and says,

