Sara and Ben were twins. They liked to play with their toys and books. But sometimes they were lazy. They did not want to help Mom and Dad with chores.

One day, Mom said, "We need to go to the shop. We have no milk and bread. Can you help me carry the bags?"

Sara and Ben said, "No, we are busy. We want to play."

Mom said, "Okay, but you will have no snack when we come back."

Sara and Ben did not care. They kept playing.

Mom went to the shop. She bought milk and bread and some cookies. She carried the bags by herself. She was tired.

She came back home. She saw Sara and Ben still playing. She said, "I have milk and bread and cookies. Who wants a snack?"

Sara and Ben said, "We do! We do!"

Mom said, "Sorry, but you were lazy. You did not help me. You have no snack."

Sara and Ben were sad. They realized they were wrong. They said, "We are sorry, Mom. We should have helped you. Can we have a snack, please?"

Mom said, "Maybe later. First, you need to do your chores. Then, you can have a snack and share with me."

Sara and Ben said, "Okay, Mom. We will do our chores. We love you."

Mom said, "I love you too. And I am proud of you. You learned a lesson today."
<|end|>


