Tom is a smart boy. He likes to show his colors to his friends. He has many colors in his box. He has red, blue, yellow, green, and more.

One day, he goes to the park with his mom. He sees his friend Lily. Lily is playing with a ball. Tom runs to her and says, "Hi, Lily. Do you want to see my colors?"

Lily nods and smiles. She likes colors too. She puts her ball down and sits with Tom. Tom opens his box and shows her his colors. He says, "This is red. It is the color of apples and fire trucks. This is blue. It is the color of the sky and the water. This is yellow. It is the color of the sun and bananas. This is green. It is the color of the grass and the frogs."

Lily listens and looks. She likes Tom's colors. She says, "Wow, Tom. You have so many colors. You are very smart. Can I use your colors too?"

Tom nods and smiles. He likes to share his colors. He says, "Yes, Lily. You can use my colors. We can draw together. What do you want to draw?"

Lily thinks and says, "I want to draw a flower. A flower has many colors. It is pretty and smells good."

Tom says, "That is a good idea. I want to draw a car. A car can go fast and make noise."

They take some paper and some colors. They start to draw. They have fun. They show their drawings to each other. They say, "Wow, you are very good. I like your drawing."

They are happy. They are friends. They like to show their colors.
