Tom was a boy who liked to play in the garden. He liked to dig and run and look for bugs. One day, he saw a lizard on a rock. The lizard was green and had a long tail. Tom wanted to catch the lizard and keep it as a pet.

He ran to the lizard and tried to grab it. But the lizard was fast and scared. It ran away from Tom and hid under a leaf. Tom was angry and frown. He did not like that the lizard ran away. He wanted to have it for himself.

He looked for the lizard and found it under the leaf. He reached his hand to take it. But the lizard was fierce and brave. It opened its mouth and bit Tom's finger. Tom cried out and let go of the lizard. He felt pain and fear. He ran to his mom and showed her his finger.

His mom was kind and gentle. She cleaned his finger and put a bandage on it. She hugged him and said, "Tom, you should not try to catch a lizard. Lizards are wild animals. They do not like to be touched or kept. They need to be free and happy in their own home. You should respect them and leave them alone. Do you understand?"

Tom nodded and said, "Yes, mom. I understand. I am sorry for the lizard. I will not bother it again. I will only watch it from far away. And I will be careful of its teeth." He smiled and said, "Thank you, mom. You are the best."

His mom smiled and said, "You are welcome, Tom. You are a good boy. I love you." She kissed him and said, "Now, let's go and have some cookies and milk. And maybe we can read a book about lizards and learn more about them. How does that sound?"

Tom said, "That sounds great, mom. I love you too." He held her hand and walked with her to the house. He learned a lesson that day. He learned to be kind and respectful to animals. And he learned that lizards are not good pets, but they are amazing creatures.
<|end|>


