Lily and Ben liked to pretend they were explorers. They had a big cardboard box that they turned into a tunnel. They crawled inside and used a flashlight to see.

"Look, there's a treasure!" Lily said, pointing to a shiny necklace she had hidden in the corner.

"Wow, let me see!" Ben said, reaching for it.

But Lily pulled it away. "No, it's mine! I found it first!"

Ben was angry. He wanted the treasure too. He tried to grab it from Lily, but she held on tight.

"Stop it, Ben! You're hurting me!" Lily cried.

"Give it to me, Lily! It's not fair!" Ben shouted.

They both pulled and tugged, but neither would let go. The necklace broke and the beads flew everywhere.

They both gasped. They looked at the broken necklace and then at each other. They felt sad and sorry.

"I'm sorry, Lily. I shouldn't have been mean to you," Ben said.

"I'm sorry, Ben. I shouldn't have been greedy," Lily said.

They hugged and said they were still friends. They decided to share the beads and make new necklaces. They smiled and crawled out of the tunnel. They saw their mom waiting for them with a bright smile.

"Did you have fun, explorers?" she asked.

"Yes, mom. We had an adventure and we learned to share," they said.

They showed her their new necklaces and she hugged them. They were happy.
<|end|>


