Lily and Tom were very happy. They were going on a holiday with Mum and Dad. They packed their bags and got in the car. They drove for a long time, and then they saw the sea. The sea was blue and shiny. Lily and Tom wanted to swim and play in the sand.

They got out of the car and ran to the beach. Mum and Dad put up a big umbrella and a blanket. They gave Lily and Tom some tasty sandwiches and juice. Lily and Tom ate and drank, and then they went to the water. They splashed and laughed and made bubbles. They had fun.

But then, a big wave came. It was very fast and loud. It crashed on the beach and took away the umbrella and the blanket. It also took away the sandwiches and the juice. Lily and Tom were scared and wet. They ran to Mum and Dad. Mum and Dad hugged them and said it was okay. They said the wave was naughty and it destroyed their picnic. They said they still had their bags and their car, and they could find another place to eat and rest.

Lily and Tom felt better. They said they were sorry for the wave. They said they still liked the sea, but they wanted to be careful. They said they still wanted to have a holiday. Mum and Dad smiled and said they loved them. They said they would have a good holiday, no matter what. They said they would find something else to do that was fun and tasty. They got in the car and drove away. They looked for a new adventure.
