Lily liked to play with her dolls every day. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Anna. Anna had long hair, a pink dress, and a smile. Lily decided to take Anna to the park on Wednesday, because it was a sunny day and she had no school.

She put Anna in her backpack and walked with her mom to the park. She saw a large slide, a swing, and a sandbox. She wanted to try them all, but she did not want to leave Anna alone. She asked her mom, "Can I take Anna with me?"

Her mom said, "Sure, but be careful. Don't let her fall or get dirty. She is very special to you."

Lily nodded and ran to the slide. She put Anna on her lap and slid down. She felt the wind in her hair and heard Anna giggle. She was happy. She did the same on the swing and the sandbox. She had a lot of fun with Anna.

But then, she saw a boy with a big dog. The dog was barking and running towards her. She was scared. She hugged Anna and tried to run away, but the dog was faster. It jumped on her and knocked her down. It grabbed Anna with its teeth and shook it. Lily screamed, "No! Give me back Anna!"

Her mom heard her and ran to help her. She pulled the dog away and took Anna from its mouth. She checked if Lily was hurt. She was not, but she was crying. She looked at Anna. Anna was not smiling anymore. Her hair was torn, her dress was dirty, and her face was scratched. Lily was very sad. She said, "Anna is broken. She is not my favorite anymore."

Her mom hugged her and said, "I'm sorry, Lily. The dog was bad. But Anna is still your favorite. She is not broken. She is just different. She still loves you and you still love her. You can fix her hair, wash her dress, and put a band-aid on her face. She will be happy again. And so will you."

Lily looked at Anna and saw that her mom was right. She still loved Anna, even if she was different. She decided to take her home and make her better. She said, "Thank you, mom. You are right. Anna is still my favorite. I will make her happy again. And I will never leave her alone."
<|end|>


