Sara and Tom were friends. They liked to play with glow sticks. Glow sticks were sticks that made light when you bent them. They had many colors: red, blue, green, yellow. Sara and Tom liked to make shapes and patterns with glow sticks.

One night, Sara and Tom wanted to play with glow sticks outside. They asked their moms if they could go. Their moms said yes, but they had to be careful and stay close to the house. Sara and Tom said okay and ran outside with their glow sticks.

They saw a big club near their house. A club was a place where big people went to dance and have fun. The club had loud music and bright lights. Sara and Tom were curious. They wanted to see the club. They forgot what their moms said. They walked to the club with their glow sticks.

The club was very busy. There were many big people inside. They were dancing and drinking and talking. Sara and Tom felt scared. They did not know anyone. They tried to find a way out. But they could not. The big people did not see them. They were too small and too dark.

Sara and Tom waved their glow sticks. They hoped someone would help them. But no one did. The big people thought their glow sticks were part of the club. They did not care. Sara and Tom cried. They wished they had listened to their moms. They wished they had stayed close to the house. They wished they had never gone to the club.
