Sara and Ben were playing in the garden. They liked to find hidden things and make up stories. Sara saw a big box behind the shed. She ran to it and called Ben.

"Look, Ben, a box! Maybe there is something inside. Let's open it!"

Ben followed Sara and helped her lift the lid. The box was empty, but it was big enough for them to fit inside. They climbed in and closed the lid.

"Now we are in a secret place," Sara said. "No one can find us here. We can relax and pretend we are on an adventure."

Ben nodded and smiled. He liked to relax with Sara. They were best friends. He looked around the box and saw some holes in the sides. He peeked through one and saw a bird on a branch.

"Look, Sara, a bird! It is singing to us. Can you hear it?"

Sara moved to the hole and listened. She heard the bird's song and felt happy. She sang back to the bird.

"Hello, bird, we are in a box. We are having fun. Do you want to join us?"

The bird tilted its head and flew closer. It landed on the edge of the box and looked inside. It saw Sara and Ben and chirped.

"Hello, children, you are in a box. You are having fun. I want to join you."

Sara and Ben laughed and clapped. They made room for the bird and invited it in. The bird hopped in and sat on Sara's shoulder. They all relaxed and enjoyed their hidden place. They were happy.
