Ben and Mia were playing with marbles on the floor. They had many marbles of different colors and sizes. They liked to roll them and make them hit each other.

"Look, I have a big blue marble!" Mia said, holding it in her hand.

"Wow, it is very pretty!" Ben said. "Can I see it?"

Mia nodded and gave him the marble. Ben looked at it closely and smiled. He liked how it shone in the light.

"Can I roll it?" he asked.

"Okay, but be careful. It is my favorite marble," Mia said.

Ben nodded and put the marble on the floor. He gave it a gentle push with his finger. The marble rolled fast and straight. It hit another marble and made a loud sound.

"Good shot!" Mia said, clapping her hands.

Ben was happy. He wanted to try again. He picked up the marble and pushed it harder. The marble rolled faster and farther. But it did not hit another marble. It rolled past the other marbles and under the sofa.

"Oh no!" Ben said. "Where did it go?"

Mia got up and looked under the sofa. She saw the marble hiding in a dark corner.

"I see it!" she said. "But I can't reach it. It is too far."

Ben got up and joined her. He tried to reach the marble with his hand. He stretched his arm as much as he could. But he was too clumsy. He knocked over a lamp and made it fall.

"Crash!" The lamp broke into pieces on the floor.

"Uh oh!" Ben said. "We are in trouble."

Mia looked at the broken lamp and the lost marble. She felt sad and scared.

"What do we do?" she asked.

Ben thought for a moment. He had an idea.

"Let's close the door and hide under the bed," he said.

Mia nodded. She followed him to the door and closed it. Then they ran to the bed and hid under it. They hoped no one would find them or the mess they made. They hugged each other and waited.
