Lily and Ben like to play in the park. They have a ball and a kite. They run and laugh and have fun. One day, they see a hole in the ground. They look inside and see a mole. The mole is brown and furry and has a long nose.

"Hello, mole!" Lily says. "Do you want to play with us?"

The mole nods and comes out of the hole. He likes the ball and the kite. He rolls the ball with his nose and chases the kite in the air. Lily and Ben are happy to have a new friend.

But then, a big wind comes. It blows the kite away. Lily and Ben run after it, but they can't catch it. They lose the kite. They are sad.

They go back to the hole, but they can't find the mole. He is gone. They lose the mole too. They are very sad.

They sit on the grass and cry. They have no ball, no kite, no mole. They have nothing to play with. They are bored and dull.

Then, they hear a noise. It is the mole. He comes out of another hole. He has the kite in his mouth. He found it in a tree. He brings it to Lily and Ben. He is happy.

Lily and Ben are happy too. They hug the mole and thank him. They have their kite back. They have their mole back. They have something to play with. They are not bored and dull anymore. They are bright and cheerful. They play with the mole until it is time to go home. They say goodbye to the mole and promise to come back soon. The mole waves and goes back to his hole. He is glad to have new friends.
