Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play with toys and draw on the board. One day, they are in the playroom with their teacher, Miss Rose.

"Look, Lily, I made a house with blocks!" Ben says. He is eager to show Lily his work.

"That's nice, Ben. Can I help you?" Lily asks. She likes to build things too.

"Sure, Lily. You can make a door and a window." Ben says. He gives Lily some blocks and a smile.

They work together and make a nice house. They are happy and proud.

"Wow, you two did a great job!" Miss Rose says. She comes to see their house. "Can I take a picture of you and your house?"

"Yes, please!" Lily and Ben say. They stand next to their house and pose.

"Say cheese!" Miss Rose says. She holds a camera.

"Cheese!" Lily and Ben say. They look at the camera.

But then, Ben does something funny. He leans over and gives Lily a kiss on the cheek.

Lily is surprised. She feels her cheek get warm. She looks at Ben and sees him blush.

Miss Rose is surprised too. She laughs and snaps the picture.

"Ben, why did you kiss Lily?" Miss Rose asks.

"Because I like her. She is my friend." Ben says.

"That's very sweet, Ben. But you should always ask before you kiss someone. Do you understand?" Miss Rose says.

"Yes, Miss Rose. I'm sorry, Lily. Can I kiss you?" Ben says.

Lily thinks for a moment. She likes Ben too. He is her friend. She nods and smiles.

"Okay, Ben. You can kiss me." Lily says.

They kiss again, gently and quickly. They giggle and hug.

Miss Rose smiles and shows them the picture. It is a nice picture. They see their house, their kiss, and their happy faces.

They like the picture. They like their house. They like each other. They are friends.
