Lily and Sam are friends. They like to play at the park. They gather rocks and sticks and leaves. They make a big pile. They say it is their castle.

They see a slide. It is long and shiny. They want to go on it. They run to the slide. They take turns. Lily goes first. She sits on the slide. She slides down fast. She laughs. Sam goes next. He slides down too. He says it is fun.

They see a dog. It is big and brown. It runs to them. It barks. Lily and Sam are scared. They drop their rocks and sticks and leaves. They run away from the dog. They hide behind a bench. They hug each other.

The dog sniffs their pile. It likes their rocks and sticks and leaves. It takes some in its mouth. It runs away with them. It is happy.

