Ben and Lily were playing in the living room. They liked to pretend they were grown-ups and had a fancy party. They had some juice in small cups and some crackers on a plate. They also had a big bottle of wine that they found in the kitchen. They did not know what wine was, but it looked pretty.

"Hello, Lily," Ben said in a deep voice. "Welcome to my party. Would you like some wine?"

"Yes, please, Ben," Lily said in a high voice. "Thank you for inviting me. You have a lovely home."

Ben poured some wine into Lily's cup. He tried to be careful, but he spilled some on the floor. He did not notice. He gave the cup to Lily and took one for himself. They clinked their cups and said, "Cheers!"

They sipped their wine and made faces. It tasted bad. They did not like it at all. They put their cups down and ate some crackers. They felt funny. They started to giggle and talk louder.

Mom came into the living room. She saw the wine bottle and the spilled wine on the floor. She saw Ben and Lily with their cups and their red faces. She was very angry.

"Ben! Lily! What are you doing?" she yelled. "That is not juice, that is wine! Wine is for grown-ups only! You are not allowed to drink wine! You could get sick!"

She took the wine bottle and the cups away. She cleaned the floor with a cloth. She looked at Ben and Lily with a stern face.

"That was very naughty and dangerous," she said. "You should never touch wine or any other drink that is not for you. You should always ask me or Dad before you take anything from the kitchen. Do you understand?"

Ben and Lily nodded. They felt sorry and scared. They did not mean to be bad. They just wanted to have fun.

"I'm sorry, Mom," Ben said.

"Me too, Mom," Lily said.

Mom hugged them and said, "I love you, but you have to be more careful. Now, go to your room and rest. You need to get the wine out of your system."

Ben and Lily went to their room. They lay down on their beds and closed their eyes. They felt sleepy and dizzy. They learned their lesson. They did not want to drink wine ever again. They only wanted juice and water.

The End.
<|end|>


