Lily and Ben were playing in the living room. They liked to pretend they were pirates and look for treasure. They used a big blanket as a sail and a wooden spoon as a sword. They had a lot of fun.

But then, Lily saw something shiny on the table. It was an ashtray that Mommy used to put her cigarettes in. Lily thought it was a treasure. She climbed on the couch and reached for it. She did not know it was bad.

"Look, Ben, I found a treasure!" she said, holding the ashtray. "It is shiny and round and has little holes in it."

Ben saw the ashtray and felt scared. He knew Mommy did not like them to touch her things. He knew the ashtray was not a treasure. He tried to stop Lily.

"No, Lily, put it back!" he said. "That is not a treasure. That is Mommy's ashtray. She will be mad if she sees you have it."

But Lily did not listen. She wanted to keep the ashtray. She thought it was pretty. She held it tight and ran away from Ben. She did not see the cord on the floor. She tripped and fell. The ashtray flew out of her hand and broke on the floor. It made a loud noise.

Mommy heard the noise and came to the living room. She saw the broken ashtray and the mess on the floor. She saw Lily and Ben. She was very mad. She yelled at them.

"What did you do?" she said. "Why did you touch my ashtray? Do you know how dangerous that is? You could have hurt yourself or started a fire. You are very naughty. Go to your room right now!"

Lily and Ben felt sorry and scared. They did not mean to break the ashtray. They did not know it was bad. They started to cry. They ran to their room. They hugged each other. They wished they had not played with the ashtray. They wished they had listened to Ben. They wished Mommy was not mad. They wished they were still pirates.
<|end|>


