Lily loved to play violin. She had a small violin that was just right for her. She liked to make music with it and sing along. She was very clever and learned many songs.

One day, Lily wanted to show her friend Ben how she could play violin. She invited him to her house and took him to her room. She said, "Look, Ben, this is my violin. Do you want to hear me play?"

Ben nodded and smiled. He liked music too. He had a drum that he liked to bang. He said, "Yes, Lily, I want to hear you play. Can I play my drum with you?"

Lily said, "Sure, Ben, that would be fun. But we have to be careful. We don't want to break anything or make too much noise."

Lily and Ben got ready to play. Lily picked up her violin and put it under her chin. She held the bow in her hand. She said, "Ben, do you know how to balance the violin?"

Ben shook his head. He said, "No, Lily, I don't know. How do you balance the violin?"

Lily said, "You have to hold it with your chin and your shoulder. Like this. See? You don't need your hands to hold it. You need your hands to play the strings and the bow. Can you try to balance the violin?"

Ben said, "OK, Lily, I will try." He took the violin from Lily and put it under his chin. He tried to hold it with his shoulder, but it was hard. The violin slipped and fell to the floor. Ben gasped and said, "Oh no, Lily, I'm sorry. I dropped your violin. Is it broken?"

Lily ran to the violin and picked it up. She checked it carefully. She said, "Don't worry, Ben, it's not broken. It's just a little dirty. You have to be more gentle with the violin. It's not like a drum. It's very delicate. Here, let me show you again how to balance it."

Lily and Ben tried again. This time, Ben was more careful. He held the violin with his chin and his shoulder. He said, "Look, Lily, I did it. I balanced the violin."

Lily smiled and said, "Good job, Ben. You are very clever. Now, let's play some music together. I will play the violin and you will play the drum. Are you ready?"

Ben nodded and said, "Yes, Lily, I'm ready. Let's play."

Lily and Ben played some music together. They had a lot of fun. They were very happy. They were good friends.
<|end|>


