Lily liked to dance. She danced every day. She danced in her room, in the garden, and in the park. She danced with her toys, with her friends, and with her family. She danced when she was happy, when she was sad, and when she was bored.

One day, Lily saw a show on TV. It was about a nation of dancers. They danced in different ways. Some danced fast, some danced slow. Some danced high, some danced low. Some danced with music, some danced with no sound. Lily was amazed. She wanted to dance like them.

She asked her mom, "Can I dance like them?" Her mom said, "Yes, you can. You are flexible. You can learn new things. You can try different moves. You can have fun." Lily was excited. She said, "Thank you, mom. I will dance like them."

She turned off the TV. She put on her favorite dress. She found a big space. She started to dance. She danced like the nation of dancers. She danced fast and slow. She danced high and low. She danced with music and no sound. She danced with joy. She danced with love. She danced with herself. She danced like Lily.
<|end|>


