Tim and Jen are twins. They like to play with their toys in their room. One day, they find a big box in the closet. They open the box and see many things inside. They see a hat, a scarf, a coat, and a pin.

"Look, Jen, a pin!" Tim says. He picks up the pin and shows it to Jen. The pin is shiny and has a star on it.

"Wow, Tim, it is pretty!" Jen says. She wants to see the pin too. She reaches for the pin, but Tim pulls it away.

"No, Jen, it is mine!" Tim says. He puts the pin on his coat. He zips up his coat and puts on the hat and the scarf. He looks at himself in the mirror. He thinks he looks cool.

"Tim, share with me!" Jen says. She is sad and angry. She does not like it when Tim does not share. She looks around the box and sees a dull knife. She picks up the knife and runs to Tim.

"Jen, what are you doing?" Tim says. He sees Jen with the knife and gets scared. He thinks Jen wants to hurt him.

"Give me the pin, Tim, or I will cut your coat!" Jen says. She waves the knife at Tim.

"Jen, no, stop!" Tim says. He tries to back away, but he trips on the scarf. He falls to the floor and the pin falls off his coat.

Jen sees the pin and grabs it. She is happy and puts it on her hat. She does not see that the knife has cut Tim's coat and made a big hole.

"Look, Tim, I have the pin!" Jen says. She shows Tim the pin and smiles.

Tim looks at Jen and then at his coat. He sees the hole and starts to cry. He does not care about the pin anymore. He only cares about his coat.

"Jen, you are mean!" Tim says. He cries louder and louder.

Mom hears Tim and Jen and comes to their room. She sees the mess and the knife and the hole. She is angry and shocked.

"Tim, Jen, what have you done?" Mom says. She takes the knife and the pin away from them. She scolds them and makes them say sorry to each other. She tells them to never play with sharp things again. She hugs them and tries to fix the coat.

Tim and Jen feel bad and hug Mom. They say sorry to Mom and to each other. They learn to share and to be careful. They do not play with the box anymore. They play with their other toys and have fun.
<|end|>


