Lily and Ben were playing in the park with their toys. They liked to make up stories with their dolls and cars. They saw a big tree with a hole in it. Lily was nosy and wanted to see what was inside.

"Let's go there!" she said to Ben. "Maybe there are animals or treasures in the hole."

Ben was not sure. He thought the hole looked dark and scary. He wanted to stay on the grass with his toys.

"No, Lily, I don't want to go there. It might be dangerous. What if there are bees or snakes or monsters in the hole?" he said.

Lily did not listen to Ben. She urged him to follow her. She said it would be fun and exciting. She ran to the tree and peeked into the hole.

"Wow, look, Ben, there is a shelter in here! Someone made a bed and a table and a lamp with sticks and leaves. Come and see!" she shouted.

Ben was curious, but he was also afraid. He walked slowly to the tree and looked into the hole. He saw the shelter, but he also saw something else. A big, furry, angry face with sharp teeth and claws. It was a bear, and it did not like visitors.

"ROAR!" the bear growled. It jumped out of the hole and chased Lily and Ben.

Lily and Ben screamed and ran away. They dropped their toys and ran to their mom, who was sitting on a bench. She hugged them and asked them what happened.

"We saw a bear in the tree, Mommy! It was scary!" Lily said.

"Why did you go to the tree, Lily? You know you should not go near strange places. You could get hurt or lost," Mommy said.

"I'm sorry, Mommy. I was nosy and wanted to see what was in the hole. I urged Ben to come with me, but he did not want to. He was right, Mommy. It was a bad idea," Lily said.

Mommy nodded and said, "I'm glad you are safe, Lily and Ben. Next time, listen to your brother and stay away from danger. And don't be so nosy, Lily. Sometimes, it is better to leave things alone."

Lily and Ben said they were sorry and hugged Mommy. They learned their lesson and never went to the tree again. They played with their toys and had fun in the park. They were happy and safe.
<|end|>


