Tom is a young boy who likes to play with his cars. He has many cars of different colors and sizes. He likes to make them go fast on the floor and make loud noises.

One day, Tom is playing with his cars in his room. He sees a big wall with a picture of a train on it. He thinks the train is very cool and wants to get closer to it. He picks up his red car and puts it on the wall. He tries to make it go on the wall like the train, but it falls down.

Tom is not happy. He wants his car to go on the wall. He picks up his blue car and puts it on the wall. He tries to make it go on the wall like the train, but it falls down too.

Tom is very sad. He thinks his cars are broken. He starts to cry. He does not know why his cars cannot go on the wall.

His mom hears him cry and comes to his room. She sees his cars on the floor and the wall with the picture of the train. She hugs Tom and tells him that his cars are not broken. She tells him that cars can only go on the floor, not on the wall. She tells him that the wall is not real, it is only a picture. She tells him that the train is real, but it can only go on the tracks, not on the wall.

Tom listens to his mom and feels better. He understands that his cars and the train are different. He stops crying and smiles. He picks up his cars and plays with them on the floor. He makes them go fast and make loud noises. He is happy again. He likes his cars and the wall with the picture of the train.
