Sara and Tom are friends. They like to play outside in the sun. One day, they find a big stick in the grass. They want to use it for a game.

"Let's play that we are wild animals," Sara says. "We can carry the stick like a bone."

"OK," Tom says. "I will be a lion and you will be a tiger. We can roar and run."

They take turns to carry the stick in their mouths. They pretend to chase each other and fight for the stick. They make loud noises and have fun.

But then, they hear a real roar. It is not from them. It is from a big dog. The dog sees the stick and wants it. It runs towards them, barking and growling.

Sara and Tom are scared. They drop the stick and run away. They hide behind a tree and hug each other.

"Go away, dog!" Sara shouts. "That is our stick!"

But the dog does not listen. It picks up the stick and runs away with it. It is happy to have a new toy.

Sara and Tom are sad. They lost their stick and their game. They go back to their house and tell their mom what happened.

"Don't worry, my sweeties," mom says. "You can find another stick tomorrow. Or you can play something else. The sun will still shine and you will still be friends."
