Ben and Lily liked to watch movies with their mom and dad. They also liked to eat popcorn when they watched movies. Mom and dad said popcorn was a good snack, but they had to be careful not to eat too fast or too much.

One day, they watched a movie about a big lion and a little mouse. The lion was loud and scary, but the mouse was smart and brave. The mouse helped the lion when he had a thorn in his paw. The lion was happy and became friends with the mouse.

Ben and Lily were so into the movie that they did not notice how much popcorn they ate. They ate and ate until the bowl was empty. Then they felt sick in their tummies. They wanted to stop the movie and go to the bathroom, but they were afraid to miss the end.

They tried to hold it in, but it was too hard. Ben felt a big burp coming up. He tried to cover his mouth, but it was too late. He burped so loud that it made a sound like a lion's roar. He also spit out some popcorn that flew across the room.

Lily was shocked and scared by Ben's burp. She thought it was the lion from the movie. She screamed and jumped off the couch. She bumped into the table and knocked over a lamp. The lamp fell to the floor and broke with a loud crash.

Mom and dad heard the noise and came running. They saw the mess and the popcorn and the broken lamp. They were not happy. They asked Ben and Lily what happened.

Ben and Lily felt bad. They knew they did something wrong. They told mom and dad the truth. They said they ate too much popcorn and Ben burped and Lily screamed and struck the lamp. They said they were sorry and they did not mean to do it.

Mom and dad were still not happy, but they saw that Ben and Lily were sorry. They said they forgave them, but they had to clean up the mess and go to bed early. They also said they had to be more careful with popcorn and movies next time.

Ben and Lily nodded and said okay. They helped mom and dad clean up the mess and went to bed early. They hugged mom and dad and said they loved them. They also said they liked the movie and the lion and the mouse. They hoped they could watch it again someday, but with less popcorn.
