One day, Rob heard a ringing. It was coming from the river. He ran to the river and saw a fine boat. The boat had a bell that was ringing. Rob climbed aboard the boat and waved goodbye to the river. 

Rob sailed down the river. He could see fish swimming and birds flying in the sky. The boat made a soft rocking motion as it sailed along. Rob was having a great time. 

Suddenly, the boat hit a rock in the river and stopped. Rob began to feel worried. He got off the boat and saw an old man standing by the riverbank. The old man showed Rob how to use a paddle to move the boat.

Rob hopped back in the boat and took the paddle. He pushed and pulled the paddle and the boat started moving again. Pretty soon, Rob was fine and the boat was back on course. He waved goodbye to the old man and continued down the river.

Rob arrived at his destination safely. He was happy and relieved. He thanked the river and the old man for helping him, and he paddled back to shore. He couldn't wait to tell his friends about his river adventure.
