Once upon a time there was an angry bird that lived in the lake. It wanted to fly up high into the sky. So the bird flapped its wings and hopped around on the lake. Everyone around the lake watched and cheered. Finally, the bird spread its wings and soared up high! It flapped its wings and flew higher and higher, up into the clouds. Once it got to the sky, it saw the other birds, small and big, and they all welcomed the angry but brave little bird. 

The bird flew and flapped around, feeling the air around it and feeling so free and happy. The bird flew until the sun began to go down and the stars and moon came out. Finally, it swooped back down to the lake and landed back on the ground. All of the animals cheered, and the little bird was so proud of itself. It had flown up high into the sky, and nothing made it prouder. 

The End
