Lucy didn't know what to do with it, so she decided to take it to her Mom. When she got home, she showed it to her Mom and asked what it was. Her Mom smiled and said it was a patch for her shirt. She told Lucy to be careful, because she didn't want the patch to tear.

Lucy nodded and started to work. She kept the patch close and tried very hard to be careful. But sometimes, she was too rough with it. She made stupid mistakes and almost ruined the patch. But eventually, Lucy managed to finish and her shirt looked beautiful with the patch on it.

From then on, Lucy remembered to be careful whenever she held something special. She knew that if she was too rough, she could easily ruin it. So she kept the patch safe and remembered to always be gentle.
