Once upon a time, there was a brave turtle called Larry. One day, he was swimming in the sea when he heard a great noise. He asked his friend, a seagull, what was happening. The seagull replied that it was a big hurricane.

Larry was scared, but he was very brave. His wings were too small to fly away, so he decided to stay and face the hurricane. He felt the wind blowing and the waves were very rough.

The hurricane was strong and Larry was scared, but he was determined to stay and not hide. Suddenly, he heard a loud roar. Larry looked up and saw the biggest wave he had ever seen! But he was still brave, and he held onto a rock and stayed in the storm.

Finally, after many hours, the hurricane was gone and the sea returned to its usual calm. Larry smiled and breathed a sigh of relief.

He had been brave in the face of a rough hurricane, and he was proud.
