Once there was a dependable little girl named Sue. She had strong muscles so that she could match her friends when it came time to play. Sue liked to run and jump and do burpees every day.

One day, Sue and her pals decided to play hide and seek. They chose Sue to go first and then she dashed off to hide. She found the perfect spot and crouched down low, trusting that her strong muscles would keep her hidden.

Afterwards, all of her friends had a turn to match Sue's hiding spot. When it was her turn to seek, Sue found all of her friends using her strong muscles. When she reached the last spot, she was the very first one to find her friend!

Everyone laughed and had so much fun playing. Sue was so proud of her dependable muscles. She thanked them and vowed to use them again when she needed a good hiding spot or a dependable friend.
<|end|>


