Once there was a girl named Anna. She wanted to go on an adventure. So her mommy said she could go find a maze.
Anna was so excited, she knew it was going to be fun. She started to measure how big the maze was so she knew exactly how far to go.
It was big and tricky and full of turns so Anna decided to be careful.
But the walls of the maze were very smooth, so Anna was able to slide along them and make her way through the maze.
When Anna made it to the end, she was so proud of herself. She hugged her mommy, who was waiting for her, and she knew that the adventure was the best she ever had.
