Once upon a time, there was a little girl called Bonnie. She was three years old and loved to dress up. She would often pick out pretty dresses and put them on.

One day, she was getting dressed for a party. She tried on a few dresses but none of them felt very comfortable. Bonnie had almost given up when she found the perfect dress. It was pink, sparkly and incredibly comfortable. She twirled around in it, feeling excited.

At the party, everyone was making lots of noise. There were children running around and lots of music playing. It was very noisy, but Bonnie loved it. She danced and sang along, feeling happy.

At the end of the party, Bonnie changed back into her normal clothes. But she couldn't wait for the next time she could dress up again.
