Once upon a time, there was a curious caterpillar. He went for a walk in the garden one day and he saw something. He scrambled over to investigate and found an interesting thing.

He mentioned it to his friends, the snails, who said it was a special plant. They said he should bring to the plant and touch it. So the curious caterpillar went back and he did just that.

As soon as he touched the plant, something magical happened. Out popped a beautiful butterfly! It was bright orange and yellow, and it flitted away in the sunshine.

The caterpillar was so happy! He had helped a butterfly come out of the plant. He asked his friends if they had seen anything so amazing. They all agreed that he was the luckiest caterpillar around!
