Once upon a time there was a fisherman. He was very clean, and tidied his clothes everyday. Every morning he would wake up early, and then say "Today I'm going to catch lots of fish!" He would take his fishing rod, and head down to the lake.

When he got to the lake, he stood on the shore and would cast his line in the water. Then he would wait quietly and say "Come on little fish, come and get my bait". After a while, he usually managed to catch a few fish. 

The fisherman was very happy when he caught the fish. He said "I'm very pleased with my catch today, I can now cook some delicious meals". So he would take his catch home and cook them for dinner. 

