Jim was a happy 3 year old boy who loved to play outside. On one sunny day, he decided to go outside and play on the lawn. It was rough because the grass hadn't been cut for a while, but Jim didn't mind.

He began to run around on the lawn, laughing and having fun. Then, suddenly, he felt something different under his feet. He stopped, and looked down. There was a hole in the lawn!

Jim started to turn in circles very slowly in the hole. When he turned three full times, something magical happened. He jumped out of the hole and the lawn was suddenly soft and smooth! Jim was amazed and laughed in delight. 

"Turning in circles really does work!", he thought. So Jim spent the rest of the day running on the smooth and perfect lawn.
<|end|>


