Once there was a famous rabbit named Timmy. Everyone knew of him because he was big and strong. 

One day, Timmy wanted to explore the forest. He hopped and hopped until he came to a river. Timmy wondered how to cross the river. 

But then he saw a frog swimming in the river. Timmy asked the frog a question.

"Can you help me get across the river?"

The frog smiled and said yes. He said he would show Timmy the way. So Timmy followed the frog, hopping from one rock to another until he was safely across the river.

When he was done, the frog said goodbye, and Timmy hopped away. He was very happy that he could explore the forest without getting wet!
<|end|>


