Once upon a time there was a small girl. She was very obedient. One day she was playing in her yard when she saw a stranger. The girl was a bit scared but she was obedient and waited. The stranger walked up and said "Hello" with a kind voice. The little girl still felt scared, so she turned and ran away.

The stranger then followed her. As she ran, his voice got kinder and gentler. He said "I just want to be your friend". The little girl stopped running, and she started to feel better.

The stranger asked the girl if she would like to come with him and help pick some apples. The girl thought about it for a little bit, then she nodded her head and said "Yes". The two of them went to the closest orchard.

At the orchard, they picked as many apples as they could and they were both having fun. They picked apples until they were tired and the sun was setting. The little girl brought the apples home and helped her mom dry them.

Once they were dry, they used the apples to make delicious apple pies and apple sauce. The little girl was happy and she thanked the stranger for his help. She said goodbye and watched the stranger walk away. The little girl never saw him again, but she always remembered him as a kind and obedient stranger.
<|end|>


