Mummy and Daddy had a lovely surprise for Emma. They had bought her a plastic tape measure. Emma was so excited! She ran and squeezed the tape measure and saw the little red numbers go up and down. Daddy taught Emma how to measure things. She measured Daddy's hand and then the length of the table. Mummy said with a giggle, "Now you can measure all kinds of things!" Emma clapped her hands and said, "I love my tape measure!" Then Emma went around the house measuring everything she could! She even asked Mummy and Daddy if she could measure them, too! Daddy said, "You will be the best measurer in the world!" Emma smiled and said, "Yes, I will be the best measurer ever!"
<|end|>


