The radish was very shy. It didn't want to meet other vegetables in the garden. It stayed hidden in the shadows until it was all alone.

One day, a strong wind came and scattered the radish far away from the garden. It couldn't believe what had happened. It was so frightened.

The radish rolled all the way down the hill and landed in a different garden. Everyone was so friendly and welcoming. The radish felt shy at first, but soon became part of the group. It felt like it belonged.

The radishes in the new garden were so different. They played, laughed and had so much fun in the sun. The shy radish soon realised that it had been missing out all this time!
