Little Sue was so excited. She was going to visit the hill today. As she packed her picnic basket, the sun came out in the sky. She put on her sun hat and skipped outside ready to explore the hill.

As she started to climb the hill, it got steeper and steeper. She stopped and looked up. It looked like it was a long way to the top. Sue hesitated for a moment, but then decided she was ready for the challenge.

But little did Sue know, as she climbed higher and higher, the hill got higher and higher. She had to stop and take a break. She looked down - it was very far to the bottom of the hill. She started to panic.

Just then, she noticed a smooth path that curved around the top of the hill. She smiled and took a deep breath. She continued to climb and minutes later, she was at the top. She was so happy and proud of herself! She had climbed the hill!
<|end|>


