Once upon a time, there was a dog named Sarah who was very hungry. She looked all around for something to eat, but she could not find anything. Then, she saw a bird flying high above in the sky. She thought, "Maybe the bird has food." 

She barked and called to the bird. The bird flew down and stopped to rest on a nearby tree. Sarah took a deep breath, and asked the bird, "Can you feed me?" The bird said it was sorry, but it had nothing to give. 

Then, Sarah noticed a fox walking in the distance. She ran to the fox and asked if it could feed her. The fox replied, "I'm sorry, I cannot feed you right now. I am looking for my pass." Sarah asked, "Where is your pass?" The fox thought for a moment, and then said, "I don't know. A bad storm blew it away." 

Sarah felt very sorry for the fox. She wished she could help him. Just as she was about to offer him a word of encouragement, Sarah heard a loud squeak from behind a nearby bush. 

Sarah ran over to the bush and found a young mouse struggling to reach a piece of cheese. She carefully grabbed the cheese and fed the hungry mouse. 

Sarah had finally found something to eat, and she happily thanked the mouse for the snack. Sarah and the mouse were very happy
<|end|>


