Once upon a time there was a bunny. His neck was long and soft. He lived in a small hole in the ground and he was very happy. 
One day he decided to go on an adventure. He hopped out of his hole and ran and ran. When he was far away from home he lay down in the grass. He was very tired but he did not know it was the wrong thing to do.

Suddenly a giant bird swooped down and grabbed him in its sharp claws. It carried him high up in the air. The bunny was scared and squirmed to get away but he could not.

The bird flew as high as he could go. The bunny was so scared he closed his eyes tight. Suddenly the bird let go of him and he fell down and down. He fell into his hole, safe and sound.

Ever since that day, the bunny has never lied in the grass again. He knows it can be dangerous and he stays close to his home and his cozy hole.
