Once outside, Ginger had a lot of fun in the sunshine. But soon, she was tired. She looked for a good spot to take a nap.

Ginger found a nice, soft spot under a tree. The smell of the perfume combined with the warmth and sunshine made it even more cozy. She snuggled into the grass and closed her eyes. She could hear birds chirping and the wind rustling in the leaves.

Ginger took a long, peaceful nap. After a while, the sun began to set. Ginger opened her eyes and stretched. Then she smiled. The nap was even better smelling with the perfume!

Ginger was happy that her mom had given her the perfume. It was helpful in calming her down and helping her sleep. She thanked her mom again when she went inside.
