Once upon a time, there was a bad farmer. He was so bad that he wanted to raise the price of his fruits and vegetables! Everyone was very sad.

The farmer's neighbors were very angry. They all wanted to do something about the bad price, but they didn't know what to do. So they got together and decided to have a big meeting.

At the meeting, they talked and talked. They discussed ways to get the bad farmer to lower the price. Everyone agreed that they should try to make the farmer understand that he was being too bad by raising the price so high. 

After talking for a long time, the farmer's neighbors came up with a plan. They decided to give the farmer some of their fruits and vegetables for free. They hoped that this would make the farmer happy and help him to lower the price.

The next day, the farmer was surprised to find free fruits and vegetables on his doorstep. He was so pleased that he decided to lower the price of his own fruits and vegetables so that everyone could afford them.

And that was the end of the bad farmer raising the price. Everyone was relieved and happy! There was much rejoicing and the farmer realized that being bad was not a good way to get things done.
