Once upon a time there was a very bright girl. She was always happy and liked to sing and laugh. But one day she found some trouble. She wanted to try and make it go away, but she couldn't. She felt scared and tried to cry, but she couldn't do that either. 

Then, she remembered something someone once told her. She remembered that if she surrendered to the trouble, it might make things better. So, she held her hands up in the air and said, "I surrender!" 

And, surprisingly, it worked! The trouble couldn't stay around. It vanished and the bright girl was happy again. She thanked herself for being brave and surrendering to the trouble. From then on, she knew that she could use this brave trick whenever something bad happened.
