Clara liked to climb. She went to the park and saw a huge, modern tree. Clara smiled and started to climb. She used the branches and held onto the trunk. With each step she got higher and higher.

When she finally reached the top, she looked around. She saw a beautiful river, forests and lots of green grass. She even saw a bird sitting close by and spreading its wings. Clara started to laugh.

The bird heard her laughter and started to wink at Clara. Clara was so happy that the bird winked at her. She started to wink back and she stayed there for quite some time, playing with the bird.

When evening came, Clara climbed down from the tree. She waved goodbye to the bird and promised to come back soon. Clara smiled and ran home, excited to tell her family all about her modern adventure.
