Once upon a time, there was a man named Joe. He was sad because he had done something wrong. He was so guilty that he decided to run away. He got on a boat and set sail.

As Joe sailed away, he shouted to the people in the port, "Goodbye!" But they couldn't hear him, so he just kept on sailing.

Days and days went by and Joe thought he was safe. But one day, he heard a loud call coming from the port. It was the people there. They had seen Joe running away and wanted him back.

Joe was so scared, but he knew he was guilty and had to go back. He turned the boat around and sailed back to the port. When he got there, the people welcomed him back and told him everyone makes mistakes. Joe was so relieved and he was glad he had decided to go back.
<|end|>


