Once upon a time, there was a girl named Jane. She was playing outside in the park with her friends. Suddenly, there was a big wave that came crashing down on the beach. Jane was scared, but her friends wanted to discuss what to do.

"Let's go to the beach," said one of her friends. Jane wasn't sure if that was a good idea. It was getting dark and she was feeling a little scared.

"It's okay," said another friend. "The water looks calm. We can go for a walk on the beach and look for shells."

Suddenly, Jane felt brave. So she followed her friends to the beach and started to search for shells in the sand. It was getting dark, but the water was calm and the waves were gentle.

As they walked, Jane's friends discussed what they could do. They talked about making sandcastles and playing tag. After a while, Jane saw a beautiful shell. It was pink and it had a pretty wave pattern on it. She was so excited that she couldn't stop talking about it!

All of Jane's friends agreed that the shell was beautiful and they discussed how they could keep it safe. In the end, they decided to take turns carrying it back to the park.

When they were all tired, they said goodbye to the moon and the waves and returned to the park. Jane still had her shell, and she was smiling all
