One day, Sally was outside playing with her friends. It was a hot day. Suddenly, she saw a big, noisy traffic. Sally got scared and refused to go closer. She said loudly "No! I won't go there." Her friends asked her why and she answered "It's too hot and noisy".

One of Sally's friends suggested that they should go somewhere else and play. Sally thought this would be a better idea. So she and her friends started walking away from the traffic. Soon they found a nice, peaceful place and started having fun.

Sally was happy they had gone away from the traffic. Refusing to go near it turned out to be a good idea!
