Once upon a time there was a little girl named Anna. Anna liked to go outside and play every day. One day, Anna went outside and saw that the sky was so big and blue. It was so big that Anna wanted to bring a piece of the sky home.

So Anna asked her mom for some help. Her mom said, "I have an idea! Let's use some string to make a big kite. Then we can fly it up high enough to reach the sky."

Anna, her mom and her dad all went outside and set up the kite. It was a very big kite with a colorful tail. Anna and her dad pulled on the string and the kite flew right up to the sky. 

But, the string was so tight that Anna couldn't pull it down. Her dad had to use his special scissors to cut the string, and the big kite flew away into the sky.

Anna was very sad, but then her mom said, "That's OK. We can still bring a piece of the sky with us! Look, when the light from the sun hits the leaves of the trees they look like they're made of gold. We can take some of that gold home to remember our adventure in the sky."

Anna smiled, and they all gazed up at the beautiful sky. Anna knew she would never forget the sky, even if she couldn't bring a piece of it home.
<|end|>


