Molly was a happy three year old girl. She loved music, dancing and playing with her toys. One day, Molly saw a guitar in the store. She wanted to buy it! 

Molly asked her mum if she could buy it. 'Yes', said her mum. Molly was so excited! 

Molly loved to strum the guitar and make music. Soon, she was able to play a few notes. But she had no idea how to make her guitar sound better. 

That night, Molly heard a noise coming from the next room. She opened the door and saw a man playing the guitar. He was amazing! His fingers flew on the strings and the notes were so beautiful. 

Molly said loudly, 'Can you teach me?' The man was deaf, so he couldn't hear her. Molly was so disappointed. 

But that didn't stop Molly from learning the guitar. She kept practising and soon she could play many numbers. In time, she even became a great guitar player!
