He said, "Little girl, why don't you come outside and play with me? We can play until you feel sleepy." 

The little girl smiled and went outside. She played with the nosy little bird until she was too tired to keep playing. Then she said goodnight to the nosy little bird and hopped back into bed. 

When she woke up the next morning, she felt very relaxed and happy. She no longer had to worry about not being able to fall asleep. She had found her own special way to sleep. 

The End.
