Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily who loved to wear a pretty bow in her hair. One day, she went to the park with her mommy and saw a big dog. The dog was not calm and started to bark at Lily. She got scared and ran away.

When they got home, Lily's mommy told her they needed to make a plan to stay safe around dogs. They decided to always ask the owner if it was okay to pet the dog and to never run away.

The next day, Lily and her mommy went back to the park. They saw the same dog, but this time they asked the owner if it was okay to pet him. The owner said yes, and the dog was calm and friendly.

But then, when they were leaving the park, Lily saw a butterfly and ran after it. The dog got scared and bit her. Lily learned that even if a dog seems calm, she should always ask before petting and never run away. The moral of the story is to always be careful and ask before doing something.
