Once upon a time, there were two friends, a cat and a dog. They both wanted to play with the same toy, but they couldn't agree on who should play with it first. The cat said, "I want to play with the toy first," but the dog disagreed and said, "No, I want to play with it first."

They argued for a while, but then the cat had an idea. She suggested that they take turns playing with the toy and put it on the shelf when they were done. The dog thought this was a good idea, and they both agreed to be careful with the toy so it wouldn't break.

From that day on, the cat and dog played with the toy together, taking turns and putting it back on the shelf when they were finished. They both learned that it was better to share and take turns than to disagree and fight over things.
