Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She had a new toy, a shiny red ball. She loved to throw it up in the air and catch it. One day, Lily went to the park to play with her ball. She saw a boy who spoke a different language than her. She wanted to play with him but didn't know how to talk to him.

Lily tried to show the boy her ball, but he didn't understand. She felt sad because she wanted to make a new friend. Suddenly, Lily had an idea. She threw the ball to the boy, and he caught it. They started to play together, and Lily realized that language didn't matter when they were having fun.

From that day on, Lily and the boy played together every day. They didn't need to speak the same language to have fun. Lily learned that throwing a ball could help her make new friends, no matter where they came from or what language they spoke.
<|end|>


