Once upon a time, there was a little fish named Bubbles who lived in a pond. Bubbles was a regular fish who loved to swim and play with her fish friends. One day, Bubbles saw a shiny hook in the water. She remembered her mother telling her to stay away from hooks because they were dangerous. 

But Bubbles was curious and wanted to see the hook up close. She swam closer and closer until she was hooked! Bubbles tried to swim away, but the hook was too strong. Suddenly, she remembered her mother's words and knew she should have listened. 

Just then, a friendly turtle swam by and saw Bubbles in trouble. The turtle used his strong jaws to bite the hook and set Bubbles free. Bubbles was so grateful and thanked the turtle for saving her life. From that day on, Bubbles listened to her mother's advice and never went near hooks again. The moral of the story is to always listen to your parents and stay away from danger.
<|end|>


