Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside with her friends. One day, Lily and her friends decided to build a tent in the backyard. They used sticks and blankets to make the tent. 

As they were playing inside the tent, they heard a loud noise. Lily felt frightened and asked her friend, "What was that noise?". Her friend replied, "It's just the wind, don't be scared". 

But Lily still felt scared and said, "I hate loud noises". Her friends tried to make her feel better by telling her funny jokes and singing songs. Soon, Lily felt better and they continued to play inside the tent until it was time to go inside for dinner. From that day on, Lily loved playing in the tent with her friends, even if the wind made scary noises. The end.
