Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to eat tasty cookies, but he didn't like to share them with his friends. One day, Timmy's mom caught him hiding a whole sheet of cookies under his bed. She was very angry and decided to punish Timmy by taking away his favorite toy.

Timmy felt sad and realized that it was not nice to keep all the cookies for himself. He decided to apologize to his friends and share his cookies with them. His friends were happy and forgave him. Timmy learned that sharing is important and it feels good to make others happy.

From that day on, Timmy always shared his cookies with his friends and he never hid anything under his bed again. His mom was proud of him for being a good friend and for learning to do the right thing.
