Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside with her friends. One day, she saw a beautiful butterfly and started to chase it. The butterfly flew away and Lily was sad.

Suddenly, Lily had an idea. She decided to make a butterfly net with a thin stick and some string. She gathered all the things she needed and started to make the net. Her friends came to help her.

After they finished making the net, they went back outside to catch the butterfly. They searched everywhere and finally saw it. They quietly approached the butterfly and Lily gently caught it in the net. They all gazed at the butterfly in amazement.

But then, they realized that they had caught the butterfly and it couldn't fly anymore. They felt bad and decided to let it go. They opened the net and the butterfly flew away. Lily and her friends felt happy that they had seen the butterfly up close, but also learned to respect nature and its creatures.
<|end|>


