Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to read books with her mom every night before bed. One day, Lily's mom gave her a new book to read. Lily was so excited to wear her new pajamas and read the book.

As Lily was reading, she noticed a page was missing from the book. She asked her mom where the page was, but her mom didn't know. Lily was sad because she couldn't finish the story.

Later that day, Lily's friend Sarah came over to play. Sarah saw that Lily was sad and asked her why. Lily told Sarah about the missing page in her book. Sarah had a thoughtful idea. She suggested they make up their own ending to the story.

Lily was so happy and they spent the rest of the day making up their own story. They had so much fun and Lily forgot all about the missing page. From that day on, Lily and Sarah made up their own stories every time they read a book together.
