Once upon a time, there was a lazy panda named Po. Po liked to sleep all day and didn't want to play with his friends. One day, Po's friend, a little girl named Lily, came to visit him. "Po, why are you so lazy? Let's play together!" said Lily.

But Po didn't want to play. He just wanted to eat his bamboo. "I don't want to play. I just want to eat," said Po. Lily was sad because she wanted to play with Po.

But then, a bird came and stole Po's bamboo! Po was upset and cried out, "My bamboo! I want it back!" Lily saw how sad Po was and decided to help him. Together, they chased after the bird and got the bamboo back. Po was so happy that he hugged Lily and said, "Thank you for helping me. Let's play together now!" And they played happily ever after.
<|end|>


