Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play with his toys all day long. One day, he received a letter in the mail from his grandma. The letter was gray and had a stamp on it.

Timmy's mom helped him open the letter and read it to him. "Your grandma is coming to visit us," his mom said. Timmy was so excited to see his grandma. He wanted to show her all of his toys.

The day finally arrived when grandma came to visit. Timmy ran to give her a big hug. They spent the whole day playing together. But when it was time for grandma to leave, Timmy started to cry. "I don't want you to go," he said.

"Don't worry, Timmy," grandma said. "We can still talk on the phone and write letters to each other. Even though we are separated by distance, we can still be close." Timmy smiled and hugged his grandma goodbye, looking forward to the next letter he would receive.
