That night, Lily went to bed and the clock started to tick-tock loudly. It was so loud that Lily couldn't sleep. She tried to cover her ears, but it didn't work. 

The next day, Lily realized that the clock was broken and needed to be fixed. She took it to her grandpa, who knew how to fix clocks. He opened it up and found a little mouse inside. The mouse had been making the clock tick-tock loudly. Lily was happy that she had made the clock pretty again, but she was even happier that her grandpa had fixed it.
