Once upon a time, there was a furry mule named Max. Max was very lazy and never wanted to study. He would always eat and sleep all day long. Max's owner tried to teach him how to read and write, but Max never paid attention.

One day, Max's owner decided to sell him to a farmer who needed a strong mule to help him plow his fields. Max was happy to be out of the classroom and in the open fields. However, Max soon realized that he didn't know how to plow or do any work.

Max tried his best, but he couldn't do the work properly. The farmer got angry and decided to sell Max to a butcher. Max realized too late that he should have studied and learned new things. Max learned a hard lesson that day, that it's important to study and learn new things, or else bad things can happen.
<|end|>


