Once upon a time, there was a big village. The village was very gray because it was always cloudy. One day, a little girl named Lily wanted to leave the village and explore the world. She packed her bag with some food and water and said goodbye to her family. 

As she walked down the road, she saw many animals like birds and rabbits. She felt happy and excited to see new things. But as the sun started to set, Lily felt scared and missed her home. She decided to go back to the village and promised herself to explore more when she was older. 

When she got back, her family was happy to see her. They hugged her and gave her some warm soup. Lily felt grateful to have a home and family that loved her. From that day on, she knew that she would always have a place to call home, even if she wanted to leave and explore the world.
