Once upon a time, there was a smart little crab. The crab lived near the shore. He loved to play with his friends in the warm sand.

One day, the crab saw a big ice cream on the shore. It started to melt in the sun. The crab called his friend, the sea turtle, and said, "Look! The ice cream is melting! We should eat it before it's gone!"

The sea turtle looked at the melting ice cream and then looked at the crab. He said, "No, we should not eat it. It is not ours. We must find the owner and give it back." The crab thought about what the sea turtle said and agreed.

Together, they found the little girl who lost her ice cream. She was very happy to get it back. The crab and the sea turtle learned that it is good to be honest and help others. They felt proud of themselves and continued to play on the shore.
