Hippy and his friends decided to make a nice place for the bird to rest. They put flowers and leaves around the bird. Then, they all stood around the bird and clapped their hands. They were applauding the bird for all the joy it brought to the forest. The moral of the story is to always remember to be kind and show love to others, even when they are gone.
