Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy was very forgetful. He would forget where he put his toys and even forget his own name sometimes. One day, Timmy's mom asked him to go to the store to buy some milk. Timmy said, "Okay, Mommy. I will go get the milk." But as he walked to the store, he forgot what he was supposed to buy. He felt sad and scared he would get in trouble.

As Timmy walked around trying to remember, he saw an old man sitting on a bench. The old man had a humble smile on his face. Timmy went up to him and said, "Hi, what are you doing?" The old man replied, "I am just enjoying the sunshine and thinking about my youth." Timmy didn't know what "youth" meant, so he asked the old man. The old man explained that "youth" means when you are young and full of energy.

Timmy was interested in what the old man had to say and they talked for a while. As they talked, Timmy remembered what he was supposed to buy and said goodbye to the old man. He went to the store and got the milk. When he got home, his mom asked him why he took so long. Timmy said, "I forgot, but I met a nice old man who taught me about youth." His mom smiled and was happy that Timmy had learned something new.
<|end|>


