Once upon a time, there was a little ant who loved to crawl around. One day, the ant saw a big ball and wanted to play with it. But the ball was too heavy for the ant to carry. So, the ant decided to crawl inside the ball and play with it. 

The ball was actually a sport ball that belonged to some children. They didn't notice the ant inside and started playing with the ball. The ant was having so much fun inside the ball that it didn't notice the children kicking it around. 

Suddenly, one of the children kicked the ball too hard and it hit a tree. The ball broke into pieces and the ant got hurt. The children were careless and didn't see the ant inside. The ant was very sad and hurt. 

The moral of the story is that we should be careful when we play, and always look out for others. Even small creatures like ants can get hurt if we are not careful.
<|end|>


