Once upon a time, there was a little bunny named Flopsy. One day, Flopsy was hopping through the forest when he found himself in a big maze. He didn't know which way to go and he got very tired from all the hopping.

Suddenly, he heard a voice. "Hello there, little bunny. Are you lost?" It was a wise old owl who lived in the forest. "Yes," said Flopsy, "I'm lost in this maze and I don't know which way to go." The owl replied, "I can help you get out of the maze, but you must surrender to me first."

Flopsy didn't know what "surrender" meant, but he trusted the owl and agreed. The owl led Flopsy through the maze, showing him which way to go. Finally, they reached the end of the maze and Flopsy was so happy to be out. "Thank you, wise old owl!" he exclaimed.

From that day on, Flopsy always remembered to listen to the wise old owl and to never give up, even when he was tired and lost in a maze.
