Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play with her toys and her friends. One day, Lily and her friend Emily decided to have a picnic. They wanted to make sandwiches, but they didn't know how.

Lily asked her mom for help. Her mom said, "It's easy! Just lay the bread down, put some quick ham on it, and then add some cheese." Lily and Emily listened carefully, and they made the sandwiches just like her mom said.

As they sat and ate their sandwiches, Lily said to Emily, "This was so easy! I'm glad we asked my mom for help." Emily agreed and said, "Yeah, it was quick too! Now we can go play again." And off they went to play with their toys, happy and full from their delicious sandwiches.
