Once upon a time, there was a boy named Timmy. Timmy was an ordinary boy who loved to play outside. One day, Timmy's mom told him to clean up his toys or he would break the law. 

Timmy didn't want to break the law, so he started cleaning up his toys. While he was cleaning, he noticed a big tree in his backyard. He wanted to climb it, but he was scared. 

His dad saw him looking at the tree and asked him, "Do you want to climb the tree, Timmy?" 

Timmy replied, "Yes, but I'm scared." 

His dad said, "You can do it, just lean against the tree and take it slow." 

So, Timmy leaned against the tree and slowly climbed up. He was so proud of himself and his dad was proud too. They both knew that Timmy had followed the law by cleaning up his toys and had overcome his fear of climbing the tree.
<|end|>


