Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily who loved to read. Every morning, she would wake up early and grab a book to read. One day, she woke up and found her favorite book missing. She looked all around her room but couldn't find it.

Lily asked her mom, "Mommy, have you seen my book? It's missing!" Her mom replied, "I'm sorry, Lily. I haven't seen it. Maybe you left it at the park yesterday."

Lily went to the park and found her book on a bench. But when she opened it, she saw that someone had drawn all over the pages. She was sad and angry. But then, she remembered her mom's advice to always look for the good in things. She decided to try and make the best of it.

Lily found a way to cover up the drawings and still read her book. She even found a new tasty snack to enjoy while she read. She realized that even though bad things can happen, there is always a way to make things better.
