Later that day, Timmy and Billy went outside to play. Billy found some rocks and started throwing them at a tree. Timmy told Billy to stop because it was not nice to destroy things. Billy didn't listen and kept throwing rocks. Suddenly, a branch from the tree fell and hit Billy on the head. 

Timmy helped Billy up and asked him if he was okay. Billy said he was sorry for trying to destroy things and promised to never do it again. Timmy forgave Billy and they went back to playing with the train set. The moral of the story is that it's important to be kind and not destroy things.
