Once upon a time, a little boy named Timmy went to visit his grandma. Timmy loved visiting his grandma because she always had yummy treats and fun toys to play with. 

One day, Timmy and his grandma were sitting on the couch when Timmy said, "Grandma, I'm feeling tired. Can I take a nap?" 

"Of course, Timmy," said his grandma. "You can nap in my big, comfy chair." 

Timmy climbed into the chair and closed his eyes. As he was dozing off, he heard a strange noise in his ear. He opened his eyes and saw a rare, colorful bird perched on the arm of the chair. 

"Wow!" exclaimed Timmy. "That bird is so pretty!" 

The bird chirped back at Timmy and said, "Thank you! I don't usually nap on chairs, but this one looked so cozy." 

Timmy giggled and said, "I like napping in this chair too. Maybe we can share it next time!" 

The bird nodded its head and Timmy drifted off to sleep, dreaming of all the fun adventures he would have with his new feathered friend.
