Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to eat spicy food, even though it made her mouth feel hot. One day, Lily's mom gave her a diary to write down all her thoughts and feelings. Lily was very happy and started writing in it every day.

One day, Lily went to a party and ate lots of spicy food. Her mouth was on fire! She drank lots of water, but it didn't help. Lily started to cry and wished she never ate the spicy food. She went home and wrote in her diary about how she felt.

The next day, Lily's mom saw her diary and read what she wrote. She told Lily that it's important to sort out what we eat and not eat too much spicy food. Lily learned her lesson and promised to be careful next time. From then on, she wrote in her diary every day and learned to eat in moderation.
