Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She lived in a house with a big chimney. One day, Lily asked her mom, "What is the chimney for?" Her mom explained, "The chimney is for the smoke to go out when we use the fireplace."

Lily thought the chimney was stupid. She said, "Why does it have to be so big? It looks silly." Her mom replied, "It needs to be big so the smoke can escape properly."

One cold winter night, Lily's family lit a fire in the fireplace to keep warm. But something went wrong with the chimney. The smoke didn't go out of the chimney like it was supposed to. Instead, it filled up the house. Lily and her family couldn't breathe and they had to go to the hospital. It was a bad ending to a scary night.
