Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to run fast and collect stones. One day, she saw a big, shiny stone on the other side of a river. She wanted it so badly that she yelled, "I want that stone!"

Her mom said, "No, Lily. The river is too dangerous. You could get hurt."

But Lily didn't listen. She ran as fast as she could and jumped into the river. The water was too strong, and she was swept away. Her mom yelled for help, but it was too late. Lily was gone.

From that day on, her mom always reminded her to listen and be safe. And every time she saw a shiny stone, she remembered the lesson she learned the hard way.
