Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside and explore the world. One day, she was walking in the park when she saw a group of squirrels. She tried to get close to them, but they were too nosy and ran away. 

Lily continued her walk and found a pile of leaves. She decided to scatter them around because it was fun. Suddenly, she heard a voice behind her. It was an old man who asked, "Why are you scattering the leaves?" 

Lily replied, "I like to make the world pretty." The old man smiled and said, "You are a kind girl. Keep exploring and making the world a better place." From that day on, Lily continued to scatter leaves and make the world a more beautiful place.
<|end|>


