Once upon a time, there was a man named Jack. Jack had a big axe that he used to cut wood for his fire. One day, Jack decided to travel to the forest to find more wood for his fire. 

As he walked through the forest, he saw a beautiful flower. "Wow, that flower is so attractive," Jack said to himself. Suddenly, he heard a voice. "Hello, Jack!" It was a wise old owl sitting on a tree branch. 

"Hello, Mr. Owl!" Jack replied. "I'm just traveling through the forest to find some wood for my fire." "Be careful with that axe," the owl warned. "It's very sharp and dangerous." 

"Thank you for the advice, Mr. Owl," Jack said. "I'll be sure to be careful." With that, Jack continued on his journey, being cautious with his sharp axe.
<|end|>


