Once upon a time, there was a little boy named Timmy. Timmy loved to play with his toys, but he didn't like to share them with his friends. One day, Timmy's mom took him to a big volcano. Timmy saw the big mountain and thought it was very important. 

As they were looking at the volcano, Timmy's mom told him that sharing is an important thing to do. She said that when we share, we make our friends happy and that is a good thing to do. Timmy didn't understand why sharing was important, but he listened to his mom. 

The next day, Timmy went to play with his friends. He remembered what his mom had said and shared his toys with his friends. His friends were very happy and they played together for a long time. Timmy realized that sharing was a good thing to do and he felt happy too. From that day on, Timmy always shared his toys with his friends. He learned that sharing was a good number one rule!
<|end|>


