<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a band of animals who loved to play music. They had a guitar, a drum, and a trumpet. They practiced every day and were very proud of their music.

One day, they decided to perform at the big concert in the forest. All the animals were excited to hear them play. But when they started, something went wrong. The guitar was out of tune and the drum was too loud. The animals were sad and disappointed.

But then, the trumpet player had an idea. He asked everyone to turn around and face the other way. They did as he said, and when they turned back, the band was playing perfectly! The animals cheered and danced, and the band was proud of themselves for finding a solution.

From that day on, the band always remembered to turn around when something wasn't going right. They continued to play music and make everyone in the forest happy.
<|end|>


