<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play with her toys and sing songs. One day, her mom was drinking coffee and Lily wanted to try it. Her mom said no because coffee is for grown-ups.

Lily felt silly because she didn't know that. She decided to ignore her mom and try to drink the coffee when her mom wasn't looking. But when she took a sip, she didn't like the taste. It was too bitter!

Lily learned that it's important to listen to grown-ups and not ignore them. And she also learned that coffee is not for kids!
<|end|>


