Once upon a time, there was a lizard named Lizzy. Lizzy loved to play outside in the sun. One day, Lizzy was climbing a tree when she fell and hurt her leg. "Ouch!" cried Lizzy. "My leg is broken."

Her friend, a rabbit named Robbie, heard her cries and came to see what was wrong. "What happened, Lizzy?" asked Robbie. "I fell and hurt my leg," replied Lizzy. "Can you help me?"

Robbie knew just what to do. He went to his house and got some sticks and some rough string. He used the sticks to repair Lizzy's leg and used the string to tie it up. "There you go," said Robbie. "Your leg is all better now."

"Thank you, Robbie," said Lizzy. "You are a good friend." From that day on, Lizzy and Robbie played together every day.
<|end|>


