<|asst|>
Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to play outside and explore the world. One day, she saw a bird flying high in the sky. She wanted to fly like the bird, but it was difficult for her.

Lily asked her mom, "Mommy, can I fly like a bird?" 

Her mom replied, "No, Lily. It's difficult to fly like a bird. But we can watch the bird fly from the chimney."

Lily looked up at the chimney and saw the bird perched on top. She smiled and said, "I love watching the bird. When will it end?"

Her mom replied, "It will end when the bird flies away. But we can always come back and watch it again." 

Lily was happy to know that she could always come back and watch the bird on the chimney. She realized that even though she couldn't fly like a bird, she could still enjoy watching them.
<|end|>


