Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to look at the moon at night. One day, she asked her mother, "Can I receive the moon as a gift?" Her mother smiled and said, "No, sweetie. The moon is too far away."

Lily was sad, but she didn't give up. She went outside every night to look at the moon. One night, she saw a shooting star and made a wish to receive the moon. The next day, she woke up deaf. She couldn't hear anything anymore.

Lily went to the doctor, but they couldn't fix her ears. She was very sad and cried a lot. Her mother hugged her and said, "I'm sorry, Lily. You can't receive the moon, but you still have me." Lily hugged her mother back and smiled a little.
<|end|>


