Once upon a time, there was a little girl named Lily. She loved to eat with her fork. One day, her mommy warned her to be careful with her fork because it was sharp. Lily listened to her mommy and ate her food slowly.

Later that day, Lily went outside to play. She saw a little bird lying on the ground. The bird was not moving and Lily knew it was dead. She felt sad for the bird and wanted to bury it in the ground.

Lily's mommy saw her digging a hole and asked what she was doing. Lily told her mommy about the dead bird and her mommy hugged her and said it was okay to feel sad. They buried the bird together and said a little prayer.
