<|asst|>
Tom and Lily are friends. They like to play in the park. They like to swing on the swings. They swing high and low. They laugh and have fun.

One day, Tom has an exam at school. He has to learn many things. He has to write and read and count. He is worried. He does not want to fail. He wants to do well.

Lily says, "Do not worry, Tom. You are smart and good. You can do it. I will help you. We can study together. We can swing later."

Tom says, "Thank you, Lily. You are kind and dependable. You are a true friend. I will study hard. We can swing after the exam."

Tom and Lily study together. They learn many things. They help each other. They are ready for the exam.

The next day, Tom and Lily take the exam. They do their best. They write and read and count. They are confident and calm.

After the exam, Tom and Lily are happy. They did well. They are proud of themselves. They hug and smile.

They go to the park. They swing on the swings. They swing high and low. They laugh and have fun.

The moral of the story is: friends help each other. Studying is important. Swinging is fun.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
You are telling a short children's story.
<|end|>
<|asst|>
Ben and Mia loved to watch the dolphins at the beach. They liked to see them jump and splash in the water. Sometimes the dolphins made funny noises that sounded like they were talking.

One day, Ben and Mia saw a huge dolphin near the shore. It was bigger than any dolphin they had ever seen. It had a long, pointy nose and a big, curved fin. It looked sad and lonely.

"Hello, dolphin!" Ben shouted. "Do you want to play with us?"

The huge dolphin looked at Ben and Mia. It made a low, sad noise.

"I think he is lost," Mia said. "Maybe he can't find his family."

Ben and Mia felt sorry for the huge dolphin. They wanted to help him.

"Maybe we can unite him with his family," Ben said. "Maybe they are looking for him too."

"How can we do that?" Mia asked.

Ben thought for a moment. He had an idea.

"Maybe we can make a big noise, like the dolphins do. Maybe his family will hear us and come to find him."

Ben and Mia nodded. They took a deep breath and started to make loud, high-pitched noises. They sounded like dolphins.

The huge dolphin heard them. He looked surprised and curious. He made a loud, high-pitched noise back.

Ben and Mia smiled. They kept making noises with the huge dolphin.

Soon, they saw more dolphins coming from the water. They were different sizes and colors, but they all looked happy. They made noises too.

The huge dolphin saw them. He recognized them. They were his family. He swam towards them. They swam towards him. They united.

Ben and Mia watched as the dolphins hugged and kissed each other. They were happy for the huge dolphin. He was not sad and lonely anymore.

"Bye, dolphin!" Ben and Mia shouted. "We are glad you found your family!"

The huge dolphin and his family waved their fins at Ben and Mia. They thanked them for their help. They jumped and splashed in the water. They were happy.
<|end|>


