<|asst|>
Tom and Lily are friends. They like to play in the park. They find a big white stick on the ground. It is smooth and shiny. They both want the stick.

"I saw it first!" Tom says. He grabs the stick and runs away.

"No, I saw it first!" Lily says. She runs after Tom and tries to take the stick.

They run and run, but they do not watch where they are going. They bump into a big tree. The stick falls out of Tom's hand. It breaks into two pieces.

They both look at the broken stick. They feel sad and sorry.

"I'm sorry, Tom. I should not have chased you," Lily says.

"I'm sorry, Lily. I should not have taken the stick," Tom says.

They hug and say sorry. They share the broken stick. They use it to draw pictures on the dirt. They are friends again. They are happy.
<|end|>


