<|asst|>
Ben and Lily were playing with their toys in the garden. Ben had a red car and Lily had a blue doll. They were happy and shared their toys.

But then a big dog came into the garden. The dog was rough and loud. He ran to Ben and Lily and took their toys in his mouth. He ran away with the car and the doll.

Ben and Lily were scared and sad. They shouted at the dog. "Stop! Stop! Give us our toys! They are ours! They are mine!" But the dog did not listen. He ran out of the garden with the toys.

Ben and Lily wept. They hugged each other and cried. They wanted their toys back. They did not like the dog.

Their mom heard them and came to the garden. She saw them weeping and asked them what happened. They told her about the dog and the toys. She felt sorry for them and hugged them too. She said, "Don't worry, my loves. I will buy you new toys. The dog was bad and mean. He should not have taken your toys. But you are good and kind. You shared your toys. I am proud of you."

Ben and Lily smiled a little. They thanked their mom and said they loved her. They still missed their toys, but they felt better. They hoped the dog would not come back. They played with each other and waited for their new toys.
<|end|>


