<|end|>
<|asst|>
Tom and Lily are friends. They like to play with toys. Tom has a big truck. Lily has a doll. They share their toys and have fun.

One day, a new boy comes to the park. His name is Sam. He has no toys. He sees Tom's truck and wants to play with it. He runs to Tom and says, "Give me your truck!"

Tom is scared. He does not want to give his truck to Sam. He says, "No, this is my truck. You can't have it."

Sam is angry. He pushes Tom and grabs the truck. He runs away with it. Tom is sad. He cries.

Lily sees what happens. She wants to help Tom. She is brave. She says, "Don't cry, Tom. I will get your truck back. You can lend me your doll. She will be my hero."

Tom stops crying. He gives his doll to Lily. He says, "Thank you, Lily. You are a good friend."

Lily takes the doll and runs after Sam. She says, "Hey, Sam. Stop. That is not your truck. That is Tom's truck. Give it back."

Sam does not listen. He says, "No, this is my truck. Go away."

Lily is clever. She says, "Look, Sam. I have a doll. She is very pretty. Do you want to play with her?"

Sam likes dolls. He says, "Yes, I want to play with her. She is very pretty."

Lily says, "OK, then. You can play with her. But you have to give me the truck. That is fair."

Sam thinks. He says, "OK, then. You can have the truck. But you have to lend me the doll. That is fair."

Lily says, "OK, then. I will lend you the doll. But you have to be nice to Tom. He is my friend."

Sam says, "OK, then. I will be nice to Tom. He can be my friend, too."

Lily and Sam trade the truck and the doll. They go back to Tom. They say, "Sorry, Tom. We were not nice to you. Can we play with you?"

Tom is happy. He says, "Yes, you can play with me. We can share our toys and have fun."

Tom, Lily, and Sam play with the truck and the doll. They are busy. They are friends. They are happy.
<|end|>


