<|asst|>
Lily and Max are twins. They like to play in the park with their parent. One day, they see a big lemon tree. They want to try the lemons.

"Can we have a lemon, please?" they ask their parent.

"Okay, but be careful. Lemons are sour. They make your mouth pucker," their parent says.

Lily and Max each pick a lemon. They peel off the yellow skin. They see the juicy flesh. They take a big bite.

"Yuck!" they both say. They spit out the lemon. They make a funny face. Their mouth feels tight and bitter.

They run to their parent. They want some water. Their parent gives them a bottle. They drink and drink.

"Are you okay?" their parent asks.

"Yes, we are okay. But we don't like lemons. They are too sour," they say.

They hug their parent. They say sorry for wasting the lemons. Their parent smiles and kisses them.

"It's okay. You learned something new. Lemons are good for some things, but not for eating by themselves. Maybe next time, we can make some lemonade. It's sweet and refreshing," their parent says.

Lily and Max nod. They like lemonade. They think it sounds yummy. They thank their parent. They go back to play in the park. They are happy.
<|end|>


