<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They saw a big dog with a red ball. The dog ran and jumped and barked. Lily and Ben liked the dog. They wanted to play with him.

"Hello, dog!" Lily said. "Can we play with you and your ball?"

The dog wagged his tail. He dropped the ball and ran away. Lily and Ben followed him. They ran and laughed and shouted.

They followed the dog to a house. The house had a fence and a gate. The dog went inside the gate. Lily and Ben stopped at the fence. They could not go inside.

"Where are you going, dog?" Ben asked. "Can we come with you?"

The dog barked again. He came back to the fence. He had something in his mouth. It was a bone. A big, tasty bone. The dog looked at Lily and Ben. He wanted to share his bone.

"Thank you, dog!" Lily said. "You are very nice. Can we have some of your bone?"

The dog nodded. He put the bone on the ground. He let Lily and Ben have a bite. The bone was tasty. Lily and Ben smiled. They liked the bone. They liked the dog. They made a new friend.
<|end|>


