<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were twins who liked to play together. One day, they saw a big truck with a picture of a cone and cream on it. It was the cream truck that came to their street sometimes. They ran to their mom and asked if they could have some cream.

Mom was thoughtful and looked at her watch. She said, "Okay, but only one cone each. And hurry, the truck will leave soon."

Lily and Ben thanked mom and ran to the truck. They saw many colors of cream and had a hard time choosing. Lily wanted pink and Ben wanted blue. But the truck only had one pink and one blue left.

"Can I have the pink one, please?" Lily asked the man in the truck.

"Can I have the blue one, please?" Ben asked the man in the truck.

The man smiled and gave them their cones. Lily and Ben were happy and licked their cream.

But then, a big dog came out of nowhere and jumped on Lily. It knocked her down and took her cone. Lily was scared and sad. She started to cry.

"Hey, that's not fair!" Ben yelled at the dog. He ran to Lily and helped her up. He looked at his cone and then at Lily. He was thoughtful and said, "Here, you can have my cone. I don't mind."

Lily stopped crying and smiled. She hugged Ben and said, "Thank you, Ben. You are the best brother ever."

Ben smiled and said, "You're welcome, Lily. You are the best sister ever."

They shared the blue cone and enjoyed their cream. The dog ran away and the man in the truck gave them a thumbs up. Mom saw them and was proud of them. She said, "You are very thoughtful and kind, Lily and Ben. I love you both."

Lily and Ben said, "We love you too, mom." They finished their cream and went back to play. They were happy and had a good day.
<|end|>


