<|asst|>
Tom and Mia are playing in the farm. They like to see the animals and hear their sounds. They see cows, pigs, sheep and horses. They also see chickens. The chickens are yellow and brown. They make cluck-cluck noises.

Tom and Mia want to touch the chickens. They run after them. The chickens are scared. They run away. They flap their wings. They make loud cluck-cluck noises. Tom and Mia think it is fun. They laugh and chase the chickens.

But one chicken is not happy. It is the big rooster. He is the boss of the chickens. He does not like Tom and Mia. He thinks they are bad. He wants to protect the chickens. He runs after Tom and Mia. He makes a loud cock-a-doodle-doo noise. He pecks at their legs.

Tom and Mia are surprised. They feel pain. They are afraid. They panic. They scream and cry. They run away from the rooster. They look for their mom and dad.

Mom and dad hear Tom and Mia. They come to the farm. They see the rooster. They see Tom and Mia. They are worried. They hug Tom and Mia. They calm them down. They say sorry to the rooster. They say sorry to the farmer. They say Tom and Mia should not chase the chickens. They say the chickens are not toys. They say the rooster is doing his job. They say Tom and Mia should be gentle and kind to the animals.

Tom and Mia understand. They say sorry too. They say they will not chase the chickens again. They say they will be nice to the rooster. They say they still like the farm. They say they want to see the other animals. They say they want to learn more about them.

Mom and dad smile. They say okay. They say they are proud of Tom and Mia. They say they love them. They take them to see the other animals. They have a good time. They are happy.
<|end|>


