<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing with blocks in the living room. They liked to build towers and knock them down. Sometimes they made noises like cars or animals.

"Look, I made a big tower!" Lily said, showing Ben her blocks.

"Wow, that's nice!" Ben said. He wanted to make a tower too, but he had fewer blocks than Lily. He looked at her tower and felt a little jealous.

He had an idea. He took a block from Lily's tower when she was not looking. He added it to his own tower. He did this again and again, until his tower was bigger than Lily's.

Lily turned around and saw what Ben had done. She was angry and sad. She shouted at Ben.

"Hey, you took my blocks! That's not fair! Give them back!"

Ben felt guilty. He knew he had done something bad. He wanted to say sorry, but he was afraid. He did not know what to do.

He tried to repeat what Lily had said. He hoped she would forgive him.

"Hey, you took my blocks! That's not fair! Give them back!" he said, in a small voice.

Lily was confused. She did not understand why Ben was saying the same thing as her. She thought he was making fun of her. She felt more angry and sad.

She picked up a block and threw it at Ben. It hit him on the head. He cried out in pain.

"Ow, that hurt! Why did you do that?" he said, rubbing his head.

Lily did not answer. She picked up another block and threw it at Ben. He dodged it, but it hit the lamp. The lamp fell over and broke. It made a loud noise.

Mom heard the noise and came into the living room. She saw the broken lamp, the blocks, and the crying children. She was not happy.

"What happened here?" she asked, in a stern voice.

Lily and Ben looked at each other. They did not know what to say. They felt very guilty.

They heard a tap on the window. They turned and saw a bird. The bird was singing a pretty song. It made them feel a little better.

They decided to tell Mom the truth. They hoped she would not be too angry. They hoped they could still be friends. They hoped the bird would come back.
<|end|>


