<|asst|>
Tim and Sam were brothers who liked to play outside. One day, they saw a large bird with a broken wing on the grass. They felt sorry for the bird and wanted to help it.

"Let's take it home and heal it," Tim said.

"OK, but we have to be careful. It might bite us," Sam said.

They picked up the bird gently and carried it to their house. They put it in a box with some water and seeds. They thought it was a good task to do.

But their mom did not like the bird. She said it was dirty and noisy and could make them sick. She told them to get rid of it.

"No, mom, please. We want to heal the bird. It is our friend," Tim said.

"Sorry, boys, but you can't keep it. It belongs to the wild, not to our house. You have to let it go," mom said.

She took the box and drove to the park. She opened the box and let the bird out. The bird tried to fly, but it could not. It fell to the ground and a cat ran after it.

Tim and Sam cried when they saw what happened. They wished they had never found the bird. They learned that some tasks are too hard for them and they should listen to their mom.

The end.
<|end|>


