<|asst|>
Lily and Max are two dogs who like to play in the park. They run, jump, and chase each other. Sometimes they find a ball and roll it with their paws. They have a lot of fun.

One day, they see a new dog in the park. He is big and black and has a serious face. He does not want to play with them. He only wants the ball. He growls and barks at them.

"Go away! This is my ball!" he says.

Lily and Max are scared and sad. They like the ball, but they do not want to fight. They look at each other and have an idea.

They pretend to run away, but then they come back from different sides. They surprise the big dog and roll the ball away from him. They run fast and catch the ball.

"Ha ha! We got the ball!" they say.

The big dog is angry and chases them. But Lily and Max are smarter and faster. They pass the ball to each other and dodge the big dog. They have more fun than before.

The big dog gets tired and gives up. He realizes that he was mean and lonely. He decides to be nice and ask them to play.

"Can I play with you? I'm sorry I was rude. I just wanted a friend," he says.

Lily and Max are happy and kind. They share the ball with him and invite him to join their game. They roll, run, and jump together. They become friends.
<|end|>


