<|asst|>
Tom is a lazy cat. He likes to sleep all day on the sofa. He does not like to play with his toys or run in the garden. He only wakes up when he is hungry or thirsty.

One night, Tom hears a noise outside. He opens his eyes and sees a dark shadow on the window. He is scared and curious. He jumps off the sofa and goes to the door. He wants to see what it is.

He opens the door and sees a small mouse. The mouse is shivering and wet. It is raining hard. The mouse looks at Tom and says, "Please, can I come in? I am cold and hungry. I have no home."

Tom feels sorry for the mouse. He remembers how he was once a stray cat, with no one to care for him. He says, "Okay, you can come in. But be quiet and don't touch my things."

He lets the mouse in and shows him a corner where he can sleep. He gives him some cheese and water. He says, "You can stay here for one night. Tomorrow, you have to go."

The mouse is grateful and happy. He says, "Thank you, Tom. You are very kind. Can I be your friend?"

Tom is surprised and flattered. He says, "Well, I guess so. But don't expect me to play with you. I am a lazy cat, remember?"

The mouse says, "That's okay. I don't mind. I just want someone to talk to."

They both go to sleep. The mouse snuggles next to Tom and rubs his nose against his fur. Tom feels warm and cozy. He thinks, "Maybe being lazy is not so bad. Maybe having a friend is nice." He purrs and closes his eyes.
<|end|>


