<|asst|>
Lily was a little girl who loved to play with her robot. Her robot was mighty and could do many things. It could run, jump, dance, and sing. Lily and her robot had fun every day.

One night, Lily did not want to sleep. She wanted to play with her robot more. She said to her robot, "Let's go outside and see the stars. Maybe we can find a spaceship and fly away."

Her robot said, "No, Lily. It is dark and cold outside. You need to sleep. Sleep is good for you. It makes you grow and learn and dream. If you sleep, tomorrow we can play more."

But Lily did not listen. She put on her coat and shoes and sneaked out of her room. She took her robot with her. She ran to the backyard and looked at the sky. She saw many stars, but no spaceship.

She said to her robot, "Where is the spaceship? I want to fly away."

Her robot said, "There is no spaceship, Lily. You are dreaming. Come on, let's go back inside. You are tired and cold. You need to sleep."

But Lily did not listen. She said, "No, I want to stay here. I want to see the spaceship."

She sat on the grass and waited. She waited and waited, but no spaceship came. She started to feel sleepy and bored. She yawned and rubbed her eyes. She said to her robot, "I'm sleepy. Can we go back inside?"

Her robot said, "Yes, Lily. Let's go back inside. You need to sleep. Sleep is good for you. It makes you grow and learn and dream. If you sleep, tomorrow we can play more."

Lily nodded and got up. She held her robot's hand and walked back to her room. She put her robot on her bed and cuddled with it. She said, "I'm sorry, robot. You were right. Sleep is good for me. Tomorrow we can play more."

Her robot said, "It's okay, Lily. I forgive you. I love you. Good night."

Lily smiled and closed her eyes. She fell asleep and had a nice dream. She dreamed of flying with her robot in a spaceship. She was happy.

The moral of the story is: Listen to your robot. Sleep is good for you. It makes you grow and learn and dream. If you sleep, tomorrow you can play more.
<|end|>


