<|asst|>
Spike was a dog who lived with a boy and a girl. The boy and the girl loved Spike very much. They gave him a name, a bed, a bowl, and many toys. They also gave him hugs and kisses and treats. Spike was a very happy dog.

But Spike was also a very spoiled dog. He did not like to share his toys with other dogs. He did not like to obey his boy and his girl. He did not like to go for walks or baths. He only liked to play and eat and sleep. Spike was a very naughty dog.

One day, Spike saw a new toy in the boy's room. It was a big, red ball. Spike wanted the ball very much. He did not care that it was the boy's ball. He jumped on the bed and grabbed the ball with his teeth. He ran away with the ball to his bed.

The boy saw Spike with his ball. He was very angry. He shouted at Spike and tried to take the ball back. But Spike growled and bit the boy's hand. The boy cried and ran to his girl. The girl saw the bite and was very sad. She scolded Spike and took the ball away. She put Spike in a corner and told him to stay.

Spike felt very bad. He knew he had been very mean to his boy and his girl. He wanted to say sorry, but he did not know how. He looked at his toys and his bowl and his bed. He realized he had everything he needed. He did not need to be greedy or rude. He needed to be good and kind. He needed to be a better dog.

Spike got up from the corner and walked to his boy and his girl. He licked their faces and wagged his tail. He gave them his toys and his bowl and his bed. He let them hug him and kiss him and treat him. He was a very sorry dog.

The boy and the girl forgave Spike. They knew he loved them very much. They gave him his name, his bed, his bowl, and his toys back. They also gave him walks and baths and lessons. Spike was a very happy dog.

But Spike was also a very good dog. He learned to share his toys with other dogs. He learned to obey his boy and his girl. He learned to go for walks and baths and have fun. He still liked to play and eat and sleep. But he also liked to be nice and polite and grateful. Spike was a very smart dog.
<|end|>


