<|asst|>
Lily and Tom are twins. They like to play in the park. They see a big slide. Lily wants to go first. She runs to the slide and climbs up the ladder. Tom follows her.

"Wait for me, Lily!" Tom says. "We can slide together!"

But Lily does not wait. She sits on the tip of the slide and pushes herself down. She goes very fast. She laughs and shouts. "Whee!"

Tom is sad. He wanted to slide with Lily. He sits on the tip of the slide too. He pushes himself down. But he does not go fast. He goes slow. He does not laugh. He cries.

"Why are you crying, Tom?" Lily asks. She is at the bottom of the slide. She sees Tom coming down.

"Because you did not wait for me!" Tom says. "You are not a good sister!"

Lily feels bad. She did not mean to make Tom cry. She wants to say sorry. But before she can, Tom falls off the slide. He lands on the grass. He hurts his knee. He cries louder.

"Tom, are you okay?" Lily asks. She runs to Tom. She hugs him. She sees his knee. It is red and wet. "You are bleeding, Tom!"

Tom is scared. He does not like blood. He holds his knee. He wants his mom.

"Mom, mom, help!" Lily and Tom yell. They see their mom coming. She is wise. She knows what to do.

She picks up Tom and carries him to a bench. She takes out a band-aid from her bag. She cleans Tom's knee and puts the band-aid on it. She kisses Tom's cheek.

"There, there, Tom. You will be fine. It is just a small cut. It will heal soon." She says.

She looks at Lily. She smiles. "And you, Lily. You are a good sister. You helped Tom. You said sorry. You showed love."

Lily smiles too. She feels happy. She loves Tom. She loves her mom. She says sorry again.

"I'm sorry, Tom. I should have waited for you. I should have slid with you. Do you forgive me?"

Tom nods. He forgives Lily. He loves Lily. He loves his mom. He says thank you.

"Thank you, mom. Thank you, Lily. You are the best."

They hug each other. They are happy. They are a family.
<|end|>


