Lila and Tom were playing in the park. They liked to pretend they were hunters in the jungle. They had sticks that they called spears. They threw them at the trees and bushes.

One day, they saw a big bird with many colors. It was sitting on a branch. They had never seen a bird like that before. It was unique.

"Wow, look at that bird!" Lila said. "It is so pretty!"

"Let's catch it!" Tom said. "Maybe it is a magic bird!"

They ran towards the bird with their spears. The bird saw them and made a loud noise. It sounded like a whistle.

The bird flew away. Lila and Tom paused. They were sad. They wanted to see the bird more.

"Where did it go?" Lila asked.

"I don't know," Tom said. "Maybe it went to another jungle."

They looked around. They saw other birds, but none like the one they saw. They wished they could find it again.

They decided to keep playing. They hoped they would see the unique bird another day. They knew it was special.
<|end|>


