Tom and Amy were twins who liked to play with their toys. They had a lot of toys, but they always wanted more. They did not like to share or say thank you. They were spoiled children.

One day, their mom made them a nice lunch. She put it on a big tray and brought it to their room. She said, "Here you go, my darlings. Enjoy your lunch. I made your favorite sandwiches and cookies."

But Tom and Amy did not say thank you. They did not even look at their mom. They just grabbed the tray and put it on the floor. They started to eat the cookies and throw the sandwiches at each other. They made a big mess.

Their mom was very sad. She went to the kitchen and cried. She worked hard to make them a nice lunch, but they did not appreciate it. They did not love her.

Then, something bad happened. The tray was on the floor, and it had a lot of crumbs and bits of food on it. A big rat came out of a hole in the wall and smelled the food. It ran to the tray and started to eat. It was very hungry and greedy.

Tom and Amy saw the rat and screamed. They were scared of the rat. They tried to run away, but the rat was faster. It bit Tom on the leg and Amy on the arm. It hurt a lot. They cried and cried.

Their mom heard them and ran to their room. She saw the rat and the mess and the blood. She was very angry and scared. She grabbed a broom and chased the rat away. She took Tom and Amy to the doctor. They had to get shots and bandages.

They learned a hard lesson. They should have been nice to their mom and enjoyed their lunch. They should have been grateful and polite. They should not have been spoiled children.
<|end|>


