Lily and Ben are twins. They like to play and have fun. One day, they find a big box in the living room. They wonder what is inside.

"Maybe it is a toy," Lily says.

"Maybe it is a cake," Ben says.

They open the box and see a lot of paper and a brush. They are confused.

"What is this?" Lily asks.

"I don't know," Ben says.

They take out the paper and the brush. They see that the brush has paint on it. They have an idea.

"Let's paint the walls!" Lily says.

"Let's make them crazy!" Ben says.

They start to paint the walls with different colors and shapes. They have a lot of fun. They make a big mess.

They hear the door open. It is their mom and dad. They come in and see the walls. They are shocked.

"What did you do?" Mom asks.

"We made a surprise for you!" Lily and Ben say.

They smile and hug their parents. Their parents are not angry. They are amused.

"You are very creative," Dad says.

"But you also need to clean up," Mom says.

They all laugh and start to clean up. They are a happy family.
