Sara and Tom were twins who liked to play in the garden. They had a big chamber full of toys and books, but they also loved to see the flowers and bugs outside. One day, they found a tiny seed on the ground. It was brown and round and had a little hole in it.

"Look, Sara, what is this?" Tom asked, holding the seed in his hand.

"I don't know, Tom. Maybe it is a flower seed. Let's plant it and see what happens," Sara said, taking the seed from Tom.

They dug a small hole in the dirt and put the seed in it. Then they covered it with more dirt and watered it with a cup. They made a sign with a stick and a paper that said "Our seed" and stuck it next to the hole.

Every day, they came to check on their seed. They watered it and talked to it and sang to it. They hoped it would grow into a beautiful flower. But nothing happened for a long time. The seed stayed hidden under the dirt.

"Maybe our seed is broken," Tom said one day, feeling sad.

"Maybe it needs more time," Sara said, trying to be hopeful.

They decided to wait a little longer and see if their seed would grow.

One morning, they ran to the garden and saw something amazing. There was a green sprout poking out of the dirt. It had two tiny leaves and a bud at the top. It was their seed! It had grown!

"Wow, Sara, look! Our seed is alive!" Tom shouted, jumping up and down.

"Yay, Tom, look! Our seed is a flower!" Sara cheered, clapping her hands.

They hugged each other and danced around their seed. They were so happy and proud. They watched as the bud opened and revealed a bright yellow flower. It was the most adorable flower they had ever seen. It smelled sweet and had a smiley face on it.

"Hello, Sara and Tom. Thank you for taking care of me. I am your friend, Sunny," the flower said, blinking its eyes.

"Hello, Sunny. We are your friends, too. You are the best flower ever," Sara and Tom said, smiling back.

They gave Sunny a kiss and a hug and told him they loved him. They played with him and told him stories and jokes. They had a lot of fun with their new friend. They learned that seeds can grow into wonderful things if you are patient and kind. They were very happy.
<|end|>


