Tom and Lily were playing in the garden. They liked to run and jump and chase each other. They saw a big gate at the end of the garden. It was brown and metal and had a lock on it.

"Let's go see what's behind the gate!" Tom said.

"No, we can't. Mommy said it's dangerous. There is fire there." Lily said.

"Fire? I want to see fire. It's bright and warm and pretty." Tom said.

He ran to the gate and tried to open it. He pulled and pushed and kicked, but the gate did not move. He saw a hole in the gate. He put his hand through the hole and felt something hot.

"Ow! Ow! Ow!" Tom screamed. He pulled his hand back and saw it was red and hurt. He had burned his hand.

Lily ran to him and hugged him. She saw his hand and was scared.

"Tom, you're hurt! You're hurt bad! We need to tell Mommy!" Lily said.

She helped him walk to the house. They saw Mommy in the kitchen. She saw Tom's hand and was shocked.

"Tom, what happened? What did you do?" Mommy asked.

"I touched the fire behind the gate. It was terrible. It burned me." Tom said.

Mommy took him to the sink and ran cold water over his hand. She wrapped it in a cloth and gave him a hug and a kiss.

"You were very naughty, Tom. You should never touch fire. It's very dangerous. It can hurt you and make you sick. You should always listen to Mommy and Lily. They love you and want you to be safe." Mommy said.

"I'm sorry, Mommy. I'm sorry, Lily. I won't touch fire again. I love you too." Tom said.

Mommy smiled and said, "I'm glad you're sorry. I hope you learned your lesson. Now let's go to the doctor and see if your hand needs medicine."
<|end|>


