Bella was a creative hippo who loved to paint with her trunk. She liked to make colorful pictures of her friends, the flowers, and the sun. But some of the other hippos did not like her paintings. They said they were messy and silly and not like real hippos.

One day, Bella was painting a big rainbow on a rock when Max came by. Max was a mean hippo who liked to tease and bully others. He saw Bella's painting and laughed.

"What is that? That is not a rainbow! That is a blob of mud! You are a bad painter, Bella! You should stop and do something else!" Max said.

Bella felt sad and angry. She wanted to say something back, but she did not know what. She felt like crying and giving up.

But then, she heard a friendly voice behind her. It was Leo, her best friend. Leo was a kind hippo who liked to encourage others. He saw Bella's painting and smiled.

"Bella, that is a beautiful rainbow! I love how you used so many colors and shapes! You are a very creative painter, Bella! You should keep going and show everyone your talent!" Leo said.

Bella felt happy and grateful. She looked at Leo and smiled back.

"Thank you, Leo! You are a very nice friend! You always make me feel good and help me try new things! I will not listen to Max. He is just mean and jealous. I will keep painting and have fun!" Bella said.

Leo nodded and hugged Bella. They decided to paint together and make more pictures. They ignored Max and his mean words. They enjoyed being creative and encouraging each other. They were happy hippos.
<|end|>


