Lily and Tom were playing in the sand. They had a bucket and a spade each. They wanted to make a big castle with towers and walls. Lily suggested they work together and share their sand. Tom agreed and they started to build.

But soon they had a problem. Lily wanted to make the towers high and round. Tom wanted to make them low and square. They argued and pulled at the spade. The spade broke in half. They both cried and dropped the bucket.

A big dog came by and saw the sand. He thought it was fun to dig and run. He jumped on the castle and knocked it down. He barked and wagged his tail. He did not know he was making Lily and Tom sad.

Lily and Tom saw the dog and stopped crying. They saw their broken spade and ruined castle. They felt sorry for each other. They decided to be friends again and share their bucket. They gave the dog a pat and a smile. They suggested they make a new castle with the dog. The dog licked their faces and agreed. They had fun and played in the sand.
