Tom and Mia were playing in the park. They liked to go on the swings, the slide and the seesaw. They had a lot of fun.

One day, they saw a new thing in the park. It was a big round thing that spun very fast. It had seats and belts and a man who pushed a button.

"Let's try it!" said Tom. He ran to the big round thing and got on a seat. He put on his belt and waited for the man to push the button.

"Are you sure?" asked Mia. She was scared of the big round thing. It looked too fast and too high.

"Yes, yes, yes!" said Tom. He was excited. He wanted to feel the wind and see the sky.

The man pushed the button and the big round thing started to spin. Tom laughed and screamed. He felt like he was flying. He saw the trees, the clouds, the birds and the other children.

Mia watched from the ground. She felt sick. She saw Tom go up and down and around and around. She wanted him to stop.

After a while, the man pushed the button again and the big round thing slowed down. Tom got off the seat and took off his belt. He was very happy.

"Thank you, thank you, thank you!" he said to the man. He gave him a big hug.

The man smiled and said, "You're welcome, you're welcome, you're welcome. Did you have fun?"

Tom nodded and said, "Yes, yes, yes! It was the best thing ever!"

He ran to Mia and said, "Come on, let's do it again!"

Mia shook her head and said, "No, no, no! It was the worst thing ever!"

Tom looked at her and saw that she was pale and sad. He felt sorry for her.

"Are you okay?" he asked.

Mia nodded and said, "Yes, yes, yes. But I don't like the big round thing. It makes me dizzy."

Tom hugged her and said, "I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I'm sorry. I didn't know. Do you want to go on the swings instead?"

Mia smiled and said, "Yes, yes, yes. I like the swings. They make me happy."

Tom and Mia went to the swings and had fun. They forgot about the big round thing. They were good friends.
<|end|>


