One day, a boy and a girl went for a walk in the woods. They saw many trees and animals. They heard birds singing and squirrels chattering. They felt happy and curious.

They came to a small hut made of wood and straw. It had a door and a window. The boy and the girl wondered who lived there. They knocked on the door, but no one answered. They decided to open the door and look inside.

They opened the door and saw a cozy room. There was a bed, a table, a chair, and a fireplace. There were also some toys, books, and pictures. The boy and the girl liked the hut. They wanted to play with the toys and read the books.

Suddenly, they heard a voice behind them. It was a friendly old woman. She had a basket of fruits and flowers. She smiled and said, "Hello, children. Welcome to my hut. I am glad you came. Do you want some fruits and flowers?"

The boy and the girl were surprised and scared. They did not know the old woman. They did not know if she was nice or mean. They said, "Sorry, ma'am. We did not mean to enter your hut. We were just curious. We will leave now."

The old woman said, "Don't be afraid, children. I am not angry. I am lonely. I live alone in the woods. I don't have many visitors. I like children. You can stay and play with me. I will share my fruits and flowers with you."

The boy and the girl looked at each other. They thought the old woman seemed friendly and kind. They decided to stay and play with her. They ate the fruits and smelled the flowers. They played with the toys and read the books. They talked and laughed with the old woman. They had a lot of fun.

They thanked the old woman for her hospitality. They said goodbye and promised to visit her again. They walked back to their home, feeling happy and grateful. They had made a new friend in the woods.
<|end|>


