Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They saw a big table with many pies on it. The pies had red, yellow and purple fruits on top. They looked yummy.

"Can we have some pie?" Lily asked Ben.

"I don't know. Maybe they are for a party," Ben said.

They went closer to the table. They saw a sign that said: "Free pies for everyone. Enjoy!"

"Wow! They are free! Let's have some pie!" Lily said.

They each took a plate and a fork. They cut a slice of pie and ate it. It was sweet and juicy. They smiled and licked their lips.

"Mmm, this is the best pie ever!" Ben said.

"I agree. It is so yummy!" Lily said.

They saw a jug of water and some cups on the table. They were thirsty after eating the pie. They poured some water and drank it. It was cold and refreshing.

"Ah, that was good. Do you want more pie?" Lily asked Ben.

"Yes, please. Let's try the purple one. It looks fun," Ben said.

They cut another slice of pie and ate it. It was sour and tangy. They made funny faces and laughed.

"This one is different. But I like it too," Lily said.

"Me too. It is fun to try new things," Ben said.

They finished their pie and water. They thanked the people who made the pies. They went back to playing in the park. They were happy and full. They had a great day.
