Ben and Lily liked to play with their dad's phone. They liked to make funny sounds and faces and record them. They also liked to watch the videos they made and laugh.

One day, they found a fake mustache in a drawer. It was black and curly and sticky. They decided to put it on and record a video.

"Hello, I am Mr. Mustache," Ben said in a deep voice, holding the phone in front of his face. "I like to eat cheese and read books."

"Hello, I am Mrs. Mustache," Lily said in a high voice, sticking the mustache under her nose. "I like to sing and dance and paint."

They made silly noises and gestures and pretended to be grown-ups. They had a lot of fun.

When their dad came home, they showed him the video. He laughed and hugged them.

"That is a very funny video," he said. "You are very creative and clever. I am happy to have you as my children."

Ben and Lily smiled and kissed him. They were happy too. They loved their dad and his phone and the fake mustache.
