Tim and Mia like to play with their toys. They have many toys, but their favorite is the big box of colorful prints. The prints are pictures of animals, cars, flowers and more. They can stick the prints on the wall, on the floor, on the table or on themselves.

One day, Tim and Mia are playing with the prints in their room. They make a big castle with the prints on the floor. They pretend to be a king and a queen. They have fun with their castle.

But then, their baby brother Tom comes in. Tom is very curious. He sees the prints and wants to touch them. He crawls to the castle and grabs some prints. He tears them and throws them. He makes a loud noise. He destroys the castle.

Tim and Mia are very sad and angry. They shout at Tom. They tell him to go away. They try to fix their castle, but it is too late. The prints are broken and messy. They cry and hug each other.

Mom hears the noise and comes in. She sees the mess and the tears. She feels sorry for Tim and Mia. She also feels sorry for Tom. He does not know what he did. He is too small. She picks up Tom and cuddles him. She tells Tim and Mia that she is sorry. She helps them clean up the prints. She tells them that they can make a new castle later. She tells them that they are good children. She tells them that she loves them. She gives them a kiss and a hug. They feel better. They smile and say thank you. They love Mom.
