Sara liked to play with her dolls. She had many dolls, but her favorite was Lily. Lily had long hair that Sara liked to brush and braid. One day, Sara found a pair of scissors in the kitchen. She had an idea. She wanted to cut Lily's hair and make her look like a princess.

She took Lily and the scissors to her room. She put Lily on the bed and started to cut her hair. She cut and cut, but Lily's hair did not look like a princess. It looked messy and short. Sara was sad. She had ruined Lily's hair. She started to cry.

Mom heard Sara crying and came to her room. She saw Lily and the scissors on the bed. She understood what Sara had done. She hugged Sara and said, "It's okay, honey. Hair can grow back. But scissors are not for playing. They are sharp and can hurt you or your dolls. You have to be careful with them."

Mom took the scissors and put them away. She picked up Lily and said, "Let's give Lily a massage. That will make her feel better." She rubbed Lily's head and body gently. She said, "Lily is a brave doll. She still loves you, even with short hair. And you know what? Short hair can be fun, too. You can try different styles and accessories. Maybe you can find a red ribbon or a red hat for Lily. Red is a pretty color, don't you think?"

Sara nodded and smiled. She felt better, too. She said, "Thank you, Mom. I'm sorry I cut Lily's hair. I won't do it again. I love Lily, and I love you." She hugged Mom and Lily. She said, "Can we go and find a red ribbon for Lily?" Mom said, "Of course, sweetie. Let's go." They went to the closet and looked for a red ribbon. Sara found one and tied it around Lily's head. She said, "Look, Mom. Lily looks like a princess now." Mom said, "Yes, she does. And you are my princess, too." They kissed and laughed. They were happy.
<|end|>


