Lila and Ben are friends. They like to play at the zoo. They see many animals, but their favorite is the gorilla. The gorilla is big and strong, but also humble. He does not show off or hurt other animals.

One day, the gorilla is sad. He misses his home in the forest. He wants to see his family and friends. Lila and Ben want to help him. They have an idea. They ask the zookeeper if they can ride the gorilla. The zookeeper says yes, but only if they are careful and gentle.

Lila and Ben climb on the gorilla's back. They hold on to his fur. The gorilla walks slowly around the zoo. He shows them his favorite places. He eats some bananas and leaves. He makes funny noises. Lila and Ben laugh and talk to him. They say, "You are a good gorilla. We are your friends. We want you to be happy."

The gorilla feels better. He likes Lila and Ben. He thinks they are kind and brave. He thanks them for the ride. He says, "You are good children. You are my friends. You make me happy."

Lila and Ben hug the gorilla. They say goodbye. They promise to visit him again. They run back to their parents. They tell them about their adventure. They say, "We rode a gorilla. He was humble and nice. We had fun."
