<|asst|>
Lily was a big girl now. She had a new bed in her room, and her baby brother had her old crib. She liked her bed, but sometimes she missed her crib. It was cozy and had a nice mobile with stars and moons.

One night, when Mom and Dad were sleeping, Lily got out of her bed. She tiptoed to her brother's room and peeked inside. He was sleeping in the crib, snoring softly. Lily felt a strong wish to be in the crib too. She opened the door and crept inside. She lifted her brother gently and put him on the floor. Then she climbed into the crib and pulled the blanket over her.

She felt happy and safe in the crib. She closed her eyes and smiled. She did not hear the door open again.

"Lily, what are you doing?" Mom asked in a surprised voice. She turned on the light and saw Lily in the crib and her brother on the floor. She was shocked and angry.

Lily opened her eyes and saw Mom. She felt a sudden fear. She had done something bad. She had taken her brother's crib and left him on the cold floor. She had been selfish and sneaky. She felt ashamed.

She did not know what to say. She looked at Mom with big, sorry eyes. She hoped Mom would not be too mad at her.

Mom sighed and shook her head. She picked up her brother and hugged him. He woke up and started to cry. She rocked him and shushed him. Then she looked at Lily again.

"Lily, you know you can't do that. You have your own bed now. You are a big girl. You have to share with your brother. He needs the crib more than you. You could have hurt him or yourself. Do you understand?" Mom said in a stern but gentle voice.

Lily nodded. She understood. She felt very sorry. She wanted to hug Mom and her brother and say she was sorry. She wanted to go back to her bed and forget this night.

Mom saw Lily's face and softened. She knew Lily was not a bad girl. She was just curious and nostalgic. She loved her brother and her crib. She needed some reassurance and guidance.

Mom smiled and said, "It's okay, Lily. I'm not mad at you. I love you. But you have to promise me you won't do that again. Okay?"

Lily nodded again. She felt relieved and grateful. She said, "Okay, Mom. I promise. I love you too. And I love my brother. And I love my bed."

Mom kissed Lily and said, "Good. Now let's go back to your bed. And tomorrow we can play with your brother and his crib. How does that sound?"

Lily smiled and said, "Good. Thank you, Mom."

Mom carried Lily to her bed and tucked her in. She kissed her again and said, "Good night, Lily. Sweet dreams."

Lily said, "Good night, Mom. Sweet dreams."

Mom turned off the light and left the room. Lily closed her eyes and felt happy and safe in her bed. She did not miss her crib anymore. She had learned a lesson. She had revealed her mistake and faced her shame. She had received love and forgiveness. She had grown a little bit more. She was a big girl now.
<|end|>


