Lila and Tom were playing on the beach. They liked to create things with sand and shells. They made a big castle with a tower and a flag. They made a bridge with sticks and stones. They made a boat with a shell and a leaf.

"Look at our boat!" Lila said. "It can sail on the water!"

"Let's try it!" Tom said. They put the boat on the edge of the water and watched it float.

But then a big wave came and took the boat away. Lila and Tom ran after it, but they could not catch it. The boat was too fast and too far.

"Help! Help!" they cried. "Our boat is gone!"

But no one heard them. Their mom and dad were busy talking to their friends. They did not see Lila and Tom running into the water.

The water was deep and cold. Lila and Tom could not swim. They felt helpless and scared. They tried to hold on to each other, but the wave pulled them apart.

They sank under the water and did not come up again.

The moral of the story is: Do not go into the water without an adult. It is dangerous and you can drown.
<|end|>


