Anna and Ben like to watch films. They have a big TV in their living room. Sometimes they watch films about animals, or princesses, or cars. They laugh and clap when they see something funny or exciting.

One night, Anna and Ben watch a film about a dragon. The dragon is big and green and has wings. He can fly and breathe fire. He is angry at the people who want to take his treasure. He roars and chases them away. Anna and Ben are scared, but they also think the dragon is cool.

When the film is over, Anna and Ben go to bed. They brush their teeth and put on their pajamas. They hug their mom and dad and say good night. They go to their rooms and turn off the lights.

Anna falls asleep quickly. She dreams about the dragon. She dreams that she is his friend. She rides on his back and flies in the sky. She sees the stars and the moon. She feels happy and free.

Ben also falls asleep, but he has a different dream. He dreams that he is one of the people who want to take the dragon's treasure. He sneaks into the dragon's cave and finds a pile of gold and jewels. He tries to grab some, but the dragon wakes up. He sees Ben and gets very angry. He roars and breathes fire at him. Ben feels afraid and runs away.

Anna and Ben wake up in the morning. They go to the kitchen and have breakfast. They tell their mom and dad about their dreams.

"I dreamed about the dragon," Anna says. "He was my friend and we flew together. It was fun."

"I dreamed about the dragon, too," Ben says. "But he was not my friend. He was angry and tried to burn me. It was scary."

Anna and Ben look at each other. They wonder why they had such different dreams. They decide to watch another film tonight. Maybe they will have the same dream then.
<|end|>


