Ben and Jen are twins. They like to play with their toys and eat snacks. One day, they find a bag of black beans in the kitchen. They think they are small balls.

"Look, Ben, black balls!" Jen says. She takes some beans and throws them in the air.

"Black balls, black balls!" Ben repeats. He catches some beans and puts them in his pocket.

Mom sees them and gets angry. "No, no, no, Ben and Jen! Those are not balls, those are beans! Beans are for eating, not for playing!" She says. She takes the bag of beans and puts it on the shelf.

"Beans, beans!" Ben and Jen repeat. They want to play with the beans again.

They wait until Mom is busy. Then they climb on a chair and reach for the bag of beans. But the chair is wobbly and they fall down. The bag of beans rips and the beans spill all over the floor.

"Oh, no, Ben and Jen! What have you done?" Mom says. She comes and sees the mess. She is very mad.

"Sorry, Mom, sorry!" Ben and Jen repeat. They help Mom clean up the beans. They promise not to play with the beans again.

Mom hugs them and forgives them. She says, "Next time, ask me before you take something from the kitchen. And remember, beans are for eating, not for playing!"

Ben and Jen nod and say, "Okay, Mom, okay!"

They eat some beans for lunch. They think they are yummy. They do not want to play with them anymore. They play with their toys and eat snacks. They are happy.
