Lily and Ben were on the same team for the game. They had to find and collect as many rare stones as they could. The team with the most stones would win a prize.

Lily and Ben saw a big hill with many stones on it. They ran to the hill and started to dig. They found some red stones, some blue stones, and some shiny stones. They were very happy.

But then they heard a loud noise. It was a horn. It meant the game was over. They had to go back to the teacher and show their stones.

Lily and Ben looked at each other. They had a problem. They had dug so much that they had made a big hole. They could not get out of the hole. They tried to climb, but the dirt was too loose. They tried to call, but no one heard them.

They were stuck in the hole. They missed the prize. They missed their team. They missed their teacher. They were scared and sad.

They regretted digging so much. They regretted not listening to the horn. They regretted being on the same team. They wished they had played differently.
