Lily and Tom are twins. They like to play with their toys. But sometimes they tease each other. They make fun of each other's toys and say mean things.

One day, Lily and Tom find a big ball of wool in their mom's closet. They think it is a fun toy. They take it to their room and start to roll it and toss it. The wool is soft and fluffy.

But soon, they start to tease each other with the wool. Lily wraps some wool around Tom's head and says, "You look like a sheep, baa baa!" Tom pulls the wool off his head and throws it at Lily. He says, "You look like a spider, eek eek!"

They keep teasing each other with the wool. They make a lot of noise. They laugh and shout and scream.

Their mom hears the noise. She comes to their room and sees the mess. The wool is everywhere. It is on the floor, on the bed, on the toys, on the twins. Their mom is not happy. She says, "What are you doing? You made a big mess with my wool. And you are teasing each other. That is not nice. You have to stop and say sorry."

Lily and Tom feel bad. They know they did something wrong. They say sorry to their mom and to each other. They help their mom clean up the wool. They hug and make up. They decide not to tease each other anymore. They say, "We love each other. We are twins."
