Tom and Lily were twins who liked to play outside. They had a big yard with a swing, a slide and a sandbox. They also had a toy jeep that they could drive around. They liked to pretend they were going on adventures in the jeep.

One day, they saw a real jeep parked on the street. It was green and shiny, with big wheels and a flag. They ran to the fence and looked at it. They wondered who owned it and where it came from.

"Hello, kids!" a voice said. They turned and saw a man in a uniform. He had a hat, a badge and a smile. He was holding a big bag. "Do you like my jeep?"

"Yes!" Tom and Lily said. They were curious and excited. They had never seen a jeep like that before.

"I'm a soldier," the man said. "I just came back from a faraway place. This is my jeep. I use it to help people and keep them safe. Do you want to see what's in my bag?"

"Yes, please!" Tom and Lily said. They nodded and smiled.

The man opened his bag and took out some things. He showed them a map, a compass, a medal and a picture. He told them stories about his jeep, his friends and his mission. Tom and Lily listened and asked questions. They learned a lot of new things.

The man also gave them a gift. He took out two small flags and handed them to Tom and Lily. They were the same as the one on his jeep. They had red, white and blue colors and stars and stripes.

"These are for you," the man said. "They are flags of our country. They mean freedom, courage and hope. You can wave them and be proud."

"Thank you!" Tom and Lily said. They took the flags and waved them. They felt happy and grateful.

The man looked at his watch and said, "I have to go now. I have to see my family. They are waiting for me. It's been a long time since I saw them."

"Bye!" Tom and Lily said. They hugged the man and thanked him again. They wished him well.

The man got in his jeep and started the engine. It was loud and rumbling. He waved to Tom and Lily and drove away. Tom and Lily waved back and watched him go. They saw the flag fluttering in the wind.

They went back to their yard and played with their toy jeep and their flags. They pretended they were soldiers too. They had a new friend and a new adventure. They never forgot the man and his jeep.
<|end|>


