Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play with boats in the pond. They have cheap boats made of wood and paper. They make them go fast with the wind.

One day, they see a big boat in the pond. It is not cheap. It is shiny and red. It has a motor and a horn. It goes very fast and makes a lot of noise.

"Wow, look at that boat!" Tom says. "It is so cool!"

"I want that boat!" Sam says. "It is much better than our boats!"

They run to the edge of the pond. They wave at the man who drives the big boat. They hope he will stop and let them see it.

But the man does not stop. He does not see them. He just passes by with his big boat. He honks his horn and makes a big splash.

Tom and Sam are sad. They feel their boats are too cheap and slow. They wish they had a big boat like the man.

But then they hear a voice. It is Lily, their friend. She has a boat too. It is not cheap. It is not shiny and red. It is not big and loud. It is small and green. It is made of plastic and has a sail.

"Hi, Tom and Sam!" Lily says. "Do you want to play with me and my boat?"

Tom and Sam look at Lily and her boat. They smile. They think her boat is nice. It is not too fast or too slow. It is just right.

"Sure, Lily!" they say. "We want to play with you and your boat!"

They go back to their boats. They put them in the pond. They make them go with the wind. They have fun. They race and chase and pass each other. They laugh and shout and cheer.

They forget about the big boat. They are happy with their cheap boats. They are happy with their friend. They are happy with their game.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
