<|end|>
<|asst|>
Ben and Mia are twins. They like to play with their toys in their room. But Ben is messy and Mia is organized. Mia puts her toys in boxes and labels them. Ben throws his toys everywhere and does not care.

One day, Mom gives them new vests. They are blue and warm and soft. Mia loves her vest and puts it on a hanger in her closet. Ben likes his vest too, but he forgets to put it away. He leaves it on the floor with his toys.

The next day, it is cold and windy. Mom says they can go to the park, but they need to wear their vests. Mia runs to her closet and gets her vest. Ben runs to his room and looks for his vest. But he cannot find it. He sees Mia's vest on the hanger, but not his.

"Where is my vest?" he asks Mia.

"I don't know. Did you put it away?" Mia asks.

"No, I did not. I left it here," Ben says.

"Well, you should have been more organized. Maybe it is under your toys. You have too many toys and they are all over the place," Mia says.

Ben gets angry and starts to cry. He does not want to look for his vest. He wants to go to the park. He calls Mom and tells her that Mia took his vest.

"Mia, did you take Ben's vest?" Mom asks.

"No, Mom. I have my own vest. Ben left his vest on the floor and now he cannot find it," Mia says.

Mom sighs and goes to Ben's room. She helps him look for his vest. They move the toys and the books and the pillows. Finally, they find the vest. It is under the bed, dirty and wrinkled.

"Here is your vest, Ben. But it is not clean or nice. You should have taken care of it like Mia did. Next time, be more organized and put your things away. Then you will not lose them or make them dirty," Mom says.

Ben feels sorry and says sorry to Mom and Mia. He puts on his vest and goes to the park with them. He learns his lesson and tries to be more organized from then on. He and Mia have fun playing with their toys and their vests.
<|end|>


<|sys|>
