<|end|>
<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were playing with their toys in the living room. They had a lot of fun making noises and pretending to be animals. Lily was a lion and Ben was a monkey. They roared and jumped and swung around the couch.

"Let's play something else!" Lily said. She was very enthusiastic and always wanted to try new things.

"Like what?" Ben asked. He was getting a little tired and bored.

"Let's play hide and seek!" Lily suggested. "You count to ten and I'll hide. Then you have to find me!"

"Okay, okay," Ben agreed. He yawned and rubbed his eyes. He was not very enthusiastic, but he did not want to upset Lily. He closed his eyes and started to count. "One, two, three..."

Lily ran to find a good hiding spot. She looked around the living room and saw a big pile of pillows on the couch. She thought it was a perfect place to hide. She crawled under the pillows and giggled. She was sure Ben would never find her there.

Ben finished counting and opened his eyes. He looked around the living room and tried to guess where Lily was hiding. He checked behind the curtains, under the table, in the closet, but he could not find her. He started to feel frustrated and bored. He yawned again and wished he could take a nap.

He walked to the couch and saw the pile of pillows. He wondered if Lily was hiding there. He decided to check. He lifted one of the pillows and saw Lily's face. She smiled and said, "Boo!"

Ben was startled and dropped the pillow. He fell back on the couch and sighed. He was not amused. He said, "Lily, that's not fair. You scared me."

Lily laughed and said, "I'm sorry, Ben. I was just playing. Did you have fun?"

Ben shook his head and said, "No, I did not. I'm tired and I want to rest. Can we stop playing now?"

Lily frowned and said, "But I'm not tired. I want to play more. Can we play something else?"

Ben shook his head again and said, "No, I don't want to play anything else. I want to sleep. Please, Lily, let me sleep."

Lily saw that Ben was serious and felt sorry for him. She said, "Okay, Ben, I'm sorry. You can sleep. I'll be quiet."

She moved the pillows and cuddled next to Ben on the couch. She yawned and closed her eyes. She realized that she was tired too. She said, "Good night, Ben."

Ben smiled and said, "Good night, Lily."

They both fell asleep on the couch, dreaming of their next adventure.
<|end|>


