<|end|>
<|asst|>
Tim and Sue like to act. They act like animals, like people, like things. They have fun and make noise. One day, they find a big loop in the yard. It is made of rope and hangs from a tree.

"Look, a loop!" Tim says. "Let's act like we are in a circus!"

"OK!" Sue says. "I will be a lion and you will be a clown!"

They run to the loop and take turns. Tim puts his head inside the loop and makes funny faces. Sue roars and pretends to bite him. They laugh and clap.

But then, Tim has an idea. He wants to act like he can fly. He grabs the loop and swings on it. He goes high and low, fast and slow. He feels like a bird.

"Look at me, Sue!" he shouts. "I can fly!"

Sue watches him and smiles. She is glad that he is happy. But she also sees something that he does not. She sees a big rock under the loop. She sees that Tim is going too fast and too high. She sees that he will hit the rock if he does not stop.

"Tim, stop!" she yells. "There is a rock! You will get hurt!"

But Tim does not hear her. He is too busy flying. He does not see the rock. He does not see the danger. He only sees the sky.

He swings one more time. He goes very high. He lets go of the loop. He flies in the air. He feels free.

But then, he falls. He falls fast. He falls hard. He falls on the rock.

He cries. He cries loud. He cries a lot.

Sue runs to him. She hugs him. She says sorry. She says she loves him.

Tim stops crying. He hugs her back. He says sorry too. He says he loves her.

They go inside. They get a band-aid. They get a kiss. They get a hug.

They are still glad. They are still friends. They still like to act.

But they do not act like they can fly anymore. They know that flying is not for them. They know that flying is for birds. They know that they are not birds.

They are Tim and Sue. And they are happy.
<|end|>


