<|asst|>
Lily and Ben were hungry. They wanted to eat soup for lunch. Mom said she had some soup available in the pot. She told them to wait at the table while she got some bowls and spoons.

But Lily and Ben did not wait. They were too curious. They wanted to see the soup. They climbed on the chairs and looked inside the pot. The soup was hot and steamy. It smelled good. They saw some carrots and noodles and chicken in the soup.

"Can we have some now?" Lily asked.

"Maybe just a little bit," Ben said.

They reached for the ladle. But they were not careful. They bumped the pot. The pot tipped over. The soup spilled out. It splashed on the floor and the table and the chairs. It made a big mess.

"Oh no!" Lily and Ben cried.

Mom heard the noise. She came back to the kitchen. She saw the soup everywhere. She saw Lily and Ben with wet and sticky clothes. She was not happy.

"What happened?" Mom asked.

"The soup disappeared!" Lily and Ben said.
<|end|>


