<|asst|>
Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They have a ball, a bike and a doll. They share their toys and have fun.

One day, they see a big dog in the park. The dog is brown and has a red collar. The dog runs to them and barks. Lily and Ben are scared. They drop their toys and run away.

"Whoa, whoa, whoa!" a voice says. "Don't be afraid. He is friendly. He just wants to say hello."

Lily and Ben stop and look. A man is holding the dog's leash. He smiles at them.

"Hi, I'm Tom. This is Rex. He is my dog. He likes to play, too. He won't hurt you. Do you want to pet him?"

Lily and Ben nod. They walk slowly to the man and the dog. They touch the dog's fur. It is soft and warm. The dog licks their hands. It tickles.

"Good boy, Rex. Good boy." Tom says. "He likes you. You are nice kids."

Lily and Ben giggle. They like Rex, too. He is a good dog.

"Can we play with him?" Lily asks.

"Sure, you can. But only for a little while. It's almost lunch time. We have to go home soon." Tom says.

"Okay. Thank you." Ben says.

They play with Rex. They throw the ball and he fetches it. They ride the bike and he runs after them. They hug the doll and he sniffs it.

They have a lot of fun. They forget about their toys.

"Time to go, kids. Say bye to Rex." Tom says.

"Bye, Rex. We'll miss you." Lily and Ben say.

They wave to Tom and Rex. They walk back to their toys.

But they see something wrong. Their toys are gone. Someone took them.

"Where are our toys?" Lily cries.

"Who took them?" Ben asks.

They look around. They see a boy and a girl. They have their toys. They are playing with them.

"Hey, those are our toys!" Lily shouts.

"Give them back!" Ben yells.

The boy and the girl look at them. They laugh.

"No, they are not. They are ours. We found them. Finders keepers." The boy says.

"That's not fair. You stole them. They belong to us. We were playing with them." The girl says.

"Too bad. We like them. They are ours now. Go away." The girl says.

They stick out their tongues. They run away with the toys.

Lily and Ben are sad and angry. They want their toys back. They don't know what to do.

They hear a bark. They see Rex. He is running to them. He has something in his mouth. It is the ball.

"Rex!" Lily and Ben say.

They hug Rex. He drops the ball. He wags his tail.

"Good boy, Rex. Good boy." Tom says. He is behind Rex. He has something in his hands. It is the bike and the doll.

"Here, kids. I saw what happened. Those kids were mean. They took your toys. But Rex and I got them back. Here you go." Tom says.

He gives them the bike and the doll. They take them.

"Thank you, Tom. Thank you, Rex. You are the best." Lily and Ben say.

They smile. They are happy. They have their toys back.

They play with Tom and Rex. They share their toys. They have more fun.

They hear a bell. It is lunch time. They have to go home.

"Bye, Tom. Bye, Rex. See you soon." Lily and Ben say.

"Bye, kids. Have a good lunch. See you later." Tom says.

They wave to Tom and Rex. They go home with their toys.

They have a sweet lunch. They have sandwiches, apples and cookies. They are yummy.

They think about Tom and Rex. They are their friends. They are nice.

They belong together.
<|end|>


