<|asst|>
Sara and Ben were best friends. They liked to play together in the park. One day, they decided to play marriage. Sara wore a white dress and Ben wore a black suit. They held hands and skipped to the big tree.

"Ben, do you want to be my husband?" Sara asked.

"Yes, Sara, I do. Do you want to be my wife?" Ben answered.

"Yes, Ben, I do. You are very nice and funny," Sara said.

They smiled and kissed each other on the cheek. They were very happy.

But then, a grumpy boy came to the park. He saw Sara and Ben playing marriage. He did not like it. He wanted to play with Sara. He ran to them and pushed Ben away.

"Hey, stop that! She is my wife!" Ben shouted.

"No, she is not! She is my friend! Go away!" the grumpy boy yelled.

He grabbed Sara's hand and tried to pull her away. Sara did not like it. She did not want to go with the grumpy boy. She wanted to stay with Ben.

"Let me go! You are mean and rude!" Sara cried.

She kicked the grumpy boy in the leg. He let go of her hand and fell to the ground. He started to cry.

Sara ran back to Ben. They hugged each other. They were not scared of the grumpy boy. They were brave and strong.

"Are you okay, Sara?" Ben asked.

"Yes, Ben, I am. Thank you for being my husband," Sara said.

"Thank you for being my wife, Sara," Ben said.

They kissed each other on the cheek again. They were very happy. They skipped away from the grumpy boy. They played marriage until it was time to go home.
<|end|>


