<|asst|>
Anna and Ben are friends. They like to play together. One day, Anna's mom says, "We are going to visit Grandma today. Do you want to come, Ben?"

Ben says, "Yes, please! I like Grandma. She has a big garden and a funny cat."

Anna and Ben get in the car with Anna's mom. They drive for a long time. Ben asks, "Are we there yet?"

Anna's mom says, "Almost, Ben. Just a few more minutes."

Soon, they see Grandma's house. It is yellow and has a red door. Grandma is waiting for them. She is cheerful. She says, "Hello, Anna and Ben! I'm so happy to see you. Come in, come in!"

Anna and Ben hug Grandma. They go inside. They see the funny cat. It is sleeping on the sofa. They pet the cat gently. The cat purrs.

Grandma says, "Do you want some cookies and milk? I baked them for you."

Anna and Ben say, "Yes, please! Thank you, Grandma!"

They sit at the table and eat the cookies and milk. They talk and laugh with Grandma. They have a lot of fun. They love to visit Grandma.
<|end|>


