Lily and Ben were twins who lived on a big ranch with many animals. They liked to play with the horses, the cows, the chickens and the dogs. They also liked to help their mom and dad with the chores, like feeding the animals, collecting the eggs and watering the plants.

One day, they saw a new animal on the ranch. It was big and brown and had a long nose and big ears. It made a loud noise like "hee-haw". Lily and Ben were curious and ran to see it.

"Mom, what is that?" Lily asked.

"That is a donkey, sweetie. His name is Jack. He is our new friend. He can help us carry things and pull the cart," mom said.

"Can we play with him?" Ben asked.

"Sure, but be gentle and careful. He is not used to children yet. He might be shy or scared," mom said.

Lily and Ben approached Jack slowly and gently. They stroked his fur and scratched his ears. They gave him some carrots and apples. Jack liked them and wagged his tail. He let them sit on his back and walk around the ranch.

Lily and Ben had a lot of fun with Jack. They decided he was not ugly, but cute and funny. They told him stories and sang him songs. They made him a crown of flowers and put it on his head.

When the sun was setting, mom called them for dinner. Lily and Ben said goodbye to Jack and thanked him for the ride. They promised to come back and play with him again.

"Good night, Jack. We love you. Sleep well," they said.

Jack hee-hawed and nodded his head. He was happy to have new friends. He lay down on the grass and closed his eyes. He dreamed of carrots and apples and flowers and songs. He slept well.
<|end|>


