Sam and Mia are twins. They like to play at home. One day, they find some paper in a box. They want to make things with the paper.

"Look, I can fold the paper like this," Sam says. He folds the paper in half, then in half again. He makes a small square.

"Wow, that is cool," Mia says. She tries to fold the paper too, but she rips it. She is sad.

"Here, you can have mine," Sam says. He gives his square to Mia. He is nice.

"Thank you, Sam," Mia says. She smiles. She folds the square one more time. She makes a tiny triangle.

They find more paper in the box. They fold and fold and fold. They make many shapes. They have fun.

They hear a noise. It is their dad. He is home from work. He works in a large office. He has a lot of paper.

He sees Sam and Mia and the paper. He is angry.

"What are you doing?" he shouts. "This is my paper! I need it for work! You have ruined it!"

He takes the paper from them. He throws it in the trash. He scolds them. He sends them to their room.

Sam and Mia are scared. They are sorry. They cry. They hug each other. They wish they had not played with the paper.
<|end|>


