Tom and Sam are friends. They like to play catch with a ball. They throw the ball to each other and run after it. Sometimes they miss the ball and it rolls away. Then they have to find it.

One day, they play catch near a hut. The hut is old and brown. It has a door and a window. Tom and Sam wonder who lives in the hut. They want to see inside. They knock on the door, but no one answers. They peek through the window, but it is dark.

They decide to open the door and go in. They are curious and brave. They push the door and it creaks. They step into the hut and look around. They see a table, a chair, a bed and a stove. On the stove, there is a pot. The pot is hot and smells spicy.

Tom and Sam are hungry. They think the pot has soup. They want to taste the soup. They go to the stove and lift the lid of the pot. But they are not careful. The soup is very spicy. It makes them cough and sneeze. They drop the lid and the pot. The soup spills on the floor.

The noise and the smell wake up the owner of the hut. He is a bear. He is big and angry. He sees Tom and Sam in his hut. He roars and chases them. Tom and Sam are scared. They run out of the hut and back to their ball. They do not play catch near the hut anymore. They learn to respect other people's homes.
<|end|>


