<|asst|>
Lily was a naughty girl. She liked to play with things that were not hers. One day, she saw a shiny red ball in the park. She wanted to have it, so she ran to it and took it. She did not care that it belonged to another boy.

The boy was sad and angry. He shouted at Lily and tried to get his ball back. But Lily was faster and ran away. She ran to the west, where the sun was setting. She thought she was clever and had gained a new toy.

But she was wrong. The ball was not just a ball. It was a magic ball. It could do things that Lily did not know. It could change its size and shape. It could fly and bounce. And it did not like naughty girls.

The ball waited until Lily was far from the park. Then it started to act. It grew bigger and bigger, until it was as big as Lily. It pushed Lily off and rolled over her. It bounced high in the air and flew away. It left Lily alone and scared in the dark.

Lily cried and cried. She wished she had not taken the ball. She wished she had been nice to the boy. She learned a lesson that day. She learned that being naughty does not pay. She learned that it is better to share and be kind.
<|end|>


