Lily was a princess who lived in a big castle. She liked to play with her dolls and her books, but she was not happy. Her mean stepmother locked her in her room every day and did not let her go out. She only gave her some bread and water for food.

One day, Lily heard a knock on her door. She was scared, but she hoped it was someone nice. She went to the door and asked, "Who is it?"

"It is me, Ben. I am a prince from another land. I came to save you," a voice said.

Lily was surprised and happy. She asked, "How did you find me?"

"I followed a bird that sang your name. It told me you were locked in this room. I have a key to unlock the door. Can I come in?" Ben said.

Lily said, "Yes, please. I want to see you and go with you."

Ben unlocked the door and opened it. He saw Lily and smiled. He said, "You are very pretty and brave. I like you. Do you want to be my friend?"

Lily nodded and smiled. She said, "Yes, I do. You are very kind and handsome. I like you too. Can we go now?"

Ben said, "Yes, we can. But first, we have to run away from your stepmother. She is very smelly and mean. She will be angry when she sees you are gone."

Lily said, "I don't care. I don't like her. She is not my real mother. Let's go."

Ben took Lily's hand and they ran out of the room. They saw the bird that helped them and thanked it. They got on a horse and rode away. They went to Ben's land, where they were happy and free. They played and laughed and hugged. They became best friends and lived happily ever after.
<|end|>


