Lily loved dolphins. She had a big picture of a dolphin on her wall. She had a soft toy dolphin that she hugged at night. She had a book about dolphins that her mom read to her. She dreamed of seeing a real dolphin one day.

One day, her mom said, "Lily, I have a surprise for you. We are going to the sea park. They have real dolphins there. You can watch them swim and play. Maybe you can even touch one."

Lily was so happy. She put on her sun hat and her swimsuit. She packed her toy dolphin and her book. She could not wait to see the sea park.

But when they got to the sea park, something was wrong. There were many people outside. They looked upset. They had signs that said, "Save the dolphins. Stop the sea park. The sea park is bad for the dolphins."

Lily did not understand. She asked her mom, "Mom, why are they upset? Why do they say the sea park is bad?"

Her mom said, "Lily, the sea park is not a good place for the dolphins. They keep them in small tanks. They make them do tricks for food. They spoil their lives. The dolphins are not happy here. They belong in the ocean, where they can swim freely and be with their families."

Lily felt sad. She did not want to see the dolphins in the sea park. She wanted to see them in the ocean. She said, "Mom, can we go to the ocean instead? Can we see the dolphins there?"

Her mom said, "Yes, Lily, we can. Maybe we can find a boat that can take us to see the dolphins. Maybe we can even hear them talk to each other. They make beautiful sounds, you know."

Lily smiled. She said, "That sounds wonderful, Mom. I love dolphins. I want them to be happy."

Her mom hugged her. She said, "I love you, Lily. You are a very kind and smart girl. Come on, let's go to the ocean."
<|end|>


