Tom and Lily are playing in the garden. They like to run and jump and hide behind the hedge. The hedge is big and green and has many flowers. Sometimes they see birds and bees and butterflies near the hedge.

One day, they see a big truck come to the garden. The truck has a loud noise and a big arm. The arm has a claw that can grab things. Tom and Lily are curious and scared. They run to their mom and ask her what is happening.

Mom says, "The truck is here to remove the hedge. The hedge is old and sick and needs to go. We will plant a new hedge soon. Don't worry, my loves."

Tom and Lily are sad. They like the hedge. They say, "But mom, the hedge is our friend. It has flowers and animals and makes us happy. Can we keep the hedge, please?"

Mom hugs them and says, "I know, my loves, but the hedge is not happy. It is hurting and dying and needs to rest. We can keep some flowers and make a bouquet. We can also make a bird feeder and a butterfly house for the new hedge. The new hedge will be white and beautiful and will grow fast. You will make new friends with the new hedge, I promise."

Tom and Lily are still sad, but they understand. They say goodbye to the hedge and thank it for the fun times. They help mom pick some flowers and make a bouquet. They watch the truck remove the hedge and leave a big space. They hope the new hedge will come soon and be nice. They hug mom and go inside for a snack.
<|end|>


