Lila and Ben were playing in the park. They liked to build towers with the blocks. They made tall towers, short towers, and colorful towers. They had fun.

Then they saw a new boy. He had a big bag of blocks. He looked shy. He did not know anyone.

"Hi, I am Lila. This is Ben. We are building towers. Do you want to play with us?" Lila asked.

The boy nodded. He smiled. He opened his bag. He had unusual blocks. They were shiny and round. They looked like balls.

"Wow, what are these?" Ben asked.

"They are my blocks. They are special. They can stick together. They can make different shapes. Look." The boy said.

He took some blocks and made a circle. Then he made a triangle. Then he made a star.

"That is cool. Can we try?" Lila asked.

The boy nodded. He shared his blocks. They all played together. They made unusual towers. They made towers that looked like animals, flowers, and rockets. They had more fun.

They became friends. They welcomed the boy to the park. They thanked him for sharing his blocks. They invited him to play again. The boy was happy. He had found new friends. He had found a place to belong.
