Lily and Tom were bored. They had played with all their toys and read all their books. They wanted to do something new and fun.

"Let's make a cake!" Lily said. She liked to bake with her mom. She knew where the flour, sugar, eggs and butter were.

"Okay!" Tom said. He liked to eat cake. He followed Lily to the kitchen.

Lily and Tom put the ingredients in a big bowl. They took turns to stir with a wooden spoon. They made a smooth batter.

"Can I lick the spoon?" Tom asked.

"No, not yet. We have to bake the cake first," Lily said. She poured the batter into a pan and put it in the oven. She set the timer for 20 minutes.

"Now what do we do?" Tom asked.

"We have to wait. Let's do a puzzle!" Lily said. She found a puzzle box on the shelf. It had a picture of a farm with animals and a tractor.

Lily and Tom opened the box and dumped the pieces on the floor. They started to look for the edges and the corners. They worked together to fit the pieces.

"Look, I found the cow!" Tom said.

"Good job! I found the barn!" Lily said.

They helped each other to complete the puzzle. They were proud of their work.

The timer beeped. The cake was ready. Lily and Tom ran to the oven. They put on oven mitts and took out the cake. It smelled good.

"Wow, it looks yummy!" Tom said.

"Let's let it cool down a bit. Then we can frost it and decorate it," Lily said.

They waited for a few minutes. Then they spread some chocolate frosting on the cake. They sprinkled some colorful candies on top.

"Can we eat it now?" Tom asked.

"Yes, but first we have to share it with mom and dad. They will be happy to see what we made," Lily said.

They cut the cake into four slices. They put them on plates and carried them to the living room. Mom and dad were watching TV.

"Surprise!" Lily and Tom said.

"Wow, what a nice surprise! Did you make this cake?" Mom asked.

"Yes, we did. We stirred and baked and frosted and decorated it. We also did a puzzle. We had fun," Lily said.

"That's wonderful. You are very helpful and creative. Thank you for the cake. It looks delicious," Dad said.

They all ate the cake and enjoyed it. Lily and Tom felt happy. They had learned that baking and puzzling were fun and rewarding activities. They had also learned to cooperate and share. They hugged mom and dad and said, "We love you."
<|end|>


