Lily and Ben were playing in the park. They liked to look for things on the ground. They found leaves, rocks, and sticks. They put them in a basket.

"Look, Ben, I found an acorn!" Lily said. She held up a small brown thing with a cap.

"What is an acorn?" Ben asked. He had never seen one before.

"It is a seed. A big tree grows from it. Like that one." Lily pointed to a tall oak tree.

"Wow, that is amazing!" Ben said. He wanted to see the acorn better. He took it from Lily and examined it. He looked at the cap, the shell, and the pointy end.

"Can I have it back?" Lily asked. She liked the acorn. She thought it was cute.

"Sure, here you go." Ben gave the acorn back to Lily. He smiled. "You can keep it. It is a nice gift from the tree."

"Thank you, Ben. You are a good friend." Lily said. She put the acorn in her pocket. She was happy.

They continued to play and look for more things. They had fun in the park.
