Tom and Mia wanted to join the club of big kids. The club had a tree house, a swing and a lot of toys. But the big kids said Tom and Mia were too small and scared. They said they had to do a dare to join the club.

The dare was to go to the dark shed and find a red ball. The shed was behind the fence, where the dog barked. Tom and Mia were afraid of the dog and the dark. But they wanted to join the club very much.

They held hands and walked to the fence. They saw the dog sleeping on a mat. They were quiet and climbed over the fence. They opened the door of the shed and looked inside. It was very dark and dusty. They saw a lot of things, but no red ball.

"Where is the ball?" Mia whispered.

"I don't know. Maybe it's under that box." Tom said.

They moved the box and saw a red ball. They were happy and grabbed it. But then they heard a loud noise. The dog woke up and saw them. It started to bark and run to the fence.

"Run!" Tom shouted.

They ran to the door with the ball. But the door was closed. Someone locked it from outside. It was the big kids. They laughed and said:

"Ha ha, you are trapped. You are too small and scared to join the club. You are not brave enough to do the dare."

Tom and Mia felt sad and angry. They wanted to get out and go home. They banged on the door and yelled for help. They were very impatient and scared. They hoped someone would hear them and open the door. They hugged each other and waited.
<|end|>


