Tom and Sam are brothers. They like to play with their toys in their room. But today, Mom says they have to go to bed early. She says they have a big day tomorrow.

"Why do we have to go to bed early, Mom?" Tom asks. He does not want to stop playing.

"Because tomorrow you are going to the zoo, remember?" Mom says. "You will see many animals and have fun. But you need to sleep well and gain energy."

Tom and Sam love the zoo. They want to see the lions, the monkeys, and the elephants. They think about the zoo and feel excited.

"Okay, Mom, we will go to bed early," Sam says. He is a serious boy. He always listens to Mom.

Tom and Sam put their toys away and brush their teeth. They hug Mom and say good night. They go to their bed and snuggle under the covers.

"Good night, Tom," Sam says.

"Good night, Sam," Tom says.

They close their eyes and dream of the zoo.
