Anna and Ben are twins who like to play in the kitchen. They have a big box of salt that they use to make shapes and patterns on the table. They also have some spoons and cups that they balance on top of each other.

One day, they decide to make a tower of salt and spoons. Anna is very enthusiastic and wants to make the tower as high as possible. She pours salt on the table and stacks spoons on top of each other. Ben is more careful and tries to make the tower stable and neat. He tells Anna to slow down and not use too much salt.

"Anna, stop! You are making a mess!" Ben says.

"No, I'm not! I'm making a great tower!" Anna says.

"Yes, you are! Look, the salt is spilling everywhere and the spoons are falling down!" Ben says.

"No, they are not! You are just jealous of my tower!" Anna says.

They start to argue and push each other. The tower wobbles and crashes to the floor. Salt and spoons scatter all over the kitchen. Anna and Ben are shocked and sad. They look at each other and feel sorry.

"I'm sorry, Ben. I was too enthusiastic and I didn't listen to you." Anna says.

"I'm sorry, Anna. I was too bossy and I didn't let you have fun." Ben says.

They hug and say they are sorry. They decide to work together and clean up the mess. They also decide to make a new tower of salt and spoons, but this time they balance it better and use less salt. They are happy and proud of their tower. They show it to their mom and dad, who praise them for their teamwork and creativity.
<|end|>


