Lily and Tom were playing in the garden. They saw a big red flower. Lily wanted to smell it. She went near the flower and bent down.

"Be careful, Lily!" Tom said. "That is not a flower. That is a flame. It is very hot and can hurt you."

Lily did not listen to Tom. She touched the flame with her hand. She felt a sharp pain. She cried out loud.

"Ow, ow, ow! It hurts, it hurts!" Lily said. She ran to Tom and showed him her hand. It was red and sore.

Tom hugged Lily and said, "I'm sorry, Lily. You need to put some water on your hand. Water will make it feel better. Come, I will help you."

He took Lily to the tap and poured some water on her hand. Lily felt a little better. She thanked Tom and said, "You are a good brother, Tom. I'm sorry I did not listen to you. I learned my lesson. Flame is not a flower. Flame is bitter and bad."
<|end|>


