Lily and Tom were playing in the garden. They saw a big red flower. It looked very pretty. Lily wanted to touch it.

"Can I touch the flower?" Lily asked Tom.

"No, you can't," Tom said. "Mom said it is a bad flower. It can hurt you. If you touch it, you will be punished."

Lily did not listen to Tom. She thought he was silly. She reached out her hand to touch the flower. But when she touched it, she felt a sharp pain. The flower had thorns. They pricked her finger. Lily cried out loud.

"Ow, ow, ow! It hurts, it hurts!" Lily said.

Tom ran to Lily. He saw her finger bleeding. He felt sorry for her. He took her to Mom.

"Mom, Mom, Lily touched the bad flower. She is hurt," Tom said.

Mom saw Lily's finger. She cleaned it and put a band-aid on it. She hugged Lily and Tom.

"I'm sorry, Lily. You should have listened to Tom. He was right. The flower is bad. It can hurt you. You were punished by the flower. Next time, be careful and do not touch things you do not know," Mom said.

Lily nodded. She learned her lesson. She said sorry to Tom. She said thank you to Mom. She did not touch the bad flower again. She played with Tom and other nice things in the garden.
