Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big square on the grass. It is green and yellow. Lily and Ben run to the square.

"What is this?" Lily asks.

"It is a blanket," Ben says. "We can sit on it and have a picnic."

Lily and Ben sit on the blanket. They have some bread and cheese and juice. They are happy. They see some birds and flowers. They wave to them.

"Hello, birds! Hello, flowers!" they say.

A lady comes to the blanket. She has a lovely smile. She is Ben's mom.

"Hello, Lily and Ben," she says. "Did you enjoy your picnic?"

"Yes, we did," Lily and Ben say. "Thank you for the blanket and the food."

"You are welcome," Ben's mom says. "It is time to go home now. Say goodbye to the park."

Lily and Ben stand up. They wave to the park.

"Goodbye, park! Goodbye, birds! Goodbye, flowers!" they say.

They hold hands and walk with Ben's mom. They are still friends. They are still happy.
