Sam and Mia liked to play with snow. They made a big snowman in the yard. They gave him a hat, a scarf, and a carrot nose. They named him Bob.

"Hello, Bob!" Sam said. "You are our friend."

"Yes, you are very big and nice," Mia said. "We will play with you every day."

But the next day, the sun was very bright and warm. Sam and Mia went outside to see Bob. But Bob was not the same. He was smaller and wet. His hat and scarf were on the ground. His carrot nose was gone.

"Oh no, Bob is melting!" Sam cried. "He is not happy."

"What can we do?" Mia asked. "We don't want to lose Bob."

They looked around and saw a mill. A mill was a big house with a big wheel. The wheel turned and made flour. Sam had an idea.

"Maybe we can take Bob to the mill," he said. "It is cool and dark inside. He will not melt there."

"Good idea!" Mia said. "Let's go."

They took Bob's hat and scarf and rolled him to the mill. They asked the miller if they could put Bob inside. The miller was kind and said yes. He helped them find a nice spot for Bob.

"There you go, Bob," Sam said. "You will be safe here. We will come back to visit you."

"Thank you, miller," Mia said. "You are very nice."

The miller smiled and said, "You are welcome, children. But remember, Bob is made of snow. He will not last forever. Enjoy him while you can."

Sam and Mia nodded. They hugged Bob and said goodbye. They hoped he would not melt too fast. They still loved him very much.
<|end|>


