Tim and Mia are friends. They like to play in the park. They see a big blue bird in the sky. The bird can fly very high and fast.

"Wow, look at the bird!" Tim says. "I wish I could fly like that."

"Me too," Mia says. "Maybe we can ask the bird to teach us how to fly."

They run after the bird and call out to it. "Hello, bird! Hello! Can you please help us? We want to fly like you."

The bird hears them and lands on a branch. It looks at them with its bright eyes. It is a polite bird. It does not fly away or scold them.

"Hello, children," the bird says. "Why do you want to fly like me?"

"Because flying is fun and cool," Tim says. "We want to see the world from up there."

"And we want to feel the wind in our hair," Mia says.

The bird nods. It understands. It likes to fly too. But it also knows that flying is not easy or safe for children.

"I'm sorry, children, but you cannot fly like me," the bird says. "You do not have wings or feathers. You have arms and legs. You are made to walk and run and jump on the ground. That is your way of having fun and seeing the world."

Tim and Mia feel sad. They really want to fly. But they also respect the bird and its wisdom.

"Thank you, bird, for telling us the truth," Tim says.

"Yes, thank you, bird, for being polite and kind," Mia says.

The bird smiles. It is happy to see that the children are polite and kind too.

"You're welcome, children," the bird says. "But do not be sad. You can still enjoy the sky and the wind. You can fly kites or balloons or paper planes. You can make your own wings with your imagination and creativity. You can fly in your dreams and stories. You can fly in many ways, as long as you are happy and safe."

Tim and Mia think about what the bird says. They feel better. They realize that the bird is right. They can fly in many ways.

"Thank you, bird, for giving us good ideas," Tim says.

"Yes, thank you, bird, for being a good friend," Mia says.

The bird flaps its wings and flies away. It waves to them with its tail.

"Goodbye, children," the bird says. "Have fun and be careful. And remember, you can always fly in your heart."
<|end|>


