Ben was sad. He had a hard day at school. He did not like his file. His file had many papers with red marks. His teacher said he had to do better. Ben felt bad.

He came home and ran to his room. He did not want to talk to anyone. He lay on his bed and cried. He hugged his teddy bear. His teddy bear was soft and warm. He liked his teddy bear.

His mom knocked on his door. She opened it and saw Ben. She smiled and sat on his bed. She stroked his hair and kissed his cheek. She said, "What's wrong, Ben? Why are you sad?"

Ben showed her his file. He said, "Look, mom. I have many red marks. I am not good at school. I am dumb."

His mom shook her head. She said, "No, Ben. You are not dumb. You are smart and kind and brave. You can do anything you want. You just need to practice more and ask for help when you need it. I am proud of you, Ben. I love you."

She hugged him and comforted him. She said, "Do you want to read a story with me? I have a new book for you. It is about a boy who goes on an adventure with his teddy bear."

Ben nodded. He wiped his tears and smiled. He said, "Yes, mom. I want to read with you. Thank you, mom. I love you too."

They went to the living room and sat on the couch. His mom opened the book and read to him. Ben listened and looked at the pictures. He felt happy and safe. He cuddled with his teddy bear and his mom. He forgot about his hard day and his file. He dreamed of his adventure.
<|end|>


