Tom and Sue were playing in the park. They liked to dig in the sand and look for shiny things. Sometimes they found coins or buttons or rings. They felt happy when they found something new.

One day, they saw a big hole in the sand. They ran to it and looked inside. There was a copper pot with a lid. It was very old and dirty. Tom felt curious and wanted to open it. Sue felt anxious and wanted to leave it alone.

"Maybe there is treasure inside," Tom said. He reached for the lid.

"Maybe there is a monster inside," Sue said. She pulled Tom's arm.

Tom did not listen. He lifted the lid and looked inside. He saw something move and heard a loud hiss. He felt scared and dropped the lid. He and Sue ran away as fast as they could.

They did not know that they had disturbed a snake that lived in the pot. The snake felt angry and followed them. It wanted to bite them and make them go away.

Tom and Sue did not see the snake behind them. They only felt the wind in their hair and the sand in their shoes. They ran until they reached their mom and dad. They hugged them and told them what they had seen. They felt safe and glad. They did not want to play in the sand anymore.
