Lily and Ben are friends. They like to play in the park. But today they quarrel. Lily wants to swing, but Ben wants to slide. They both say "mine, mine, mine!" and pull the swing and the slide.

"Stop it, stop it, stop it!" says a voice. It is Sam, the park keeper. He is helpful. He comes to Lily and Ben and says "Why are you quarreling? You can share the swing and the slide. There is enough for everyone."

Lily and Ben feel sorry. They say "sorry, sorry, sorry!" to each other and to Sam. They hug and smile. Sam smiles too. He says "I have a secret for you. Do you want to hear it?"

Lily and Ben nod. They love secrets. Sam says "Follow me. I will show you something special." He leads them to a corner of the park. There is a big tree with a hole. Sam says "Look inside. There is a surprise for you."

Lily and Ben look inside. They see a nest with four baby birds. They are fluffy and cute. They chirp and flap their wings. Lily and Ben are amazed. They say "wow, wow, wow!" and clap their hands. Sam says "This is my secret. I take care of the birds. They are my friends. You can be their friends too. But you have to be quiet and gentle. Do you promise?"

Lily and Ben promise. They say "thank you, thank you, thank you!" to Sam. They watch the birds with wonder. They forget about the swing and the slide. They are happy. They learn a new word: "nest". They say it over and over. Sam is happy too. He says "You are good kids. I am glad you are friends again. Friends are better than quarrels."
