Lily and Ben were best friends. They liked to play in the pool with their toys. One day, they decided to go on a journey under the water. They put on their goggles and held their breath.

"Are you ready, Ben?" Lily asked.

"Yes, I am, Lily. You are a dependable friend. You will not let go of my hand, right?" Ben said.

"Of course not, Ben. I will always hold your hand. Let's dive together!" Lily said.

They dived into the water and saw many colorful fish and plants. They felt like they were in a different world. They smiled at each other and waved to the fish. They had so much fun.

But soon, they needed to breathe again. They looked up and saw the sun shining through the water. They let go of each other's hand and swam to the surface. They took a big breath and laughed.

"That was an amazing journey, Lily. Thank you for diving with me," Ben said.

"Thank you, too, Ben. You are a dependable friend. Let's do it again sometime," Lily said.

They hugged and splashed each other. They were happy.
