Tom was a boy who liked to crawl. He crawled under the table, he crawled behind the sofa, he crawled in the closet. He crawled everywhere he could find a space. One day, he crawled into the garage, where his dad kept his tools and machines. Tom saw a big machine that looked like a box with wheels and a pipe. He wanted to crawl inside the machine and see what it was.

He opened the door of the machine and crawled in. It was dark and dusty inside. He saw some buttons and levers and wires. He touched them and pulled them and pushed them. He heard some noises and felt some movements. He did not know that he had turned on the machine. He did not know that the machine was a shredder, that could cut things into tiny pieces.

The machine started to work. It made a loud sound and a strong wind. The pipe sucked in the air and everything near it. Tom felt scared and tried to crawl out, but it was too late. The pipe grabbed him and pulled him in. He screamed and cried, but no one heard him. The machine shredded him into tiny pieces. He was gone.

The machine stopped. It was quiet and still. The door was open and empty. No one knew what had happened to Tom. His mom and dad looked for him everywhere, but they could not find him. They were very sad and worried. They did not know that he was inside the machine, that he had crawled into an incredible danger. They did not know that he was never coming back.
