Lily was an adventurous girl who liked to explore the universe. She had a big rocket that she made from boxes and cans. She put on her helmet and gloves and got ready to blast off.

She counted down from ten to one and pushed a red button. The rocket made a loud noise and flew up into the sky. Lily saw stars and planets and moons. She was very happy and excited.

But then she saw a big black hole. It was like a giant mouth that wanted to eat everything. Lily was scared and tried to turn her rocket away. But the black hole was too strong and pulled her closer and closer.

Lily did not want to go into the black hole. She looked for something to help her. She saw a long rope that she used to tie her boxes. She had an idea. She threw one end of the rope out of the window and hoped it would catch something.

The rope snapped around a bright star. The star was very hot and bright. It gave Lily a lot of power. Lily pulled the rope hard and made her rocket go faster. She escaped from the black hole and flew back to her home.

Lily was very brave and smart. She landed her rocket safely and ran to her mom and dad. She hugged them and told them about her adventure. They were very proud of her and gave her a big kiss. Lily smiled and said she loved the universe.
