Sara and Tom like to play in the park. They see a big boat on the lake. They want to go on the boat.

"Can we go on the boat, Mom?" Sara asks.

"Sorry, no. The boat is for sailors. They work on the boat. We can watch them from here," Mom says.

Sara and Tom are sad. They want to be sailors too. They see a big box near a tree. The box is empty and open.

"Look, Tom! We can make our own boat with the box!" Sara says.

They run to the box and get inside. They pretend the box is a boat. They use sticks as oars and a towel as a sail.

"We are sailors now! We can go anywhere!" Tom says.

They sing a song and rock the box. They have fun.

A dog sees them and runs to them. The dog is big and black. He barks loud.

"Wow, a dog! He wants to play with us!" Sara says.

She tries to pet the dog. The dog jumps on the box and breaks it. The box falls apart. Sara and Tom fall out.

"Help, Mom! The dog is scary!" Tom cries.

Mom runs to them and picks them up. She hugs them and makes them feel safe.

"Are you okay, Sara and Tom? The dog didn't mean to hurt you. He is harmless. He just wanted to say hello," Mom says.

She pets the dog and he wags his tail. He licks Sara and Tom.

"Sorry, dog. We didn't know you were friendly. You can be our sailor friend," Sara says.

They smile and play with the dog. They forget about the boat and the box. They are happy.
<|end|>


