Anna loves to sing. She sings at home, in the car, and at school. She likes to make up songs about her toys, her friends, and her family. She has a soft voice that sounds like a bird.

One day, her teacher tells the class that they will have a show. They will perform songs and dances for their parents and other teachers. Anna is very excited. She wants to sing a song that she made up about her cat, Fluffy.

She practices her song every day. She sings it to Fluffy, who purrs and rubs his head on her. She sings it to her mom and dad, who clap and hug her. She sings it to her best friend, Lily, who says, "You are a great singer, Anna!"

The day of the show comes. Anna wears a pretty dress and a bow in her hair. She waits with her classmates backstage. She feels a little nervous, but also happy. She sees her mom and dad in the audience. They smile and wave at her.

It is her turn to perform. She walks on the stage and holds the microphone. She looks at Fluffy, who is sitting in a basket next to her. She starts to sing:

"Fluffy is my cat, he is white and black
He likes to play with yarn and nap on my lap
He is soft and cuddly, he is sweet and funny
He is my best friend, I love him to the end"

The audience listens and smiles. They like Anna's song. They clap and cheer when she finishes. Anna feels proud and happy. She bows and hugs Fluffy. She hears her mom and dad say, "We are so proud of you, Anna! You did a wonderful job!" She smiles and says, "Thank you! I love you!"
<|end|>


