<|asst|>
Lily and Tom were playing in the yard. They saw a big pile of leaves that dad had raked. They wanted to jump in the leaves and have fun.

"Can we play in the leaves, dad?" Lily asked.

"Sure, but you have to help me rake them again when you are done," dad said.

"Okay, dad," Tom said.

Lily and Tom ran to the pile and jumped in. They laughed and threw leaves in the air. They made leaf angels and leaf hats. They had a lot of fun.

Then they saw a big stick on the ground. Lily picked it up and said, "Look, Tom, I have a marker. I can mark the leaves with it."

She dragged the stick on the leaves and made lines and shapes. Tom joined her and they marked the leaves with their names and pictures.

"Look, dad, we marked the leaves," Lily said.

Dad came over and smiled. He saw their marks on the leaves. He said, "You did a good job, kids. You are very creative. But now it's time to rake the leaves again. Can you help me?"

Lily and Tom nodded. They put down the stick and picked up the rake. They helped dad rake the leaves into a new pile. They worked hard and fast.

"Thank you, kids. You are very helpful. You are good rakers," dad said.

He gave them a hug and a kiss. He said, "Now you can play in the leaves one more time. But then we have to put them in the bags."

Lily and Tom cheered. They jumped in the leaves again and had more fun. They were happy. They loved playing in the leaves with dad.
<|end|>


