<|asst|>
Sara liked to collect makeup. She had many colors of lipstick, eye shadow, and nail polish. She kept them in a big box under her bed. Sometimes, she played with them and made herself look pretty.

One day, her brother Tom found her box of makeup. He thought it was stupid. He did not like makeup. He liked cars and trucks and dinosaurs. He took some of Sara's makeup and drew on the walls and the floor. He made a big mess.

Sara saw what Tom did and was very angry. She yelled at him and told him to stop. She said he was a bad brother and he ruined her makeup. She ran to her mom and told her what happened.

Mom came and saw the mess. She was not happy. She scolded Tom and made him clean up. She said he had to say sorry to Sara and give her some of his toys. She said he had to learn to respect Sara's things and not touch them without asking.

Tom felt sorry. He did not mean to make Sara and mom angry. He said sorry to Sara and gave her some of his cars and trucks and dinosaurs. He said he would not touch her makeup again. Sara forgave him and hugged him. She said she would share some of her makeup with him if he wanted to play with her. They both smiled and went to play together.
<|end|>


