<|asst|>
Lily liked to play with her toy rod. It was long and shiny and made a funny noise when she shook it. She pretended it was a magic wand and waved it at her stuffed animals. She wanted to make them talk and dance.

One day, she saw a big box in the living room. It had a bow and a tag that said "For Lily". She wondered what was inside. She thought maybe it was a new toy or a dress or a book. She wanted to open it right away, but her mom said she had to wait until her birthday.

Lily was very curious. She decided to sneak a peek when her mom was not looking. She took her toy rod and poked a hole in the box. She hoped to see something shiny or colorful. But instead, she saw something furry and wet. It moved and made a loud sound. It was a puppy!

Lily was so surprised and happy. She loved puppies. She wanted to hug it and play with it. She pulled the box open and reached for the puppy. But the puppy was scared and angry. It did not like being poked and woken up. It bit Lily's hand with its sharp teeth.

Lily screamed and dropped her toy rod. Her hand was bleeding and hurt a lot. Her mom heard her and ran to see what happened. She saw the puppy and the box and the rod and understood. She was angry and sad. She scolded Lily for being naughty and spoiled the surprise. She took her to the doctor to fix her hand.

Lily cried and said she was sorry. She did not mean to hurt the puppy or herself. She just wanted to see what was in the box. She learned a hard lesson. She should not be too curious and impatient. She should listen to her mom and respect her gifts. She hoped the puppy would forgive her and be her friend. She hoped her mom would still love her and give her another chance. She hoped her hand would heal and not hurt anymore. She hoped her toy rod would still work and make funny noises. She hoped her birthday would be better and happier.
<|end|>


