<|asst|>
Sara and Tom were playing outside in the snow. They made a big snowman with a hat and a scarf. They gave him a carrot nose and two rocks for eyes. They were having a lot of fun.

But then, Sara heard her mom calling from the house. "Sara, Tom, come inside! It's time for your meal!" Sara's mom said. Sara and Tom were hungry, so they ran to the house. But they forgot to say goodbye to the snowman.

The snowman was sad. He wanted to play with Sara and Tom more. He wished he had friends to talk to. He felt very lonely and cold.

Then, he saw a bird flying in the sky. The bird saw the snowman and landed on his hat. "Hello, snowman. You look nice. Can I be your friend?" the bird asked.

The snowman was happy. He smiled and said, "Yes, please. I would love to be your friend. What is your name?"

The bird said, "My name is Blue. I'm looking for a place to stay for the night. Do you have a place available?"

The snowman said, "You can stay on my hat. It's warm and cozy. And you can share my carrot nose if you are hungry."

The bird said, "Thank you, snowman. You are very kind and generous. I'm glad I met you."

The snowman and the bird became good friends. They talked and sang and laughed until the sun went down. They were not lonely or cold anymore.

The moral of the story is: Be friendly and helpful to others, and you will find friends and happiness.
<|end|>


