It was Tom's birthday and he was very happy. He had a big cake with four candles and many presents. His friends came to his house to celebrate with him. They played games, sang songs and ate cake.

"Happy birthday, Tom!" his friends said. "You are a big boy now!"

"Thank you, thank you!" Tom said. "I love you all!"

But then, Tom saw something bad. There was a leak in the ceiling. Water was dripping on the floor. Tom was scared. He did not want his cake and presents to get wet.

"Mom, Dad, look!" he cried. "There is a leak!"

His mom and dad came to see. They saw the leak and frowned. They tried to stop the water with a bucket and a towel. But the leak was persistent. It did not stop.

"Sorry, Tom," his dad said. "We have to call someone to fix the leak. We have to end the party now."

Tom was sad. He did not want his party to end. He wanted to celebrate more with his friends.

"But, Dad, it's my birthday!" he said.

"I know, Tom, I know," his dad said. "But we have to be safe. The leak could make the ceiling fall. We don't want that to happen."

